    '{"id":"01KBQVSNM69KFSRTH700R6CKJP","title":"Verisk // New North Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Content Production and Distribution**\n\nThe team is successfully advancing podcast episode production and scheduling with precise timelines for launches.\n\n- **The edited episode featuring Kelly Chapman is set to go live on Tuesday**, with subsequent uploads starting Wednesday or Thursday to maintain a steady release cadence (04:53).  \n    - Tim Finnigan confirmed he will complete related campaign materials within two hours after the meeting.  \n    - Igor Zagradjanin is overseeing the campaign setup aimed for launch on Monday, ensuring all assets are ready.  \n    - The team is addressing minor editing details, such as correcting the spelling of guest Rustam’s name, to maintain professionalism.  \n    - Pat Sullivan’s episode is queued next for submission post-call to sustain content flow.  \n\n- **LinkedIn campaign URLs will be updated to include Marketo UTM parameters**, replacing existing ones to improve CRM tracking accuracy, as clarified by Baylee Gunnell and Christina Bila (08:03).  \n    - Baylee offered to assist Christina with swapping links to ensure seamless integration with their marketing system.  \n    - The team agreed to monitor campaign performance closely after launch, intending to apply iterative improvements based on engagement data.  \n\n- **Social media content is being refined with creative concepts inspired by popular trends**, such as using visuals that mimic AI chat interactions to boost engagement (10:27).  \n    - Igor confirmed the production of related graphics to complement the social copy for better audience connection.  \n    - This aligns with the broader strategy to leverage trending formats and increase shareability of promotional content.\n\n## **Podcast Performance and Audience Insights**\n\nThe podcast has achieved strong traction and recognition, demonstrating healthy audience engagement and industry standing.\n\n- **Since inception, the podcast has published 17 episodes with a total of approximately 1,700 downloads, averaging 102 downloads per episode**, far exceeding the 10% survival rate past episode three typical in the industry (11:58).  \n    - Notable download spikes occurred in February and May linked to guests Lisa Kopp and Sasha, who recently became the first woman to climb El Capitan, adding unique content value.  \n    - Audience demographics are mainly North American, followed by Europe and Asia, with iPhone and Apple Podcasts capturing **65% and 55%** of listens, respectively (13:39).  \n    - Web browsers surprisingly rank second as an access point, indicating strong traffic via the website or direct links.  \n\n- **The last five episodes gathered a total of 234 downloads, with the top episode by Nola Solomon leading at 54 downloads**, showing sustained interest in recent content (14:45).  \n    - YouTube engagement includes **1,500 views and 108 hours of watch time** since the start of the year, highlighting growth potential through video distribution (15:46).  \n    - Tim Finnigan requested monthly performance reports, including YouTube stats, to track progress and inform strategy adjustments.  \n\n- **The podcast earned notable accolades this year, ranking number two on the list of 15 best data-driven marketing podcasts and number 71 on the 100 best marketing podcasts list as of December 5th** (17:58).  \n    - Gab plans to promote this recognition on social media to boost brand credibility and audience trust.  \n    - Igor committed to sharing the source links immediately after the meeting to support marketing efforts.\n\n## **2026 Strategic Planning and Content Roadmap**\n\nThe leadership is preparing for a structured 2026 content strategy focusing on refining processes and deepening marketing themes.\n\n- **Gab previewed plans to develop a more structured and visual 2026 strategy, including an annual ebook project slated for Q4 with work beginning between end of Q2 and start of Q3** (22:30).  \n    - The goal is to improve process efficiency year over year, aiming for a clockwork production rhythm.  \n    - This approach reflects a commitment to continuous refinement and higher quality deliverables.  \n\n- **The team will intensify focus on the ''four P''s'' marketing framework but is open to expanding beyond these traditional pillars** (22:48).  \n    - This suggests a flexible strategy adapting to evolving market demands and client needs.  \n    - Tim Finnigan emphasized engaging the group more deeply for written content and metrics to enrich storytelling and case studies.  \n\n- **Plans include tapping internal customer success managers and sellers for richer use cases and deeper performance metrics**, which will support stronger promotional content across social and email channels (23:20).  \n    - This integration aims to enhance authenticity and relevance by leveraging frontline insights.  \n    - Baylee and the team expressed readiness to assist with these efforts for broader impact.\n\n## **Process Improvements and Team Collaboration**\n\nThe team is focused on improving workflows and communication to support content delivery and campaign success.\n\n- **Campaign setup and asset delivery processes are well coordinated, with clear task ownership and timelines**, exemplified by Igor’s management of episode scheduling and Tim’s commitment to rapid content finalization post-call (07:40).  \n    - Minor errors like guest name misspellings are caught early to avoid rework, with open communication among members.  \n    - The collaborative review of social copy and graphics indicates a proactive approach to quality and creativity.  \n\n- **The team agreed to maintain regular monitoring and provide strategic feedback on campaign performance post-launch**, enabling agile adjustments to maximize outcomes (09:27).  \n    - Christina Bila will handle UTM parameter updates with support from Baylee, ensuring accurate tracking across systems.  \n    - This process improvement strengthens data-driven decision-making and CRM alignment.  \n\n- **Meeting cadence will adjust around holidays, with the next planned meeting on January 2nd, maintaining momentum while respecting team availability** (21:24).  \n    - This scheduling reflects a practical balance between productivity and workplace culture.  \n    - Gab noted the marketing team’s internal gift exchange as a reason for maintaining the current meeting schedule on December 19th.\n\n## **Market Position and Brand Growth**\n\nThe podcast and marketing efforts have solidified a respected position in the competitive marketing podcast landscape.\n\n- **The podcast’s high rankings and positive reviews across Spotify and Apple Podcasts confirm strong market acceptance and brand trust**, supported by **five-star ratings from 14 to 17 reviewers** (20:00).  \n    - Gab’s plan to increase engagement by commenting on episodes signals a push for deeper community interaction and visibility.  \n    - Recognition from external sources boosts confidence and offers leverage in PR and outreach efforts.  \n\n- **Gab highlighted intentions to re-engage PR activities in 2026, aiming to secure more placements and appearances for Tim on other podcasts**, expanding reach and authority (19:19).  \n    - This multi-channel PR approach aligns with the broader growth strategy to elevate the brand beyond owned media.  \n    - The team’s pride and motivation reflect a strong internal culture supporting ongoing success.\n\n- **The competitive context includes maintaining momentum against other top marketing podcasts and leveraging unique content like guest achievements and industry insights to differentiate** (13:15).  \n    - Tim and Gab’s references to standout guests and trending topics reinforce the importance of fresh, compelling content in sustaining audience interest.  \n    - Igor’s data-driven approach to audience demographics and platform usage informs strategic targeting and content adaptation.","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast Episodes","Campaign Launch","Marketing Strategy","LinkedIn UTM Parameters","Podcast Performance Metrics","PR and Promotion"],"overview":"- **Podcast Launch Schedule:** Edited episode featuring Kelly Chapman goes live on Tuesday; subsequent uploads planned mid-week to ensure continuity.  \n- **Campaign URL Updates:** LinkedIn UTM parameters will be updated for better CRM tracking; close monitoring of performance post-launch is planned.  \n- **Podcast Performance Metrics:** 17 episodes published, approximately 1,700 downloads total; top episodes linked to notable guests and strong audience engagement.  \n- **2026 Strategic Planning:** Structured content strategy to develop, including an annual ebook project; improving efficiency and marketing flexibility is key.  \n- **Team Collaboration:** Clear task ownership enhances workflow; regular performance reviews of campaigns will facilitate agile adjustments for better results.  \n- **Brand Growth Strategy:** Plans for increased PR activity in 2026, focusing on securing placements and expanding reach through unique content offerings.","action_items":"\n**Gabrielle Verzella**\nSubmit Pat Sullivan episode immediately after meeting (07:06)\nShare corrected guest name spelling “Rustam” for editing accuracy (05:37)\nPost social brag about podcast ranking on social media (18:24)\nFind and share link to the podcast ranking article in New North channel (19:10)\nProvide update on 2026 strategy with structured visuals when available (22:30)\n\n**Tim Finnigan**\nComplete rough cuts of upcoming episodes and knock out tasks immediately after call (07:40)\nEngage team for write-ups on marketing four P’s for 2026 deeper focus (23:13)\n\n**Christina Bila**\nReplace existing campaign URL UTM parameters on LinkedIn with Marketo UTMs and request assistance if needed (08:03)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nMonitor LinkedIn campaign performance post-launch and recommend tweaks as appropriate (09:27)\nProvide assistance and training on updating UTM parameters for LinkedIn campaign (08:48)\nProvide monthly reports on podcast and YouTube analytics (16:41)\n\n**Igor Zagradjanin**\nSchedule video episode, clips, and promo release aligned with Kelly Chapman episode launch (04:01)\nFinalize campaign setup and prepare to launch Monday (07:45)\nCreate social graphic incorporating LLM/ChatGPT style visual concept as suggested (10:27)\nShare links to podcast ranking lists and confirm all received materials (19:15)\n"},"duration":24.100000381469727,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":1,"name":"Christina Bila"},{"id":2,"name":"Gab"},{"id":3,"name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"id":4,"name":"Igor Zagradjanin"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, how''s it going?","index":0,"end_time":7.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":5.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Going great.","index":1,"end_time":8.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":7.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Are you still at your.","index":2,"end_time":12.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":10.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Your company getaway thing?","index":3,"end_time":14.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":12.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, we.","index":4,"end_time":17.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":15.76,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"That wrapped up.","index":5,"end_time":18.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":17.76,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"On what days?","index":6,"end_time":19.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":18.68,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"That Wednesday and then I came back to the city and then.","index":7,"end_time":23.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":19.72,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":8,"end_time":24.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":24.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Have been here ever since.","index":9,"end_time":26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":24.88,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Okay.","index":10,"end_time":26.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":26.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Nice.","index":11,"end_time":27.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":26.8,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Oh, is that a dog?","index":12,"end_time":28.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":27.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"My little baby.","index":13,"end_time":30.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":29.38,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Say hello.","index":14,"end_time":32.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":31.86,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Oh my goodness.","index":15,"end_time":34.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":33.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"His eyes are so big.","index":16,"end_time":36.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":34.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"They are.","index":17,"end_time":37.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":37.22,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"He just got a haircut, so he''s a little bigger than usual.","index":18,"end_time":43.299,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":38.9,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"But when he has his full face of hair, it''s like sunken down a little bit.","index":19,"end_time":47.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":43.299,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Hey, Tim.","index":20,"end_time":49.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":48.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I need to clarify what Christina''s talking about.","index":21,"end_time":53.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":51.22,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Christina, tell the truth.","index":22,"end_time":55.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":53.86,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Don''t say your dog got a haircut.","index":23,"end_time":57.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":55.47,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"It did.","index":24,"end_time":58.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":57.63,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Professionally done.","index":25,"end_time":60.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":59.07,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Tell the truth.","index":26,"end_time":60.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":60.11,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"It''s now professionally done.","index":27,"end_time":62.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":61.23,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"After that incident, I. I''ve sworn I''m never taking a pairs of scissors in my hand.","index":28,"end_time":67.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":62.87,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"So it''s professional.","index":29,"end_time":70.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":67.95,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Did you tell him that you tried to save money by cutting your own dog''s hair?","index":30,"end_time":74.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":70.43,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"No.","index":31,"end_time":75.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":74.83,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"A couple months ago I tried what Tim said and then did not end up well.","index":32,"end_time":81.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":76.03,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"He.","index":33,"end_time":82.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":81.74,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"I cut his hair flap a little bit.","index":34,"end_time":86.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":83.82,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"The skin on his ear flap.","index":35,"end_time":87.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":86.38,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"So after that I was like, Christina.","index":36,"end_time":89.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":87.98,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"You''Re such a liar.","index":37,"end_time":91.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":90.7,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I saw a picture of it.","index":38,"end_time":93.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":91.98,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"It''s a.","index":39,"end_time":93.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":93.06,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"It''s a gaping wound.","index":40,"end_time":95.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":93.98,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"It should be on Gray''s Anatomy.","index":41,"end_time":97.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":95.26,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"This should be an episode on Grey''s Anatomy.","index":42,"end_time":99.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":97.58,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Was there a lot of blood?","index":43,"end_time":100.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":99.74,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Not too much, but yeah, there was blood.","index":44,"end_time":106.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":102.14,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"So I''m just glad he forgave me.","index":45,"end_time":109.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":107.52,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"You are?","index":46,"end_time":110.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":109.88,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It''s all relative on what too much blood is.","index":47,"end_time":113.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":110.28,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"The thing was covered in blood.","index":48,"end_time":115.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":113.36,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Oh, man.","index":49,"end_time":116.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":115.92,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"How''s your puppy doing, Tim?","index":50,"end_time":120,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":118.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I mean, is there a level above perfect Angel.","index":51,"end_time":127.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":121.76,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"An angel?","index":52,"end_time":128.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":127.36,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":53,"end_time":128.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":128.24,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Oh, man.","index":54,"end_time":132.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":131.44,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Hi, everyone.","index":55,"end_time":132.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":132.12,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Hey.","index":56,"end_time":133.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":133.2,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Look at Gab rocking the NHL stuff.","index":57,"end_time":137.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":134,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Oh yeah.","index":58,"end_time":138.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":138.16,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I have a original six hat now and I can name all six.","index":59,"end_time":142.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":138.76,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Go ahead.","index":60,"end_time":143.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":142.96,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"Boston Bruins, New York Rangers, Chicago Blackhawks, Montreal Canadiens, Toronto Maple Leafs and Detroit Red Wings.","index":61,"end_time":156.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":144.64,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Wow.","index":62,"end_time":158.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":157.6,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Impression rested.","index":63,"end_time":159.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":158.12,"speaker_name":"Tim Finnigan"},{"text":"I only know Juan Gab.","index":64,"end_time":161.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":159.96,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"And that''s.","index":65,"end_time":162.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":161.44,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Oh, and that''s the Blackhawks because we.","index":66,"end_time":164.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":162.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Went to a Blackhawk.","index":67,"end_time":165.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":164.12,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":68,"end_time":165.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":165.08,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":69,"end_time":167.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":167.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"How was your marketing getaway?","index":70,"end_time":169,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":167.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It was good.","index":71,"end_time":170.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":169.72,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It was productive.","index":72,"end_time":172.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":170.52,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And equally fun in my opinion.","index":73,"end_time":174.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":172.4,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Tim does not agree.","index":74,"end_time":175.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":174.52,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I thought it was productive.","index":75,"end_time":179.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":177.96,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I got to see our camera equipment for the first time for Cesar.","index":76,"end_time":184.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":179.48,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So I was playing around with that a little bit.","index":77,"end_time":186.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":184.61,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Tim kept calling me like a kid on Christmas morning.","index":78,"end_time":189.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":186.29,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Me taking everything out of the boxes, playing with the tripod like.","index":79,"end_time":195.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":192.13,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":80,"end_time":196.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":196.29,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So over like the holidays.","index":81,"end_time":198.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":197.33,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I''m going to take some time to.","index":82,"end_time":200.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":198.81,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"While everyone''s away and nothing is busy.","index":83,"end_time":202.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":200.33,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Just trying to set up like how we will probably set up in.","index":84,"end_time":206.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":202.77,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"In.","index":85,"end_time":206.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":206.53,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I almost said Las Vegas.","index":86,"end_time":209.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":208.05,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So amazing.","index":87,"end_time":212.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":210.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s always fun getting new presents.","index":88,"end_time":216.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":213.61,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Get a. Oh, yeah, yeah.","index":89,"end_time":217.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":216.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And they shipped everything to my house to play with over the holiday.","index":90,"end_time":221.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":217.81,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I was like, great, this is great.","index":91,"end_time":223.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":221.69,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"That''s amazing.","index":92,"end_time":225.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":225.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But yeah, I know.","index":93,"end_time":229.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":228.65,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"We have some stuff in motion.","index":94,"end_time":231.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":229.65,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"You want to walk through it?","index":95,"end_time":232.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":231.13,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, I think Igor''s got it all pulled up, so.","index":96,"end_time":236.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":233.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":97,"end_time":237.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":237.43,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Get over to him.","index":98,"end_time":238.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":237.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Let''s do it.","index":99,"end_time":240.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":239.67,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yep.","index":100,"end_time":241.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":241.35,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So.","index":101,"end_time":243.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":243.59,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Oh, I hate when this happens.","index":102,"end_time":258.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":256.23,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Like when I have to up here it is.","index":103,"end_time":262.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":258.39,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So.","index":104,"end_time":264.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":264.23,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"First things first.","index":105,"end_time":270.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":269.35,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So Kelly Chapman was.","index":106,"end_time":273.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":270.63,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Episode.","index":107,"end_time":274.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":273.91,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Was.","index":108,"end_time":274.63,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":274.43,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Episode was edited and delivered and.","index":109,"end_time":278.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":274.63,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":110,"end_time":280.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":279.83,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Gab, do you know when that''s gonna be online?","index":111,"end_time":282.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":280.39,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Just so I know when to schedule the.","index":112,"end_time":286.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":283.43,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"The video episode and short clips and promo video on YouTube.","index":113,"end_time":292.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":286.87,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, we are aiming for Tuesday now, right, Tim?","index":114,"end_time":296.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":293.26,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Because Tim sent a follow up note to Callie with the edited assets.","index":115,"end_time":301.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":297.66,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Anything else you want to add to that, Tim?","index":116,"end_time":306.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":304.62,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"No.","index":117,"end_time