    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83512186019?pwd=BNyHZsomC0rkaqnAXBp4GXb262jtaj.1',
    '{"id":"01KBQVSNM6N4K9X7KB01XGM7D8","title":"Tyfone // Marketers in Demand - Weekly Meeting (new)","summary":{"notes":"## **AI Integration and Content Automation**\n\nThe team is leveraging advanced AI tools to analyze extensive podcast data, enabling smarter content creation and training.\n\n- **Josh DeTar highlighted** that **Google’s NotebookLM now scans over 300 large documents**, allowing them to upload nearly **300 hours of podcast transcripts** for in-depth querying and insight extraction (01:11).  \n    - This capability helped identify common themes and concerns across episodes, providing a strong base for marketing content and product management training.  \n    - Josh pointed out the AI’s accuracy in summarizing market fears and opportunities, validating its usefulness for their current projects.  \n    - The approach accelerates content generation and ensures relevance by pulling real, data-driven insights from historical material.  \n    - This also reduces manual research time, creating scalable workflows for ongoing content needs.\n\n- The team decided to **produce narrated videos using a draft script from Josh**, with Baylee’s team creating video cuts and transitions to enhance flow (03:38).  \n    - Josh will record the voiceover himself via Riverside once the script is polished collaboratively.  \n    - Baylee noted the script might need adjustments to better capture natural speech intonations and pacing.  \n    - This hybrid process balances in-house voice talent with expert video editing to maintain quality and authenticity.  \n    - It supports faster turnaround for marketing assets while keeping costs controlled.\n\n## **Conference Speaking and Industry Positioning**\n\nSpeaking engagements are a strategic priority to build credibility and showcase thought leadership within highly regulated financial sectors.\n\n- **Josh DeTar shared** that he recently spoke for **50 minutes at a credit union conference**, demonstrating safe, practical AI use without exposing sensitive data (05:32).  \n    - His talk covered simple examples that credit union execs can adopt now, addressing widespread AI fear and regulatory hesitation.  \n    - Josh explained the typical conference narratives are either dystopian or overhyped, so his focus on realistic first steps fills a critical gap in the market.  \n    - This practical approach has resonated well, leading to invitations for additional talks, including one scheduled for **early February**.  \n    - By emphasizing accessible AI adoption, Josh is positioning the company as a trusted resource for cautious financial institutions.\n\n- The team plans to **create polished speaker videos** showcasing Josh and other staff’s stage presence to improve conference submission success (08:12).  \n    - These videos will help demonstrate dynamic public speaking and industry authority to event organizers.  \n    - Josh is coordinating with Kevin to send recent footage for production, aligning with the broader strategy to win more speaking slots.  \n    - The goal is to move beyond booth presence, using speaking gigs as the main driver for visibility and lead generation.  \n    - This shift reflects a long-term investment in personal branding and trust building in a conservative market.\n\n## **Podcast Performance and Growth Metrics**\n\nThe podcast shows steady growth with strong audience engagement and increasing recognition in industry rankings.\n\n- **Igor Zagradjanin reported** that the podcast has released **24 episodes this year** with an average of nearly **200 downloads per episode**, showing consistent growth without spikes (08:59).  \n    - The audience is primarily in **North America**, followed closely by **Europe (21%) and Asia (20%)**, mostly listening via **Apple Podcasts and Spotify (18%)**.  \n    - Top episodes in **January, April, and August** each reached about **174 downloads**, indicating steady interest throughout the year.  \n    - Recent episodes maintain healthy engagement, with the top five totaling **572 downloads**, led by the \"KT the Fail\" episode with **141 downloads**.  \n    - This steady performance suggests a loyal and growing listener base.\n\n- The podcast achieved high visibility with rankings of **#4 on Feedspot’s 80 best banking podcasts** and **#17 on Million Podcasts'' top 50 banking podcasts in the U.S.** (11:22).  \n    - Igor noted an opportunity to investigate ranking criteria to inform future content and promotional strategies.  \n    - Baylee added that consistency and longevity are key ranking drivers, emphasizing the value of sustained publishing over time.  \n    - She highlighted that the podcast is outperforming about **75-85% of shows**, given most podcasts don’t surpass episode three or reach even 27 downloads in the first week.  \n    - This performance supports ongoing brand building and relationship growth in the financial sector.\n\n## **Content Strategy and Future Planning**\n\nThe team is focused on refining scripts, improving video assets, and expanding educational content to support marketing and training.\n\n- Baylee’s team will **develop rough video cuts** aligned with Josh’s draft script and propose narration pacing and transitions to improve flow (04:00).  \n    - The iterative script refinement aims to capture natural delivery and better reflect speaker intonations for audience engagement.  \n    - Josh’s availability to record voiceovers directly accelerates production timelines and maintains message authenticity.  \n    - This process combines creative editing with expert review to produce polished marketing videos efficiently.  \n    - The output will serve dual purposes: external marketing and internal product management training.\n\n- The plan includes gathering more speaker footage to build a library of dynamic content for conference submissions and marketing collateral (08:12).  \n    - This content will position the team as industry thought leaders and trusted experts in AI applications for finance.  \n    - The strategy leverages live speaking success to generate ongoing video assets supporting multiple business goals.  \n    - Coordinated production scheduling and asset management are critical to maintaining momentum.  \n    - These efforts align with long-term goals of increasing visibility and market credibility.\n\n## **Market Insights and Competitive Positioning**\n\nThe team is strategically using data and real-world feedback to guide messaging and product focus in a cautious, regulated environment.\n\n- Josh emphasized the widespread **fear of AI adoption in regulated industries**, especially financial services, where data privacy and legal concerns dominate (06:41).  \n    - His talks and content focus on **simple, safe AI use cases** that avoid sensitive data exposure but deliver operational gains.  \n    - This pragmatic approach contrasts with extreme narratives and helps build trust with cautious prospects.  \n    - The company’s messaging aims to break through the paralysis caused by overhyped or dystopian views of AI.  \n    - By aligning product education with regulatory realities, they improve adoption chances and customer confidence.\n\n- Speaker reputation and authentic demonstrations of AI in action are key differentiators in conference and marketing efforts (07:51).  \n    - The team recognizes that credibility comes from showing real examples, not just abstract claims.  \n    - This approach fosters deeper engagement and positions the company as a practical AI partner.  \n    - Long-term, this strategy supports broader platform adoption and competitive differentiation in a crowded market.  \n    - The focus on trust and simplicity addresses a critical barrier to entry for target customers.","outline":null,"keywords":["Google Notebook LM","podcast analytics","AI in banking","credit union executives","marketing content creation","podcast rankings"],"overview":"- **AI Tools for Content Creation:** Advanced AI analyzes podcast data, improving content generation and reducing manual research time. \n\n- **Speaker Engagements Strategy:** Focus on building credibility through practical AI talks at conferences, with an emphasis on trust-building.\n\n- **Podcast Growth Metrics:** Released 24 episodes this year, averaging nearly 200 downloads each, with a strong North American audience.\n\n- **High Podcast Visibility:** Achieved #4 ranking on Feedspot’s best banking podcasts, outperforming 75-85% of shows in the market.\n\n- **Content Strategy Focus:** Develop polished video assets and educational content for marketing and internal training to enhance engagement.\n\n- **Market Positioning Insights:** Emphasize safe AI use to mitigate fears in regulated industries, fostering confidence in target customers.","action_items":"\n**Josh DeTar**\nRecord narration for the video after receiving the finalized script via Riverside (03:38)\nCoordinate with Kevin to share the recent conference speaking video for marketing and submissions (08:12)\nReview script and communicate any questions during the video production process with Baylee (14:15)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nShare the video production brief to create a rough cut of the video with suggested visuals and transitions (03:16)\nRefine script length and content for an improved flow and natural narration style (04:50)\nInitiate contact with listing platforms (Feedspot, Million Podcasts) to inquire about podcast ranking criteria (12:51)\nProvide Josh with the finalized script when ready for recording (14:15)\n\n**Igor Zagradjanin**\nFollow up on gathering more detailed data or strategy behind podcast rankings on external lists (11:59)\nProvide ongoing podcast performance statistics and analytics updates (08:48)\n"},"duration":14.829999923706055,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":1,"name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"id":2,"name":"Josh DeTar"}],"sentences":[{"text":"That is a beautiful cup.","index":0,"end_time":22.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":21.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":1,"end_time":25.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":24.64,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It''s, it''s actually made in Japan.","index":2,"end_time":28.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":26.2,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Wow.","index":3,"end_time":30.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":29.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, my girlfriend got it from her best friend and yeah, we have two.","index":4,"end_time":35.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":30.52,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And I''m always like, I need to be extra careful.","index":5,"end_time":38.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":35.84,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It''s a special cup.","index":6,"end_time":41.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":40.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":7,"end_time":43.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":42.44,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Very nice.","index":8,"end_time":45.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":44.6,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I''m, I''m that guy who just.","index":9,"end_time":47.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":46.36,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I don''t know, I like nice things, but like, I, I prefer to keep this on a shelf in a kitchen as a decoration.","index":10,"end_time":56.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":48.28,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Not meant to be.","index":11,"end_time":57.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":56.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":12,"end_time":58.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":58.1,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Just not, not to break it.","index":13,"end_time":60.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":58.34,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":14,"end_time":60.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":60.26,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Hey guys.","index":15,"end_time":62.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":61.62,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":16,"end_time":62.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":62.5,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"No worries.","index":17,"end_time":65.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":64.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":18,"end_time":67.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":66.98,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"I''m on, on another call at the same time.","index":19,"end_time":69.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":67.34,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Oh, you got a busy day.","index":20,"end_time":71.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":69.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s gonna be one of those days.","index":21,"end_time":73.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":71.86,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"But I did want to just hop on so we could chat about the wrap up if you guys had any questions on that.","index":22,"end_time":80.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":73.86,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"So, yeah, I don''t know if you guys, you know, have played around with that or not, but yeah, you know, Google has been making some massive improvements to Notebook LM over the last little bit.","index":23,"end_time":90.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":80.26,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"And just recently they''ve significantly increased the number and size of documents that it can scan.","index":24,"end_time":97.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":90.83,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"So now it can scan over 300 large, complex documents.","index":25,"end_time":100.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":97.71,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"So I uploaded every single transcript in the history of the podcast.","index":26,"end_time":105.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":101.79,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"It totaled almost 300 hours of spoken content into NotebookLM.","index":27,"end_time":113.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":105.79,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"And I''ve just started playing with it and querying it, being able to ask questions across every single one of those episodes for common trend, pull out certain things.","index":28,"end_time":122.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":113.34,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"And the insights have been absolutely fascinating.","index":29,"end_time":125.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":123.26,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"So we''re using it to create a bunch of marketing content.","index":30,"end_time":128.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":125.82,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"We''re literally even using it.","index":31,"end_time":130.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":129.26,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"There''s so much good content in there for us to train some of our product management people on things like market expectations.","index":32,"end_time":137.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":130.82,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"But so one of the things that I had to do is I was just like, hey, I gave it a bunch of criteria and I was like, go create, you know, a summary of this last year.","index":33,"end_time":149.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":139.49,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"So just looking at episodes 100, I think 11 till today, what were the common themes, what got brought up the most, that kind of stuff.","index":34,"end_time":159.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":149.81,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"And so that''s what it pulled out of it.","index":35,"end_time":162.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":159.33,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"And I was like, hot damn.","index":36,"end_time":163.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":162.46,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Like, it was pretty freaking spot on.","index":37,"end_time":165.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":163.54,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Like, if you were to just ask me what was my assessment of the state of the market, what are people''s fears and concerns and opportunities?","index":38,"end_time":171.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":165.14,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Like, it basically nailed it.","index":39,"end_time":173.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":171.42,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"So anyway, I thought that would also help us with this project.","index":40,"end_time":177.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":174.3,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"So I used it to kind of then go through and pull out some different quotes that helped to validate that that we could use as the, you know, the videos, snippets throughout.","index":41,"end_time":191.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":178.46,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"And then I just have the timestamps attached, so hopefully makes it easy for you guys to find those.","index":42,"end_time":196.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":191.75,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"But yeah, yeah, it looks like the.","index":43,"end_time":201.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":196.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If I''m looking at the right document, maybe I''ll just share my screen to make sure I''m looking at the.","index":44,"end_time":205.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":201.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The right one.","index":45,"end_time":207.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":206.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Is this the one you''re talking about?","index":46,"end_time":214.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":212.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I think so.","index":47,"end_time":216.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":215.67,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":48,"end_time":217.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":216.87,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":49,"end_time":218.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":217.75,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"What do you want to do for the narrator?","index":50,"end_time":220.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":218.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do you want to record that or do you want to.","index":51,"end_time":222.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":220.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I think.","index":52,"end_time":223.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":222.43,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"No, I think I can record that.","index":53,"end_time":225.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":223.67,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"I just want to know, like, I think what would be good is if you.","index":54,"end_time":232.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":226.63,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Because I.","index":55,"end_time":233.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":232.31,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"This is like a.","index":56,"end_time":234.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":233.67,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"If I''m being totally honest, like a half assed baked script of everything.","index":57,"end_time":238.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":234.59,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"It''s not a perfect word for word, so.","index":58,"end_time":240.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":238.27,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"So if you guys could maybe create like some of the video and stuff like that and like, hey, this is what it should look like.","index":59,"end_time":246.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":240.72,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"And these are the transitions that we would need.","index":60,"end_time":248.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":246.28,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"And then we can work on a script that you would just give the voiceover actor, but I can just be the voiceover actor.","index":61,"end_time":254.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":248.8,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"And then you guys want me to just record that in Riverside?","index":62,"end_time":257.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":254.88,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":63,"end_time":259.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":258.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think for other clients we''ve done like a brief intro to each guest, so.","index":64,"end_time":264.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":259.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":65,"end_time":265.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":264.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It sounds like we''re kind of thinking the same thing then.","index":66,"end_time":267.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":265.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, yeah.","index":67,"end_time":269.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":269.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we can get started.","index":68,"end_time":270.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":269.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Pull that in.","index":69,"end_time":272.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":271.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Because sometimes we''ve noticed too, the script doesn''t always take into account the intonations and the way people talk.","index":70,"end_time":282.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":273.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we might want to lengthen it a little bit from what''s in there or cut out some parts to make sure it flows well.","index":71,"end_time":290,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":282.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But that script looks really great.","index":72,"end_time":292.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":290,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I think we can go ahead and start working on a rough cut and then put together some suggestions for how you would narrate all the parts.","index":73,"end_time":301.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":292.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":74,"end_time":302.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":301.59,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Works for me.","index":75,"end_time":302.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":302.15,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"And then I just wanted to check and see.","index":76,"end_time":304.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":303.03,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Did you guys get.","index":77,"end_time":305.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":304.87,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":78,"end_time":306.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":306.23,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"We had some issues getting it uploaded and everything, but did you guys get a video of me speaking at a conference recently?","index":79,"end_time":313.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":306.79,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"To do.","index":80,"end_time":313.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":313.03,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Okay, so we''re going to do another one of those projects where we had you guys do that video of Seva speaking at the conference.","index":81,"end_time":320.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":313.67,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"So we shot some video of me speaking at one recently.","index":82,"end_time":325.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":322.32,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"We''ll just do the same thing.","index":83,"end_time":326.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":325.76,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":84,"end_time":327.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":327.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s so exciting.","index":85,"end_time":328.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":328.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"What was this one about?","index":86,"end_time":330.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":329.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So funny enough, this one was about how credit union executives could use tools like chat GPT without having to like have a protected environment, without having to think about having to put sensitive information or PII into it to get value out of it.","index":87,"end_time":354.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":332.32,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"You know, I talked to all these even big credit Union executives and they''re not using it at all.","index":88,"end_time":360.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":355.68,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"And I''m like, look, here''s like five super simple, easy examples of how you can just gain a lot of operational efficiency.","index":89,"end_time":368.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":360.88,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"And so it was like a 50 minute speaking spot where I talked about and actually showed.","index":90,"end_time":376.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":369.44,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"I wrote the prompt, I ran the example, walked them through it live, and then shared with them a document that literally was, here''s the prompt, you can copy and paste it, change to your credit union name.","index":91,"end_time":390.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":377.11,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"And so yeah, it was a, was a talk on how to use AI.","index":92,"end_time":395.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":391.67,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Wow, that''s blowing my mind that they''re not using it.","index":93,"end_time":401.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":396.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh no, it''s, they''re like terrified of it.","index":94,"end_time":403.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":401.74,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Okay, well, because what''s funny?","index":95,"end_time":405.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":404.06,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"And so, I mean, Bailey, this is, this is literally why I started.","index":96,"end_time":408.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":405.58,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"This is now the second time I''ve given this talk at a conference and I actually just got asked to do it a third time at another conference in early, I think February.","index":97,"end_time":418.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":408.78,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"But it''s because most people, especially you got to think about it, we''re in a highly regulated industry, right.","index":98,"end_time":426.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":418.38,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"So they''re like terrified of putting sensitive information in here, lawsuits, you name it.","index":99,"end_time":431.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":426.63,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"And so what we find is that people who speak about AI at conferences for like banking executives go one of two directions.","index":100,"end_time":440.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":432.23,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"One is the huge ethereal conversation of it''s going to be Skynet robots are going to take over the world and this is horrible.","index":101,"end_time":447.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":441.11,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"And the other is it''s going to radically change everything.","index":102,"end_time":450.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":447.83,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"It''s going to do everything for you.","index":103,"end_time":452.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":450.91,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Here''s how you can have it fully automate your lending, decision making, approvals process and all of this.","index":104,"end_time":458.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":452.87,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"And you have to buy tens of millions of dollars of software and you''ve got to get it through your procurement process and you''ve got to think.","index":105,"end_time":464.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":458.93,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"And I''m like, guys, you guys aren''t even taking AI notes yet.","index":106,"end_time":467.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":465.09,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Like, let''s just start there.","index":107,"end_time":468.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":467.73,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":108,"end_time":469.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":469.41,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So that was how I kind of structured that and it''s been a hit.","index":109,"end_time":474.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":471.97,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"So we, and we just, we''re trying to do more of.","index":110,"end_time":478.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":475.41,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"As much as I hate to admit it, like myself and a couple of other folks on our staff are pretty good, you know, speakers with some pretty good reputations in our industry.","index":111,"end_time":486.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":478.77,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"And that''s where the value of going to conferences, it''s not standing at a booth, it''s speaking on stage.","index":112,"end_time":491.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":487.56,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":113,"end_time":492.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":492.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And they just, they want to see examples of seeing you speak previously.","index":114,"end_time":495.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":492.56,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"So we''re just trying to put together more of those examples.","index":115,"end_time":499.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":496.92,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"So when we, you know, submit to speak at a conference, we submit it alongside a video that Shows, you know, hey, they''re a dynamic speaker.","index":116,"end_time":506.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":499.48,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Like they''re fun.","index":117,"end_time":507.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":506.44,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"And having you guys make it look really nice too.","index":118,"end_time":510.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":507.72,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Even just up levels are our game when we submit those.","index":119,"end_time":513.539,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":510.6,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"So.","index":120,"end_time":513.899,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":513.539,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Yeah, so I''ll work with Kevin to get that over to you.","index":121,"end_time":516.259,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":514.219,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"He''s out today, but okay.","index":122,"end_time":517.419,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":516.259,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s great.","index":123,"end_time":518.459,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":517.419,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":124,"end_time":519.419,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":519.019,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"I know Igor had put together a bit of an end of year recap for you.","index":125,"end_time":523.899,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":519.419,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We have some stats of just how your podcast is done this year if you have a few extra minutes.","index":126,"end_time":528.139,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":523.899,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh yeah, yeah, I''d be fascinated.","index":127,"end_time":529.899,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":528.219,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Great.","index":128,"end_time":531.419,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":531.019,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So here it is.","index":129,"end_time":540.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":539.67,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Oh, sorry.","index":130,"end_time":544.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":542.87,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So.","index":131,"end_time":547.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":547.43,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Yeah, so 24 episodes so far and total downloads are just.","index":132,"end_time":557.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":550.95,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, great, great.","index":133,"end_time":560.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":558.07,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It''s.","index":134,"end_time":561.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":561.27,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And this is like all time downloads, which basically is for this year is almost 200 downloads per episode on average.","index":135,"end_time":572.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":563.44,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"What really interests me, it was really interesting to me to see that like this steady growth since the beginning of, since January and then through December, there are no notable spikes, but there''s like this amazing steady growth actually, which is I think even better, which shows that like people, you, you are listened to basically more and more since the beginning of this year.","index":136,"end_time":602.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":574.08,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then unsurprisingly, most people who listens, who listen to your podcast are from North America and then Europe and Asia are basically, they share the second place with 21 and 20%.","index":137,"end_time":622.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":604.35,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Most of them listen through iPhone and on Apple podcasts.","index":138,"end_time":629.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":625.5,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then Spotify is at 18%.","index":139,"end_time":632.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":629.06,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Top performing episodes are these three.","index":140,"end_time":639.339,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":635.9,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And they''re pretty close actually.","index":141,"end_time":641.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":639.66,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"174 and 174 and 173 downloads.","index":142,"end_time":646.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":642.06,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And January, April and August.","index":143,"end_time":649.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":647.18,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So they''re pretty evenly distributed like these three.","index":144,"end_time":654.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":650.14,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Maybe this one in December coming up is going to be like the fourth one and then they''re going to be the Fantastic Four.","index":145,"end_time":663.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":655.92,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And for the last five episodes, so it''s 572 downloads.","index":146,"end_time":673.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":666.16,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"The top episode from within those five last ones is KT the Fail.","index":147,"end_time":680.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":674.4,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It''s 141 downloads, Apple and Spotify and of course again North America and Europe.","index":148,"end_time":691.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":682.08,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then this is finally the best thing.","index":149,"end_time":696.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":692.88,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So I''m sure you guys know about some of these.","index":150,"end_time":701.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":696.56,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So on the feedspot list, you''ve been ranked number four on 80 best banking podcasts and by a million podcasts, you''re number 17 on best 50 banking podcasts in the U.S. that''s awesome.","index":151,"end_time":718.769,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":701.68,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"These are some.","index":152,"end_time":719.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":718.769,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Have you guys seen anything that drives like why would you be number four or number 17 versus number 80 or number 50 or number one?","index":153,"end_time":728.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":719.61,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"I want to be number one.","index":154,"end_time":730.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":729.45,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":155,"end_time":731.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":730.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You mean like on these lists?","index":156,"end_time":736.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":733.77,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":157,"end_time":736.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":736.17,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Honestly, yeah.","index":158,"end_time":740.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":739.37,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I think we could take a better look into that and just let you know.","index":159,"end_time":746.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":740.37,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, so just make sure if they shared something that is specifically related to a strategy or guests or something.","index":160,"end_time":757.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":746.97,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"But I honestly don''t think they.","index":161,"end_time":760.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":758.06,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"They''re gonna share this like, in.","index":162,"end_time":762.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":760.38,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"In a list like that, but we can try for sure.","index":163,"end_time":764.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":762.06,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":164,"end_time":765.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":765.1,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Just be curious to know, like, what, what they look for in how they rank.","index":165,"end_time":770.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":765.54,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ve never had a client ask that.","index":166,"end_time":773.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":771.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we can, we can ask them.","index":167,"end_time":776.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":774.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We can reach out to them and see if they''d.","index":168,"end_time":778.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":776.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"They''d let us know how they decide.","index":169,"end_time":780.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":778.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Some things that I''ve just noticed with our other clients is like consistency and longevity.","index":170,"end_time":788.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":781.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, like, I, we.","index":171,"end_time":791.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":789.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We probably have 2 to 3 ish clients that I notice keep popping up on these boards, and it''s because they are super consistent and they''ve been doing it for a while, whereas some of our newer clients, who are just getting started, like, I''ve never seen them pop up on one of these lists.","index":172,"end_time":807.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":791.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But, like, you have been doing this for a really long time and you''ve started to get a really strong following.","index":173,"end_time":814.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":807.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''ve also, I think I''ve shared this with you before, but I think it just helps put into perspective, like, really how well your podcast is doing is like 90% of podcasts don''t make it past episode three, and you are so far beyond that.","index":174,"end_time":829.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":816.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then if you just get 27 downloads in the first week, that puts you in the top 50% of shows.","index":175,"end_time":835.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":829.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So you''re also well above that.","index":176,"end_time":837.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":835.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So you''re really, like, in the 75th, 85th percentile for how your podcast is performing.","index":177,"end_time":845.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":837.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And I know we don''t always do this because we want to be the best, but, like, you''re building a lot of great relationships and helping grow your business.","index":178,"end_time":855.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":846.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, I mean, this is a never ending strategy for us now, unfortunately, like, I''m kind of stuck doing this.","index":179,"end_time":863.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":855.79,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, it works.","index":180,"end_time":865.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":863.43,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"So cool.","index":181,"end_time":867.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":866.26,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Well, hey, I got to jump back over to this other call, but yeah, Bailey, just let me know if you have any questions as you go through that script and stuff.","index":182,"end_time":876.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":867.46,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"And then when you''ve got a script ready for me to read, just let me know.","index":183,"end_time":878.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":876.82,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Okay?","index":184,"end_time":879.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":878.94,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"You got it.","index":185,"end_time":880.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":879.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":186,"end_time":881.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":880.66,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Okay, we''ll see you.","index":187,"end_time":882.219,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":881.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thanks, guys.","index":188,"end_time":882.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":882.219,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"See you.","index":189,"end_time":883.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":882.78,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Have a great day.","index":190,"end_time":883.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":883.14,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Bye.","index":191,"end_time":883.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":883.66,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Bye.","index":192,"end_time":884.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":883.94,"speaker_name":"Josh DeTar"},{"text":"Bye.","index":193,"end_time":884.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":884.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"dateString":"2025-12-12T16:30:00.000Z","host_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83512186019?pwd=BNyHZsomC0rkaqnAXBp4GXb262jtaj.1","participants":["baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,kevin.welsch@tyfone.com,josh.detar@tyfone.com,igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com","kevin.welsch@tyfone.com","josh.detar@tyfone.com","igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KBQVSNM6N4K9X7KB01XGM7D8","organizer_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Josh uploaded 300 hours of transcripts into NotebookLM to extract trends and insights.","Team is producing a video project using AI-powered script generation and narrator voiceover.","Client requested another conference video edit to help secure future speaking opportunities.","Podcast showed steady growth with nearly 200 downloads per episode and strong global reach.","Show ranked #4 and #17 on major podcast lists, attributed to quality and consistency."],"highlights":[{"quote":"The insights have been absolutely fascinating.","speaker":"Josh DeTar"},{"quote":"There’s amazing steady growth actually, which shows that you are listened to more and more.","speaker":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"quote":"You''re really, like, in the 75th, 85th percentile for how your podcast is performing.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"topics":["AI","podcast","delivery","content","growth"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-12T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **AI Integration and Content Automation**\n\nThe team is leveraging advanced AI tools to analyze extensive podcast data, enabling smarter content creation and training.\n\n- **Josh DeTar highlighted** that **Google’s NotebookLM now scans over 300 large documents**, allowing them to upload nearly **300 hours of podcast transcripts** for in-depth querying and insight extraction (01:11).  \n    - This capability helped identify common themes and concerns across episodes, providing a strong base for marketing content and product management training.  \n    - Josh pointed out the AI’s accuracy in summarizing market fears and opportunities, validating its usefulness for their current projects.  \n    - The approach accelerates content generation and ensures relevance by pulling real, data-driven insights from historical material.  \n    - This also reduces manual research time, creating scalable workflows for ongoing content needs.\n\n- The team decided to **produce narrated videos using a draft script from Josh**, with Baylee’s team creating video cuts and transitions to enhance flow (03:38).  \n    - Josh will record the voiceover himself via Riverside once the script is polished collaboratively.  \n    - Baylee noted the script might need adjustments to better capture natural speech intonations and pacing.  \n    - This hybrid process balances in-house voice talent with expert video editing to maintain quality and authenticity.  \n    - It supports faster turnaround for marketing assets while keeping costs controlled.\n\n## **Conference Speaking and Industry Positioning**\n\nSpeaking engagements are a strategic priority to build credibility and showcase thought leadership within highly regulated financial sectors.\n\n- **Josh DeTar shared** that he recently spoke for **50 minutes at a credit union conference**, demonstrating safe, practical AI use without exposing sensitive data (05:32).  \n    - His talk covered simple examples that credit union execs can adopt now, addressing widespread AI fear and regulatory hesitation.  \n    - Josh explained the typical conference narratives are either dystopian or overhyped, so his focus on realistic first steps fills a critical gap in the market.  \n    - This practical approach has resonated well, leading to invitations for additional talks, including one scheduled for **early February**.  \n    - By emphasizing accessible AI adoption, Josh is positioning the company as a trusted resource for cautious financial institutions.\n\n- The team plans to **create polished speaker videos** showcasing Josh and other staff’s stage presence to improve conference submission success (08:12).  \n    - These videos will help demonstrate dynamic public speaking and industry authority to event organizers.  \n    - Josh is coordinating with Kevin to send recent footage for production, aligning with the broader strategy to win more speaking slots.  \n    - The goal is to move beyond booth presence, using speaking gigs as the main driver for visibility and lead generation.  \n    - This shift reflects a long-term investment in personal branding and trust building in a conservative market.\n\n## **Podcast Performance and Growth Metrics**\n\nThe podcast shows steady growth with strong audience engagement and increasing recognition in industry rankings.\n\n- **Igor Zagradjanin reported** that the podcast has released **24 episodes this year** with an average of nearly **200 downloads per episode**, showing consistent growth without spikes (08:59).  \n    - The audience is primarily in **North America**, followed closely by **Europe (21%) and Asia (20%)**, mostly listening via **Apple Podcasts and Spotify (18%)**.  \n    - Top episodes in **January, April, and August** each reached about **174 downloads**, indicating steady interest throughout the year.  \n    - Recent episodes maintain healthy engagement, with the top five totaling **572 downloads**, led by the \"KT the Fail\" episode with **141 downloads**.  \n    - This steady performance suggests a loyal and growing listener base.\n\n- The podcast achieved high visibility with rankings of **#4 on Feedspot’s 80 best banking podcasts** and **#17 on Million Podcasts'' top 50 banking podcasts in the U.S.** (11:22).  \n    - Igor noted an opportunity to investigate ranking criteria to inform future content and promotional strategies.  \n    - Baylee added that consistency and longevity are key ranking drivers, emphasizing the value of sustained publishing over time.  \n    - She highlighted that the podcast is outperforming about **75-85% of shows**, given most podcasts don’t surpass episode three or reach even 27 downloads in the first week.  \n    - This performance supports ongoing brand building and relationship growth in the financial sector.\n\n## **Content Strategy and Future Planning**\n\nThe team is focused on refining scripts, improving video assets, and expanding educational content to support marketing and training.\n\n- Baylee’s team will **develop rough video cuts** aligned with Josh’s draft script and propose narration pacing and transitions to improve flow (04:00).  \n    - The iterative script refinement aims to capture natural delivery and better reflect speaker intonations for audience engagement.  \n    - Josh’s availability to record voiceovers directly accelerates production timelines and maintains message authenticity.  \n    - This process combines creative editing with expert review to produce polished marketing videos efficiently.  \n    - The output will serve dual purposes: external marketing and internal product management training.\n\n- The plan includes gathering more speaker footage to build a library of dynamic content for conference submissions and marketing collateral (08:12).  \n    - This content will position the team as industry thought leaders and trusted experts in AI applications for finance.  \n    - The strategy leverages live speaking success to generate ongoing video assets supporting multiple business goals.  \n    - Coordinated production scheduling and asset management are critical to maintaining momentum.  \n    - These efforts align with long-term goals of increasing visibility and market credibility.\n\n## **Market Insights and Competitive Positioning**\n\nThe team is strategically using data and real-world feedback to guide messaging and product focus in a cautious, regulated environment.\n\n- Josh emphasized the widespread **fear of AI adoption in regulated industries**, especially financial services, where data privacy and legal concerns dominate (06:41).  \n    - His talks and content focus on **simple, safe AI use cases** that avoid sensitive data exposure but deliver operational gains.  \n    - This pragmatic approach contrasts with extreme narratives and helps build trust with cautious prospects.  \n    - The company’s messaging aims to break through the paralysis caused by overhyped or dystopian views of AI.  \n    - By aligning product education with regulatory realities, they improve adoption chances and customer confidence.\n\n- Speaker reputation and authentic demonstrations of AI in action are key differentiators in conference and marketing efforts (07:51).  \n    - The team recognizes that credibility comes from showing real examples, not just abstract claims.  \n    - This approach fosters deeper engagement and positions the company as a practical AI partner.  \n    - Long-term, this strategy supports broader platform adoption and competitive differentiation in a crowded market.  \n    - The focus on trust and simplicity addresses a critical barrier to entry for target customers.","outline":null,"keywords":["Google Notebook LM","podcast analytics","AI in banking","credit union executives","marketing content creation","podcast rankings"],"overview":"- **AI Tools for Content Creation:** Advanced AI analyzes podcast data, improving content generation and reducing manual research time. \n\n- **Speaker Engagements Strategy:** Focus on building credibility through practical AI talks at conferences, with an emphasis on trust-building.\n\n- **Podcast Growth Metrics:** Released 24 episodes this year, averaging nearly 200 downloads each, with a strong North American audience.\n\n- **High Podcast Visibility:** Achieved #4 ranking on Feedspot’s best banking podcasts, outperforming 75-85% of shows in the market.\n\n- **Content Strategy Focus:** Develop polished video assets and educational content for marketing and internal training to enhance engagement.\n\n- **Market Positioning Insights:** Emphasize safe AI use to mitigate fears in regulated industries, fostering confidence in target customers.","action_items":"\n**Josh DeTar**\nRecord narration for the video after receiving the finalized script via Riverside (03:38)\nCoordinate with Kevin to share the recent conference speaking video for marketing and submissions (08:12)\nReview script and communicate any questions during the video production process with Baylee (14:15)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nShare the video production brief to create a rough cut of the video with suggested visuals and transitions (03:16)\nRefine script length and content for an improved flow and natural narration style (04:50)\nInitiate contact with listing platforms (Feedspot, Million Podcasts) to inquire about podcast ranking criteria (12:51)\nProvide Josh with the finalized script when ready for recording (14:15)\n\n**Igor Zagradjanin**\nFollow up on gathering more detailed data or strategy behind podcast rankings on external lists (11:59)\nProvide ongoing podcast performance statistics and analytics updates (08:48)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"b7eef4d4-02c8-4dbf-b9f5-7b7b273ae1e7","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
    '2025-12-12 18:58:44.55971+00',
    '2025-12-12 18:58:44.55971+00'
  )
  RETURNING meeting_id, contract_id
)
INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Tyfone // Marketers in Demand - Weekly Meeting (new)',
  '## **AI Integration and Content Automation**

The team is leveraging advanced AI tools to analyze extensive podcast data, enabling smarter content creation and training.

- **Josh DeTar highlighted** that **Google’s NotebookLM now scans over 300 large documents**, allowing them to upload nearly **300 hours of podcast transcripts** for in-depth querying and insight extraction (01:11).  
    - This capability helped identify common themes and concerns across episodes, providing a strong base for marketing content and product management training.  
    - Josh pointed out the AI’s accuracy in summarizing market fears and opportunities, validating its usefulness for their current projects.  
    - The approach accelerates content generation and ensures relevance by pulling real, data-driven insights from historical material.  
    - This also reduces manual research time, creating scalable workflows for ongoing content needs.

- The team decided to **produce narrated videos using a draft script from Josh**, with Baylee’s team creating video cuts and transitions to enhance flow (03:38).  
    - Josh will record the voiceover himself via Riverside once the script is polished collaboratively.  
    - Baylee noted the script might need adjustments to better capture natural speech intonations and pacing.  
    - This hybrid process balances in-house voice talent with expert video editing to maintain quality and authenticity.  
    - It supports faster turnaround for marketing assets while keeping costs controlled.

## **Conference Speaking and Industry Positioning**

Speaking engagements are a strategic priority to build credibility and showcase thought leadership within highly regulated financial sectors.

- **Josh DeTar shared** that he recently spoke for **50 minutes at a credit union conference**, demonstrating safe, practical AI use without exposing sensitive data (05:32).  
    - His talk covered simple examples that credit union execs can adopt now, addressing widespread AI fear and regulatory hesitation.  
    - Josh explained the typical conference narratives are either dystopian or overhyped, so his focus on realistic first steps fills a critical gap in the market.  
    - This practical approach has resonated well, leading to invitations for additional talks, including one scheduled for **early February**.  
    - By emphasizing accessible AI adoption, Josh is positioning the company as a trusted resource for cautious financial institutions.

- The team plans to **create polished speaker videos** showcasing Josh and other staff’s stage presence to improve conference submission success (08:12).  
    - These videos will help demonstrate dynamic public speaking and industry authority to event organizers.  
    - Josh is coordinating with Kevin to send recent footage for production, aligning with the broader strategy to win more speaking slots.  
    - The goal is to move beyond booth presence, using speaking gigs as the main driver for visibility and lead generation.  
    - This shift reflects a long-term investment in personal branding and trust building in a conservative market.

## **Podcast Performance and Growth Metrics**

The podcast shows steady growth with strong audience engagement and increasing recognition in industry rankings.

- **Igor Zagradjanin reported** that the podcast has released **24 episodes this year** with an average of nearly **200 downloads per episode**, showing consistent growth without spikes (08:59).  
    - The audience is primarily in **North America**, followed closely by **Europe (21%) and Asia (20%)**, mostly listening via **Apple Podcasts and Spotify (18%)**.  
    - Top episodes in **January, April, and August** each reached about **174 downloads**, indicating steady interest throughout the year.  
    - Recent episodes maintain healthy engagement, with the top five totaling **572 downloads**, led by the "KT the Fail" episode with **141 downloads**.  
    - This steady performance suggests a loyal and growing listener base.

- The podcast achieved high visibility with rankings of **#4 on Feedspot’s 80 best banking podcasts** and **#17 on Million Podcasts'' top 50 banking podcasts in the U.S.** (11:22).  
    - Igor noted an opportunity to investigate ranking criteria to inform future content and promotional strategies.  
    - Baylee added that consistency and longevity are key ranking drivers, emphasizing the value of sustained publishing over time.  
    - She highlighted that the podcast is outperforming about **75-85% of shows**, given most podcasts don’t surpass episode three or reach even 27 downloads in the first week.  
    - This performance supports ongoing brand building and relationship growth in the financial sector.

## **Content Strategy and Future Planning**

The team is focused on refining scripts, improving video assets, and expanding educational content to support marketing and training.

- Baylee’s team will **develop rough video cuts** aligned with Josh’s draft script and propose narration pacing and transitions to improve flow (04:00).  
    - The iterative script refinement aims to capture natural delivery and better reflect speaker intonations for audience engagement.  
    - Josh’s availability to record voiceovers directly accelerates production timelines and maintains message authenticity.  
    - This process combines creative editing with expert review to produce polished marketing videos efficiently.  
    - The output will serve dual purposes: external marketing and internal product management training.

- The plan includes gathering more speaker footage to build a library of dynamic content for conference submissions and marketing collateral (08:12).  
    - This content will position the team as industry thought leaders and trusted experts in AI applications for finance.  
    - The strategy leverages live speaking success to generate ongoing video assets supporting multiple business goals.  
    - Coordinated production scheduling and asset management are critical to maintaining momentum.  
    - These efforts align with long-term goals of increasing visibility and market credibility.

## **Market Insights and Competitive Positioning**

The team is strategically using data and real-world feedback to guide messaging and product focus in a cautious, regulated environment.

- Josh emphasized the widespread **fear of AI adoption in regulated industries**, especially financial services, where data privacy and legal concerns dominate (06:41).  
    - His talks and content focus on **simple, safe AI use cases** that avoid sensitive data exposure but deliver operational gains.  
    - This pragmatic approach contrasts with extreme narratives and helps build trust with cautious prospects.  
    - The company’s messaging aims to break through the paralysis caused by overhyped or dystopian views of AI.  
    - By aligning product education with regulatory realities, they improve adoption chances and customer confidence.

- Speaker reputation and authentic demonstrations of AI in action are key differentiators in conference and marketing efforts (07:51).  
    - The team recognizes that credibility comes from showing real examples, not just abstract claims.  
    - This approach fosters deeper engagement and positions the company as a practical AI partner.  
    - Long-term, this strategy supports broader platform adoption and competitive differentiation in a crowded market.  
    - The focus on trust and simplicity addresses a critical barrier to entry for target customers.',
  '2025-12-12 16:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Record narration for the video after receiving the finalized script via Riverside (03:38)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with Kevin to share the recent conference speaking video for marketing and submissions (08:12)","completed":false},{"text":"Review script and communicate any questions during the video production process with Baylee (14:15)","completed":false},{"text":"Share the video production brief to create a rough cut of the video with suggested visuals and transitions (03:16)","completed":false},{"text":"Refine script length and content for an improved flow and natural narration style (04:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Initiate contact with listing platforms (Feedspot, Million Podcasts) to inquire about podcast ranking criteria (12:51)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide Josh with the finalized script when ready for recording (14:15)","completed":false},{"text":"Follow up on gathering more detailed data or strategy behind podcast rankings on external lists (11:59)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide ongoing podcast performance statistics and analytics updates (08:48)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: Baylee Gunnell and Kate Hahn (2025-12-12 15:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '833f1003-bf16-434b-afab-a705072e5eef',
    '2025-12-12 15:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KBQHTX9HAPQEMHVJSN6SKHPZ',
    'Baylee Gunnell and Kate Hahn',
    '{"Baylee Gunnell","audreysteuerwald","Pooja ParasuRaman","Victoria Owen","katehahn"}'::text[],
    1777,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/81711381072?pwd=lWPLEgazaDVZLAJcTI6G5R9yoa7H1B.1',
    '{"id":"01KBQHTX9HAPQEMHVJSN6SKHPZ","title":"Baylee Gunnell and Kate Hahn","summary":{"notes":"## **Post-Event Content Strategy**\n\nThe team agreed to focus on creating an **AI Playbook** and related content from the Bazaar Voice Summit rather than a direct event recap (20:23).\n\n- **The main deliverable will be a comprehensive AI Playbook** that consolidates key insights from Summit sessions, with potential smaller workbooks or practical guides on themes like the AAA framework and supply chain (05:43).\n    - Victoria Owen emphasized building practical workbooks using quotes from brand leaders and retailers to support implementation.\n    - Kate Hahn confirmed the content should stand alone, not tied tightly to Summit branding, ensuring longer-term use.\n    - Baylee Gunnell suggested video clips from each session plus a polished highlight compilation to enrich the playbook.\n    - The team stressed letting available source content guide deliverables without forcing additional materials, prioritizing efficiency (23:41).\n\n- **Promotional strategy will bundle most assets together** to maximize reach but allow some standalone pieces for evergreen value, focusing on LinkedIn and YouTube as key channels (06:52).\n    - Audrey Steuerwald supported using multi-touch campaigns combining video clips, document ads, and banner ads.\n    - Kate flagged document ads as the most effective LinkedIn ad format, with carousels deprioritized due to poor performance.\n    - Organic social will leverage the same creative assets as paid to simplify execution (27:13).\n\n- **Sales enablement assets like one-pagers linking to on-demand sessions are under consideration** for select sessions featuring external speakers to support outreach follow-up (14:24).\n    - Kate and Pooja discussed piloting one-pagers for two sessions, such as Coca-Cola and Nestlé, to provide bite-sized takeaways with session links.\n    - The decision depends on sales team interest and session relevance.\n\n## **Content Development Process and Timeline**\n\nClear coordination and phased content development steps were established to align on deliverables and timelines (09:05).\n\n- **Templates for quote cards, ads, and video promos will be created ahead of the event** to accelerate post-event production once source code is available (09:42).\n    - Baylee Gunnell will lead on template creation, allowing insertion of session quotes later.\n    - A detailed brief outlining Summit messaging, session types, and target themes will be provided by Victoria Owen within days to guide content work (19:49).\n    - Dry runs with speakers will be leveraged to capture key points early for content prep.\n\n- **The post-event content production is expected to start immediately after Summit on January 21st**, with an initial asset push soon after January 22nd when source materials are accessible (09:05).\n    - Baylee will confirm rough timelines once deliverables are finalized.\n    - The team agreed on flexibility to roll out initial promos quickly, followed by subsequent detailed assets.\n\n- **Content will be hosted on a promo landing page within the existing Bazaar Voice resources page due to website constraints**, focusing on simple header images and copy rather than a full custom page (12:18).\n    - Kate clarified that technical limits make a basic landing page with downloadable assets the preferred approach.\n    - Design support for banners and headers will be provided by Baylee''s team once specifications are shared.\n\n- **Canva is the preferred design tool for assets**, and Audrey confirmed their team can supply Canva templates for efficient collaboration (28:40).\n\n## **Video and Multimedia Utilization**\n\nVideo assets are prioritized for engagement across paid and organic channels to drive awareness and nurture leads (23:50).\n\n- **Short video clips under 30 seconds will be created for Google Performance Max campaigns**, with the goal to tease the AI Playbook and Summit highlights (24:08).\n    - Kate emphasized PMAX videos should have a clear call to action linking to the broader playbook.\n    - Audrey noted the value of teaser videos to boost event hype and maintain momentum post-event.\n\n- **YouTube and LinkedIn will be the main platforms for video distribution**, with an emphasis on repurposing video clips for organic social posts (11:51).\n    - Baylee confirmed no additional video hosting platforms are planned beyond these.\n    - The team discussed potential for a highlight reel or podcast-style recap to serve as a hero video asset.\n\n- **Potential for a “bloopers reel” or more authentic behind-the-scenes content was raised** as a creative engagement tool, though its usage remains exploratory (25:25).\n    - Audrey and Kate saw this as a way to add authenticity and personality to the campaign.\n\n## **Collaboration and Tools Integration**\n\nThe team outlined collaborative workflows and tools to streamline content creation and sharing (17:20).\n\n- **New North will receive a detailed Summit brief and session materials from Victoria Owen**, establishing a single point of contact for ongoing communication (19:49).\n    - The brief will include session narratives, panel vs. presentation formats, and key speaker info.\n    - Dry runs and speaker question decks will be shared early to identify rich content.\n\n- **Video source code and recordings will be pulled by Bazaar Voice and shared with New North**, avoiding duplicate access and easing content extraction (17:44).\n    - Kate offered to provide Boldcast platform access for AI-assisted clip generation.\n    - Baylee welcomed the opportunity to explore AI tools within Boldcast to accelerate clip creation.\n\n- **Email marketing will include both newsletter-style sends and nurture program one-offs**, with New North providing copy options for flexibility (10:41).\n    - Banner ads sized for email will be supplied by Bazaar Voice.\n    - The team confirmed alignment on channels and formats to ensure smooth integration.\n\n## **Brand Positioning and Messaging Alignment**\n\nThe group prioritized aligning content with Bazaar Voice’s broader brand narratives rather than rigid frameworks (21:19).\n\n- **The “Be Discovered, Be Trusted, Be Chosen” framework was deprioritized** in favor of messaging driven by session content and client relevance (21:36).\n    - Pooja advocated for a client-centric content approach rather than forcing brand narratives.\n    - Kate emphasized leveraging rich source content from Summit to avoid extra production work.\n\n- **Content themes will focus on AI and practical guidance**, reflecting the evolving market demand and Bazaar Voice’s thought leadership (05:43).\n    - This approach aims to strengthen Bazaar Voice’s position as a knowledge leader in AI-driven marketing.\n    - The AAA framework and supply chain topics will be highlighted as core sub-themes.\n\n- **Packaging content as an AI Playbook rather than just Summit recap enhances longevity and market relevance**, supporting ongoing engagement beyond the event (20:23).\n    - This strategic positioning was agreed upon by key speakers including Kate and Baylee.\n\n## **Sales Enablement and Internal Use**\n\nThere is interest in creating assets to support sales teams with quick-reference materials linking to full sessions (14:24).\n\n- **One-pagers summarizing key takeaways and linking to on-demand videos will be developed for select external speaker sessions** (14:57).\n    - These would serve as easy “grab and share” tools in sales meetings and follow-ups.\n    - The team will pilot this approach with two sessions to assess usefulness.\n\n- **The decision on scale will depend on sales team feedback and session relevance**, with potential to expand if successful (15:59).\n    - Pooja noted the need to balance asset creation with practical usage to avoid wasted effort.\n\n- **These sales tools complement the broader content campaign by providing targeted, actionable insights for client conversations**.","outline":null,"keywords":["Bazaar Voice Summit","AI Playbook","Post-Event Content","Content Strategy","Video Assets","Promotion Channels"],"overview":"- **Focus on AI Playbook:** Key insights from the Bazaar Voice Summit will create a standalone AI Playbook, enhancing long-term value.\n\n- **Efficient Production Timeline:** Post-event content production starts January 21, with initial assets ready shortly after, ensuring quick rollouts.\n\n- **Promotion Strategy:** Bundle content for maximum reach while allowing some materials to stand alone, targeting LinkedIn and YouTube primarily.\n\n- **Video Clips for Engagement:** Short clips under 30 seconds will support Google campaigns to tease the AI Playbook and highlight event key points.\n\n- **Collaboration Tools Established:** New North will handle Summit briefs, with effective access to content resources to streamline communication.\n\n- **Sales Enablement Assets Considered:** Developing one-pagers summarizing key session takeaways to assist sales teams following specific external speaker sessions.","action_items":"\n**Pooja ParasuRaman**\nProvide New North team with a comprehensive Summit brief covering event overview, messaging, sessions, and post-event content strategy (16:06)\n\n**Victoria Owen**\nOwn briefing process and coordinate sharing of detailed content packages with New North for informed content creation (16:06)\n\n**Kate Hahn**\nProvide event slide decks and descriptions of speakers in more detail to New North as available (18:13)\nPull video recordings post-event and share with New North (17:44)\nDetermine preferred deliverables and timeline with New North based on briefing and content from the event (28:00)\nRegister New North team for the Summit event to enable their attendance (29:18)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nCreate templates for quote cards and promotional ads ahead of Summit event for faster post-event delivery (09:42)\nDevelop recommended content deliverables and proposed timeline after finalizing Summit materials (27:46)\nCollaborate with Bazaar Voice on leveraging Boldcast AI clipping functionality for post-event video assets if given access (18:01)\n\n**Audrey Steuerwald**\nAlign with Bazaar Voice team on the preferred structure and bundling of post-event content to maintain consistency (08:07)\nCoordinate sharing of Canva design templates to facilitate asset production with New North (28:40)\n"},"duration":29.610000610351562,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":1,"name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"id":2,"name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"id":3,"name":"Victoria Owen"},{"id":4,"name":"katehahn"}],"sentences":[{"text":"It is.","index":0,"end_time":0.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Every single room has these, like, cute little, like, trees or bubbles.","index":1,"end_time":6.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":0.96,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"She does it all.","index":2,"end_time":8.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":7.12,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Oh, it''s really cute.","index":3,"end_time":10.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":8.64,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"You''re staying there for the weekend?","index":4,"end_time":12.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":11.28,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"No, I''m just here for the morning.","index":5,"end_time":17.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":13.92,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"I''m.","index":6,"end_time":18.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m only 30 minutes away, so I''m meeting the Jersey girls, Alex Kirk and Laura Staples.","index":7,"end_time":25.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":18.44,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":8,"end_time":26.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":25.32,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Oh, so they live really close to my mom.","index":9,"end_time":29.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":26.78,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Amazing.","index":10,"end_time":30.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":29.98,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Always nice to get a change of scenery, especially if you''ve beautiful windows to look out.","index":11,"end_time":41.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":35.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I mean, ifI could work here all day.","index":12,"end_time":44.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":41.82,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":13,"end_time":44.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":44.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So nice.","index":14,"end_time":47.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":46.62,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"I love this little room.","index":15,"end_time":48.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":47.22,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s.","index":16,"end_time":50.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":49.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s a great setup.","index":17,"end_time":51.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":50.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Windows all around too.","index":18,"end_time":54.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":53.51,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"It looks amazing.","index":19,"end_time":57.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":56.23,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Looks like a nice virtual background for sure.","index":20,"end_time":60.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":57.15,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Right?","index":21,"end_time":61.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":60.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I should just take a photo of it.","index":22,"end_time":62.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":61.27,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"And swap it out.","index":23,"end_time":65.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":64.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That would be awesome.","index":24,"end_time":67.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":66.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Bailey, I love your background too.","index":25,"end_time":70.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":68.55,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Where are you located?","index":26,"end_time":71.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":70.07,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"I''m in Utah.","index":27,"end_time":73.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":72.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":28,"end_time":74.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":74.31,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Yeah, I do like it here.","index":29,"end_time":77.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":75.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We have lots of pretty mountains.","index":30,"end_time":78.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":77.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, gorgeous.","index":31,"end_time":80.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":79.63,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"I''ve only been once, but we went hiking.","index":32,"end_time":82.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":80.35,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"It was into Arches.","index":33,"end_time":84.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":82.51,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"That''s in Utah, right?","index":34,"end_time":85.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":84.87,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Arches, yeah.","index":35,"end_time":86.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":85.71,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s definitely one of the more iconic places here.","index":36,"end_time":91.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":88.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Amazing.","index":37,"end_time":97.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":96.83,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Okay.","index":38,"end_time":98.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":98.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I mean, while we wait, I know you guys know Audrey.","index":39,"end_time":101.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":98.71,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"While we wait, maybe for Kate, maybe Victoria and I can give you a quick intro because we''re meeting for the first time.","index":40,"end_time":108.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":101.79,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"So.","index":41,"end_time":109.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":109.28,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"So one.","index":42,"end_time":111.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":110.48,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"So I. I head the brand portfolio here at Bazaar Voice.","index":43,"end_time":115.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":111.12,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"And so basically that covers the content side of it, which covers content marketing and content strategy as well.","index":44,"end_time":124.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":115.92,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"And then obviously Aubrey''s team, which is the creative team on the social and the design side.","index":45,"end_time":130.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":125.2,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"We also have comms, like the PR digital comm side of things.","index":46,"end_time":135.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":131.52,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"And then more recently, we also kind of got advocacy into the brand remit.","index":47,"end_time":142.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":136.18,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"So that''s more on the client advocate.","index":48,"end_time":145.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":142.74,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"I know you guys have been working on some of the case study initially with Lauren V. As well, but yeah, so that, that kind of pretty much covers the portfolio.","index":49,"end_time":154.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":145.1,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"And yeah, I''ve been at.","index":50,"end_time":155.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":154.46,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Was always, I want to say about 2ish years now.","index":51,"end_time":158.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":155.94,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":52,"end_time":160.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":159.68,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"And I''ve heard of New north quite a bit.","index":53,"end_time":162.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":160.64,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"So glad to be meeting you guys for the first time in a while.","index":54,"end_time":166.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":162.76,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"And Victoria, are you.","index":55,"end_time":169.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":167.76,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Are you able to speak right now?","index":56,"end_time":171.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":169.4,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"You okay to connect?","index":57,"end_time":173.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":171.8,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I''m fine.","index":58,"end_time":175.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":174.24,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"I''m just having.","index":59,"end_time":176.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":176,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"I''ve not got great wi fi today, so I''m via my phone, so that''s why I''m off camera noise.","index":60,"end_time":186.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":177.44,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"You want to give them a quick intro to you and what you''re also connecting with New north for?","index":61,"end_time":191.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":186.13,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Yeah, sure.","index":62,"end_time":193.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":192.33,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"So I lead on content strategy and the content strategist.","index":63,"end_time":197.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":193.21,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"So sort of determining what kind of content we need to be put now, how that then folds back into sort of like our brand messaging and campaign plans and all of that good stuff.","index":64,"end_time":208.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":197.53,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"And yeah, that''s sort of whistle stop tool.","index":65,"end_time":213.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":210.42,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"Amazing.","index":66,"end_time":218.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":217.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I actually don''t think I''ve met you, Audrey, yet.","index":67,"end_time":220.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":218.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I believe you''ve been working with Natalie on some other projects.","index":68,"end_time":225.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":220.78,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yes, yes.","index":69,"end_time":227.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":226.42,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"So I think, yeah, this is our first time meeting, so I''m Audrey Sterwald, as Pooja said, head creative design and social media.","index":70,"end_time":235.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":227.58,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Been with Bizarre Voice for almost five years.","index":71,"end_time":238.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":235.97,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Audrey, you look so fancy today.","index":72,"end_time":241.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":239.57,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"We were just talking about that.","index":73,"end_time":243.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":242.37,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"We spent 15 minutes talking about Audrey and her background.","index":74,"end_time":246.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":243.69,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"It''s at my mom''s house and she is so fancy.","index":75,"end_time":251.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":247.17,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"It''s the sweater, too.","index":76,"end_time":255.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":253.81,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"I''m a girl.","index":77,"end_time":255.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":255.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, well, I''m going to lunch with Laura Staples and Alex Kirk.","index":78,"end_time":258.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":255.89,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Do it up a little bit.","index":79,"end_time":260.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":259.89,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"You''re fancy, I see.","index":80,"end_time":262.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":261.01,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Amazing.","index":81,"end_time":264.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":263.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, I believe this conversation is to talk about the Bizarre Voice Summit strategy, mostly for post event.","index":82,"end_time":272.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":264.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Kate already gave us some details about the event and maybe where we can get plugged in.","index":83,"end_time":278.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":272.78,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We have some stuff prepped with, like, questions, but if you have stuff prepped, we''re flexible on however you want to go about this.","index":84,"end_time":285.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":278.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''ll jump in just to kind of like, I think we''ve all, like, chatted about this, but I talked with Gab, one of, I don''t know whatever, whether to call you guys New north or Marketers in Demand.","index":85,"end_time":297.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":285.34,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"So I feel like I always, like, stumble a touch.","index":86,"end_time":300.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":297.87,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"But with these other humans and one of the things that they work on with them is an annual podcast, kind of like roundup Playbooks, like a very large anchor piece of content, given all the source code that we''re going to have from Summit.","index":87,"end_time":318.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":300.23,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"I was like, ooh, that''s kind of interesting.","index":88,"end_time":319.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":318.16,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"If we would then like use New north off the back of that to pull together kind of that, like actual AI Playbook, given all the content that we''ll have.","index":89,"end_time":329.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":319.88,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"And so I know, Victoria, you were thinking through like a bill of materials or kind of thoughts around, like, what types of things we might want to engage New north with.","index":90,"end_time":338.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":329.72,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Do you have more specific thoughts to today to share?","index":91,"end_time":342.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":338.88,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that main, like almost like a hero piece, Playbook piece is one of the main ones.","index":92,"end_time":351.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":343.58,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"And then I was also thinking we could depending on what sort of like key themes come out of it.","index":93,"end_time":357.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":351.7,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"Obviously AI is like the main one.","index":94,"end_time":359.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":357.419,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"We''ve got like the AAA framework content, supply chain piece and all of those bits.","index":95,"end_time":369.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":360.14,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"So I was thinking we could do like practical like E guides based off of those pieces.","index":96,"end_time":376.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":369.06,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"Sort of like almost like a bit of a.","index":97,"end_time":378.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":376.28,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"A workbook for how people can implement those different elements and we can leverage sort of like quotes from like the brand leaders and retailers that we''ve got speaking at the event to sort of support that messaging was sort of like the key things themes that I was thinking.","index":98,"end_time":397.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":378.92,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"So sort of like that hero piece that kind of encapsulated everything AI and then sort of almost like little offshoots from that which are more practical type workbook pieces were my.","index":99,"end_time":410.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":397.32,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"My main thoughts.","index":100,"end_time":411.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":410.01,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"I love that question.","index":101,"end_time":413.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":412.05,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"For the bizarre boy side on like promo for those pieces, would we want to keep those all packaged together as part of this so then we get like the paid promo or an organic promo that then connects into like that playbook download or to these other guides Just to like keep it all packaged is one thing.","index":102,"end_time":435.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":413.57,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"I''d say potentially some of them could stand up on their own like the AAA framework 100%.","index":103,"end_time":443.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":437.7,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"That could be sort of like a standalone piece.","index":104,"end_time":445.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":443.78,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"We can bundle it up as sort of like a all encompassing summit piece but then also separate it out.","index":105,"end_time":452.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":445.78,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"So that''s got a bit more longevity.","index":106,"end_time":454.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":452.7,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"It''s.","index":107,"end_time":454.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":454.42,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"It doesn''t have to sort of like talk about summit particularly within that so that it has sort of like that longer evergreen sort of status.","index":108,"end_time":462.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":454.7,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":109,"end_time":463.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":463.26,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"But then I think like for like the promo posts to drive to the thing in addition to organic or like selfishly even like for nurture emails that like then like LinkedIn like we might want to just build the like promo surround in to like how to drive to these.","index":110,"end_time":479.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":463.78,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"But Audrey, would you prefer that we just keep it all bundled together or do you want to pull certain pieces in house?","index":111,"end_time":486.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":479.86,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"I think it makes sense to just keep it all with you all and we can.","index":112,"end_time":494.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":487.07,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"We should probably align on our side like what that looks like.","index":113,"end_time":498.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":494.43,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":114,"end_time":498.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":498.35,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"I''m assuming we want some video clips maybe, but possibly also I don''t know like would there be any like banner ads or anything you think Kate?","index":115,"end_time":510.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":499.79,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Or mostly video for a promo?","index":116,"end_time":513,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":510.68,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"I think potentially we could do banner ads for the bigot.","index":117,"end_time":517.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":513.4,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"For the big playbook, like for the biggest like that, that AI playbook asset I think could be kind of interesting.","index":118,"end_time":524.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":517.36,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":119,"end_time":525.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":525.32,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Or maybe even like document ad.","index":120,"end_time":527.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":525.8,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Yep.","index":121,"end_time":529.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":528.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then those same things I think we could also repurpose on organic social.","index":122,"end_time":536.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":530.44,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"So I think this could just be a really interesting fully fleshed out campaign.","index":123,"end_time":543.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":537.83,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Multiple touch points.","index":124,"end_time":544.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":543.43,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"So I''m curious Bailey, on timing, like if the event is January 21st and we have like A tight plan of like what we want post event going into the event, but then you don''t actually like, obviously have the source code until January 22nd.","index":125,"end_time":562.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":545.51,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Like once it''s all all over, what does that look like?","index":126,"end_time":567.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":562.67,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Like, what is the kind of like the timeline then?","index":127,"end_time":569.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":567.23,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"And like, could we roll it so that we get the first bunch of like the asset with the promos around and then move on to the other pieces just so we''re not like waiting for everything to come all at once?","index":128,"end_time":582.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":570.11,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Yeah, that is a great question.","index":129,"end_time":584.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":582.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think before we can decide a timeline, we need to know exactly like what the deliverables are going to be.","index":130,"end_time":592.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":586.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And I think since we''re a little bit early on this, we could probably start creating templates for some things in advance.","index":131,"end_time":600.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":592.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So like the quote cards, we get enough templates already in place and then just add in the quotes later, we could probably start some templates for the ads and then put in the text after the event.","index":132,"end_time":609.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":600.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So things like that you, you''re already touching on a lot of things that I put in the slides.","index":133,"end_time":614.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":609.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I''ll just go ahead and share my screen and we can go through a couple questions that I have and then we can nail down exactly what those deliverables are and we can get into maybe some timeline things.","index":134,"end_time":626.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":614.78,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So first, just starting off with the channels that you want to use, it sounds like you''re already talking email.","index":135,"end_time":633.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":628.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Is that primarily a newsletter or do you have a list that you send just like simple text emails?","index":136,"end_time":640.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":633.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We have a few different options.","index":137,"end_time":643.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":641.62,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"I would say a newsletter option would be interesting and maybe like a series of them.","index":138,"end_time":651.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":643.86,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Like we''ve talked about wanting to launch a newsletter, but we need like a touch more time.","index":139,"end_time":654.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":651.18,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"So this might be a like stop gap for us, like if we used this for that.","index":140,"end_time":659.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":654.82,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"But then also we have nurture programs.","index":141,"end_time":663.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":660.58,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"So it''d be like just like a one off email to this asset that would be a part of like a broader stream.","index":142,"end_time":669.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":663.02,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Okay, and then where would you want us to plug in there?","index":143,"end_time":673.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":669.49,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like do you want us to put together like maybe two or three copy options for the email and then your team can plug in where you want to use it?","index":144,"end_time":682.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":673.41,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yep.","index":145,"end_time":683.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":682.769,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":146,"end_time":684.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":683.57,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So the next is just for like.","index":147,"end_time":687.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":685.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Also banner, graphic banners.","index":148,"end_time":689.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":687.25,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Is that right, Kate?","index":149,"end_time":691.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":690.93,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"The website for the email.","index":150,"end_time":694.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":692.58,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Oh, email.","index":151,"end_time":696.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":695.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And we can give you sizes.","index":152,"end_time":698.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":697.22,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":153,"end_time":699.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":699.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":154,"end_time":700.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":699.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, we can do that.","index":155,"end_time":701.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":700.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So then next is organic social.","index":156,"end_time":705.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":702.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"What primary platforms do you like to use?","index":157,"end_time":710.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":707.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It would mostly be LinkedIn and YouTube.","index":158,"end_time":714.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":711.46,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Okay, so for that, well, my next slide we can get into the types of stuff we we do there.","index":159,"end_time":721.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":715.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We could do there.","index":160,"end_time":722.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":721.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then for the website, do you want help with like designing maybe some of the landing pages?","index":161,"end_time":730.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":722.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I actually wanted to ask about that.","index":162,"end_time":734.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":732.75,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"So I think like even just going up, if you remember even the.","index":163,"end_time":738.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":734.71,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"And.","index":164,"end_time":738.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":738.67,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"And this is like more for the bizarre voice theme.","index":165,"end_time":740.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":738.95,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Like but if you remember the holiday headquarters that we kind of bundled up towards the end which literally was all encompassing like a video and a downloadable and whatever.","index":166,"end_time":750.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":740.71,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Like.","index":167,"end_time":751.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":750.87,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"So we are planning to do like a all summit page like last year or is it not?","index":168,"end_time":758.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":751.51,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"I. Audrey, have you and Katie talked about that?","index":169,"end_time":762.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":759.03,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"I know we''re not.","index":170,"end_time":762.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":762.07,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"We''re moving away from Sarah.","index":171,"end_time":763.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":762.75,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"So like I don''t think planning to create a Saros experience.","index":172,"end_time":767.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":763.95,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":173,"end_time":767.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":767.11,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"We do typically like tag them in a way so that you can like pull them all together to see them.","index":174,"end_time":778.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":771.83,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"But I think like for me it''s like less about a landing page design, especially just given like our site challenges.","index":175,"end_time":784.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":778.08,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Currently it''s more about like the promo landing page to like put the asset on to get the download.","index":176,"end_time":792.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":784.12,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"So it''s like whatever assets we create would then have a corresponding landing page copy and a header.","index":177,"end_time":799.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":792.96,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Okay.","index":178,"end_time":800.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":800.06,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Okay.","index":179,"end_time":802.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":801.98,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"So if we do copy and a header and when you say a header like the.","index":180,"end_time":806.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":802.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The full top bar design for that or is it just like a nice single image at the top?","index":181,"end_time":811.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":807.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We can send that.","index":182,"end_time":813.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":812.7,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"But it''s just like on our resources page we''re pretty.","index":183,"end_time":816.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":813.74,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Our website''s a little janky.","index":184,"end_time":821.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":818.06,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"It''s a technical term that we use here and so like we don''t have a ton of flexibility without a lot of development.","index":185,"end_time":829.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":821.9,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"So like what you see is what we will be asking for.","index":186,"end_time":833.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":830.22,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"There won''t be something like special.","index":187,"end_time":834.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":833.02,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Okay, sounds good.","index":188,"end_time":836.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":835.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then for video too, it sounds like mostly maybe posting some stuff on YouTube and LinkedIn.","index":189,"end_time":845.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":838.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think you''d maybe talked about some sales enablement things is there.","index":190,"end_time":851.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":846.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m.","index":191,"end_time":851.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":851.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m guessing maybe you''d still post that on YouTube but you.","index":192,"end_time":854.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":851.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do you have any other places you would maybe host that?","index":193,"end_time":856.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":854.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Not from a video perspective.","index":194,"end_time":860.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":858.83,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"I don''t think.","index":195,"end_time":861.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":860.91,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"One of the things.","index":196,"end_time":864.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":863.95,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"That we had talked about and I''m curious like or we had talked about internally within the growth team, but I''d be curious to get the BD side''s thoughts is like would we want session one pagers that then like links to the on demand sessions for sales to pull into the things that they''re doing.","index":197,"end_time":882.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":864.83,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"So they have just like a super simple like grab for like meetings that they have or like that they could send afterwards.","index":198,"end_time":892.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":882.67,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Is it like in like an email for them to send.","index":199,"end_time":899.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":897.23,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Or you mean like a.","index":200,"end_time":900.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":899.91,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Like a one page?","index":201,"end_time":901.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":901.07,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"A one pager?","index":202,"end_time":902.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":902.03,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":203,"end_time":903.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":902.91,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"That they could like link to and.","index":204,"end_time":904.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":903.27,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Share out, which would be like takeaways from that session.","index":205,"end_time":907.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":904.79,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":206,"end_time":909.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":909.23,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"And then a link to like the full session if people want to see it.","index":207,"end_time":912.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":909.59,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, if it''s useful to them, I think we could try that.","index":208,"end_time":917.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":914.15,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"I''m just wondering how much they will also really use like single session one pages as well.","index":209,"end_time":925.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":918.31,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"I think for me it like depends on the session.","index":210,"end_time":927.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":925.59,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Like the Coke, if we would have done it for the Coca Cola.","index":211,"end_time":930.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":927.75,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"I feel like there were like enough good tidbits that I could see enterprise, like using that as a thing to be like, hey, you missed it.","index":212,"end_time":937.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":930.59,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"But we actually, because we''re just talking about these topics so much that then they could be like, oh, we actually just talked to Coke about this.","index":213,"end_time":943.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":937.67,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Let me send you the thing like after our call.","index":214,"end_time":946.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":943.55,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"You know what I mean?","index":215,"end_time":947.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":946.35,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"So it might be more relevant to the ones that we have external speakers for.","index":216,"end_time":953.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":947.31,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Yeah, like the Nestle person as well.","index":217,"end_time":958.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":955.31,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"I think maybe we just pick like.","index":218,"end_time":959.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":958.31,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Two of them or something and then see if we want to do more.","index":219,"end_time":963.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":959.87,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":220,"end_time":966.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":966.04,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"And again, like going back to some of this and you know, just to start off with, for the team as well, for the new north team, like one of the things that Victoria and I were discussing is like, we will start this off for you guys with a brief initially.","index":221,"end_time":981.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":966.36,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"So we are all on the same page.","index":222,"end_time":982.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":981.4,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"We already have like a summit brief.","index":223,"end_time":985.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":983.32,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"But I think what we can put together is just in terms of like a quick even understanding for you guys in terms of what is summit and what is the kind of messaging that we''re going for, what are the kind of sessions that will have and even in terms of like the thought in terms of post con, post event content packaging, like this is the ideal kind of content we would like to package up with.","index":224,"end_time":1007.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":985.24,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"And then we can maybe further build that out into, you know, which are the ones that like Kate and Audrey want to take into channel planning and channel play.","index":225,"end_time":1015.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1007.14,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"So then I think like we can build up over the next couple of days.","index":226,"end_time":1019.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1015.9,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"So I just wanted to let you guys know that we''ll kick it off with a brief for you guys.","index":227,"end_time":1023.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1019.54,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"So you have a sense and I think in that a couple of things, even in terms of timing, I''m just wondering if you guys can indicate is like there are some things, I think based on that brief and based on the sessions, we can start thinking of working on things even before summit.","index":228,"end_time":1039.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1024,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"And then obviously, like if you Guys can also join Summit.","index":229,"end_time":1043.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1040.32,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"That also gives you a better understanding of what''s happening session by session.","index":230,"end_time":1047.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1043.52,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"So you can kind of pick on what are some of the meaty points to kind of start thinking of building on as well.","index":231,"end_time":1053.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1047.44,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"And then Kate, would you prefer that we give the team like Goldcast the login or do we pull and then share it with the team?","index":232,"end_time":1061.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1053.5,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"All of the videos?","index":233,"end_time":1062.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1061.54,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"We pull them anyways.","index":234,"end_time":1065.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1064.3,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"I think we can pull them and share them.","index":235,"end_time":1068.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1066.54,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Okay.","index":236,"end_time":1068.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1068.38,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":237,"end_time":1069.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1068.9,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"Then we can maybe put on Vista or something and share it across with the team.","index":238,"end_time":1073.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1069.22,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":239,"end_time":1074.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1073.74,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Bailey, do you all use boldcast?","index":240,"end_time":1076.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1074.22,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Not a ton.","index":241,"end_time":1079.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1078.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":242,"end_time":1080.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1079.88,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":243,"end_time":1081.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1080.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If you do and you''re interested, we could give you a login.","index":244,"end_time":1084.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1081.4,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Just as like a note, if someone on the team, they have some AI functionality of like getting to clips.","index":245,"end_time":1090.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1084.08,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"That''s kind of interesting.","index":246,"end_time":1091.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1090.56,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Okay, yeah.","index":247,"end_time":1093.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1091.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And talk more about that.","index":248,"end_time":1094.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1093.44,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":249,"end_time":1095.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1094.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I thought if, if you''re open to it, it would be.","index":250,"end_time":1098.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1095.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":251,"end_time":1099.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1099,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Just nice to get in there and, and see what kind of stuff they can do to create some of the clips.","index":252,"end_time":1105.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1099.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So that is really great news.","index":253,"end_time":1108.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1106.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We can get maybe some materials beforehand.","index":254,"end_time":1111.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1108.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That was actually going to be my next question.","index":255,"end_time":1114.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1112.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I think like any, any maybe slides that are ready before the event or like because we got this from Kate earlier so like we have a rough outline of like what the event''s going to be about, but if there''s like a bit more of a description for each of the speakers, speaking speakers, that would help a lot.","index":256,"end_time":1135.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1114.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll definitely do that.","index":257,"end_time":1137.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1135.75,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"I like, I think Victoria''s Internet is a bit wonky, but ideally like she''ll own the briefing process with you guys and like share the entire package of like this is what the entirety of Summit is, the kind of targeting, the kind of messaging and all of that.","index":258,"end_time":1151.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1137.07,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"And I think it''ll definitely be useful for you guys like as and when we complete a session narrative.","index":259,"end_time":1158.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1152.47,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"So like summer panel conversations versus summer presentation or case study led.","index":260,"end_time":1163.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1158.39,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"So like as and when we complete those decks or questions, you know, moderation questions as well, I think we''ll start passing them on to you guys.","index":261,"end_time":1172.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1163.64,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"We will run some dry session, like dry run sessions with the actual speakers as well.","index":262,"end_time":1177.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1172.76,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"So like if they share any meaty points in terms of what they''re going to cover there, we can get just preempt and give you those points as well.","index":263,"end_time":1184.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1177.44,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Just so yeah, you''re always in the thread as you go.","index":264,"end_time":1187.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1184.56,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":265,"end_time":1189.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1189.29,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"So she''ll be your point contact.","index":266,"end_time":1190.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1189.57,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"So like we can, we can start working through that and come back to you guys.","index":267,"end_time":1194.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1190.89,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Yeah, that would Be great.","index":268,"end_time":1195.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1194.33,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, we lost Victoria.","index":269,"end_time":1197.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1195.49,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I think she''s.","index":270,"end_time":1199.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1197.45,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":271,"end_time":1200.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1199.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So the one thing I do want to, I want to touch on that Victoria I think mentioned a bit earlier, but I want to make sure we''re aligned on as a Bazaar voice team.","index":272,"end_time":1210.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1201.53,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"This package.","index":273,"end_time":1211.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1210.97,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Are we, Are we leaning into Summit as like this is this is a recap of Bazaar Voice Summit or is it more going to be like this is your AI playbook?","index":274,"end_time":1222.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1211.93,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"For me it''s the AI Playbook.","index":275,"end_time":1224.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1223.14,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Like I don''t, I don''t.","index":276,"end_time":1225.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1224.78,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"It doesn''t need to be about Summit from my perspective, like it''s like about the content.","index":277,"end_time":1230.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1225.9,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"I agree with that.","index":278,"end_time":1232.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1231.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And how you package it.","index":279,"end_time":1233.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1232.66,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that''s what she was also going for.","index":280,"end_time":1236.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1234.34,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Like how can you use some of it more long term and not necessarily just connected back to the summit as a conversation.","index":281,"end_time":1242.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1236.58,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Okay.","index":282,"end_time":1245.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1245.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s a good clarification though, Audrey, just to make sure we''re all thinking about it the same way.","index":283,"end_time":1250.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1245.75,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s a great point.","index":284,"end_time":1254.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1252.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So the next is just the things that you want help with.","index":285,"end_time":1258.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1255.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So Kate, you had sent us this to us earlier.","index":286,"end_time":1261.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1258.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we want to get aligned on all of the main deliverables.","index":287,"end_time":1265.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1261.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it sounds like everybody''s pretty on board for like a holistic playbook.","index":288,"end_time":1269.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1265.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Talking about like your AI Playbook essentially.","index":289,"end_time":1273.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1270.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Then we could also potentially do three mini playbooks about question for the crew on that.","index":290,"end_time":1279.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1274.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like what do you think about like would we want a be discovered, be trusted, be chosen like based on the sections or do we think that we don''t actually need that because it''ll like what, what are your thoughts on the BB side?","index":291,"end_time":1291.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1279.66,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"I just wonder if like, I mean we shouldn''t be forcing it if it doesn''t make sense.","index":292,"end_time":1301.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1296.03,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean I would rather go by the, by the topic and the concept that makes sense to the client.","index":293,"end_time":1308.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1302.03,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s fair.","index":294,"end_time":1310.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1309.15,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"So I think we can ditch that second one.","index":295,"end_time":1312.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1310.31,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Okay.","index":296,"end_time":1313.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1312.51,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we had also mentioned maybe some like workbooks and that could maybe come from individual sessions that are.","index":297,"end_time":1321.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1313.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s seems more like something people can fill in to further businesses.","index":298,"end_time":1326.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1321.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do you mean it''s.","index":299,"end_time":1329.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1328.77,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"It''s more like a checklist and like kind of things that you need to remember as you.","index":300,"end_time":1333.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1329.57,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":301,"end_time":1333.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1333.45,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s maybe where these could come into play.","index":302,"end_time":1339.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1333.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Maybe we have a checklist for each of those sections.","index":303,"end_time":1342.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1340.13,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, we could, we could see how to, how to navigate it again.","index":304,"end_time":1349.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1346.21,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Like I think just one of the things we don''t want to do is, I mean end of the day the whole discover trust chosen aspect is More from a high level brand messaging narrative.","index":305,"end_time":1359.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1349.33,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"And it''s not necessary that we kind of force it into every asset or every play.","index":306,"end_time":1364.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1359.17,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"If it kind of naturally fits in, it makes sense.","index":307,"end_time":1367.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1365.09,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"So like, at this point, it depends on how you''re kind of thinking about it.","index":308,"end_time":1371.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1367.41,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"So like, at this point I''m not a fan yet because it just, it feels a little too forced.","index":309,"end_time":1377.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1371.81,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I think.","index":310,"end_time":1378.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1377.87,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"I think the other thing that I want to make sure that we''re able to do is like, from my perspective, the whole point of this entire project is to use the source code from Summit and not have to gather like additional details in to like build out workbooks or build out.","index":311,"end_time":1395.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1379.15,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"So if we have everything, I think we can absolutely flip that over.","index":312,"end_time":1399.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1395.43,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"If we don''t, I think we should like parking lot it as a future thing.","index":313,"end_time":1403.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1399.71,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Just because I don''t want to get caught up in having to develop something versus having to like use the source code we have, do we that?","index":314,"end_time":1414.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1403.99,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Because I think there''s gonna be a lot of like, very rich source code to pull from.","index":315,"end_time":1419.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1415.52,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"So we sort of want to let the content determine the deliverables, like as much value as we can get without forcing anything.","index":316,"end_time":1428.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1421.04,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":317,"end_time":1429.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1428.84,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"I think videos is gonna be great then, because I think we can use all of the recordings that you have, so we can do like a couple video clips from each session and maybe have one really nice polished video that''s maybe like a compilation of a lot of the highlights.","index":318,"end_time":1448.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1430.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The other thing that I might put on this list, just thinking about it this way too, is a pmax series, a Google pmax video series.","index":319,"end_time":1457.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1448.8,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"And so then we would just need to think about, like, what is the CTA to that?","index":320,"end_time":1462.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1458.24,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Maybe it is to the overall playbook.","index":321,"end_time":1464.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1462.4,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"So it''s just trying to like drive people into that broader thing.","index":322,"end_time":1467.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1464.68,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"But I would love to put that on the list.","index":323,"end_time":1469.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1467.56,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that would be great.","index":324,"end_time":1471.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1470.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And I do think, and something to keep in mind with the PMAX is it needs to be under 30 seconds compilation video.","index":325,"end_time":1481.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1473.18,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Kate, that is interesting to me just because I feel like we always, the next year especially want to have what you meant, like this was last year to get people hyped up for it.","index":326,"end_time":1493.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1481.34,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Yeah, I agree.","index":327,"end_time":1497.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1494.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":328,"end_time":1498.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1497.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Actually, when you mentioned that to me last time, when we spoke about that podcast highlight reel of sort like, that was also one of the things that stood out because I know, like, for instance, Audrey did something on the Inspire vibe side last time a couple of years back.","index":329,"end_time":1515.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1498.7,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"So similarly, we just had something that we could use as a teaser post event to say this is all what you missed.","index":330,"end_time":1521.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1515.34,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"And then also use that after.","index":331,"end_time":1522.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1521.26,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"I think that would be great as one deliverable.","index":332,"end_time":1525.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1522.42,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"I always want a bloopers reel, but then I''m like, how would we use it?","index":333,"end_time":1528.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1525.19,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"That would be so fun.","index":334,"end_time":1530.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1529.11,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Maybe we should go into the dry run sessions and get those.","index":335,"end_time":1534.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1531.03,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"That would be amazing.","index":336,"end_time":1537.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1535.75,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"It like leads into authenticity, right?","index":337,"end_time":1540.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1539.03,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"I know.","index":338,"end_time":1541.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1540.95,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"It''s always like my favorite of like the credits or something when they showers.","index":339,"end_time":1545.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1541.35,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"I''m like, oh, it''s so good.","index":340,"end_time":1547.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1545.71,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"How do I share the screen?","index":341,"end_time":1549.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1547.67,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"How do I turn on the mic by now?","index":342,"end_time":1552.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1550.31,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"I love that.","index":343,"end_time":1555.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1554.17,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"And then what paid platforms are you hoping to use?","index":344,"end_time":1558.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1555.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Sounds like Google, PMAX.","index":345,"end_time":1560.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1559.13,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Any others?","index":346,"end_time":1561.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1561.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"LinkedIn.","index":347,"end_time":1563.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1562.89,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Okay.","index":348,"end_time":1564.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1564.17,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Like image ads, carousel ads.","index":349,"end_time":1567.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1564.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"All the things I would say, like we''ve had.","index":350,"end_time":1570.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1567.69,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"I think we''ve had less success with carousels, more success with document ads actually.","index":351,"end_time":1577.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1572.17,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"And we haven''t done a lot of video in LinkedIn, but we would like.","index":352,"end_time":1588.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1581.59,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"I.","index":353,"end_time":1588.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1588.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I think, yeah.","index":354,"end_time":1591.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1589.11,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"The only one I would from a paid perspective take off the list is carousels, but I''m not sure like how those have been performing organically.","index":355,"end_time":1598.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1591.39,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"If you''d still.","index":356,"end_time":1599.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1599.03,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Document ads.","index":357,"end_time":1601.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1600.23,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Document ads are with the way to go.","index":358,"end_time":1602.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1601.23,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"I agree.","index":359,"end_time":1603.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1602.95,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Because those work well on organic as well.","index":360,"end_time":1606.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1603.83,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":361,"end_time":1606.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1606.31,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"The single image promo, we haven''t done a lot of single image promo either.","index":362,"end_time":1611.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1607.6,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Not sure that''s necessary.","index":363,"end_time":1614.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1612.4,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Curious your thoughts, Kate?","index":364,"end_time":1616.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1615.28,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"I agree.","index":365,"end_time":1617.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1616.88,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Okay.","index":366,"end_time":1620.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1619.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then for organic social on LinkedIn, what kind of formats do you prefer there?","index":367,"end_time":1627.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1620.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It sounds like probably video.","index":368,"end_time":1628.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1627.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The document ads.","index":369,"end_time":1630.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1628.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do you want to play with anything else?","index":370,"end_time":1632.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1630.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think a lot of we can just use the same thing.","index":371,"end_time":1635.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1633.13,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":372,"end_time":1636.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1636.25,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"We need anything specific for organic.","index":373,"end_time":1639.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1636.85,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":374,"end_time":1641.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1639.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Love using the same things on organic as paid.","index":375,"end_time":1644.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1641.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Makes life a lot easier.","index":376,"end_time":1645.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1644.37,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, well, I know we''re getting really close to time, so we can put together maybe like our recommended list of things and also you guys can give us more details on the event and let us know what your final decisions are on the delivery purples.","index":377,"end_time":1664.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1646.73,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But we can always tweak as needed.","index":378,"end_time":1666.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1664.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Would we want any blogs related to this?","index":379,"end_time":1669.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1666.47,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we could like bundle up certain things as like takeaways as well.","index":380,"end_time":1677.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1672.55,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"That would make sense.","index":381,"end_time":1678.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1677.75,"speaker_name":"Pooja ParasuRaman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":382,"end_time":1680.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1679.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we lost Victoria too, so that would be really helpful just to get your kind of like list back.","index":383,"end_time":1686.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1680.63,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"We can give you any additional feedback and then I''d love to understand timeline.","index":384,"end_time":1689.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1686.15,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Like when do you want more of the brief from our side and some of the pieces that Pooja was talking about.","index":385,"end_time":1696.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1689.71,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"And then like, what does it look like?","index":386,"end_time":1697.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1696.16,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"January 22nd?","index":387,"end_time":1699.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1698.56,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Like how just when can we expect, like, those pieces would be really helpful.","index":388,"end_time":1706.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1700.08,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Yes.","index":389,"end_time":1707.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1706.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":390,"end_time":1708.039,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1707.6,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"I.","index":391,"end_time":1708.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1708.039,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Let''s finalize what we want to do exactly, and then I can give you a rough idea of timeline on some things, but.","index":392,"end_time":1716.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1710.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s.","index":393,"end_time":1717.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1716.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That is a great point.","index":394,"end_time":1718.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1717.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Did you have another question, Audrey?","index":395,"end_time":1720.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1718.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I did.","index":396,"end_time":1721.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1720.68,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Before.","index":397,"end_time":1721.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1721.16,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Before I forget, I did want to mention we do a lot of our design in Canva for this.","index":398,"end_time":1728.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1721.64,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Is.","index":399,"end_time":1728.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1728.52,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Is that something that if we were to send you Canva assets that your design team would be able to work from?","index":400,"end_time":1735.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1729,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Yeah, if you already have some templates in place, that''d be super helpful.","index":401,"end_time":1739,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1735.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":402,"end_time":1740.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1739.56,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":403,"end_time":1742.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1742.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Great.","index":404,"end_time":1742.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1742.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, I.","index":405,"end_time":1743.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1742.84,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"},{"text":"It was awesome to meet all of you who we haven''t chatted before, so we''re super excited to be working on this.","index":406,"end_time":1749.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1743.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We would love to.","index":407,"end_time":1752.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1751.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"To come to the event.","index":408,"end_time":1753.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1752.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I don''t know if we can come to the whole thing, but any of.","index":409,"end_time":1755.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1753.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Any that we can come to.","index":410,"end_time":1757.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1755.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We would love to join.","index":411,"end_time":1758.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1757.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":412,"end_time":1759.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1758.9,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Yeah, you can just register and we will look for.","index":413,"end_time":1764.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1759.62,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"Okay, we''ll do that then.","index":414,"end_time":1766.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1764.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":415,"end_time":1766.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1766.419,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, we''ll see ya.","index":416,"end_time":1768.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1767.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":417,"end_time":1769.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1768.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":418,"end_time":1770.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1769.5,"speaker_name":"Victoria Owen"},{"text":"Bye, y''.","index":419,"end_time":1770.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1770.1,"speaker_name":"katehahn"},{"text":"All.","index":420,"end_time":1770.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1770.7,"speaker_name":"audreysteuerwald"}],"dateString":"2025-12-12T15:00:00.000Z","host_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/81711381072?pwd=lWPLEgazaDVZLAJcTI6G5R9yoa7H1B.1","participants":["victoria.owen@bazaarvoice.com,kate.hahn@bazaarvoice.com,audrey.steuerwald@bazaarvoice.com,pooja.parasuraman@bazaarvoice.com,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com","victoria.owen@bazaarvoice.com","kate.hahn@bazaarvoice.com","audrey.steuerwald@bazaarvoice.com","pooja.parasuraman@bazaarvoice.com","igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KBQHTX9HAPQEMHVJSN6SKHPZ","organizer_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.94,"bullets":["Confirmed AI Playbook as the central post-event asset instead of a general Summit recap.","Decided New North will own full promo package, including video, ads, and landing page content.","Team aligned to start templating assets pre-event to enable quick post-event turnaround.","Agreed on promoting across LinkedIn, YouTube, and Google PMAX with emphasis on document and video ads.","Victoria to lead content briefing and session-level prep, including quotes and moderation questions."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I think this could just be a really interesting fully fleshed out campaign.","speaker":"audreysteuerwald"},{"quote":"For me it''s the AI Playbook. It doesn''t need to be about Summit.","speaker":"katehahn"},{"quote":"We will start this off for you guys with a brief initially.","speaker":"Pooja ParasuRaman"}],"topics":["launch","delivery","promo","content","strategy"],"model":"openai/gpt-4","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-12T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Post-Event Content Strategy**\n\nThe team agreed to focus on creating an **AI Playbook** and related content from the Bazaar Voice Summit rather than a direct event recap (20:23).\n\n- **The main deliverable will be a comprehensive AI Playbook** that consolidates key insights from Summit sessions, with potential smaller workbooks or practical guides on themes like the AAA framework and supply chain (05:43).\n    - Victoria Owen emphasized building practical workbooks using quotes from brand leaders and retailers to support implementation.\n    - Kate Hahn confirmed the content should stand alone, not tied tightly to Summit branding, ensuring longer-term use.\n    - Baylee Gunnell suggested video clips from each session plus a polished highlight compilation to enrich the playbook.\n    - The team stressed letting available source content guide deliverables without forcing additional materials, prioritizing efficiency (23:41).\n\n- **Promotional strategy will bundle most assets together** to maximize reach but allow some standalone pieces for evergreen value, focusing on LinkedIn and YouTube as key channels (06:52).\n    - Audrey Steuerwald supported using multi-touch campaigns combining video clips, document ads, and banner ads.\n    - Kate flagged document ads as the most effective LinkedIn ad format, with carousels deprioritized due to poor performance.\n    - Organic social will leverage the same creative assets as paid to simplify execution (27:13).\n\n- **Sales enablement assets like one-pagers linking to on-demand sessions are under consideration** for select sessions featuring external speakers to support outreach follow-up (14:24).\n    - Kate and Pooja discussed piloting one-pagers for two sessions, such as Coca-Cola and Nestlé, to provide bite-sized takeaways with session links.\n    - The decision depends on sales team interest and session relevance.\n\n## **Content Development Process and Timeline**\n\nClear coordination and phased content development steps were established to align on deliverables and timelines (09:05).\n\n- **Templates for quote cards, ads, and video promos will be created ahead of the event** to accelerate post-event production once source code is available (09:42).\n    - Baylee Gunnell will lead on template creation, allowing insertion of session quotes later.\n    - A detailed brief outlining Summit messaging, session types, and target themes will be provided by Victoria Owen within days to guide content work (19:49).\n    - Dry runs with speakers will be leveraged to capture key points early for content prep.\n\n- **The post-event content production is expected to start immediately after Summit on January 21st**, with an initial asset push soon after January 22nd when source materials are accessible (09:05).\n    - Baylee will confirm rough timelines once deliverables are finalized.\n    - The team agreed on flexibility to roll out initial promos quickly, followed by subsequent detailed assets.\n\n- **Content will be hosted on a promo landing page within the existing Bazaar Voice resources page due to website constraints**, focusing on simple header images and copy rather than a full custom page (12:18).\n    - Kate clarified that technical limits make a basic landing page with downloadable assets the preferred approach.\n    - Design support for banners and headers will be provided by Baylee''s team once specifications are shared.\n\n- **Canva is the preferred design tool for assets**, and Audrey confirmed their team can supply Canva templates for efficient collaboration (28:40).\n\n## **Video and Multimedia Utilization**\n\nVideo assets are prioritized for engagement across paid and organic channels to drive awareness and nurture leads (23:50).\n\n- **Short video clips under 30 seconds will be created for Google Performance Max campaigns**, with the goal to tease the AI Playbook and Summit highlights (24:08).\n    - Kate emphasized PMAX videos should have a clear call to action linking to the broader playbook.\n    - Audrey noted the value of teaser videos to boost event hype and maintain momentum post-event.\n\n- **YouTube and LinkedIn will be the main platforms for video distribution**, with an emphasis on repurposing video clips for organic social posts (11:51).\n    - Baylee confirmed no additional video hosting platforms are planned beyond these.\n    - The team discussed potential for a highlight reel or podcast-style recap to serve as a hero video asset.\n\n- **Potential for a “bloopers reel” or more authentic behind-the-scenes content was raised** as a creative engagement tool, though its usage remains exploratory (25:25).\n    - Audrey and Kate saw this as a way to add authenticity and personality to the campaign.\n\n## **Collaboration and Tools Integration**\n\nThe team outlined collaborative workflows and tools to streamline content creation and sharing (17:20).\n\n- **New North will receive a detailed Summit brief and session materials from Victoria Owen**, establishing a single point of contact for ongoing communication (19:49).\n    - The brief will include session narratives, panel vs. presentation formats, and key speaker info.\n    - Dry runs and speaker question decks will be shared early to identify rich content.\n\n- **Video source code and recordings will be pulled by Bazaar Voice and shared with New North**, avoiding duplicate access and easing content extraction (17:44).\n    - Kate offered to provide Boldcast platform access for AI-assisted clip generation.\n    - Baylee welcomed the opportunity to explore AI tools within Boldcast to accelerate clip creation.\n\n- **Email marketing will include both newsletter-style sends and nurture program one-offs**, with New North providing copy options for flexibility (10:41).\n    - Banner ads sized for email will be supplied by Bazaar Voice.\n    - The team confirmed alignment on channels and formats to ensure smooth integration.\n\n## **Brand Positioning and Messaging Alignment**\n\nThe group prioritized aligning content with Bazaar Voice’s broader brand narratives rather than rigid frameworks (21:19).\n\n- **The “Be Discovered, Be Trusted, Be Chosen” framework was deprioritized** in favor of messaging driven by session content and client relevance (21:36).\n    - Pooja advocated for a client-centric content approach rather than forcing brand narratives.\n    - Kate emphasized leveraging rich source content from Summit to avoid extra production work.\n\n- **Content themes will focus on AI and practical guidance**, reflecting the evolving market demand and Bazaar Voice’s thought leadership (05:43).\n    - This approach aims to strengthen Bazaar Voice’s position as a knowledge leader in AI-driven marketing.\n    - The AAA framework and supply chain topics will be highlighted as core sub-themes.\n\n- **Packaging content as an AI Playbook rather than just Summit recap enhances longevity and market relevance**, supporting ongoing engagement beyond the event (20:23).\n    - This strategic positioning was agreed upon by key speakers including Kate and Baylee.\n\n## **Sales Enablement and Internal Use**\n\nThere is interest in creating assets to support sales teams with quick-reference materials linking to full sessions (14:24).\n\n- **One-pagers summarizing key takeaways and linking to on-demand videos will be developed for select external speaker sessions** (14:57).\n    - These would serve as easy “grab and share” tools in sales meetings and follow-ups.\n    - The team will pilot this approach with two sessions to assess usefulness.\n\n- **The decision on scale will depend on sales team feedback and session relevance**, with potential to expand if successful (15:59).\n    - Pooja noted the need to balance asset creation with practical usage to avoid wasted effort.\n\n- **These sales tools complement the broader content campaign by providing targeted, actionable insights for client conversations**.","outline":null,"keywords":["Bazaar Voice Summit","AI Playbook","Post-Event Content","Content Strategy","Video Assets","Promotion Channels"],"overview":"- **Focus on AI Playbook:** Key insights from the Bazaar Voice Summit will create a standalone AI Playbook, enhancing long-term value.\n\n- **Efficient Production Timeline:** Post-event content production starts January 21, with initial assets ready shortly after, ensuring quick rollouts.\n\n- **Promotion Strategy:** Bundle content for maximum reach while allowing some materials to stand alone, targeting LinkedIn and YouTube primarily.\n\n- **Video Clips for Engagement:** Short clips under 30 seconds will support Google campaigns to tease the AI Playbook and highlight event key points.\n\n- **Collaboration Tools Established:** New North will handle Summit briefs, with effective access to content resources to streamline communication.\n\n- **Sales Enablement Assets Considered:** Developing one-pagers summarizing key session takeaways to assist sales teams following specific external speaker sessions.","action_items":"\n**Pooja ParasuRaman**\nProvide New North team with a comprehensive Summit brief covering event overview, messaging, sessions, and post-event content strategy (16:06)\n\n**Victoria Owen**\nOwn briefing process and coordinate sharing of detailed content packages with New North for informed content creation (16:06)\n\n**Kate Hahn**\nProvide event slide decks and descriptions of speakers in more detail to New North as available (18:13)\nPull video recordings post-event and share with New North (17:44)\nDetermine preferred deliverables and timeline with New North based on briefing and content from the event (28:00)\nRegister New North team for the Summit event to enable their attendance (29:18)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nCreate templates for quote cards and promotional ads ahead of Summit event for faster post-event delivery (09:42)\nDevelop recommended content deliverables and proposed timeline after finalizing Summit materials (27:46)\nCollaborate with Bazaar Voice on leveraging Boldcast AI clipping functionality for post-event video assets if given access (18:01)\n\n**Audrey Steuerwald**\nAlign with Bazaar Voice team on the preferred structure and bundling of post-event content to maintain consistency (08:07)\nCoordinate sharing of Canva design templates to facilitate asset production with New North (28:40)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"6db06cc9-81c4-483c-a7e3-6aff2c16d07a","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
