  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Baylee Gunnell and Kate Hahn',
  '## **Post-Event Content Strategy**

The team agreed to focus on creating an **AI Playbook** and related content from the Bazaar Voice Summit rather than a direct event recap (20:23).

- **The main deliverable will be a comprehensive AI Playbook** that consolidates key insights from Summit sessions, with potential smaller workbooks or practical guides on themes like the AAA framework and supply chain (05:43).
    - Victoria Owen emphasized building practical workbooks using quotes from brand leaders and retailers to support implementation.
    - Kate Hahn confirmed the content should stand alone, not tied tightly to Summit branding, ensuring longer-term use.
    - Baylee Gunnell suggested video clips from each session plus a polished highlight compilation to enrich the playbook.
    - The team stressed letting available source content guide deliverables without forcing additional materials, prioritizing efficiency (23:41).

- **Promotional strategy will bundle most assets together** to maximize reach but allow some standalone pieces for evergreen value, focusing on LinkedIn and YouTube as key channels (06:52).
    - Audrey Steuerwald supported using multi-touch campaigns combining video clips, document ads, and banner ads.
    - Kate flagged document ads as the most effective LinkedIn ad format, with carousels deprioritized due to poor performance.
    - Organic social will leverage the same creative assets as paid to simplify execution (27:13).

- **Sales enablement assets like one-pagers linking to on-demand sessions are under consideration** for select sessions featuring external speakers to support outreach follow-up (14:24).
    - Kate and Pooja discussed piloting one-pagers for two sessions, such as Coca-Cola and Nestlé, to provide bite-sized takeaways with session links.
    - The decision depends on sales team interest and session relevance.

## **Content Development Process and Timeline**

Clear coordination and phased content development steps were established to align on deliverables and timelines (09:05).

- **Templates for quote cards, ads, and video promos will be created ahead of the event** to accelerate post-event production once source code is available (09:42).
    - Baylee Gunnell will lead on template creation, allowing insertion of session quotes later.
    - A detailed brief outlining Summit messaging, session types, and target themes will be provided by Victoria Owen within days to guide content work (19:49).
    - Dry runs with speakers will be leveraged to capture key points early for content prep.

- **The post-event content production is expected to start immediately after Summit on January 21st**, with an initial asset push soon after January 22nd when source materials are accessible (09:05).
    - Baylee will confirm rough timelines once deliverables are finalized.
    - The team agreed on flexibility to roll out initial promos quickly, followed by subsequent detailed assets.

- **Content will be hosted on a promo landing page within the existing Bazaar Voice resources page due to website constraints**, focusing on simple header images and copy rather than a full custom page (12:18).
    - Kate clarified that technical limits make a basic landing page with downloadable assets the preferred approach.
    - Design support for banners and headers will be provided by Baylee''s team once specifications are shared.

- **Canva is the preferred design tool for assets**, and Audrey confirmed their team can supply Canva templates for efficient collaboration (28:40).

## **Video and Multimedia Utilization**

Video assets are prioritized for engagement across paid and organic channels to drive awareness and nurture leads (23:50).

- **Short video clips under 30 seconds will be created for Google Performance Max campaigns**, with the goal to tease the AI Playbook and Summit highlights (24:08).
    - Kate emphasized PMAX videos should have a clear call to action linking to the broader playbook.
    - Audrey noted the value of teaser videos to boost event hype and maintain momentum post-event.

- **YouTube and LinkedIn will be the main platforms for video distribution**, with an emphasis on repurposing video clips for organic social posts (11:51).
    - Baylee confirmed no additional video hosting platforms are planned beyond these.
    - The team discussed potential for a highlight reel or podcast-style recap to serve as a hero video asset.

- **Potential for a “bloopers reel” or more authentic behind-the-scenes content was raised** as a creative engagement tool, though its usage remains exploratory (25:25).
    - Audrey and Kate saw this as a way to add authenticity and personality to the campaign.

## **Collaboration and Tools Integration**

The team outlined collaborative workflows and tools to streamline content creation and sharing (17:20).

- **New North will receive a detailed Summit brief and session materials from Victoria Owen**, establishing a single point of contact for ongoing communication (19:49).
    - The brief will include session narratives, panel vs. presentation formats, and key speaker info.
    - Dry runs and speaker question decks will be shared early to identify rich content.

- **Video source code and recordings will be pulled by Bazaar Voice and shared with New North**, avoiding duplicate access and easing content extraction (17:44).
    - Kate offered to provide Boldcast platform access for AI-assisted clip generation.
    - Baylee welcomed the opportunity to explore AI tools within Boldcast to accelerate clip creation.

- **Email marketing will include both newsletter-style sends and nurture program one-offs**, with New North providing copy options for flexibility (10:41).
    - Banner ads sized for email will be supplied by Bazaar Voice.
    - The team confirmed alignment on channels and formats to ensure smooth integration.

## **Brand Positioning and Messaging Alignment**

The group prioritized aligning content with Bazaar Voice’s broader brand narratives rather than rigid frameworks (21:19).

- **The “Be Discovered, Be Trusted, Be Chosen” framework was deprioritized** in favor of messaging driven by session content and client relevance (21:36).
    - Pooja advocated for a client-centric content approach rather than forcing brand narratives.
    - Kate emphasized leveraging rich source content from Summit to avoid extra production work.

- **Content themes will focus on AI and practical guidance**, reflecting the evolving market demand and Bazaar Voice’s thought leadership (05:43).
    - This approach aims to strengthen Bazaar Voice’s position as a knowledge leader in AI-driven marketing.
    - The AAA framework and supply chain topics will be highlighted as core sub-themes.

- **Packaging content as an AI Playbook rather than just Summit recap enhances longevity and market relevance**, supporting ongoing engagement beyond the event (20:23).
    - This strategic positioning was agreed upon by key speakers including Kate and Baylee.

## **Sales Enablement and Internal Use**

There is interest in creating assets to support sales teams with quick-reference materials linking to full sessions (14:24).

- **One-pagers summarizing key takeaways and linking to on-demand videos will be developed for select external speaker sessions** (14:57).
    - These would serve as easy “grab and share” tools in sales meetings and follow-ups.
    - The team will pilot this approach with two sessions to assess usefulness.

- **The decision on scale will depend on sales team feedback and session relevance**, with potential to expand if successful (15:59).
    - Pooja noted the need to balance asset creation with practical usage to avoid wasted effort.

- **These sales tools complement the broader content campaign by providing targeted, actionable insights for client conversations**.',
