    '{"Colin Costigan","bwillans","Guille Santana"}'::text[],
    1844,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/89786281993?pwd=li2lwrSFpmITXPKEdOBBgaXPwh8ONO.1',
    '{"id":"01KC45CVGN4G5Z67FJ31J9JQP9","title":"AQI // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Salesforce to HubSpot Data Integration**\n\nThe team confirmed the need to precisely define which Salesforce contacts and opportunities migrate into HubSpot to avoid data bloat and duplication.\n\n- **Salesforce contains 56,000 contact records with 29,110 associated with opportunities**, which exceeds expectations and requires a deeper dive into opportunity definitions to clarify scope (00:00)  \n    - Barb Willans noted they initially bought **17,000 contacts** and expressed interest in understanding opportunity definitions due to the company''s size of **200 employees**  \n    - Colin Costigan proposed filtering opportunities by a **cutoff date, such as within the last two years**, to focus data migration and prioritize recent engagement  \n    - A clear mapping plan will be developed to align HubSpot and Salesforce fields, avoiding transferring unnecessary or noisy data  \n    - Barb requested a **spreadsheet comparing Salesforce fields to HubSpot properties** to confirm which data is essential, aiming to finalize after Wednesday (00:13)  \n\n- **Duplication prevention relies on email address matching in HubSpot**, with Salesforce using a custom contact-to-lead conversion process that must be synchronized (00:03)  \n    - Barb explained past duplication issues stemmed mainly from third-party sponsorship lists, not internal processes, causing **50% overcount in MQL reporting** during Q4  \n    - This problem was linked to incorrect data mapping by a vendor, Graziti, which will be addressed in the new system to prevent recurrence  \n    - The team agreed current cleaning and standard operating procedures should maintain data hygiene moving forward  \n\n## **Lifecycle Stages and BDR Workflow Alignment**\n\nClarifying lifecycle stages in HubSpot and their reflection in Salesforce is key to ensuring sales development reps (BDRs) work efficiently and marketing has full funnel visibility.\n\n- **Adopting the HubSpot lifecycle stages including Lead, MQL, and SQL will enable marketing transparency and proper BDR engagement triggers** (00:06)  \n    - Barb stressed the importance of including the Lead stage as synonymous with MQL to gain top-of-funnel visibility, which has not been a focus historically but is planned for 2026  \n    - Discussions are underway about granting Blake limited HubSpot access (view license) to monitor but not alter data, balancing transparency with control  \n    - The lifecycle stage data will be connected to Salesforce triggers so BDRs know when to act, improving lead follow-up efficiency  \n\n- **No new web pages are required for embedding HubSpot forms, simplifying implementation and reducing technical overhead** (00:07)  \n\n## **ABM Campaigns and Pipeline Planning**\n\nThe leadership team set priorities to build out ABM infrastructure in Q1 focused on Food and Beverage verticals, deferring Aquarius mining campaigns to Q2.\n\n- **L1 leadership postponed Aquarius ABM to Q2 and prioritized ABM infrastructure for Food and Beverage in Q1, targeting up to three sub-verticals** (00:14)  \n    - Barb identified Hawk, a sister company with matching personas, as a valuable source for initial Food and Beverage contacts, accelerating list building  \n    - The team plans to leverage an existing **ZoomInfo license for North America-centric contact research** to supplement data beyond current Salesforce records  \n    - Colin emphasized starting ABM infrastructure by **end of Q1** to allow timely campaign launches and content development  \n\n- **Lists for ABM will combine existing Salesforce records and net-new research to cover prioritized verticals effectively** (00:16)  \n\n## **Email Marketing and Newsletter Strategy**\n\nThe team agreed to launch a fresh, forward-looking newsletter in January focusing on new programs and customer success instead of retrospective content.\n\n- **Barb proposed a January newsletter emphasizing upcoming initiatives, featured stories, and customer voice assets, avoiding past performance retrospectives** (00:18)  \n    - The newsletter will include sections for news mentions, customer success stories, and user group events, which happen **140 times annually** but are currently unpublicized  \n    - The goal is to provide clear calls to action and sign-ups for relevant programs, strengthening engagement and awareness  \n    - Colin confirmed the newsletter will use a flexible, drag-and-drop HubSpot template allowing customization per send  \n\n- **Current email lists are being carefully cleaned and managed in Constant Contact, with approximately 2,100 contacts processed so far** (00:21)  \n    - Barb is consolidating multiple lists where contacts appear in up to **five different segments**, ensuring accurate targeting and message relevance  \n    - The cleaned lists will be migrated into HubSpot, retaining segment associations to maintain personalized messaging  \n\n## **Tracking, Analytics, and Tooling Setup**\n\nThe team is establishing baseline metrics and tools tracking while preparing to onboard new recording and webinar platforms.\n\n- **A foundational \"data box\" dashboard will track website engagement, social media, paid media, and CRM metrics to provide a holistic view of marketing performance** (00:25)  \n    - Colin offered to send a standard set of tracked metrics for review, including **time on page, page views, and source attribution**, which have never been tracked before internally  \n    - The dashboard will be customizable to highlight specific channels like newsletters or paid campaigns based on stakeholder needs  \n\n- **Transitioning from Big Marker to Zoom Webinar for events starting January will enable better tracking and recording capabilities** (00:24)  \n    - Barb is archiving legacy event data and preparing upcoming events to be recorded and tracked in Zoom Webinar, laying groundwork for measurable engagement  \n    - Riverside video recording licenses will be procured through Colin’s team to centralize management and billing, costing **one point** from their tech stack budget (00:27)  \n    - Licensing will support field teams, primarily in APAC, with app-based upload access, enabling decentralized content capture for Aquarius  \n\n## **Process Coordination and Next Steps**\n\nClear next steps include data field mapping, contract clarifications, and scheduling to keep the migration and campaign launches on track.\n\n- **Colin will send a detailed spreadsheet comparing Salesforce fields to HubSpot properties for Barb''s team to review and confirm necessary data mappings** (00:14)  \n    - This will clarify which Salesforce objects transfer fully, partially, or not at all to HubSpot, reducing noise and focusing on actionable data  \n\n- **The marketing blackout period concern for January was alleviated; Marketo will remain active until April 1st to ensure smooth transition without campaign disruption** (00:08)  \n\n- **Barb confirmed readiness to send a Christmas card campaign through HubSpot on Monday using staged lists of 8,000 to 10,000 customers and prospects** (00:23)  \n    - The team agreed to ensure all data properties are properly mapped before sending and to allow batch updates or removals as needed for list hygiene  \n\n- **Regular status meetings will continue weekly on Fridays, with awareness of holiday closures on December 25th and January 1st, maintaining momentum through year-end** (00:29)","outline":null,"keywords":["Salesforce","HubSpot","Data Migration","ABM Campaigns","Lifecycle Stages","Marketing Automation"],"overview":"- **Salesforce to HubSpot Integration:** 56,000 Salesforce contacts, 29,110 opportunities; prioritizing data mapping to reduce bloat and duplication.\n\n- **BDR Workflow Alignment:** HubSpot lifecycle stages will enhance visibility and efficiency for sales reps; ensuring quick lead follow-up.\n\n- **ABM Campaigns Focus:** Q1 will prioritize Food and Beverage ABM infrastructure; Aquarius campaigns to roll out in Q2.\n\n- **Newsletter Launch:** New newsletter in January will spotlight initiatives and success stories, moving away from past-focused content.\n\n- **Analytics Setup:** Developing a “data box” dashboard for tracking website and CRM metrics; moving to Zoom Webinar for better engagement tracking.\n\n- **Ongoing Coordination:** Weekly status updates to continue; Christmas card campaign sending planned for early next week with proper list hygiene.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nExport Salesforce fields and prepare a spreadsheet mapping to HubSpot properties; send to Barb for review (13:45)\nClean up and finalize the implementation plan document to remove highlights and incorporate feedback, then send updated version to Barb and team (12:54)\nProvide standard work list of tracking metrics for Data Box (website, social, paid media, HubSpot/Salesforce) to Barb (25:45)\nManage purchase and setup of Riverside license under Marketers In Demand account and coordinate sharing with Aquarius field team (28:10)\nContinue building modular email templates in HubSpot supporting January newsletter launch and ongoing communications (18:00)\nSupport onboarding and migration of Constant Contact nurture lists into HubSpot while maintaining segmentation (21:30)\nCoordinate sending of staged Christmas card campaign through HubSpot with Barb''s list once provided (23:40)\nKeep ongoing communication and schedule follow-up meeting for next Friday (29:56)\n\n**Barb Willans**\nConfirm with sales team how far back opportunity data should be pulled for migration and verify company counts linked to 29,000+ contacts (00:20)\nSend details of the external product feedback form with redirect URL to Marketers In Demand to ensure no disruption during Aquarius team’s January launch (09:20)\nCoordinate with Maria, Vivian, and Kyle to review implementation plan and define which Salesforce objects/fields are essential for HubSpot sync (13:50)\nFinalize vertical segment definition for ABM Food & Beverage, particularly the three sub-verticals for Whims campaign (15:40)\nProvide lists from Veralta''s Hawk and ZoomInfo contacts for Food & Beverage ABM targeting (16:00)\nShare cleaned nurturing contact lists from Constant Contact and new lists from Salesforce for import into HubSpot (21:00)\nProvide final customer list(s) for Christmas card email campaign planned for Monday (23:45)\nMonitor and provide feedback on Data Box metrics and tracking requirements (26:00)\nConfirm holiday schedules and availability for future meetings (30:00)\n\n**Guille Santana**\nMonitor and report any standalone forms outside embedded ones found on website or campaigns (09:00)\n"},"duration":30.729999542236328,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"bwillans"},{"id":2,"name":"Guille Santana"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Sorry.","index":0,"end_time":0.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Getting a notification from Zoom.","index":1,"end_time":3.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What we see is 56,000 contact records in Salesforce and 29,110 of those associated with an opportunity.","index":2,"end_time":12.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Does that sound the ballpark of where you were expecting?","index":3,"end_time":16.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":12.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was expecting less.","index":4,"end_time":19.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":17.76,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So that''s interesting, but I will take a look at that for sure because we bought 17,000 up front.","index":5,"end_time":24.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":19.2,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"If we need to bump it up, that''s a nice problem to have.","index":6,"end_time":27.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":24.52,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It is, yeah.","index":7,"end_time":29.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":27.89,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s just I''d have to take a deep dive.","index":8,"end_time":31.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":29.65,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I mean, we''re a 200 person company, so I''d be really curious of what their definition of opportunity look like.","index":9,"end_time":38.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":31.89,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That is a very good point, Barb.","index":10,"end_time":42.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":39.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And let me just log right in to show you.","index":11,"end_time":44.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":42.209,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And of course, I''m getting it with another two FA code.","index":12,"end_time":47.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":44.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, do you need something from me?","index":13,"end_time":50.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":48.45,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"No, I got it on our end.","index":14,"end_time":51.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":50.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":15,"end_time":52.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":52.09,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All right, here we go.","index":16,"end_time":63.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":62.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So here''s where we pulled a report to show this in Salesforce.","index":17,"end_time":70.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":64.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s just contacts with opportunities associated.","index":18,"end_time":73.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":70.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"More than zero.","index":19,"end_time":74.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":73.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s where we got the 29,110 records.","index":20,"end_time":77.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":75.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Obviously, a lot of contacts associated with various accounts.","index":21,"end_time":83.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":80.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, City of Palo Alto has got 44 people associated with.","index":22,"end_time":88.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":83.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Would also be interesting if we consider like a cutoff date.","index":23,"end_time":92.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":89.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, do we say like opportunities within the last two years is who we want to focus on?","index":24,"end_time":96.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":92.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Migrating over to HubSpot first and then we expand.","index":25,"end_time":99.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":96.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So a few different schools of thought there.","index":26,"end_time":101.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":100.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":27,"end_time":102.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":102.27,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":28,"end_time":103.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":103.07,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''d be curious to know.","index":29,"end_time":104.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":103.39,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So number of contacts to 29,000 and change.","index":30,"end_time":107.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":104.75,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''d be curious the number of companies that reflects.","index":31,"end_time":110.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":107.37,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And then I''ll go to the sales.","index":32,"end_time":112.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":110.97,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We have a sales lead discussion after this call and I''ll ask them how far we go back because we can always add more.","index":33,"end_time":120.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":112.49,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But gosh, I mean, this isn''t an iPhone.","index":34,"end_time":123.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":120.65,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yesterday I heard this is like an 8 to 12 month sale, so maybe 2 years depending on when they come into the system.","index":35,"end_time":130.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":123.21,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But I''ll.","index":36,"end_time":131.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":130.77,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''ll firm that up for you for sure.","index":37,"end_time":132.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":131.17,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":38,"end_time":133.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":132.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":39,"end_time":136.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":135.57,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":40,"end_time":136.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":136.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So once we land there, obviously that clears up everything and we can really start building or setting up the connections between the two systems.","index":41,"end_time":143.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":136.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sure.","index":42,"end_time":143.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":143.41,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We''ve also updated the implementation plan document based on Blake''s feedback.","index":43,"end_time":151.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":145.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There are a few things, though, that we wanted to run through.","index":44,"end_time":154.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":151.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''ll remove the highlights before we send it over, but.","index":45,"end_time":158.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":155.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So he left a few comments on here.","index":46,"end_time":161.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":160.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we updated the content.","index":47,"end_time":163.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":161.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Where we updated is marked in yellow, so we feel pretty good about those.","index":48,"end_time":166.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":163.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The ones that we wanted to clarify were marked in red.","index":49,"end_time":170.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":166.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, let me go a little bit further down to the first one.","index":50,"end_time":175.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":170.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Boom, here we go.","index":51,"end_time":180.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":177.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one of the questions was, will this bi directional sync also help reduce or prevent duplicate opportunities or even lead tasks coming through for accounts and contacts that have existing open opportunities or are existing customers?","index":52,"end_time":192.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":180.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, for duplication.","index":53,"end_time":194.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":192.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"HubSpot relies on email addresses for deduplication, as you know.","index":54,"end_time":198.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":195.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So contacts should not be created in HubSpot if they don''t have an email address associated.","index":55,"end_time":203.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":199.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I guess we just need to really fully understand the BDR aspect of HubSpot versus Salesforce.","index":56,"end_time":212.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":204.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What I would picture is contacts are handled and not being duplicated, but we just need to make sure that process is clean.","index":57,"end_time":221.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":213.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In Salesforce, I know that you guys had built like a button that transforms a contact to a lead and then into an opportunity.","index":58,"end_time":228.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":221.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we just need to make sure that we''re all locked in there.","index":59,"end_time":230.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":229.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But as far as duplication, it''s really just based on email address.","index":60,"end_time":233.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":230.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, I can give like a really quick color around that.","index":61,"end_time":237.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":233.99,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So what was happening again?","index":62,"end_time":241.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":237.43,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''ve only been here four months, but what was happening anytime?","index":63,"end_time":244,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":241.12,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It only happens in my purview when we try to convert a list from a third party sponsorship.","index":64,"end_time":255.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":244.24,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So not from big marker.","index":65,"end_time":257.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":255.12,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Nothing that we did internally whenever we put together a list and we have a standard work document that says, okay, here''s what you need to do, which is a little bonkers in it of itself.","index":66,"end_time":266.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":257.16,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s awesome.","index":67,"end_time":267.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":266.89,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But it didn''t make a lot of sense to me why a webinar is called a trade show.","index":68,"end_time":271.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":267.89,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But okay, you know, we''re fixing that.","index":69,"end_time":275.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":271.45,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That.","index":70,"end_time":275.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":275.09,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That was just a funny.","index":71,"end_time":276.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":275.49,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But it''s, you know, for instance, we had three webinars that we sponsored over the last six months.","index":72,"end_time":284.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":276.65,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Externally, anytime we tried to upload or whenever Graziti through Marketo uploaded that information.","index":73,"end_time":292.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":284.53,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Let''s say it was 200mql that we scored.","index":74,"end_time":297.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":293.37,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"X Grizziti would see 100.","index":75,"end_time":302.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":298.25,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Salesforce would see 200.","index":76,"end_time":304.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":302.49,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So Blake was seeing both a bubble up and a hand raise for every single one of the external MQL contacts.","index":77,"end_time":313.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":305.05,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That''s.","index":78,"end_time":314.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":314.09,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That''s where that''s coming from.","index":79,"end_time":315.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":314.53,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":80,"end_time":317.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":317.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we had to make a decision to, well, if it''s a hand raise or a bubble up, which one did we take away?","index":81,"end_time":325.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":319.86,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Because it was the same.","index":82,"end_time":326.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":325.7,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So we.","index":83,"end_time":327.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":327.3,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Every Friday we have a daily management call that we have to report on our MQLs and we''ve been doing really well for Q4, but I''ve had to go through and sift through Every single one of them.","index":84,"end_time":342.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":327.94,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And you''ve met Kyle, he''s had to go in and scrape out 50% because everything was third party and it doubled everything.","index":85,"end_time":350.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":342.66,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I think that''s a marketo issue.","index":86,"end_time":353.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":351.19,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I don''t think that''s going to happen here.","index":87,"end_time":356.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":354.15,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"There is something in the trigger on the Graziti side that it was duplicating everything into bubble up and hand raised.","index":88,"end_time":363.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":356.87,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":89,"end_time":365.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":363.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s something that he.","index":90,"end_time":366.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":365.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That Graziti was mapping incorrectly then.","index":91,"end_time":368.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":366.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, because it was a.","index":92,"end_time":370.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":369.5,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It was times two.","index":93,"end_time":372.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":370.86,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":94,"end_time":373.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":372.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like.","index":95,"end_time":373.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":373.66,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And that''s why Blake.","index":96,"end_time":375.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":373.98,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":97,"end_time":376.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":375.66,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I''m not so concerned about that.","index":98,"end_time":377.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":376.06,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I just wanted to give you some context.","index":99,"end_time":378.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":377.46,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, no, that''s very helpful, thank you.","index":100,"end_time":380.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":378.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then there was a question around the life cycle stages and how that impacts when BDR work will be performed or noted within Salesforce.","index":101,"end_time":393.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":383.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so utilizing the HubSpot lifecycle stages lead, MQL SQL.","index":102,"end_time":397.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":393.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know you guys weren''t currently using lead, but I think that''s a valuable lifecycle stage to have will allow marketing to have full visibility into the journey of each prospect.","index":103,"end_time":405.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":397.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this field can be mapped to an existing field.","index":104,"end_time":407.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":405.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can create a whole new property in Salesforce and just make sure that''s connected to whatever trigger the BDR needs to know that they need to follow up.","index":105,"end_time":414.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":407.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":106,"end_time":416.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":415.42,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, so I did speak with him on that and you guys can speak with him at any time.","index":107,"end_time":420.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":416.3,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But I mean I know we only have so many points but you know, if, if it makes sense, he''s, he''s ready to, you know, he''s a great guy.","index":108,"end_time":429.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":420.77,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"You''ll, you''ll like very much.","index":109,"end_time":431.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":429.81,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So we do in the life cycle we need the mal''s or slash lead.","index":110,"end_time":436.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":431.81,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So everyone is, is fine with that definition.","index":111,"end_time":439.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":436.69,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Lead is mal.","index":112,"end_time":440.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":439.09,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So far we haven''t really paid attention to the top of the funnel and we will for 20, 26.","index":113,"end_time":448.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":441.17,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So it''s really critically important that we have that visibility.","index":114,"end_time":452.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":448.2,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Now how that maps over to Blake.","index":115,"end_time":454.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":452.68,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"He''s never had Marketo access.","index":116,"end_time":456.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":454.84,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Does he need Hub spot access?","index":117,"end_time":458.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":456.68,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We can give him a view license, but we don''t want him rooting around in there unless he needs to.","index":118,"end_time":466,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":459.4,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So.","index":119,"end_time":466.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":466,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":120,"end_time":466.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":466.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":121,"end_time":469.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":468.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so sounds like we''re all set there then.","index":122,"end_time":471.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":469.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think so.","index":123,"end_time":472.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":471.72,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":124,"end_time":473.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":472.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":125,"end_time":474,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":473.52,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I think there was one or two more.","index":126,"end_time":476.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":474,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":127,"end_time":479.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":478.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He asked the question about do we need like new pages for the new forms.","index":128,"end_time":482.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":479.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We do not.","index":129,"end_time":483.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":482.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Forms are embedded so we won''t need new pages or redirects or anything there.","index":130,"end_time":486.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":483.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re good.","index":131,"end_time":489.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":488.08,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And, and then he asked if we have a blackout Period for marketing in January.","index":132,"end_time":495.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":490.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, Barbie worked with us.","index":133,"end_time":497.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":495.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We don''t have.","index":134,"end_time":498,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":497.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re like, cut off, turn on.","index":135,"end_time":501.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":498.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":136,"end_time":502.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":502.13,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I, I talked to him about that.","index":137,"end_time":504.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":503.17,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"He seemed really concerned about that.","index":138,"end_time":505.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":504.49,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I, I think I was the one who triggered his anxiety, to be honest.","index":139,"end_time":511.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":505.97,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I said, we''re going to stop sending things out of Marketo.","index":140,"end_time":515.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":511.65,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So we''re cutting off Graziti.","index":141,"end_time":516.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":515.33,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We''re not, but they''re still there and we have marketo till April 1st.","index":142,"end_time":521.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":517.25,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like, we''re fine.","index":143,"end_time":521.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":521.21,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Don''t worry about it.","index":144,"end_time":522.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":521.77,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But, you know, he''s.","index":145,"end_time":523.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":522.49,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"You just got a little anxious and chopped them off the ledge.","index":146,"end_time":528.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":523.61,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Broken.","index":147,"end_time":528.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":528.03,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":148,"end_time":529.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":528.95,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All right.","index":149,"end_time":530.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":529.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that''s everything that we had just wanted to cover specifically in here.","index":150,"end_time":535.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":530.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome guy.","index":151,"end_time":536.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":536.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was there anything else that you wanted to mention out of this document?","index":152,"end_time":539.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":536.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I think for the forms, unless you have a standalone form somewhere on the website or on a campaign, they should all be embedded.","index":153,"end_time":552.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":540.63,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"But let us know if you find, like, something that''s not.","index":154,"end_time":556.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":552.2,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, if there''s anything extraneous that we''re not seeing in the, like, website ecosystem.","index":155,"end_time":560.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":556.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I doubt it.","index":156,"end_time":563.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":561.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll send over something that I saw this morning, actually.","index":157,"end_time":567.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":563.48,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So it may be something.","index":158,"end_time":570.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":567.72,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s from the product team and it goes to an external form.","index":159,"end_time":573.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":570.12,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I''ll send those over just to make sure that you guys are aware.","index":160,"end_time":576.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":573.72,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But I didn''t know what to do with them, so I sent it to James yesterday.","index":161,"end_time":579.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":576.88,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":162,"end_time":580.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":580.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, and I''ll send that over.","index":163,"end_time":582.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":580.94,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But yeah, thank you for, for raising that gig.","index":164,"end_time":587.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":582.14,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Because I. I was like, I don''t know what to do with this thing, but I will send it over just to make sure we don''t break anything.","index":165,"end_time":595.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":587.94,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And is that when you''re saying it redirects to a different form?","index":166,"end_time":598.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":595.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it.","index":167,"end_time":599.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":598.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that like a separate from the aquatic informatics website?","index":168,"end_time":601.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":599.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let me.","index":169,"end_time":604.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":604.06,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s a redirect URL for Aquarius that says it''s asking for feedback.","index":170,"end_time":611.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":605.59,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So James redirected it last night.","index":171,"end_time":614.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":612.39,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Do you want me to show you or just.","index":172,"end_time":617.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":616.47,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I can say.","index":173,"end_time":618.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":617.63,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, I can.","index":174,"end_time":618.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":618.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, yeah, yeah, just show us real quick, if you don''t mind.","index":175,"end_time":621.429,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":619.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then.","index":176,"end_time":621.829,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":621.429,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, Let me just share my screen.","index":177,"end_time":631.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":621.91,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Back on PC.","index":178,"end_time":650.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":649.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Barb.","index":179,"end_time":650.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":650.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know how much I love that coin.","index":180,"end_time":654.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":652.92,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I tried it this year and I just.","index":181,"end_time":657.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":656.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Black Friday deal popped up for a Mac Mini and I was like, I gotta go back.","index":182,"end_time":660.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":657.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I have my Mac on the side right here.","index":183,"end_time":664.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":661.27,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I can''t do anything confidential on there, but I do a lot of stuff on there because I cannot understand this thing.","index":184,"end_time":673.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":665.19,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So can you see my Screen.","index":185,"end_time":676.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":675.03,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We can.","index":186,"end_time":676.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":676.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so it says DRT feedback.","index":187,"end_time":680.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":677.03,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Fill out this form.","index":188,"end_time":682.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":681.03,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So James did some redirects, so you can see forms office.","index":189,"end_time":685.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":682.31,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Interesting.","index":190,"end_time":686.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":686.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there any particular reason that we wouldn''t have this as a HubSpot form on the website?","index":191,"end_time":691.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":687.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m.","index":192,"end_time":693.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":692.84,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I can''t.","index":193,"end_time":694.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":693.48,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I could not answer that question for you.","index":194,"end_time":696.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":694.44,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We.","index":195,"end_time":697.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":697,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We can.","index":196,"end_time":697.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":697.32,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I don''t know enough about this.","index":197,"end_time":700.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":699.08,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So the Aquarius team apparently is launching something in January and they wanted to have this linked, and so this is net new to me, so I will send it over to you guys.","index":198,"end_time":711.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":700.56,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I just didn''t want to break their product plan, so James said, no, we do a URL redirect and he did it yesterday and it looks fine, but I have no idea.","index":199,"end_time":723.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":711.12,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I.","index":200,"end_time":724.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":723.87,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"They seemed a little bit amped up that they needed this for January 1st, so I didn''t want to mess it up.","index":201,"end_time":729.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":724.99,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But I can send it over to you guys.","index":202,"end_time":731.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":729.95,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, it looks like an anonymous survey, so, like, it says it would not automatically collect your details, so maybe it''s not, like, relevant for marketing.","index":203,"end_time":742.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":731.55,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, well, it''s a product feedback form.","index":204,"end_time":746.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":744.34,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":205,"end_time":747.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":746.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":206,"end_time":747.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":747.38,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":207,"end_time":748.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":747.82,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, but I''ll send it over.","index":208,"end_time":750.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":748.5,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that''d be great.","index":209,"end_time":752.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":751.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just so we''re aware of it for.","index":210,"end_time":754.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":752.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sure, they were getting 404s and getting a little anxious, and to be fair, they did reach out to me a couple of weeks ago, and I put it on ice because I had no idea what they were talking about, and I was a little busy.","index":211,"end_time":765.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":754.5,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And they reached back out last night to say hello.","index":212,"end_time":769.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":766.18,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":213,"end_time":771.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":770.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, okay, I''ll send it over for an FYI.","index":214,"end_time":774.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":771.48,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, that''d be great.","index":215,"end_time":775.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":774.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so then we''ll.","index":216,"end_time":776.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":775.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll clean up the highlights in the plan document, send that back over, and then just as far as next steps on your side, do we need sign off from, like, Vivian and Kyle?","index":217,"end_time":784.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":776.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And is it Maria?","index":218,"end_time":787.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":784.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s Maria.","index":219,"end_time":788.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":787.96,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":220,"end_time":789.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":788.72,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I guess my question is to do what?","index":221,"end_time":793.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":790.44,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And that seems a little flippant, and I don''t mean it that way.","index":222,"end_time":796.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":793.8,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"What we want to make sure is happening is that, you know, we''re getting into HubSpot.","index":223,"end_time":803.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":797.15,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"What we need.","index":224,"end_time":803.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":803.03,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I mean, there are what, hundreds of fields, objects in.","index":225,"end_time":807.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":804.11,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"In Salesforce.","index":226,"end_time":809.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":807.99,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So which ones are being mapped over to HubSpot?","index":227,"end_time":812.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":809.51,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Is it all of them?","index":228,"end_time":813.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":812.87,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Is it a percentage of them?","index":229,"end_time":815.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":814.03,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Do we need to go through a pick list?","index":230,"end_time":817.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":815.91,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And.","index":231,"end_time":818.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":817.71,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I.","index":232,"end_time":818.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":818.03,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That came up yesterday from Viv, and she just said, I just want to make sure that everybody is getting what they need.","index":233,"end_time":824.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":818.59,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Is it 100% here, 100% there?","index":234,"end_time":826.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":824.67,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I don''t think, you know, just looking for new norths.","index":235,"end_time":831.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":826.83,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Knowing what you know now, what is it that you need from us to be able to get this signed up?","index":236,"end_time":838.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":831.77,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":237,"end_time":838.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":838.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we''ll do is we''ll just export the fields out of Salesforce and put that into a spreadsheet with the fields from HubSpot and just say here''s what we feel we need as properties in HubSpot and here''s just all the extra Salesforce stuff.","index":238,"end_time":850.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":838.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is noise.","index":239,"end_time":850.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":850.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is perfect.","index":240,"end_time":853.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":852.33,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And if you could send that over, we''ve got some time probably after Wednesday, but we have some time to go through that as soon as possible.","index":241,"end_time":860.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":853.17,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I think we''ll make the time.","index":242,"end_time":861.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":860.52,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So you guys.","index":243,"end_time":862.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":862.2,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I mean everybody deserves a break but obviously we''re on the clock for this.","index":244,"end_time":867.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":862.88,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So.","index":245,"end_time":867.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":867.12,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, sooner you can get that over to me, that''d be great.","index":246,"end_time":869.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":867.44,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Of course.","index":247,"end_time":870.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":869.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":248,"end_time":871.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":871.4,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And then just wanted to touch on the ABM plan.","index":249,"end_time":874.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":872.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know that this is kind of in the early stages, more of discussion than launch as we are really focused on HubSpot.","index":250,"end_time":882.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":874.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But you know, if we''re thinking working backwards, when do we want these campaigns live and running so that we know like, all right, here''s when we have to build lists and content, etc.","index":251,"end_time":891.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":882.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a really good question.","index":252,"end_time":892.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":891.47,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I know we talked just in the abstract about mining for Aquarius.","index":253,"end_time":897.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":892.59,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"What came up yesterday?","index":254,"end_time":899.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":898.589,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So just so you guys know, our leadership team is called L1.","index":255,"end_time":903.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":900.19,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So if you ever hear that, it''s like six people who make all the decisions and they''re great.","index":256,"end_time":910.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":903.67,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Viviselle2 and I''m below her.","index":257,"end_time":913.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":911.42,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So L1 yesterday said, I think we need to focus and we need to confirm this next week.","index":258,"end_time":921.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":914.06,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We''re going to focus.","index":259,"end_time":922.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":921.98,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Aquarius mining is important.","index":260,"end_time":924.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":923.02,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We''re going to push that to Q2.","index":261,"end_time":927.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":925.58,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We need an ABM infrastructure in Q1 for whims for food and beverage.","index":262,"end_time":934.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":927.5,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Okay.","index":263,"end_time":934.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":934.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Now within Food and Bev there are verticals, right?","index":264,"end_time":938.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":935.3,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Is it dairy?","index":265,"end_time":939.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":938.26,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Is it brewing?","index":266,"end_time":940.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":939.54,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Is it whatever, like name something.","index":267,"end_time":943.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":940.62,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We haven''t got there yet, but we think there are three.","index":268,"end_time":946.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":944.66,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And so I said to Vivian, like we''ll run Aquarius ABM, which is one, Wims, which is another three.","index":269,"end_time":956.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":947.54,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But I think we start with Wims in Q1 to have the infrastructure ready to go at the end of Q1.","index":270,"end_time":961.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":956.98,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Gotcha is what we''re looking at.","index":271,"end_time":963.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":962.39,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":272,"end_time":965.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":963.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All right, that sounds good.","index":273,"end_time":967.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":965.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then as far as like contact list and everything for that, is that existing records in Salesforce that we want to start out with or net new research that we can say like, here''s a list of companies that qualify and the titles that we want to talk to within both.","index":274,"end_time":981.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":968.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So when we look at Food and Bev, we have another company within Veralta called Hawk, who has all of the Personas that match ours.","index":275,"end_time":989.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":981.27,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So we''re pulling those now, which is such a win.","index":276,"end_time":992.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":989.83,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s.","index":277,"end_time":994.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":993.99,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s going to be really good.","index":278,"end_time":996.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":994.43,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So which they did their first past at Food, first pass at Food and Bev last this year and are going to share that list.","index":279,"end_time":1006.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":996.55,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But then we''re going to have to take a look at what makes sense for us.","index":280,"end_time":1010.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1007.35,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We just renewed our Zoom Info license, so we can share that and we can use Zoom Info.","index":281,"end_time":1016.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1011.27,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''ll be North America centric.","index":282,"end_time":1018.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1017.31,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So we just have to decide on what those three verticals are and what we''re going to prioritize.","index":283,"end_time":1024.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1018.99,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But we''re ahead of the curve in that we have more.","index":284,"end_time":1027.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1024.03,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like, we know who we''re going to talk to.","index":285,"end_time":1029.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1027.95,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We just don''t have them in the system.","index":286,"end_time":1031.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1029.75,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"They''re not customers, they''re not current opportunities.","index":287,"end_time":1034.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1031.31,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"They''re probably an outlier or two, but they''re not in the system.","index":288,"end_time":1037.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1034.43,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":289,"end_time":1038.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1038.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":290,"end_time":1039.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1038.67,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":291,"end_time":1039.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1039.31,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All right.","index":292,"end_time":1040.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1039.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That all sounds good.","index":293,"end_time":1040.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1040.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, you know us, we like to be ahead so that if anything changes, we can quickly adapt.","index":294,"end_time":1044.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1040.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sure.","index":295,"end_time":1045.889,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1045.649,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I''ll send that over.","index":296,"end_time":1046.889,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1045.889,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Plus the mining, like, the mining is pretty close on the Personas, but these are all net new for us.","index":297,"end_time":1051.569,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1046.889,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like, we don''t.","index":298,"end_time":1052.289,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1051.569,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We don''t have anything.","index":299,"end_time":1055.809,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1054.769,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I got you.","index":300,"end_time":1056.569,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1055.969,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, sounds good.","index":301,"end_time":1057.649,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1056.569,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":302,"end_time":1059.209,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1058.769,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''re going to start building some new templates into HubSpot for the emails to start sending out.","index":303,"end_time":1063.569,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1059.209,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did you have anything in mind?","index":304,"end_time":1065.969,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1064.289,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because I know newsletters were like kind of a net new thing that we want to get into.","index":305,"end_time":1069.809,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1065.969,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did you have anything in mind for, like, direction that would.","index":306,"end_time":1074.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1070.209,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or like messaging that you want to include that would influence how we design?","index":307,"end_time":1078.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1075.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":308,"end_time":1080.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1080.45,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"You know, at first, Colin, I thought we''d do this in December, but no, nobody''s listening.","index":309,"end_time":1086.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1081.33,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Nobody cares about a retrospective.","index":310,"end_time":1089.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1086.69,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I''d like to jump out of the gate sometime in January to say, look, fresh start, fresh year.","index":311,"end_time":1094.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1089.53,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We''ve got these new programs.","index":312,"end_time":1096.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1094.69,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"You know, we''ve talked about the pillars of productivity.","index":313,"end_time":1099.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1096.05,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We.","index":314,"end_time":1099.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1099.53,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We had to push that.","index":315,"end_time":1100.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1099.85,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Terry wasn''t ready, so we had to push that to January.","index":316,"end_time":1104.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1101.32,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Also, that did, you know, series through Riverside.","index":317,"end_time":1108.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1105.56,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That''s important to us.","index":318,"end_time":1109.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1108.52,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So we want to talk about what''s new and what''s coming up.","index":319,"end_time":1112.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1109.68,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We don''t want to look behind.","index":320,"end_time":1113.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1112.32,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I started on a newsletter, and I''m just like, I just can''t even, I mean no offense, but I can''t even care.","index":321,"end_time":1122.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1114.52,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I just like, let''s just.","index":322,"end_time":1124.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1122.6,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"The past is the past.","index":323,"end_time":1126.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1125.16,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"This is a rebuilding year for us.","index":324,"end_time":1127.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1126.2,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So let''s, that''s.","index":325,"end_time":1129.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1127.8,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And we''re hitting our numbers like we''re doing really well.","index":326,"end_time":1132.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1129.41,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So let''s, let''s look ahead and have a fresh start.","index":327,"end_time":1135.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1132.13,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I think those sections look like we have a lot of featured stories.","index":328,"end_time":1141.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1135.49,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like we have a lot of in the news stuff where we''re featured in different publications and people are interviewed.","index":329,"end_time":1149.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1141.17,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We never populate that.","index":330,"end_time":1152.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1150.05,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I think there''s an in the news section.","index":331,"end_time":1154.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1152.13,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Not backpadding, but you know, here''s something that you Sharing.","index":332,"end_time":1159.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1155.33,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":333,"end_time":1159.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1159.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Take a look at customer success.","index":334,"end_time":1161.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1159.89,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We have a lot of voice of customer assets that are almost finished that I would like to highlight.","index":335,"end_time":1168.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1162.37,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But we also need sections, microsites for those on the website.","index":336,"end_time":1172.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1169.01,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, through, you know, we just, there''s no place to put any videos on our website.","index":337,"end_time":1177.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1173.65,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"There''s a couple embedded but.","index":338,"end_time":1180.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1179.25,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And then it''s what''s, what''s new, what''s upcoming.","index":339,"end_time":1185.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1181.98,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We have user groups every like we have 140 user groups meetings every year.","index":340,"end_time":1190.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1185.46,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We don''t talk about those at all.","index":341,"end_time":1192.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1191.42,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I think, you know, if we stick to the top three, I mean well about us, why you should still care.","index":342,"end_time":1201.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1193.18,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Is there any new product information, customer insights.","index":343,"end_time":1207.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1201.5,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And then I would take a look at.","index":344,"end_time":1210.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1208.47,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Hey, sign yourself up for the following.","index":345,"end_time":1211.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1210.27,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I think that was my, my view.","index":346,"end_time":1214.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1212.15,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, that makes total sense.","index":347,"end_time":1216.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1214.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the way that we''ll build it is, you know, same style as, as Avanti in the sense that you''ll be able to do the drag and drop the way that we''ll build it.","index":348,"end_time":1225.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1216.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''ll have custom modules and you can say I don''t need this section for this email, et cetera.","index":349,"end_time":1229.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1225.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":350,"end_time":1230.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1230.23,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, that makes sense.","index":351,"end_time":1231.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1230.67,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All right.","index":352,"end_time":1232.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1232.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I know you sent over this list before the call, so I wanted to make sure that we dedicated time to this and also just making sure that anything for our like additional contract if there''s any new things that we need to go through to help you out.","index":353,"end_time":1246.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1233.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sure, yeah.","index":354,"end_time":1247.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1247.04,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"No thanks.","index":355,"end_time":1248.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1247.76,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So list mapping.","index":356,"end_time":1251.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1249.6,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I just want to make sure that we''re.","index":357,"end_time":1252.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1251.12,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I think you answered that already, so I think we''re good.","index":358,"end_time":1255.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1252.64,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Constant contact.","index":359,"end_time":1256.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1256,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I was doing a little bit of nurturing and I mean oddly enough whatever we do, there is a big bump.","index":360,"end_time":1262.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1256.8,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s just that we hadn''t done anything.","index":361,"end_time":1265.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1263.94,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So even if you look at social, you know, it''s, it''s all green and we''re doing the bare minimum out of absolutely everything.","index":362,"end_time":1275.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1266.34,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And everyone is so impressed.","index":363,"end_time":1276.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1275.3,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''m like, I''m not impressed.","index":364,"end_time":1279.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1276.66,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But yeah, you''re going to be impressed next year, but not right now.","index":365,"end_time":1283.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1279.54,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So constant contact.","index":366,"end_time":1284.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1283.34,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"What I''m doing, Colin, is I''m.","index":367,"end_time":1286.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1284.42,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''m.","index":368,"end_time":1286.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1286.14,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Any list that I receive, I am just very 10.","index":369,"end_time":1290.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1286.9,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Literally putting.","index":370,"end_time":1291.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1290.64,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''m parking them there.","index":371,"end_time":1292.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1291.44,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It doesn''t have all of the salesforce.","index":372,"end_time":1296.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1293.92,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It doesn''t have all the salesforce fields or objects, but just I know what is clean and not clean.","index":373,"end_time":1304.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1298.24,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And then I. I think I have like 2100 contacts so far.","index":374,"end_time":1307.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1304.28,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Not a big deal.","index":375,"end_time":1309.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1308.16,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But you can see, you know, some.","index":376,"end_time":1312.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1309.28,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Some contacts are in multiple lists.","index":377,"end_time":1314.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1312.32,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Right.","index":378,"end_time":1314.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1314.2,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I think that''s important to know.","index":379,"end_time":1316.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1314.4,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I don''t know how new north will, you know, once you pull people over.","index":380,"end_time":1323.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1316.32,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Do we pull those lists and put them into HubSpot so we know that we have different.","index":381,"end_time":1328.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1323.39,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"There''s different messages, right?","index":382,"end_time":1331.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1329.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That it''s like they''re interested in this and this and this.","index":383,"end_time":1334.229,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1331.31,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"They could be on five different lists.","index":384,"end_time":1335.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1334.229,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But I am very tenderly cleaning every single one of these lists.","index":385,"end_time":1339.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1335.75,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So, I mean, I think since you''ve done that work, I mean, we wouldn''t throw that away.","index":386,"end_time":1344.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1339.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we do import those lists in or like the association of contacts with those lists so that, you know, when we send out the newsletters or anything like that, you kind of already have your.","index":387,"end_time":1353.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1344.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Your starting batch that you''re working from.","index":388,"end_time":1355.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1353.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep, I think so too.","index":389,"end_time":1357.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1355.76,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So thanks for that.","index":390,"end_time":1358.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1357.28,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So it''s in there and I''ve got a whole ton of stuff coming today because I''m jumping around here.","index":391,"end_time":1365.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1358.68,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I want the Riverside question to be last.","index":392,"end_time":1367.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1365.88,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We have four minutes.","index":393,"end_time":1368.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1367.72,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So Christmas card through HubSpot.","index":394,"end_time":1370.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1368.6,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I already staged it in HubSpot.","index":395,"end_time":1373.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1370.52,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Now I''m going to.","index":396,"end_time":1375.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1373.85,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I really want to send it out of HubSpot.","index":397,"end_time":1377.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1375.13,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I don''t have to.","index":398,"end_time":1378.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1377.17,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I will have the list today.","index":399,"end_time":1379.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1378.33,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But they''re all customers.","index":400,"end_time":1384.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1382.09,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I can put it in a HubSpot and that I can take it right out.","index":401,"end_time":1387.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1384.85,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like, it doesn''t.","index":402,"end_time":1388.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1387.45,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It doesn''t have to be there.","index":403,"end_time":1390.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1388.329,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I think people need to see that I''m using HubSpot.","index":404,"end_time":1394.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1390.73,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s really the only reason versus constant contact.","index":405,"end_time":1398.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1394.33,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We don''t want to put it through marketo.","index":406,"end_time":1400.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1398.25,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So it''s just an FYI that I''ve got some lists that we''re working on, you know, prospect list, customer lists out of salesforce that, that Kyle is pulling for me.","index":407,"end_time":1410.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1400.41,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So it could be.","index":408,"end_time":1412.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1410.9,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Who knows, at this point it could be like 8 to 10,000 people that I may Put in to send on Monday.","index":409,"end_time":1420.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1413.7,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"They want to send a card on Monday.","index":410,"end_time":1421.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1420.02,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But I have it staged.","index":411,"end_time":1422.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1421.34,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I just don''t have any lists in yet.","index":412,"end_time":1424.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1422.38,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But I just want to check with you.","index":413,"end_time":1426.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1424.9,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I can just send it and we can just delete.","index":414,"end_time":1429.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1426.3,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We can just take them all right out.","index":415,"end_time":1431.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1429.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":416,"end_time":1432.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1431.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because the only thing there is just making sure that whenever we.","index":417,"end_time":1434.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1432.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because we''ll be mapping all the properties and everything, obviously, we just want to make sure that''s associated on all of those records.","index":418,"end_time":1440.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1434.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we could either do like a sweep and update or just remove and then add all in batches again.","index":419,"end_time":1446.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1440.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, because I. Oh, thanks.","index":420,"end_time":1448.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1446.91,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Because I won''t have the mapping into Salesforce.","index":421,"end_time":1450.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1448.43,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Every list is different.","index":422,"end_time":1452.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1451.15,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Right.","index":423,"end_time":1452.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1452.23,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So, okay, that''s.","index":424,"end_time":1453.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1452.51,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That''s the biggest thing.","index":425,"end_time":1454.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1453.83,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Website.","index":426,"end_time":1455.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1454.99,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We already talked about that.","index":427,"end_time":1457.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1455.55,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Riverside question.","index":428,"end_time":1458.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1457.66,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''ll leave last data box.","index":429,"end_time":1459.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1458.3,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So everyone is really excited.","index":430,"end_time":1463.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1460.62,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I think I sold you guys on this data box that I showed Avanti in my interview.","index":431,"end_time":1467.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1463.26,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And.","index":432,"end_time":1468.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1467.74,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I said, well, to be honest, we don''t have anything to show because we haven''t.","index":433,"end_time":1472.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1468.38,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"There''s nothing in there.","index":434,"end_time":1473.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1472.58,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So, yeah, I think we''re gonna have to wait until there is something there to actually show.","index":435,"end_time":1480.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1474.54,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And so, for example, Zoom Webinar, which we bought, we''re moving away from Big Marker, so I''m making sure everything is out of big Marker, even though it''s archived.","index":436,"end_time":1493.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1481.18,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''m pulling it out and we''re moving to Zoom Webinar.","index":437,"end_time":1497.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1494.35,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And we''ve got a couple of events in January.","index":438,"end_time":1501.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1498.43,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"They''re going to be recorded for various reasons, but then we can start tracking, you know, for the website as well as these different activities.","index":439,"end_time":1512.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1502.43,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But I did set the expectation that I''ll.","index":440,"end_time":1515.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1512.93,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''ll send you guys my.","index":441,"end_time":1516.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1515.97,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"My calendar, but I said there''s nothing really to track yet because there isn''t anything in there.","index":442,"end_time":1521.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1517.05,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So it''s chicken and egg.","index":443,"end_time":1523.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1522.25,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We have to pull things in there before we start tracking.","index":444,"end_time":1527.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1523.45,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So the next question Yesterday from the L1 was, well, what are we tracking?","index":445,"end_time":1533.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1527.93,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I''m so used to calling everything you did for Rico and Avanti.","index":446,"end_time":1539.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1534.17,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I didn''t think much about it.","index":447,"end_time":1541.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1539.4,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I.","index":448,"end_time":1541.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1541.04,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Do you have a standard work list of what you usually track?","index":449,"end_time":1546.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1542.24,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And then.","index":450,"end_time":1547.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1547.36,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I like that.","index":451,"end_time":1549.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1547.84,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, it would.","index":452,"end_time":1550.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1549.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It would typically be like owned experiences, which would be the website and tracking a few different metrics there, like time on page views for pages, things like that.","index":453,"end_time":1560,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1551.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we could build that slide out right now.","index":454,"end_time":1562.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1560,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then obviously we would want to have, like, social media in there from an organic perspective.","index":455,"end_time":1568.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1564.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any paid media metrics that we''re tracking.","index":456,"end_time":1570.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1568.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"HubSpot and salesforce metrics, things like that.","index":457,"end_time":1573.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1570.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s.","index":458,"end_time":1573.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1573.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s what I would consider kind of the first batch of information for AQI''s data box.","index":459,"end_time":1579.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1573.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":460,"end_time":1580.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1579.85,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Could you just.","index":461,"end_time":1581.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1580.57,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Either of you just kind of jot that down and send that over, and I''ll take a look and see what else they meet.","index":462,"end_time":1588.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1582.09,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Need to break down.","index":463,"end_time":1589.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1588.56,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But I. I just.","index":464,"end_time":1590.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1589.2,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I just kind of took it for granted.","index":465,"end_time":1592.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1591.04,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I. Yeah.","index":466,"end_time":1594.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1592.76,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And we can break the information out, you know, any way that someone needs to consume it.","index":467,"end_time":1598.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1594.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we want to have a whole slide dedicated to newsletters or something, for example, we can do that.","index":468,"end_time":1603.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1598.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And source is really, really important.","index":469,"end_time":1606,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1604.319,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like, that''s something they.","index":470,"end_time":1607.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1606.56,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"They''ve never tracked.","index":471,"end_time":1608.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1607.56,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":472,"end_time":1609.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1608.72,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Okay, that''s cool.","index":473,"end_time":1610.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1609.68,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Last question.","index":474,"end_time":1612,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1611.36,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"If you have two more minutes.","index":475,"end_time":1614.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1612.8,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":476,"end_time":1614.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1614.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have to buy it today to get it into the budget, so I''ve only used Riverside through you guys, and I''ve kind of sold them on Riverside.","index":477,"end_time":1625.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1615.99,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s not that expensive.","index":478,"end_time":1626.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1625.67,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But just two questions.","index":479,"end_time":1628.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1626.59,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"One, I don''t need a license for everybody.","index":480,"end_time":1631.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1628.35,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Right.","index":481,"end_time":1631.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1631.39,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like, it''s just we''ve got some people in the field to upload through the.","index":482,"end_time":1635.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1631.63,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"The app, and that''s fine.","index":483,"end_time":1638.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1635.83,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, we.","index":484,"end_time":1639.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1638.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When.","index":485,"end_time":1639.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1639.43,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So when we create Riverside for our clients, we do one license, and everyone logs in through the same account.","index":486,"end_time":1644.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1639.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":487,"end_time":1647.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1647.25,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Is it better for you guys to.","index":488,"end_time":1649.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1647.81,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Us do it through you?","index":489,"end_time":1651.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1650.13,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, we can do that.","index":490,"end_time":1653.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1652.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have a standing relationship with Riverside, so.","index":491,"end_time":1655.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1653.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we got no problem setting that up.","index":492,"end_time":1656.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1655.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":493,"end_time":1658.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1657.89,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"If that''s better.","index":494,"end_time":1658.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1658.25,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like, it wasn''t like, I mean, that''ll come out of our points.","index":495,"end_time":1661.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1658.97,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Right?","index":496,"end_time":1662.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1661.93,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like, we don''t like.","index":497,"end_time":1663.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1662.17,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":498,"end_time":1663.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1663.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a tech stack charge.","index":499,"end_time":1665.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1663.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":500,"end_time":1665.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1665.41,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Do you know what that charge is?","index":501,"end_time":1667.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1666.13,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Because I''m.","index":502,"end_time":1667.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1667.25,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''m totally okay with doing that and making everything congruent.","index":503,"end_time":1671.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1667.77,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":504,"end_time":1672.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1672.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let me check real quick.","index":505,"end_time":1673.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1672.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":506,"end_time":1674.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1673.97,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Before I buy it, because I just.","index":507,"end_time":1677.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1675.49,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''m going through it and I''m like, okay, how do we do this?","index":508,"end_time":1679.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1677.09,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"One point.","index":509,"end_time":1687.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1687.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s it.","index":510,"end_time":1689.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1688.53,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yep.","index":511,"end_time":1689.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1689.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, let''s do it through.","index":512,"end_time":1691.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1690.29,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"You.","index":513,"end_time":1691.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1691.13,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Will do.","index":514,"end_time":1693.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1692.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, let''s do it.","index":515,"end_time":1694.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1693.89,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":516,"end_time":1695.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1694.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But you said you need that today, or is that just if you were doing it for your own budget?","index":517,"end_time":1699.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1695.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, if we were not doing it through you, I would have to put it on my credit card today.","index":518,"end_time":1705.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1699.5,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But it was getting a little bit complex.","index":519,"end_time":1707.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1705.18,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I tried to buy what I wanted, and they wouldn''t let me until I talked to somebody.","index":520,"end_time":1711.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1707.3,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I''m like, I don''t remember doing that out of Vante or Rico.","index":521,"end_time":1715.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1711.26,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I remember Colin just kind of saying, here''s what you do.","index":522,"end_time":1718.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1715.42,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, thanks.","index":523,"end_time":1721.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1719.18,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"No, I don''t need it today, so.","index":524,"end_time":1723.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1721.5,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I appreciate that.","index":525,"end_time":1723.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1723.02,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":526,"end_time":1724.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1723.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we can get that done early next week, no problem.","index":527,"end_time":1725.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1724.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That sounds great.","index":528,"end_time":1727.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1726.48,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, Vivian would like to play with it for a little bit and then kind of train the Aquarius team.","index":529,"end_time":1733.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1727.16,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And again, just a sanity check here.","index":530,"end_time":1736.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1733.6,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So we''ve got people mostly in APAC for the Aquarius team.","index":531,"end_time":1742.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1736.2,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"They''re in the field all the time.","index":532,"end_time":1744.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1742.56,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"They want to just have it on their app to upload it.","index":533,"end_time":1747.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1744.12,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That''s all they want to do.","index":534,"end_time":1748.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1747.84,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we can do that.","index":535,"end_time":1752,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1750.08,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I just haven''t bought the license or whatever you call it subscription.","index":536,"end_time":1756.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1753.43,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So if we can do it through you and I can share it with them, then that''s great.","index":537,"end_time":1761.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1756.63,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":538,"end_time":1762.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1761.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":539,"end_time":1762.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1762.55,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yep, sounds good.","index":540,"end_time":1763.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1762.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect, thanks.","index":541,"end_time":1765.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1764.31,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Thank you so much, guys.","index":542,"end_time":1766.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1765.51,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I. I feel good.","index":543,"end_time":1768.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1766.75,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I was feeling a little blind there for a while, but I. I never lost faith.","index":544,"end_time":1771.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1768.35,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"You guys have never let me down.","index":545,"end_time":1773.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1771.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I''m.","index":546,"end_time":1773.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1773.07,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''m busy over here and I wasn''t even like, I was not worried, so.","index":547,"end_time":1777.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1773.91,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":548,"end_time":1778.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1777.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":549,"end_time":1778.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1778.35,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I was out for a week in, in the end of November too, and.","index":550,"end_time":1781.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1778.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, but we''ve got all these documents and now we''re actually rolling up our sleeves and doing the work in HubSpot and everything, so.","index":551,"end_time":1788.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1782.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, let''s do it.","index":552,"end_time":1789.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1788.53,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":553,"end_time":1790.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1789.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, Barb, if anything else pops up, you know how to reach me.","index":554,"end_time":1793.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1790.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":555,"end_time":1794.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1793.97,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And do we meet next Friday or are you off?","index":556,"end_time":1796.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1794.93,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, we do meet next Friday, same time.","index":557,"end_time":1801.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1796.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not sure your guys holiday schedule.","index":558,"end_time":1804.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1802.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The only day we''re closed is the 25th and the first.","index":559,"end_time":1808.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1805.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, to be honest, I don''t know.","index":560,"end_time":1812.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1811.58,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I mean, let''s.","index":561,"end_time":1813.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1812.9,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Let''s go with that.","index":562,"end_time":1814.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1813.9,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Okay.","index":563,"end_time":1815.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1814.94,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''m not taking any holidays because I have to do stuff, but.","index":564,"end_time":1819.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1815.66,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, I gotcha.","index":565,"end_time":1820.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1819.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, for sure.","index":566,"end_time":1821.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1820.78,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But yeah, we''ll be in touch with a few emails, obviously today and then next week as well and building out HubSpot and then we''ll meet on Friday.","index":567,"end_time":1829.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1821.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Unless you have anything you wanted to meet on before then.","index":568,"end_time":1832.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1829.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I''ll let you know.","index":569,"end_time":1833.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1832.86,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But thanks everybody.","index":570,"end_time":1834.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1833.78,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s been really good.","index":571,"end_time":1836.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1834.7,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":572,"end_time":1836.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1836.06,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Thank you, Barb.","index":573,"end_time":1837.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1836.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, bye.","index":574,"end_time":1838.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1837.62,"speaker_name":"bwillans"}],"dateString":"2025-12-12T16:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/89786281993?pwd=li2lwrSFpmITXPKEdOBBgaXPwh8ONO.1","participants":["guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,barb.willans@aquaticinformatics.com","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","barb.willans@aquaticinformatics.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KC45CVGN4G5Z67FJ31J9JQP9","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Confirmed alignment on HubSpot-Salesforce integration scope; field mapping export to be delivered post-Wednesday.","Agreed Q1 focus for ABM is WIMS in Food & Beverage verticals; Aquarius pushed to Q2.","Cleaned contacts and lists in Constant Contact will be imported to HubSpot for campaign continuity.","Newsletter strategy set for January emphasizing customer success, industry coverage, and upcoming programs.","Barb confirmed Riverside licensing will proceed via vendor to consolidate tools and reduce friction."],"highlights":[{"quote":"It''s a rebuilding year for us. So let''s... have a fresh start.","speaker":"bwillans"},{"quote":"That all sounds good. Well, you know us, we like to be ahead.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"So I think that''s a marketo issue. I don''t think that''s going to happen here.","speaker":"bwillans"}],"topics":["integration","data quality","ABM","newsletter","tooling"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-12T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Salesforce to HubSpot Data Integration**\n\nThe team confirmed the need to precisely define which Salesforce contacts and opportunities migrate into HubSpot to avoid data bloat and duplication.\n\n- **Salesforce contains 56,000 contact records with 29,110 associated with opportunities**, which exceeds expectations and requires a deeper dive into opportunity definitions to clarify scope (00:00)  \n    - Barb Willans noted they initially bought **17,000 contacts** and expressed interest in understanding opportunity definitions due to the company''s size of **200 employees**  \n    - Colin Costigan proposed filtering opportunities by a **cutoff date, such as within the last two years**, to focus data migration and prioritize recent engagement  \n    - A clear mapping plan will be developed to align HubSpot and Salesforce fields, avoiding transferring unnecessary or noisy data  \n    - Barb requested a **spreadsheet comparing Salesforce fields to HubSpot properties** to confirm which data is essential, aiming to finalize after Wednesday (00:13)  \n\n- **Duplication prevention relies on email address matching in HubSpot**, with Salesforce using a custom contact-to-lead conversion process that must be synchronized (00:03)  \n    - Barb explained past duplication issues stemmed mainly from third-party sponsorship lists, not internal processes, causing **50% overcount in MQL reporting** during Q4  \n    - This problem was linked to incorrect data mapping by a vendor, Graziti, which will be addressed in the new system to prevent recurrence  \n    - The team agreed current cleaning and standard operating procedures should maintain data hygiene moving forward  \n\n## **Lifecycle Stages and BDR Workflow Alignment**\n\nClarifying lifecycle stages in HubSpot and their reflection in Salesforce is key to ensuring sales development reps (BDRs) work efficiently and marketing has full funnel visibility.\n\n- **Adopting the HubSpot lifecycle stages including Lead, MQL, and SQL will enable marketing transparency and proper BDR engagement triggers** (00:06)  \n    - Barb stressed the importance of including the Lead stage as synonymous with MQL to gain top-of-funnel visibility, which has not been a focus historically but is planned for 2026  \n    - Discussions are underway about granting Blake limited HubSpot access (view license) to monitor but not alter data, balancing transparency with control  \n    - The lifecycle stage data will be connected to Salesforce triggers so BDRs know when to act, improving lead follow-up efficiency  \n\n- **No new web pages are required for embedding HubSpot forms, simplifying implementation and reducing technical overhead** (00:07)  \n\n## **ABM Campaigns and Pipeline Planning**\n\nThe leadership team set priorities to build out ABM infrastructure in Q1 focused on Food and Beverage verticals, deferring Aquarius mining campaigns to Q2.\n\n- **L1 leadership postponed Aquarius ABM to Q2 and prioritized ABM infrastructure for Food and Beverage in Q1, targeting up to three sub-verticals** (00:14)  \n    - Barb identified Hawk, a sister company with matching personas, as a valuable source for initial Food and Beverage contacts, accelerating list building  \n    - The team plans to leverage an existing **ZoomInfo license for North America-centric contact research** to supplement data beyond current Salesforce records  \n    - Colin emphasized starting ABM infrastructure by **end of Q1** to allow timely campaign launches and content development  \n\n- **Lists for ABM will combine existing Salesforce records and net-new research to cover prioritized verticals effectively** (00:16)  \n\n## **Email Marketing and Newsletter Strategy**\n\nThe team agreed to launch a fresh, forward-looking newsletter in January focusing on new programs and customer success instead of retrospective content.\n\n- **Barb proposed a January newsletter emphasizing upcoming initiatives, featured stories, and customer voice assets, avoiding past performance retrospectives** (00:18)  \n    - The newsletter will include sections for news mentions, customer success stories, and user group events, which happen **140 times annually** but are currently unpublicized  \n    - The goal is to provide clear calls to action and sign-ups for relevant programs, strengthening engagement and awareness  \n    - Colin confirmed the newsletter will use a flexible, drag-and-drop HubSpot template allowing customization per send  \n\n- **Current email lists are being carefully cleaned and managed in Constant Contact, with approximately 2,100 contacts processed so far** (00:21)  \n    - Barb is consolidating multiple lists where contacts appear in up to **five different segments**, ensuring accurate targeting and message relevance  \n    - The cleaned lists will be migrated into HubSpot, retaining segment associations to maintain personalized messaging  \n\n## **Tracking, Analytics, and Tooling Setup**\n\nThe team is establishing baseline metrics and tools tracking while preparing to onboard new recording and webinar platforms.\n\n- **A foundational \"data box\" dashboard will track website engagement, social media, paid media, and CRM metrics to provide a holistic view of marketing performance** (00:25)  \n    - Colin offered to send a standard set of tracked metrics for review, including **time on page, page views, and source attribution**, which have never been tracked before internally  \n    - The dashboard will be customizable to highlight specific channels like newsletters or paid campaigns based on stakeholder needs  \n\n- **Transitioning from Big Marker to Zoom Webinar for events starting January will enable better tracking and recording capabilities** (00:24)  \n    - Barb is archiving legacy event data and preparing upcoming events to be recorded and tracked in Zoom Webinar, laying groundwork for measurable engagement  \n    - Riverside video recording licenses will be procured through Colin’s team to centralize management and billing, costing **one point** from their tech stack budget (00:27)  \n    - Licensing will support field teams, primarily in APAC, with app-based upload access, enabling decentralized content capture for Aquarius  \n\n## **Process Coordination and Next Steps**\n\nClear next steps include data field mapping, contract clarifications, and scheduling to keep the migration and campaign launches on track.\n\n- **Colin will send a detailed spreadsheet comparing Salesforce fields to HubSpot properties for Barb''s team to review and confirm necessary data mappings** (00:14)  \n    - This will clarify which Salesforce objects transfer fully, partially, or not at all to HubSpot, reducing noise and focusing on actionable data  \n\n- **The marketing blackout period concern for January was alleviated; Marketo will remain active until April 1st to ensure smooth transition without campaign disruption** (00:08)  \n\n- **Barb confirmed readiness to send a Christmas card campaign through HubSpot on Monday using staged lists of 8,000 to 10,000 customers and prospects** (00:23)  \n    - The team agreed to ensure all data properties are properly mapped before sending and to allow batch updates or removals as needed for list hygiene  \n\n- **Regular status meetings will continue weekly on Fridays, with awareness of holiday closures on December 25th and January 1st, maintaining momentum through year-end** (00:29)","outline":null,"keywords":["Salesforce","HubSpot","Data Migration","ABM Campaigns","Lifecycle Stages","Marketing Automation"],"overview":"- **Salesforce to HubSpot Integration:** 56,000 Salesforce contacts, 29,110 opportunities; prioritizing data mapping to reduce bloat and duplication.\n\n- **BDR Workflow Alignment:** HubSpot lifecycle stages will enhance visibility and efficiency for sales reps; ensuring quick lead follow-up.\n\n- **ABM Campaigns Focus:** Q1 will prioritize Food and Beverage ABM infrastructure; Aquarius campaigns to roll out in Q2.\n\n- **Newsletter Launch:** New newsletter in January will spotlight initiatives and success stories, moving away from past-focused content.\n\n- **Analytics Setup:** Developing a “data box” dashboard for tracking website and CRM metrics; moving to Zoom Webinar for better engagement tracking.\n\n- **Ongoing Coordination:** Weekly status updates to continue; Christmas card campaign sending planned for early next week with proper list hygiene.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nExport Salesforce fields and prepare a spreadsheet mapping to HubSpot properties; send to Barb for review (13:45)\nClean up and finalize the implementation plan document to remove highlights and incorporate feedback, then send updated version to Barb and team (12:54)\nProvide standard work list of tracking metrics for Data Box (website, social, paid media, HubSpot/Salesforce) to Barb (25:45)\nManage purchase and setup of Riverside license under Marketers In Demand account and coordinate sharing with Aquarius field team (28:10)\nContinue building modular email templates in HubSpot supporting January newsletter launch and ongoing communications (18:00)\nSupport onboarding and migration of Constant Contact nurture lists into HubSpot while maintaining segmentation (21:30)\nCoordinate sending of staged Christmas card campaign through HubSpot with Barb''s list once provided (23:40)\nKeep ongoing communication and schedule follow-up meeting for next Friday (29:56)\n\n**Barb Willans**\nConfirm with sales team how far back opportunity data should be pulled for migration and verify company counts linked to 29,000+ contacts (00:20)\nSend details of the external product feedback form with redirect URL to Marketers In Demand to ensure no disruption during Aquarius team’s January launch (09:20)\nCoordinate with Maria, Vivian, and Kyle to review implementation plan and define which Salesforce objects/fields are essential for HubSpot sync (13:50)\nFinalize vertical segment definition for ABM Food & Beverage, particularly the three sub-verticals for Whims campaign (15:40)\nProvide lists from Veralta''s Hawk and ZoomInfo contacts for Food & Beverage ABM targeting (16:00)\nShare cleaned nurturing contact lists from Constant Contact and new lists from Salesforce for import into HubSpot (21:00)\nProvide final customer list(s) for Christmas card email campaign planned for Monday (23:45)\nMonitor and provide feedback on Data Box metrics and tracking requirements (26:00)\nConfirm holiday schedules and availability for future meetings (30:00)\n\n**Guille Santana**\nMonitor and report any standalone forms outside embedded ones found on website or campaigns (09:00)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"3fbd72d9-5935-4ff7-b7f5-6f7051153ee6","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
    '2025-12-12 16:37:59.202528+00',
    '2025-12-12 16:37:59.202528+00'
  )
