)
INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: AQI // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
  '## **Salesforce to HubSpot Data Integration**

The team confirmed the need to precisely define which Salesforce contacts and opportunities migrate into HubSpot to avoid data bloat and duplication.

- **Salesforce contains 56,000 contact records with 29,110 associated with opportunities**, which exceeds expectations and requires a deeper dive into opportunity definitions to clarify scope (00:00)  
    - Barb Willans noted they initially bought **17,000 contacts** and expressed interest in understanding opportunity definitions due to the company''s size of **200 employees**  
    - Colin Costigan proposed filtering opportunities by a **cutoff date, such as within the last two years**, to focus data migration and prioritize recent engagement  
    - A clear mapping plan will be developed to align HubSpot and Salesforce fields, avoiding transferring unnecessary or noisy data  
    - Barb requested a **spreadsheet comparing Salesforce fields to HubSpot properties** to confirm which data is essential, aiming to finalize after Wednesday (00:13)  

- **Duplication prevention relies on email address matching in HubSpot**, with Salesforce using a custom contact-to-lead conversion process that must be synchronized (00:03)  
    - Barb explained past duplication issues stemmed mainly from third-party sponsorship lists, not internal processes, causing **50% overcount in MQL reporting** during Q4  
    - This problem was linked to incorrect data mapping by a vendor, Graziti, which will be addressed in the new system to prevent recurrence  
    - The team agreed current cleaning and standard operating procedures should maintain data hygiene moving forward  

## **Lifecycle Stages and BDR Workflow Alignment**

Clarifying lifecycle stages in HubSpot and their reflection in Salesforce is key to ensuring sales development reps (BDRs) work efficiently and marketing has full funnel visibility.

- **Adopting the HubSpot lifecycle stages including Lead, MQL, and SQL will enable marketing transparency and proper BDR engagement triggers** (00:06)  
    - Barb stressed the importance of including the Lead stage as synonymous with MQL to gain top-of-funnel visibility, which has not been a focus historically but is planned for 2026  
    - Discussions are underway about granting Blake limited HubSpot access (view license) to monitor but not alter data, balancing transparency with control  
    - The lifecycle stage data will be connected to Salesforce triggers so BDRs know when to act, improving lead follow-up efficiency  

- **No new web pages are required for embedding HubSpot forms, simplifying implementation and reducing technical overhead** (00:07)  

## **ABM Campaigns and Pipeline Planning**

The leadership team set priorities to build out ABM infrastructure in Q1 focused on Food and Beverage verticals, deferring Aquarius mining campaigns to Q2.

- **L1 leadership postponed Aquarius ABM to Q2 and prioritized ABM infrastructure for Food and Beverage in Q1, targeting up to three sub-verticals** (00:14)  
    - Barb identified Hawk, a sister company with matching personas, as a valuable source for initial Food and Beverage contacts, accelerating list building  
    - The team plans to leverage an existing **ZoomInfo license for North America-centric contact research** to supplement data beyond current Salesforce records  
    - Colin emphasized starting ABM infrastructure by **end of Q1** to allow timely campaign launches and content development  

- **Lists for ABM will combine existing Salesforce records and net-new research to cover prioritized verticals effectively** (00:16)  

## **Email Marketing and Newsletter Strategy**

The team agreed to launch a fresh, forward-looking newsletter in January focusing on new programs and customer success instead of retrospective content.

- **Barb proposed a January newsletter emphasizing upcoming initiatives, featured stories, and customer voice assets, avoiding past performance retrospectives** (00:18)  
    - The newsletter will include sections for news mentions, customer success stories, and user group events, which happen **140 times annually** but are currently unpublicized  
    - The goal is to provide clear calls to action and sign-ups for relevant programs, strengthening engagement and awareness  
    - Colin confirmed the newsletter will use a flexible, drag-and-drop HubSpot template allowing customization per send  

- **Current email lists are being carefully cleaned and managed in Constant Contact, with approximately 2,100 contacts processed so far** (00:21)  
    - Barb is consolidating multiple lists where contacts appear in up to **five different segments**, ensuring accurate targeting and message relevance  
    - The cleaned lists will be migrated into HubSpot, retaining segment associations to maintain personalized messaging  

## **Tracking, Analytics, and Tooling Setup**

The team is establishing baseline metrics and tools tracking while preparing to onboard new recording and webinar platforms.

- **A foundational "data box" dashboard will track website engagement, social media, paid media, and CRM metrics to provide a holistic view of marketing performance** (00:25)  
    - Colin offered to send a standard set of tracked metrics for review, including **time on page, page views, and source attribution**, which have never been tracked before internally  
    - The dashboard will be customizable to highlight specific channels like newsletters or paid campaigns based on stakeholder needs  

- **Transitioning from Big Marker to Zoom Webinar for events starting January will enable better tracking and recording capabilities** (00:24)  
    - Barb is archiving legacy event data and preparing upcoming events to be recorded and tracked in Zoom Webinar, laying groundwork for measurable engagement  
    - Riverside video recording licenses will be procured through Colin’s team to centralize management and billing, costing **one point** from their tech stack budget (00:27)  
    - Licensing will support field teams, primarily in APAC, with app-based upload access, enabling decentralized content capture for Aquarius  

## **Process Coordination and Next Steps**

Clear next steps include data field mapping, contract clarifications, and scheduling to keep the migration and campaign launches on track.

- **Colin will send a detailed spreadsheet comparing Salesforce fields to HubSpot properties for Barb''s team to review and confirm necessary data mappings** (00:14)  
    - This will clarify which Salesforce objects transfer fully, partially, or not at all to HubSpot, reducing noise and focusing on actionable data  

- **The marketing blackout period concern for January was alleviated; Marketo will remain active until April 1st to ensure smooth transition without campaign disruption** (00:08)  

- **Barb confirmed readiness to send a Christmas card campaign through HubSpot on Monday using staged lists of 8,000 to 10,000 customers and prospects** (00:23)  
    - The team agreed to ensure all data properties are properly mapped before sending and to allow batch updates or removals as needed for list hygiene  

- **Regular status meetings will continue weekly on Fridays, with awareness of holiday closures on December 25th and January 1st, maintaining momentum through year-end** (00:29)',
  '2025-12-12 16:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Export Salesforce fields and prepare a spreadsheet mapping to HubSpot properties; send to Barb for review (13:45)","completed":false},{"text":"Clean up and finalize the implementation plan document to remove highlights and incorporate feedback, then send updated version to Barb and team (12:54)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide standard work list of tracking metrics for Data Box (website, social, paid media, HubSpot/Salesforce) to Barb (25:45)","completed":false},{"text":"Manage purchase and setup of Riverside license under Marketers In Demand account and coordinate sharing with Aquarius field team (28:10)","completed":false},{"text":"Continue building modular email templates in HubSpot supporting January newsletter launch and ongoing communications (18:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Support onboarding and migration of Constant Contact nurture lists into HubSpot while maintaining segmentation (21:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate sending of staged Christmas card campaign through HubSpot with Barb''s list once provided (23:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Keep ongoing communication and schedule follow-up meeting for next Friday (29:56)","completed":false},{"text":"Confirm with sales team how far back opportunity data should be pulled for migration and verify company counts linked to 29,000+ contacts (00:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Send details of the external product feedback form with redirect URL to Marketers In Demand to ensure no disruption during Aquarius team’s January launch (09:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with Maria, Vivian, and Kyle to review implementation plan and define which Salesforce objects/fields are essential for HubSpot sync (13:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Finalize vertical segment definition for ABM Food & Beverage, particularly the three sub-verticals for Whims campaign (15:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide lists from Veralta''s Hawk and ZoomInfo contacts for Food & Beverage ABM targeting (16:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Share cleaned nurturing contact lists from Constant Contact and new lists from Salesforce for import into HubSpot (21:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide final customer list(s) for Christmas card email campaign planned for Monday (23:45)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor and provide feedback on Data Box metrics and tracking requirements (26:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Confirm holiday schedules and availability for future meetings (30:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor and report any standalone forms outside embedded ones found on website or campaigns (09:00)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
