    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/82164087465?pwd=HIMrVfQh9H8oWdIxFsR0aU3slIkuOP.1',
    '{"id":"01KBQHTX9N7X3WGHF3T8K7W9C7","title":"EASE // MiD - Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Outreach Campaign Strategy**\n\nThe team decided to pause the current outreach efforts due to low engagement and plan a targeted campaign launch after January 2nd.\n\n- **No responses or link clicks were reported in the past two weeks, signaling a need to refresh the outreach approach** (02:01)  \n    - Baylee Gunnell confirmed no prospects have scheduled meetings despite ongoing messaging  \n    - Ease Marketing suggested the holiday season and manufacturing busyness may be reducing responsiveness  \n    - The team agreed to follow up again before pausing current outreach  \n    - A new campaign list will be prepared focusing on a smaller, highly personalized segment of 20 to 30 executives who are speaking at 2026 events for better engagement\n\n- **The strategy will continue targeting C-suite executives but with more personalization to improve response rates** (03:47)  \n    - Baylee identified prior success with personalized outreach to event speakers compared to broader blasts  \n    - Ease Marketing agreed smaller, focused lists may overcome seasonal attention challenges  \n    - The campaign will be ready to launch in early January to catch renewed attention post-holidays  \n    - This approach aims to increase meetings booked and overall campaign ROI by engaging decision-makers with relevant event participation\n\n## **Video Production and Content Refinement**\n\nSignificant progress has been made on video assets with detailed feedback guiding final revisions, especially around audio and visual authenticity.\n\n- **The team is advancing toward final animations using new mixed audio tracks designed to build tension and highlight Ease’s value proposition** (06:29)  \n    - Ease Marketing described the music’s slow build and climax as key to matching the script’s narrative flow  \n    - Baylee committed to sharing these audio cues with the creative and audio teams for precise alignment  \n    - The aim is to enhance viewer engagement by syncing music shifts with solution reveals  \n    - This audio-driven storytelling supports clearer messaging and emotional impact in the videos\n\n- **Stock photography choices are under close review to ensure authentic representation of manufacturing environments** (09:01)  \n    - Ease Marketing requested alternatives to overly clean or office-style images, preferring realistic factory scenes with high-visibility vests but generally no hard hats  \n    - Baylee confirmed use of Shutterstock and will seek images that better match actual manufacturing settings and worker attire  \n    - The feedback reflects a strategic push for credibility and relatability in marketing visuals  \n    - This effort supports building trust with target industrial customers by accurately reflecting their work environments\n\n- **Visual animation details for dashboards and integration demos are being fine-tuned to improve clarity and user understanding** (25:37)  \n    - Ease Marketing suggested animated arrows and connectors to visually link Ease’s dashboard with other systems, enhancing perceived integration  \n    - Sound effects and cursor color changes were proposed to emphasize navigation between multiple dashboard panels  \n    - Baylee agreed to incorporate these elements to boost user comprehension and video polish  \n    - These improvements aim to demonstrate Ease’s system flexibility and ease of use, enhancing buyer confidence\n\n## **Project Workflow and Collaboration**\n\nA collaborative review process with extensive feedback is streamlining video production while balancing quality with timely delivery.\n\n- **Ease Marketing is providing detailed, constructive feedback early to allow easier changes before final animation stages** (04:18)  \n    - Baylee emphasized that early nitpicking helps avoid costly revisions later in production  \n    - The team values this feedback for raising quality without delaying timelines  \n    - Ease Marketing acknowledged the importance of balancing perfectionism with project momentum  \n    - This workflow reflects a mature partnership focused on delivering high-impact content efficiently\n\n- **Comments and suggestions are documented clearly and shared with creative and audio teams to guide ongoing refinements** (11:15)  \n    - Specific requests include animation transitions for images and text to maintain viewer interest  \n    - Ease Marketing uses examples and references to communicate desired styles and effects  \n    - Baylee coordinates with creative director and audio specialists to ensure alignment with client vision  \n    - This structured feedback loop supports a smooth production pipeline and high client satisfaction\n\n## **Timing and Resource Planning**\n\nThe team is aligning campaign launches and video production milestones with seasonal rhythms and resource availability to maximize impact.\n\n- **The next outreach campaign is targeted for launch after January 2nd to capitalize on post-holiday engagement spikes** (02:46)  \n    - This timing reflects awareness of manufacturing customer workloads during the holiday season  \n    - Planning includes list curation and personalization efforts in December to meet this deadline  \n    - Ease Marketing is managing episode scheduling with two planned shows in the near term  \n    - This schedule aims to optimize lead generation and meeting conversion in Q1 2024\n\n- **Video production is nearing completion with multiple rounds of reviews and refinements expected in the coming weeks** (26:41)  \n    - Ease Marketing is closing in on final feedback to reduce last-minute changes  \n    - Baylee confirmed ongoing audio mixing and animation work with the goal of delivering polished final assets soon  \n    - The focus remains on quality and authentic representation balanced against project deadlines  \n    - Successful completion will provide fresh, engaging marketing content to support sales efforts early next year","outline":null,"keywords":["Outreach Campaign","Video Production","Audio Mixing","Stock Photography","Manufacturing","Dashboard Animation"],"overview":"- **Outreach Campaign Paused:** Current efforts halted due to low engagement; new campaign targeting C-suite executives after January 2nd.  \n- **Personalized Approach:** Focus on 20-30 event speakers for better engagement and increased meeting bookings; smaller, focused lists planned.  \n- **Video Production Progress:** Final animations in progress with key audio cues and authentic visuals to enhance viewer engagement.  \n- **Authentic Visuals Required:** Stock photography will reflect realistic manufacturing environments, avoiding overly polished images to build credibility.  \n- **Feedback Loop Established:** Early constructive feedback streamlines production, enhances quality, and ensures timely delivery.  \n- **Resource Alignment:** Campaign launch and video milestones synchronized with seasonal rhythms to maximize impact in early 2024.","action_items":"\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nFollow up with outreach contacts who have not engaged recently to try to book meetings (02:07)\nDevelop a new personalized outreach list targeting 20-30 speakers for 2026 events and plan campaign launch after January 2nd (02:46)\nCommunicate client’s detailed audio/music vision to audio specialists to ensure alignment with the script and desired music dynamics (06:47)\nRequest animation team to add intermediate slides showing how images appear to pull in and animate, e.g., for scene six (11:15)\nAdd animation notes about arrows and lines emanating from Ease dashboard visuals to clarify integration with other systems (13:11)\nIncorporate suggestions for sound effects and cursor/color changes to emphasize dashboard navigation (25:37)\nWrite notes regarding authenticity concerns for stock photos and seek alternative imagery that better matches client’s vision of factory attire and environment (15:47)\n\n**Ease Marketing**\nContinue reviewing video drafts and provide feedback with emphasis on realism and authenticity in visuals (04:07)\nProvide specific examples and link preferred stock photo styles for manufacturing scenes using platforms like Shutterstock (15:53)\nConfirm approach to customer quotes usage (keep name without company) and communicate any concerns related to outdated references (14:28)\nEvaluate the animation concepts for dashboards and suggest any additional improvements to emphasize software features (24:53)\nCoordinate internally to finalize reviews and communicate feedback to Paula and production team to maintain momentum toward completion (26:21)\n"},"duration":27.510000228881836,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":1,"name":"Ease Marketing"}],"sentences":[{"text":"No worries.","index":0,"end_time":0.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No worries.","index":1,"end_time":1.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think you said, are you on site this week?","index":2,"end_time":4.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I was on Monday.","index":3,"end_time":6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":5.12,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"Tuesday.","index":4,"end_time":6.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":6.08,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"Okay.","index":5,"end_time":7.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":7.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"How''s that?","index":6,"end_time":8.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":8.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Good.","index":7,"end_time":10.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":9.68,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"It''s always good going and hanging out with customers.","index":8,"end_time":12.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":10.4,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"This is a H vac manufacturer, so we got to see how the AC units are made.","index":9,"end_time":18.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":13.68,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"Ooh, nice.","index":10,"end_time":20.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":19.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Looks very complicated.","index":11,"end_time":22.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":21.28,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s crazy.","index":12,"end_time":24.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":23.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"What about you?","index":13,"end_time":27.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":27.05,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"How things.","index":14,"end_time":27.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":27.49,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":15,"end_time":28.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":27.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Going great.","index":16,"end_time":30.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":29.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":17,"end_time":31.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":30.81,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Feels like things are finally slowing down just a little bit.","index":18,"end_time":34.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":31.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Not a ton, but a tiny bit.","index":19,"end_time":37.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":35.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like right before.","index":20,"end_time":38.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":37.61,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll be out for a little bit for the holidays.","index":21,"end_time":42.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":39.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":22,"end_time":43.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":42.41,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"Well, we can jump into it.","index":23,"end_time":49.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":46.41,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ve got podcast updates, content updates, just some outreach campaign things, and then also just some stuff on the videos we''re working on.","index":24,"end_time":63.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":54.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":25,"end_time":64.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":63.94,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"So for the podcast, we were able to publish the episode with Ishant.","index":26,"end_time":71.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":66.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So that is live now.","index":27,"end_time":73.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":71.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then we also sent over the blog post.","index":28,"end_time":78.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":74.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So that is all taken care of.","index":29,"end_time":79.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":78.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then just on that note, for the outreach campaign, it looks like we have had a few people who''ve been interested in and talking through it.","index":30,"end_time":89.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":82.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"How has that been going on your end?","index":31,"end_time":92.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":90.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''ve not heard from anybody.","index":32,"end_time":96.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":93.88,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"Like, in the last week or two.","index":33,"end_time":99.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":97.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"At all.","index":34,"end_time":101.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":100.84,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"Yeah, Like, I.","index":35,"end_time":102.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":101.36,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"No one''s.","index":36,"end_time":103.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":102.36,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"No one''s followed the link.","index":37,"end_time":104.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":103.16,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":38,"end_time":105.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":105.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we sent.","index":39,"end_time":106.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":105.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":40,"end_time":107.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":106.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just.","index":41,"end_time":107.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":107.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No one''s actually followed through then.","index":42,"end_time":109,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":107.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, if we''re.","index":43,"end_time":110.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":109.6,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"If we''re sending the link because, you know, whoever''s managing the messages, I''ve just not even reading through them, but nobody has set up anything.","index":44,"end_time":121.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":110.2,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"Okay.","index":45,"end_time":122.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":121.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do you want us just to poke them again and see if they.","index":46,"end_time":126.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":122.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, for sure.","index":47,"end_time":127.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":127.12,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"We''re.","index":48,"end_time":128.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":127.92,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"We''re.","index":49,"end_time":128.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":128.36,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"I''m out of folks.","index":50,"end_time":131.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":130.08,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"I''ve got two episodes scheduled.","index":51,"end_time":133.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":131.68,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"One this week, one next week, but that''s all I have set up.","index":52,"end_time":139.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":134,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"Okay, well, we''ll reach out to them again then and just follow up and try to get some time book then.","index":53,"end_time":146.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":139.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So then we''re up to the time where we should probably get another campaign rolling.","index":54,"end_time":152.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":147.81,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I think we can start putting together another list, but let''s plan on probably launching it after, like, January 2nd.","index":55,"end_time":161.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":154.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we''ll probably see more success doing that, if that sounds good to you.","index":56,"end_time":165.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":162.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":57,"end_time":166.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":166.02,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"Then do you have any preferences on, like, how we put together the list?","index":58,"end_time":170.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":167.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think this last one, we were going for, like, C Suite.","index":59,"end_time":173.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":170.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"People mostly.","index":60,"end_time":176.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":175.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do you have any other preferences?","index":61,"end_time":179.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":177.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, I think Execs is a good one.","index":62,"end_time":182.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":179.78,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":63,"end_time":185.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":184.74,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"I don''t know if this is just time of year.","index":64,"end_time":188.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":185.54,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"I mean, it''s a busy time for manufacturers.","index":65,"end_time":191.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":188.74,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"Not really a slowdown for them.","index":66,"end_time":193.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":191.54,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":67,"end_time":194.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":193.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it could be That.","index":68,"end_time":195.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":194.06,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":69,"end_time":198.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":197.42,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":70,"end_time":200.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":200.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":71,"end_time":201.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":200.9,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"We''ll.","index":72,"end_time":201.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":201.46,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"We''ll.","index":73,"end_time":202.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":201.82,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"We''ll work on getting together another list.","index":74,"end_time":204.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":202.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we, we saw some success with like, th.","index":75,"end_time":210.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":205.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Those events.","index":76,"end_time":211.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":210.34,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Where we had it a bit more personalized, so we can maybe try like a smaller segment and just really try and personalize it for maybe like 20 to 30 people who are going to be speaking at events for 2026.","index":77,"end_time":226.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":212.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":78,"end_time":227.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":227.2,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"Because I feel like of the campaigns we''ve run, that, that one maybe saw more, more bites than the other ones.","index":79,"end_time":235.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":229.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s people who like to speak.","index":80,"end_time":237.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":236,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":81,"end_time":238.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":238.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay then.","index":82,"end_time":240.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":239.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Then we''ll get working on that.","index":83,"end_time":242.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":241.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it''s ready to go by the start of the new year.","index":84,"end_time":245.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":242.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":85,"end_time":246.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":246,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"And then videos.","index":86,"end_time":248.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":247.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Seems like you''ve been reviewing a lot of stuff.","index":87,"end_time":251.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":249.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We have a lot, A lot bacon right now.","index":88,"end_time":254.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":251.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"How''s all that going?","index":89,"end_time":256.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":255.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Good.","index":90,"end_time":258.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":258.16,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":91,"end_time":262.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":262.08,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"I know I''m being very nitpicky about things.","index":92,"end_time":265.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":262.6,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"So certainly give your team my thanks.","index":93,"end_time":269.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":267.2,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":94,"end_time":275.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":275.53,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":95,"end_time":277.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":276.57,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":96,"end_time":277.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":277.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, we talk a lot about this over slack, so I think we''re.","index":97,"end_time":281.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":278.01,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''re looking pretty good on stuff.","index":98,"end_time":282.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''re.","index":99,"end_time":283.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":282.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''re working on a lot of revisions right now.","index":100,"end_time":285.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":283.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''re working through using that new audio for the.","index":101,"end_time":289.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":285.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The mixed or the music for the new mixed audio and all that stuff.","index":102,"end_time":293.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":289.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''re getting really close to being able to start animations.","index":103,"end_time":297.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":293.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But like, I do appreciate the nitpickiness now.","index":104,"end_time":301.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":297.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s a lot easier to change things now than it is once we did things.","index":105,"end_time":306.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":301.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":106,"end_time":307.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":306.78,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":107,"end_time":308.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":308.06,"speaker_name":"Ease Marketing"},{"text":"Okay.","index":1