INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: EASE // MiD - Weekly Meeting',
  '## **Outreach Campaign Strategy**

The team decided to pause the current outreach efforts due to low engagement and plan a targeted campaign launch after January 2nd.

- **No responses or link clicks were reported in the past two weeks, signaling a need to refresh the outreach approach** (02:01)  
    - Baylee Gunnell confirmed no prospects have scheduled meetings despite ongoing messaging  
    - Ease Marketing suggested the holiday season and manufacturing busyness may be reducing responsiveness  
    - The team agreed to follow up again before pausing current outreach  
    - A new campaign list will be prepared focusing on a smaller, highly personalized segment of 20 to 30 executives who are speaking at 2026 events for better engagement

- **The strategy will continue targeting C-suite executives but with more personalization to improve response rates** (03:47)  
    - Baylee identified prior success with personalized outreach to event speakers compared to broader blasts  
    - Ease Marketing agreed smaller, focused lists may overcome seasonal attention challenges  
    - The campaign will be ready to launch in early January to catch renewed attention post-holidays  
    - This approach aims to increase meetings booked and overall campaign ROI by engaging decision-makers with relevant event participation

## **Video Production and Content Refinement**

Significant progress has been made on video assets with detailed feedback guiding final revisions, especially around audio and visual authenticity.

- **The team is advancing toward final animations using new mixed audio tracks designed to build tension and highlight Ease’s value proposition** (06:29)  
    - Ease Marketing described the music’s slow build and climax as key to matching the script’s narrative flow  
    - Baylee committed to sharing these audio cues with the creative and audio teams for precise alignment  
    - The aim is to enhance viewer engagement by syncing music shifts with solution reveals  
    - This audio-driven storytelling supports clearer messaging and emotional impact in the videos

- **Stock photography choices are under close review to ensure authentic representation of manufacturing environments** (09:01)  
    - Ease Marketing requested alternatives to overly clean or office-style images, preferring realistic factory scenes with high-visibility vests but generally no hard hats  
    - Baylee confirmed use of Shutterstock and will seek images that better match actual manufacturing settings and worker attire  
    - The feedback reflects a strategic push for credibility and relatability in marketing visuals  
    - This effort supports building trust with target industrial customers by accurately reflecting their work environments

- **Visual animation details for dashboards and integration demos are being fine-tuned to improve clarity and user understanding** (25:37)  
    - Ease Marketing suggested animated arrows and connectors to visually link Ease’s dashboard with other systems, enhancing perceived integration  
    - Sound effects and cursor color changes were proposed to emphasize navigation between multiple dashboard panels  
    - Baylee agreed to incorporate these elements to boost user comprehension and video polish  
    - These improvements aim to demonstrate Ease’s system flexibility and ease of use, enhancing buyer confidence

## **Project Workflow and Collaboration**

A collaborative review process with extensive feedback is streamlining video production while balancing quality with timely delivery.

- **Ease Marketing is providing detailed, constructive feedback early to allow easier changes before final animation stages** (04:18)  
    - Baylee emphasized that early nitpicking helps avoid costly revisions later in production  
    - The team values this feedback for raising quality without delaying timelines  
    - Ease Marketing acknowledged the importance of balancing perfectionism with project momentum  
    - This workflow reflects a mature partnership focused on delivering high-impact content efficiently

- **Comments and suggestions are documented clearly and shared with creative and audio teams to guide ongoing refinements** (11:15)  
    - Specific requests include animation transitions for images and text to maintain viewer interest  
    - Ease Marketing uses examples and references to communicate desired styles and effects  
    - Baylee coordinates with creative director and audio specialists to ensure alignment with client vision  
    - This structured feedback loop supports a smooth production pipeline and high client satisfaction

## **Timing and Resource Planning**

The team is aligning campaign launches and video production milestones with seasonal rhythms and resource availability to maximize impact.

- **The next outreach campaign is targeted for launch after January 2nd to capitalize on post-holiday engagement spikes** (02:46)  
    - This timing reflects awareness of manufacturing customer workloads during the holiday season  
    - Planning includes list curation and personalization efforts in December to meet this deadline  
    - Ease Marketing is managing episode scheduling with two planned shows in the near term  
    - This schedule aims to optimize lead generation and meeting conversion in Q1 2024

- **Video production is nearing completion with multiple rounds of reviews and refinements expected in the coming weeks** (26:41)  
    - Ease Marketing is closing in on final feedback to reduce last-minute changes  
    - Baylee confirmed ongoing audio mixing and animation work with the goal of delivering polished final assets soon  
    - The focus remains on quality and authentic representation balanced against project deadlines  
    - Successful completion will provide fresh, engaging marketing content to support sales efforts early next year',
  '2025-12-10 22:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Follow up with outreach contacts who have not engaged recently to try to book meetings (02:07)","completed":false},{"text":"Develop a new personalized outreach list targeting 20-30 speakers for 2026 events and plan campaign launch after January 2nd (02:46)","completed":false},{"text":"Communicate client’s detailed audio/music vision to audio specialists to ensure alignment with the script and desired music dynamics (06:47)","completed":false},{"text":"Request animation team to add intermediate slides showing how images appear to pull in and animate, e.g., for scene six (11:15)","completed":false},{"text":"Add animation notes about arrows and lines emanating from Ease dashboard visuals to clarify integration with other systems (13:11)","completed":false},{"text":"Incorporate suggestions for sound effects and cursor/color changes to emphasize dashboard navigation (25:37)","completed":false},{"text":"Write notes regarding authenticity concerns for stock photos and seek alternative imagery that better matches client’s vision of factory attire and environment (15:47)","completed":false},{"text":"Continue reviewing video drafts and provide feedback with emphasis on realism and authenticity in visuals (04:07)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide specific examples and link preferred stock photo styles for manufacturing scenes using platforms like Shutterstock (15:53)","completed":false},{"text":"Confirm approach to customer quotes usage (keep name without company) and communicate any concerns related to outdated references (14:28)","completed":false},{"text":"Evaluate the animation concepts for dashboards and suggest any additional improvements to emphasize software features (24:53)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate internally to finalize reviews and communicate feedback to Paula and production team to maintain momentum toward completion (26:21)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: Marketing Videos (2025-12-12 15:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'e50afe94-037e-49d6-8f2e-8c05ac7e3294',
    '2025-12-12 15:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KC4GM53VAH4RZ2YHYHA9N7EJ',
    'Marketing Videos',
    '{"Hendrik Pollex","Colin Costigan"}'::text[],
    630,
    'https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_MTY4Y2VhYTctNmNjYS00NTk2LTg4MTAtYzllMWY5NGQyYWY4@thread.v2/0?context={"Tid":"c978af67-e2b1-467a-ba4c-29cfac272602","Oid":"3e0a517d-16ae-45c8-9fa2-d70ab1b4a277"}',
    '{"id":"01KC4GM53VAH4RZ2YHYHA9N7EJ","title":"Marketing Videos","summary":{"notes":"## **Video Production and Content Alignment**\n\nThe team is nearly finished preparing video materials, needing only final AI response scripts to complete animated content.\n\n- **Hendrik Pollex produced 10 initial videos** for review, with **Colin Costigan confirming 95% completion** of required footage for animation purposes (06:13)  \n    - Colin explained animation allows control over text and visuals, avoiding full platform exposure.  \n    - The AI chatbot footage is sufficient, pending final prompts and responses from Axel.  \n    - Hendrik will supplement videos with comments specifying expected AI agent inputs and outputs to guide animation.  \n    - This approach reduces risks from incomplete AI features by simulating final behavior in animation.\n\n- **AI agent capabilities are currently limited but planned for expansion**; Hendrik clarified partial functions like resource request creation exist, but full AI agent features remain in beta (03:09)  \n    - Hendrik noted the AI can extract requirements from resource descriptions but only via a separate feature, not the agent itself.  \n    - Colin emphasized the animation can portray planned AI features before full implementation, requiring clear script inputs.  \n    - Hendrik committed to providing updated prompts and expected responses by Monday to finalize video content (06:57).  \n    - This ensures marketing materials align with future product capabilities and set accurate user expectations.\n\n## **AI Agent Development and Feature Roadmap**\n\nThe AI agent is in beta with partial functionality, requiring clear definition of target behaviors to guide both product and video development.\n\n- **Hendrik highlighted that the AI agent can create requests with descriptions but cannot fully handle candidate search tasks yet** (03:09)  \n    - Hendrik demonstrated the agent’s current limitations with a video where the AI declined or failed to respond properly to a candidate search request (04:40).  \n    - The team agreed to specify the intended final agent responses to simulate them in video content ahead of full feature rollout.  \n    - Hendrik will provide detailed prompts and expected AI replies as a script to support animation and future development alignment.  \n    - This clarifies the product roadmap by linking video messaging to upcoming AI capabilities.\n\n- **Colin reinforced the need for consistent AI responses for scripted animations**, citing instances of varied outputs from identical prompts causing confusion (05:46)  \n    - To address this, the team will standardize prompt-response pairs in documentation to maintain clarity in messaging.  \n    - This process supports synchronized marketing and engineering efforts for a smooth launch.  \n    - It also mitigates user confusion by setting clear expectations on AI agent behavior in promotional materials.\n\n## **Collaboration and Communication Workflow**\n\nClear communication and documentation are critical to finalize videos and align product expectations across teams.\n\n- **Colin requested Hendrik to annotate the shared script document with comments on desired AI responses and prompts** to fill gaps where the AI agent is not yet fully functional (05:25)  \n    - Hendrik agreed to add comments and possibly submit additional videos demonstrating expected interactions (06:26).  \n    - This shared documentation will serve as the single source of truth for production and development teams.  \n    - The approach reduces delays and rework by ensuring everyone understands the final video requirements and product capabilities.\n\n- **Scheduling considerations were noted with Hendrik targeting Monday to provide updates**, acknowledging limited availability during the weekend (06:57)  \n    - Colin confirmed no urgency during the weekend, prioritizing quality and accuracy over speed.  \n    - This respects team bandwidth while maintaining momentum toward the video completion milestone.  \n    - The timeline aligns with marketing launch preparations needing finalized content early next week.\n\n## **Quality Assurance and Video Output Standards**\n\nThe video quality is generally acceptable, but the team remains attentive to feedback and technical constraints.\n\n- **Colin noted Axel’s concern about video quality, but overall footage appeared fine on the production side** (06:42)  \n    - Ensuring clear visuals is essential for effective user guidance and product demonstration.  \n    - The team will continue monitoring video quality to avoid user confusion or dissatisfaction.  \n    - This quality check supports brand professionalism and user comprehension in final materials.","outline":null,"keywords":["AI agent","resource management dashboard","video animation","script prompts","beta features","video recordings"],"overview":"- **Video Production Update:** 10 initial videos are ready; 95% of animation footage is complete pending AI response scripts.\n\n- **AI Agent Limitations:** Current AI features are in beta, can create resource requests but lack full candidate search capabilities.\n\n- **Script Consistency Needed:** Team to standardize prompt-response pairs to avoid confusion from varied outputs in animations.\n\n- **Documentation as a Guide:** Shared script document will clarify AI responses and desired prompts for consistent production and development.\n\n- **Quality Monitoring:** Team will ensure video quality meets standards to guide users and maintain brand professionalism. \n\n- **Timeline for Finalization:** Hendrik aims to provide updates by Monday, prioritizing quality over rapid completion for marketing launch.","action_items":"\n**Hendrik Pollex**\nAdd comments in the shared document specifying the planned input prompts and expected AI agent responses for the animations (06:26)\nPotentially add a new video to demonstrate correct interaction and outputs of the AI agent (06:42)\nProvide final clarifications and feedback on the video content by Monday at the latest (06:57)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nReview Hendrik’s comments and additional video once provided, to finalize animation scripts and video production setup (06:42)\n"},"duration":10.5,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Sam.","index":0,"end_time":25.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.24,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Hi, Colin.","index":1,"end_time":47.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":46.41,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Hey, Hendrik.","index":2,"end_time":48.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":47.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":3,"end_time":48.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":48.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":4,"end_time":50.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":49.69,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":5,"end_time":51.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":50.01,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"All right.","index":6,"end_time":51.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":51.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s Friday and you are definitely at the end of your day, right?","index":7,"end_time":55.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":51.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I am.","index":8,"end_time":56.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":55.7,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":9,"end_time":57.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":56.62,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"It''s not long for you either.","index":10,"end_time":60.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":58.74,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s 10:30 in the morning here, so.","index":11,"end_time":63.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":60.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":12,"end_time":68.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":66.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":13,"end_time":69.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":69.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you said that you had some questions just on what''s needed for those video recordings?","index":14,"end_time":73.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":69.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":15,"end_time":74.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":74.26,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"So it''s pretty difficult for me because I''m not that sure what you expect in those videos.","index":16,"end_time":82.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":74.7,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"So I made, I think now, 10 videos in the folder.","index":17,"end_time":88.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":83.91,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Have you reviewed it yet?","index":18,"end_time":90.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":88.87,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ve reviewed them.","index":19,"end_time":91.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":90.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The main thing was Axel reviewing those and just making sure that''s what he wanted to illustrate in the videos.","index":20,"end_time":97.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":91.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As you can see.","index":21,"end_time":99.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":98.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you in the document right now with the script?","index":22,"end_time":101.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":99.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":23,"end_time":104.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":103.59,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Okay, so if you scroll down a little bit and I can even share my screen, I''ve highlighted basically what we''re looking for screen recordings for.","index":24,"end_time":113.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":104.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So let me just kind of take a step back here.","index":25,"end_time":116.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":114.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re not going to show any actual footage of your recordings.","index":26,"end_time":120.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":116.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just need that so that our team can animate the entire video.","index":27,"end_time":124.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":120.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll be able to control the text on screen, what''s shown, what''s not shown.","index":28,"end_time":129.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":125.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We do that because it can be a little bit overwhelming to show an entire platform, and we really want to guide the user''s eye to specific features.","index":29,"end_time":138.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":130.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the mindset going into this in your videos, you had it.","index":30,"end_time":143.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":139.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I told Axel we can just change the text on, like, the AI response for the agent, etc.","index":31,"end_time":148.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":143.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think the video there was fine.","index":32,"end_time":152.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":149.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, for showing the chatbot, that''s really all we need.","index":33,"end_time":155.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":152.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we just need to know from Axle what prompt we want to put in and what we want the return to be.","index":34,"end_time":159.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":155.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":35,"end_time":160.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":159.64,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":36,"end_time":160.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":160.12,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Then the resource management dashboard.","index":37,"end_time":163.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":161.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just showing, like, the entire team in that spreadsheet.","index":38,"end_time":166.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":164.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Um, and then I don''t know if the AI agent is capable of doing this currently.","index":39,"end_time":174.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":167.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know it''s in beta phase, but.","index":40,"end_time":177.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":174.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just like, just a little bit of it.","index":41,"end_time":180.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":177.74,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"So not everything.","index":42,"end_time":181.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":180.3,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"That''s where I was struggling.","index":43,"end_time":183.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":181.46,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Yeah, gotcha.","index":44,"end_time":184.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":183.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, what is the agent able to handle out of this list right now?","index":45,"end_time":188.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":184.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so we have different things.","index":46,"end_time":191.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":189.54,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"So the agent is capable of creating requests for people.","index":47,"end_time":200.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":192.18,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"So, like, with different descriptions and some small AI features are capable of extracting the requirements from descriptions.","index":48,"end_time":212.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":200.24,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"So I have a separate video for that just generated maybe 10 minutes ago.","index":49,"end_time":216.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":212.4,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Okay.","index":50,"end_time":217.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":217.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it was.","index":51,"end_time":218.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":217.68,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":52,"end_time":219.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":218.88,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"And was also in that big video that is inside from Trupyr.","index":53,"end_time":224.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":219.32,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Yeah, it is AI resource Request extraction.","index":54,"end_time":233.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":228.05,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Yes, but that''s not really the agent.","index":55,"end_time":236.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":233.25,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"It''s a separate feature on the resource request.","index":56,"end_time":239.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":236.49,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":57,"end_time":241.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":240.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so I think the plan is to make the AI agent do that, but I''m not sure when it''s implemented.","index":58,"end_time":255.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":247.33,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":59,"end_time":256.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":255.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s the cool thing about animating the video is we can control that.","index":60,"end_time":259.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":256.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if we wanted to show that, I mean, before it''s built, we''re fully able to.","index":61,"end_time":263.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":259.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just need to know basically what we need to show in the video.","index":62,"end_time":267.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":263.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":63,"end_time":268.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":268.13,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"So if the plan is for the AI agent to be able to do these things, we can design that.","index":64,"end_time":273.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":268.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just need to know basically what text you want to pop up on screen, what does someone have to enter, what button do they have to click, etc.","index":65,"end_time":279.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":273.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so I had one video in the.","index":66,"end_time":283.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":280.47,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"In the folder where I mentioned too big screen.","index":67,"end_time":286.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":283.67,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"So Excel told me that it''s too big there.","index":68,"end_time":290.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":286.55,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"I had one.","index":69,"end_time":291.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":290.39,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Let''s see.","index":70,"end_time":296.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":295.91,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Maybe it''s the first one.","index":71,"end_time":299.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":297.91,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Check that.","index":72,"end_time":301.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":301.18,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Because I asked the AI agent to create a resource request and then find candidates for it, and the response was, okay, I''m not capable of doing that, or it''s thinking and not giving a correct response.","index":73,"end_time":318.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":302.14,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"So that''s what I would expect the AI agent to do afterwards.","index":74,"end_time":324.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":320.7,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":75,"end_time":325.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":325.18,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Okay, so then basically what we would need from here is just anywhere that the screen recording or the AI agent, for example, didn''t give the response that it will when it''s out of beta.","index":76,"end_time":336.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":325.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just need to know what that response should be, and then we can populate that when we.","index":77,"end_time":341.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":336.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When we animate the entire video.","index":78,"end_time":343.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":341.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":79,"end_time":345.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":345.23,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Because I even saw.","index":80,"end_time":347.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":346.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can''t remember which video it was specifically, but I know you put in like, the same prompt twice and got two different outputs.","index":81,"end_time":354.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":347.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":82,"end_time":355.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":354.68,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"So, yeah, we just need to know.","index":83,"end_time":357.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":356.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if you guys just want to leave comments, even on the document of just like, you know, hey, when we do this, we want the response to say xyz.","index":84,"end_time":366.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":357.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then from there we''ll be pretty set to start producing the video.","index":85,"end_time":370.279,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":366.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":86,"end_time":371.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":370.68,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Okay.","index":87,"end_time":373.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":373.08,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"We have the dashboard and everything, so I think you''re like 95% of the way there.","index":88,"end_time":377.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":373.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we just need the context of.","index":89,"end_time":379,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":377.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know the agent isn''t fully built out and running exactly how you guys want it to right now.","index":90,"end_time":384.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":379.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just need to know, like, what is the end plan?","index":91,"end_time":385.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":384.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, Okay, I will get back to you with that.","index":92,"end_time":389.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":386.37,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"So I will just make a comment here and maybe add another video to showcase what I would get into the prompt field and what the expected answer is.","index":93,"end_time":402.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":389.37,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Yeah, that would be perfect.","index":94,"end_time":403.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":402.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know Axel said that some of the video quality wasn''t great on his end, but it looks fine on our end.","index":95,"end_time":409.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":404.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think.","index":96,"end_time":409.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":409.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we should be all good there.","index":97,"end_time":410.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":409.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, good.","index":98,"end_time":412.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":411.72,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":99,"end_time":413.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":413.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":100,"end_time":414.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":414.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any other questions, or does that clear everything up?","index":101,"end_time":416.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":414.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s pretty clear for me now.","index":102,"end_time":418.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":417.32,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"So thank you very much.","index":103,"end_time":419.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":418.76,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"I will get back to you Monday at latest, I would say.","index":104,"end_time":424.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":420.52,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"So I''m not sure if I can reach out to anyone today because.","index":105,"end_time":428.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":424.2,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Yeah, no problem at all.","index":106,"end_time":429.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":428.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Everybody''s in the weekend right now.","index":107,"end_time":431.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":429.8,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Yeah, totally understand.","index":108,"end_time":433.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":431.48,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"All right, well, Hendrick, have an awesome weekend.","index":109,"end_time":436.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":433.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, you too.","index":110,"end_time":437.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":436.93,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"All right, bye.","index":111,"end_time":440.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":437.73,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"},{"text":"Sa.","index":112,"end_time":615.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":615.48,"speaker_name":"Hendrik Pollex"}],"dateString":"2025-12-12T15:30:00.000Z","host_email":"pollex@data-assessment.com","meeting_link":"https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_MTY4Y2VhYTctNmNjYS00NTk2LTg4MTAtYzllMWY5NGQyYWY4@thread.v2/0?context={\"Tid\":