    'fireflies',
    '01KBQFDB6NASPGZSS3CPZ61A36',
    'Data Assessment // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
    '{"Axel Völker","Eli Bebinger","Colin Costigan","Joachim Giesen"}'::text[],
    1588,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86344108572?pwd=qdakcUFJbrjywReJlBZ3DxNLrBYqXb.1',
    '{"id":"01KBQFDB6NASPGZSS3CPZ61A36","title":"Data Assessment // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Lead Generation and Campaign Performance**\n\nThe team identified that while the LinkedIn campaign generated **176 connection requests** and achieved a **19% acceptance rate with 34 accepted** (03:29), the conversion to meaningful leads remains low with only **three demo requests** to date, none progressing to sales.  \n- **Colin Costigan** highlighted the campaign’s strong **11,000 impressions and 62 clicks**, outperforming the industry average click-through rate at **0.56% versus 0.44%** (07:13).  \n- Despite promising ad engagement, Eli Bebinger noted delays in follow-up responses, pointing to a lag between lead form submissions and team outreach as a key conversion bottleneck (02:52).  \n- The team agreed that faster, more personalized email follow-ups using softer language about interest in the platform could increase engagement, with Eli adjusting messaging accordingly (08:13).  \n- To support conversions, Colin plans to develop a **leave-behind document or guide** tailored for consulting companies to explain platform benefits and provide a reference point for prospects after initial contact (09:45).  \n\n## **Market Focus and Regional Strategy**\n\nThe group decided to **shift primary marketing efforts to the German-speaking market** due to stronger brand recognition, easier time zone alignment, and richer existing contact lists (10:38).  \n- Axel Völker emphasized the resource strain caused by parental and sick leaves, and the challenge of covering **14 time zones** between Japan, the US, and Germany, making a focused regional approach more viable (12:17).  \n- Colin confirmed that prior research covers European markets, including Germany, enabling a swift pivot by translating ads and content with local adaptation (14:03).  \n- The team expects this shift to improve conversion rates by targeting warmer leads and leveraging success stories and podcast guests already lined up in Germany (11:58, 19:38).  \n- Axel will provide a list of existing German contacts and faded leads from CRM, enabling tailored campaigns for re-engagement and tapping into closed-lost accounts with different messaging (16:54).  \n\n## **Sales Process and Resource Constraints**\n\nThe team recognized the need for more extensive touch points, with Colin noting modern buyers require **15 to 20 touches** and make up to **80% of their decision before contact** (22:55).  \n- Eli committed to following up on all leads multiple times to maintain engagement, despite some unclear or stalled responses (23:32).  \n- Joachim Giesen flagged time zone challenges during demos and sales calls, highlighting the need for extended sales coverage or adjusted expectations around scheduling (23:43).  \n- Resource shortages due to leaves and limited availability were cited as a major bottleneck limiting the ability to sustain US market efforts and follow through on leads (12:24, 22:27).  \n\n## **Content Production and Marketing Assets**\n\nThe video content planned to showcase platform features required rework due to technical issues; Axel reported videos had poor resolution and were unusable (24:37).  \n- Colin is meeting with Hendrik to clarify recording needs, aiming to create flexible, animated videos where responses can be controlled and customized, including beta AI features (24:50).  \n- The team agreed to proceed with podcast production focused on the German market to leverage easier scheduling and richer guest availability, with Axel or local team members potentially hosting (19:40).  \n- Translation and captioning of all content will be handled collaboratively, with Colin’s team leading and Axel’s team reviewing for accuracy (20:02).  \n\n## **Campaign Timing and Budget Management**\n\nRecognizing the impact of the holiday season on campaign effectiveness, Colin proposed pausing LinkedIn ads during this period to conserve budget and refocus efforts after content and market shifts (19:12).  \n- Axel supported the pause, agreeing that a temporary halt would prevent wasted spend and improve efficiency once new German-focused content is ready (19:33).  \n- Eli suggested experimenting with limited-time discounts or promotions to incentivize form completions during the holidays, pending internal approval (15:55).  \n- Colin emphasized focusing budget on one market—either US or Germany—to avoid diluted efforts and maximize ROI (15:09).  \n\n## **Next Steps and Collaboration**\n\nThe team agreed on concrete next steps:  \n- Colin will build the German contact list, rewrite and translate campaign content, and provide materials for review by Axel’s team (16:54).  \n- Eli will continue lead follow-up using updated messaging and explore incentives to boost demo requests (08:13, 15:55).  \n- Content production for videos and podcasts will proceed with Hendrik and podcast guests, focusing on the German market first (24:42, 19:40).  \n- Axel will onboard additional internal resources to reduce bottlenecks and improve responsiveness in sales and marketing (20:20).  \n- All agreed to pause US LinkedIn campaigns during the holidays and revisit strategy and budget allocation at the start of next year (19:12).","outline":null,"keywords":["LinkedIn Ads","Lead Generation","German Market","Marketing Strategy","Resource Constraints","Video Production"],"overview":"- **LinkedIn Campaign Performance:** Achieved 176 connection requests but only 3 demo requests, indicating low conversion rates.  \n- **Regional Focus Shift:** Marketing efforts will focus on German-speaking markets due to easier engagement and existing contacts.  \n- **Sales Touchpoints Needed:** Modern buyers require 15-20 touches before decision-making; follow-ups must be consistent and multiple.  \n- **Content Production Issues:** Technical problems in video content require rework; flexible animated videos will be prioritized for platform features.  \n- **Budget Management Strategy:** Recommendations to halt LinkedIn ads during holidays to conserve budget; focus on either US or Germany market.  \n- **Next Steps Identified:** Action items include building German contact lists and updating campaign content and messaging accordingly.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nPrepare and deliver updated LinkedIn ad metrics slide deck for review (02:26)\nStart building German market campaign list and rewrite marketing content for German audience (16:54)\nMeet with Hendrik to review and improve video recordings for tool feature demonstrations (24:36)\nDevelop supportive documents/checklists for consulting companies to improve lead conversion and follow-up automation (09:28)\nPause US LinkedIn ad campaign during holiday season to save budget (18:48)\nReview feedback and comments on Eli and David podcast episode and coordinate recording (24:21)\nAnalyze closed lost CRM accounts for targeted re-engagement campaigns (16:39)\nCoordinate transcript translation for German market marketing materials and share for approval (16:54)\n\n**Eli Bebinger**\nFollow up with leads Bhavesh, Carlos Testillo, and Ganesh immediately (06:22)\nAdjust follow-up email language to a softer tone focusing on expressed interest, not form submission (08:00)\nExplore possibility of offering promotional discounts to US leads as gentle engagement during holiday season (15:55)\nContinue to follow-up regularly with existing leads and new form submitters (22:46)\nSend calendar invite for follow-up meeting on Monday (26:18)\n\n**Axel Völker**\nProvide lists of contacts and email addresses for semi-warm and closed lost accounts for marketing use (17:29)\nInclude additional team members to support German campaign execution (18:10)\nFacilitate translation of ads and marketing materials for German market (16:54)\nInvestigate and coordinate podcast hosting and guest invitations in Germany (19:38)\nCommunicate specific reasons for lost deals to aid content tailoring (16:39)\nWork with Hendrik and Colin to produce higher quality video recordings (24:50)\n\n**Joachim Giesen**\nProvide input on resource constraints during sales and demo phases affected by time zones (23:43)\n"},"duration":26.459999084472656,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Axel Völker"},{"id":1,"name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"id":2,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":3,"name":"Joachim Giesen"}],"sentences":[{"text":"It.","index":0,"end_time":0.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.24,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Hey, what''s up, Colin?","index":1,"end_time":36.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":34.97,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"How''s it going, Eli?","index":2,"end_time":37.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":36.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":3,"end_time":38.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":37.93,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yourself?","index":4,"end_time":38.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":38.33,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Doing all right.","index":5,"end_time":40.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":39.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s Friday.","index":6,"end_time":41.929,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":41.21,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"There we go.","index":7,"end_time":43.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":43.21,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"What''s going on this weekend?","index":8,"end_time":45.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":44.49,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I think.","index":9,"end_time":48.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":47.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think my mom''s coming over to babysit and I actually might get out to.","index":10,"end_time":53.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":49.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To eat without a baby with my wife.","index":11,"end_time":55.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":53.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":12,"end_time":56.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":55.95,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"It''s a rare commodity.","index":13,"end_time":59.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":58.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Happy for you.","index":14,"end_time":60.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":59.87,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":15,"end_time":61.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":60.83,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"How about you?","index":16,"end_time":62.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":61.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any plans?","index":17,"end_time":63.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":62.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nothing really.","index":18,"end_time":65.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":64.11,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Maybe going to go on a little road trip and spend the night in this smaller town tomorrow and then.","index":19,"end_time":73.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":65.23,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":20,"end_time":74.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":74.51,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Nice shooting it.","index":21,"end_time":78.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":76.91,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":22,"end_time":79.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":78.96,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yep.","index":23,"end_time":79.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":79.36,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"It said.","index":24,"end_time":81.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":81.28,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Oh, nice.","index":25,"end_time":82.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":82.16,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I had.","index":26,"end_time":83.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":82.8,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":27,"end_time":88.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":88.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hello.","index":28,"end_time":90.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":90.32,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Great.","index":29,"end_time":91.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":90.8,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So it''s not too cold weekend coming up, so.","index":30,"end_time":95.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":91.36,"speaker_name":"Joachim Giesen"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m jealous.","index":31,"end_time":97.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":96.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s very cold.","index":32,"end_time":99.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":98.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, Axel.","index":33,"end_time":100.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":99.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi.","index":34,"end_time":101.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":100.56,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":35,"end_time":102.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":101.04,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Well.","index":36,"end_time":102.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":102.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How about you?","index":37,"end_time":103.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":102.48,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Busy.","index":38,"end_time":104.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":104,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Very busy.","index":39,"end_time":105.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":104.52,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Still dealing with a lot of sick leaves.","index":40,"end_time":109.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":106.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sick leaf and all kinds of leaves, Parental leaves and customer projects and a lot of stuff.","index":41,"end_time":119.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":109.75,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":42,"end_time":120.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":119.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":43,"end_time":122.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":121.75,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So what is that with this ad that failed?","index":44,"end_time":127.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":123.75,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I forwarded you this mail.","index":45,"end_time":129.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":127.59,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we got that email too.","index":46,"end_time":131.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":129.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s already back up and running.","index":47,"end_time":133.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":132.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was a LinkedIn automation sweep that just disabled it.","index":48,"end_time":137.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":133.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There was no actual reason that it got disabled, so it''s back on already.","index":49,"end_time":141.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":137.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":50,"end_time":142.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":141.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And how''s it going?","index":51,"end_time":144.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":143.59,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Was that.","index":52,"end_time":145.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":144.71,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think the ads are performing well.","index":53,"end_time":147.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":146.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have the metrics in our slide deck today that we''ll go through.","index":54,"end_time":151.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":147.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, we.","index":55,"end_time":152.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":151.99,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So far we only got like three.","index":56,"end_time":154.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":152.47,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":57,"end_time":155.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":155.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have three.","index":58,"end_time":156.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":155.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And they failed to.","index":59,"end_time":159.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":158.47,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s kind of strange.","index":60,"end_time":160.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":159.51,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"What.","index":61,"end_time":160.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":160.55,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"How do we follow up?","index":62,"end_time":162.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":161.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Because we could.","index":63,"end_time":162.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":162.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We didn''t get anywhere with them, it looks like.","index":64,"end_time":165.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":162.95,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":65,"end_time":166.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":166.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I have a few questions there and then a few ideas as well.","index":66,"end_time":169.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":166.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":67,"end_time":171.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":171.26,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":68,"end_time":172.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":171.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I definitely want to think that we need to do something instantaneously.","index":69,"end_time":177.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":172.22,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Right.","index":70,"end_time":178.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":177.98,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I think that.","index":71,"end_time":179.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":179.1,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"What if I were to request any sort of information?","index":72,"end_time":183.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":179.7,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"It''s pretty likely that I''m going to check my email right after.","index":73,"end_time":187.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":184.78,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"No.","index":74,"end_time":188.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":188.06,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So I think that we''re having a little.","index":75,"end_time":192.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":191.67,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Maybe.","index":76,"end_time":193.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":192.87,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I mean, maybe not the only thing, but potentially there''s too much lag between when they''re submitting the form and when I''m like receiving the information that they submitted the form and stuff.","index":77,"end_time":204.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":193.35,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":78,"end_time":205.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":205.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s kind of tied into one of the ideas that I had.","index":79,"end_time":207.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":205.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":80,"end_time":209.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":209.03,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So just looking at the metrics of outreach.","index":81,"end_time":213.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":209.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So with this new campaign, we sent out 176 connection requests, 34 of which have been accepted, which is just over 19%.","index":82,"end_time":220.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":213.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve sent 34 messages in, four have replied.","index":83,"end_time":224.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":221.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have a few interesting ones noted down here.","index":84,"end_time":227.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":224.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Eli.","index":85,"end_time":228.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":228.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It looks like for Bavesh, he was Saying the platform is pretty interesting, and I think that that would be a good person to follow up with.","index":86,"end_time":236.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":228.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":87,"end_time":237.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":236.85,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You''re not following up with all of them.","index":88,"end_time":239.289,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":237.73,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I thought you follow up with all of them.","index":89,"end_time":240.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":239.289,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m following up with all of them.","index":90,"end_time":241.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":240.49,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":91,"end_time":242.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":241.65,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Let me see.","index":92,"end_time":243.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":242.29,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"What was his name?","index":93,"end_time":247.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":246.05,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"There was a Ganesh and a Bavesh.","index":94,"end_time":251.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":250.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is Bhavesh.","index":95,"end_time":253.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":252.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I can even just pull up real quick.","index":96,"end_time":257.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":254.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not seeing Bevers right now.","index":97,"end_time":265.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":263.66,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, here we go.","index":98,"end_time":284.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":283.27,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I have Bhavesh open here.","index":99,"end_time":289.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":288.39,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s a good one to follow up with.","index":100,"end_time":291.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":289.75,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"When did he.","index":101,"end_time":293.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":292.95,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But then he.","index":102,"end_time":295.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":294.79,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Then he started to try to sell me something.","index":103,"end_time":297.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":295.43,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"He said, we also offer custom data collection services, including workforce Data Skill Mapping to better insights and market charting.","index":104,"end_time":304.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":297.75,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"This helps platforms like your strengthen your positioning and work with cleaner, more accurate data sets.","index":105,"end_time":310.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":305.04,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"That''s when I kind of.","index":106,"end_time":312,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":310.88,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I was a little confused by your.","index":107,"end_time":313.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":312.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Response because he said, hi.","index":108,"end_time":316,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":313.68,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"He said.","index":109,"end_time":316.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":316,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"He called me Ibrahim.","index":110,"end_time":317.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":316.6,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Your platform was very impressive.","index":111,"end_time":319.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":317.76,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Ibrahim.","index":112,"end_time":319.759,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":319.12,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"And I said Ibrahim.","index":113,"end_time":321.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":320.4,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"And then, like, I kind of said that as I was thinking, like, all right, he''s trying to sell me something and he''s calling me Ibrahim.","index":114,"end_time":328.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":322.72,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"This might be a dead end.","index":115,"end_time":330,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":328.72,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I don''t see where.","index":116,"end_time":334.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":333.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He said.","index":117,"end_time":335.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":334.53,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"He said your platform looks very impressive.","index":118,"end_time":338.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":336.33,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Comma.","index":119,"end_time":339.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":338.65,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Ibrahim.","index":120,"end_time":339.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":339.01,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Oh, got it.","index":121,"end_time":341.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":340.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":122,"end_time":343.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":342.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we know more about XBITE Group?","index":123,"end_time":346.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":344.25,"speaker_name":"Joachim Giesen"},{"text":"Yeah, they look like they kind of build websites and apps and stuff like that for people.","index":124,"end_time":352.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":347.69,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So.","index":125,"end_time":353.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":353.05,"speaker_name":"Joachim Giesen"},{"text":"So could potentially could.","index":126,"end_time":355.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":353.53,"speaker_name":"Joachim Giesen"},{"text":"It could be interesting.","index":127,"end_time":357.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":356.34,"speaker_name":"Joachim Giesen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":128,"end_time":357.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":357.46,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I''ll still try to set up a call with him.","index":129,"end_time":359.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":357.86,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Right.","index":130,"end_time":359.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":359.7,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Which shouldn''t be too hard to do because I could just kind of say that I''m potentially interested in their services as well.","index":131,"end_time":368.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":359.9,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"And we''ll get it scheduled pretty quick.","index":132,"end_time":371.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":368.7,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Okay.","index":133,"end_time":376.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":375.38,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Right.","index":134,"end_time":376.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":376.42,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"What else do we have, red?","index":135,"end_time":382.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":380.34,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Carlos.","index":136,"end_time":383.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":382.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":137,"end_time":388.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":388.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And this person said.","index":138,"end_time":389.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":388.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this was a wrong title match.","index":139,"end_time":392.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":390.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, Eli, I would follow up and ask who his organization we should be in touch with for sure.","index":140,"end_time":398.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":392.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Carlos Testillo.","index":141,"end_time":400.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":399.34,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Okay, I''ll do that right now.","index":142,"end_time":401.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":400.46,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":143,"end_time":401.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":401.26,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, the last one was Ganesh.","index":144,"end_time":404.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":402.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":145,"end_time":416.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":416.55,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So he had responded and then it looks like it just kind of fell off.","index":146,"end_time":420.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":416.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I was kind of confused by his response there as well, but I think I''ll still follow up with him.","index":147,"end_time":430.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":425.35,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I will.","index":148,"end_time":433.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":432.63,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":149,"end_time":433.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":433.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Carlos and Dinesh.","index":150,"end_time":434.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":433.99,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":151,"end_time":435.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":434.95,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"On the email side, we''ve sent out 719.","index":152,"end_time":442.902,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":440.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"430, which.","index":153,"end_time":444.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":443.078,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"430.","index":154,"end_time":445.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":444.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One of which have been opened.","index":155,"end_time":446.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":445.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The only responses have been out of office.","index":156,"end_time":448.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":446.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As we''re in that season right now.","index":157,"end_time":450.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":448.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On the ad side of things.","index":158,"end_time":453.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":452.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"11,000 impressions with 62 clicks.","index":159,"end_time":456.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":453.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We are above the Industry standard click through rate, which is 0.44.","index":160,"end_time":461.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":456.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re at 0.56.","index":161,"end_time":462.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":461.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''re also hovering at a pretty low cost per click, which is great to see.","index":162,"end_time":466.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":462.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Means that we''re getting great depth into our audience at a, at a controlled cost.","index":163,"end_time":472.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":466.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ve seen a few leads come through and actually I saw your comment that it looks like this is a much better targeting on the, on the ads.","index":164,"end_time":479.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":472.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, but still we''re not getting anywhere with the leads.","index":165,"end_time":483.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":480.65,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":166,"end_time":484.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":484.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so I wanted to talk about that.","index":167,"end_time":486.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":484.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, Eli, can you tell me a little bit about, like, what the email that you''re sending is?","index":168,"end_time":490.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":486.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The follow up email?","index":169,"end_time":491.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":490.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I can read them too.","index":170,"end_time":493.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":492.02,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, that would be great.","index":171,"end_time":494.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":493.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, for example, there is Bradley and I said, hi, Bradley, thank you for taking the time to request more information about Desi dalo via our LinkedIn ad.","index":172,"end_time":513.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":498.58,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I would be happy to answer any questions you may have and introduce you to the capabilities of our powerful software.","index":173,"end_time":519.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":513.7,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Are you available Thursday?","index":174,"end_time":522.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":520.83,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"And then what do you think about that?","index":175,"end_time":525.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":524.19,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So I would take a different approach.","index":176,"end_time":528.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":526.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What I would recommend is instead of directly saying like, hey, you filled out our LinkedIn ad.","index":177,"end_time":533.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":528.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I would say, hey, I saw that you expressed interest in our platform.","index":178,"end_time":536.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":533.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Desi Dalo wanted to see if there''s anything specifically that was interesting to you and we could hop on a call and go through that, something like that.","index":179,"end_time":543.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":536.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I had some where I went with that approach as well, but then I was a little bit concerned that maybe they wouldn''t have the name recognition.","index":180,"end_time":552.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":543.79,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So I wanted to remind them about the LinkedIn ad.","index":181,"end_time":556.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":552.66,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, either way, they''re filling out a form, so I would just, I think it''s a lesser violation of privacy to say, like, you expressed interest.","index":182,"end_time":567.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":558.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool, yeah, I''ll go for that approach.","index":183,"end_time":572.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":568.34,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"And then I send the follow up.","index":184,"end_time":574.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":572.58,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"You''re just kind of saying like, I want to follow up on your demo request and my previous message to see if you have any availability next week to learn more about the Desi Dollo platform.","index":185,"end_time":584.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":574.14,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that''s good.","index":186,"end_time":586.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":585.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The other thing to keep in mind here is that we are approaching holiday season and people are kind of just not thinking about work as much.","index":187,"end_time":594.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":587.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But one other piece I was thinking here, Axel, is I''m meeting with Hendrik later to go through the video recording so that we can get that produced.","index":188,"end_time":603.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":595.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But one other thing I think would be valuable is a document, whether that is a guide for these consulting companies and how they can benefit from a Desi Dollo type platform or a checklist of Sorts.","index":189,"end_time":618.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":605.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you have all these resources or tools available to you?","index":190,"end_time":622.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":619.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Some sort of calculator, something.","index":191,"end_time":626.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":624.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think a document would do best because it gives them sort of a leave behind to go to their team with.","index":192,"end_time":631.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":626.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":193,"end_time":635.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":634.59,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":194,"end_time":638.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":638.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I so we.","index":195,"end_time":640.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":639.31,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We are.","index":196,"end_time":640.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":640.31,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We are basically doing a lot of like planning for the next year and how we want to position and it is.","index":197,"end_time":653.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":641.63,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So one thing that.","index":198,"end_time":657.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":654.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That we''re considering is could we do all the same stuff that we''re doing just for the German market?","index":199,"end_time":664.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":658.3,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Because honestly we.","index":200,"end_time":666.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":664.94,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It would be much easier for us to go after after leads and contacts there.","index":201,"end_time":672.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":666.86,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We have much more references.","index":202,"end_time":674.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":672.78,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We just did two interviews for success stories with our customers.","index":203,"end_time":677.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":674.06,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They''re super happy and.","index":204,"end_time":680.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":677.98,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And recommending us and.","index":205,"end_time":682.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":680.62,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But that we have actually that would do podcasts.","index":206,"end_time":686.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":682.42,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We have a lot of people that we could invite to podcast.","index":207,"end_time":690.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":686.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We don''t.","index":208,"end_time":690.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":690.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We.","index":209,"end_time":691.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":690.71,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We have.","index":210,"end_time":691.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":691.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We are struggling to get two for.","index":211,"end_time":693.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":691.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"For English and all of this would be so much easier.","index":212,"end_time":701.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":693.59,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Just the time zone would make it so much easier that we are wondering if you should basically do the same thing which is for the German market.","index":213,"end_time":711.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":701.71,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We can translate it for you.","index":214,"end_time":712.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":711.18,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I would actually even think we get higher conversions or higher rates because we.","index":215,"end_time":718.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":713.34,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Have some name recognition.","index":216,"end_time":721.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":718.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have a name recognition already and.","index":217,"end_time":724.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":721.26,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And I think we''re just leaving.","index":218,"end_time":726.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":724.7,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s kind of.","index":219,"end_time":728.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":727.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We''re going after.","index":220,"end_time":729.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":728.26,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It sometimes feels we''re going after like the highest hanging fruit and not first, not below, starting with the low hanging fruits.","index":221,"end_time":737.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":729.34,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I don''t think your intention was ever to neglect the German market with going after the US Market.","index":222,"end_time":743.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":737.58,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Right.","index":223,"end_time":743.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":743.46,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So I don''t know.","index":224,"end_time":744.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":743.82,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"But we''re doing it.","index":225,"end_time":745.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":744.98,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"The problem is we have limited resources.","index":226,"end_time":748.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":745.94,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"The problem at the moment is so many people on parental leave, on sick leave and we have so little resources that we really need to prioritize.","index":227,"end_time":757.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":748.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And the other thing that makes it harder at the moment is we have our largest customer now is in Japan that they plan a roll out in April.","index":228,"end_time":768.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":757.46,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They are eight hours ahead of us and you are six hours after us.","index":229,"end_time":775.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":769.41,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That is like 14 time zones we have to cover not working with at the moment and so.","index":230,"end_time":787.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":775.97,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And we would have much more people to work with you honestly if you do it in Germany.","index":231,"end_time":793.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":790.46,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Because I''m really a bottleneck at the moment.","index":232,"end_time":796.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":793.66,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You have for a lot of things you have to talk to me because I''m the only one who is somewhat familiar with U S market and but if we do it for Germany it would be.","index":233,"end_time":805.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":796.46,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Actually a lot of things will be much easier for us.","index":234,"end_time":807.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":805.86,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We could do Germany.","index":235,"end_time":808.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":807.86,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So the German speaking market so I wonder, is there anything, is there anything that would not work?","index":236,"end_time":816.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":808.98,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think there was this one tool.","index":237,"end_time":817.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":816.63,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They said they''re not serving Europe for GDPR stuff, but I''m not even sure if you''re using that.","index":238,"end_time":821.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":817.71,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, that would be, that is RB2B but we would still be able to get account level de anonymization at a GDPRP compliance through factors.","index":239,"end_time":835.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":823.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":240,"end_time":837.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":836.63,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Otherwise I think we can just translate the ads basically.","index":241,"end_time":842.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":839.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, we can do.","index":242,"end_time":844.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":843.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":243,"end_time":845.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":845.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean we''ve already conducted all the research because that''s what we were planning originally in our roadmap that we rolled out was including all of the European markets as well as the U.S. and then we had the budgeting conversation.","index":244,"end_time":856.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":845.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was to focus on the U.S. so if we want to switch to Germany, I mean we have the research in place so probably want to rewrite some of the content to be a little bit more focused.","index":245,"end_time":865.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":856.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Even that is easier for us because we just have more people that, that, that could do it.","index":246,"end_time":870.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":866.05,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And we have like a pretty long list of like semi warm contacts that we have already talked to at one point and so it''s not all completely cold.","index":247,"end_time":884.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":870.92,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":248,"end_time":885,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":884.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And there''s clothes lost as well that we could tap into.","index":249,"end_time":887.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":885,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":250,"end_time":888.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":887.8,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think it would also be helpful to like see what we''re going to do post.","index":251,"end_time":893.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":888.52,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"You know, let''s say someone fills out that form in Germany.","index":252,"end_time":896.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":893.96,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"How do we convert them into a customer and you know, try to mimic that process in the United States and stuff like that.","index":253,"end_time":904.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":897.33,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Because maybe there are some things that we need to iron out in that process.","index":254,"end_time":906.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":904.09,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":255,"end_time":908.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":908.05,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Well, what I will say is with the budget we would want to focus on one region.","index":256,"end_time":912.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":909.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''d be US or Germany.","index":257,"end_time":914.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":912.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that we don''t limit.","index":258,"end_time":916.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":914.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We don''t, we won''t, we don''t want to stay like flat.","index":259,"end_time":918.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":916.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We want to get some.","index":260,"end_time":920.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":919.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, we should market.","index":261,"end_time":921.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":920.05,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You should.","index":262,"end_time":921.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":921.37,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We shouldn''t do both in parallel.","index":263,"end_time":922.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":921.69,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That would, that would be just too much and I would just switch this to Germany and I think a lot of things will be easier and easier for me for sure.","index":264,"end_time":933.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":922.85,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And probably even higher rates I would assume.","index":265,"end_time":936.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":933.8,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":266,"end_time":938.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":937.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can start working on the content there.","index":267,"end_time":942.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":939.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Eli, to your point of the follow up, what we can do is develop especially if we go with like a document that they fill out the form and download or something like that.","index":268,"end_time":950,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":942.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s much easier to create an automation follow up.","index":269,"end_time":953.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":950,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That would come from your email.","index":270,"end_time":954.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":953.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":271,"end_time":954.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":954.42,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Also what do you think about they mentioned at the holiday season and stuff.","index":272,"end_time":959.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":955.86,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"What if I was maybe not too promotional or too spammy But I could also try to reach out with like a discount to people who fill out the form.","index":273,"end_time":972.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":960.26,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Say, like, thanks for filling out this form and inquiring more about the CDalo.","index":274,"end_time":976.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":972.98,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"After reviewing your firm''s name, I''m excited to be able to offer you some sort of promotion.","index":275,"end_time":986.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":977.48,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I think that would do well, but that''s obviously up to your team, if that''s something that''s possible.","index":276,"end_time":993.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":988.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, you can try it in the US because why not?","index":277,"end_time":997.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":994.2,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right, and then so we''ll build a list and then we''ll also go into your CRM and look at the closed lost and see what we can do there.","index":278,"end_time":1009.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":999.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":279,"end_time":1009.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1009.46,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So what do you need from us to make the switch?","index":280,"end_time":1013.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1010.34,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So what we''ll do is we''ll start building a list.","index":281,"end_time":1016.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1014.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll rewrite some of the content and send that over to you to make sure translation is accurate.","index":282,"end_time":1023.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1017.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''ll tap into the list out of your CRM for closed lost.","index":283,"end_time":1030.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1024.819,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''ll probably be somewhat different content because there''s much more name recognition there.","index":284,"end_time":1034.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1030.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Probably more of like, is the.","index":285,"end_time":1037.299,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1035.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is now the time to implement this?","index":286,"end_time":1040.819,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1037.299,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I might need some information from you on just reasons that those deals were lost specifically that we can tap into.","index":287,"end_time":1047.539,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1041.699,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just.","index":288,"end_time":1049.299,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1048.899,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have a long list of that are not close loss that are just not never.","index":289,"end_time":1054.019,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1049.459,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, they''re just kind of like faded away.","index":290,"end_time":1057.379,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1055.459,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, faded away, basically.","index":291,"end_time":1059.619,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1057.379,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":292,"end_time":1060.499,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1060.019,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we can give you probably a list of accounts, maybe even people.","index":293,"end_time":1066.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1062.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So it''s a bit harder.","index":294,"end_time":1067.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1066.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You cannot just buy the email addresses here, but we have a list of email addresses that we can just mail to because we already have them and I guess maybe.","index":295,"end_time":1076.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1067.39,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I don''t know, probably some.","index":296,"end_time":1077.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1076.11,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think LinkedIn is probably a good starting point.","index":297,"end_time":1080.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1077.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":298,"end_time":1080.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1080.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This Haywitch stuff that also works and should work the same way, correct?","index":299,"end_time":1086.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1080.83,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s anywhere.","index":300,"end_time":1087.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1086.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, that sounds good.","index":301,"end_time":1092.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1088.26,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Let me know what I need.","index":302,"end_time":1093.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1092.5,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''ll include some other person then from here and then let''s switch that because it''s really hard to sustain this overall, these time zones.","index":303,"end_time":1107.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1093.78,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I hear you.","index":304,"end_time":1111.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1110.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":305,"end_time":1112.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1111.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, we''ll start putting all that together then.","index":306,"end_time":1113.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1112.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That sounds good.","index":307,"end_time":1117.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1116.53,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":308,"end_time":1118.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1117.73,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I did want to see if there is a way that we could get any notifications from people signing up on the registration page.","index":309,"end_time":1124.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1118.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just checked.","index":310,"end_time":1128.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1128.13,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"There''s no new registrations from.","index":311,"end_time":1130.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1128.89,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"There''s.","index":312,"end_time":1131.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1130.53,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"There''s actually somebody from Germany, so that.","index":313,"end_time":1134.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1131.01,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You mean for the two registrations?","index":314,"end_time":1136.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1134.53,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I just checked.","index":315,"end_time":1138.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1136.29,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I haven''t checked when it has last been updated, but it should be up to date and there''s no.","index":316,"end_time":1144.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1138.45,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"No new.","index":317,"end_time":1145.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1144.73,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"None coming from the campaign, at least.","index":318,"end_time":1148.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1146.53,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":319,"end_time":1149.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1148.85,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And then I also wanted to just consider pausing for.","index":320,"end_time":1155.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1152.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That should be 1231, not 1 31.","index":321,"end_time":1159.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1156.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Pausing the campaign on LinkedIn for a week.","index":322,"end_time":1164.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1162.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, especially if we''re switching over and rewriting ads, but just during the holiday season.","index":323,"end_time":1169.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1164.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not going to see a lot of performance and I think better to just save the spend.","index":324,"end_time":1172.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1169.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, makes sense.","index":325,"end_time":1174.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1173.45,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Makes sense.","index":326,"end_time":1175.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1174.57,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":327,"end_time":1177.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1176.81,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Okay, so we''ll podcast.","index":328,"end_time":1180.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1178.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I would probably also do in Germany because that''s easier also for us.","index":329,"end_time":1184.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1180.17,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I probably could even be the host or someone here could be the host and we would just have much more people that we could interview.","index":330,"end_time":1192.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1185.29,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":331,"end_time":1193.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1192.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Again, we''ll just need to confirm like translations and everything as we work through all the captions and things like that.","index":332,"end_time":1201.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1195.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, just send it over.","index":333,"end_time":1203.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1202.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s fine.","index":334,"end_time":1204.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1203.39,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And the way that we set up the podcast, anyone can be the host.","index":335,"end_time":1209.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1206.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":336,"end_time":1210.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1209.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, if you send us over, hey, this person''s interested in joining as a guest.","index":337,"end_time":1215.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1211.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can do the research and develop a framework.","index":338,"end_time":1218.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1215.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Same as we did for Eli and David.","index":339,"end_time":1219.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1218.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, Because David sent me his comments and I was not able to look at them yet because I was completely booked out.","index":340,"end_time":1227.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1220.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And as I figured out, this is not working.","index":341,"end_time":1230.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1228.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I need to hand this over to someone else.","index":342,"end_time":1232.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1230.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But then we probably need to run it here.","index":343,"end_time":1236.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1233.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":344,"end_time":1237.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1237.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, no, we can absolutely do that.","index":345,"end_time":1239.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1237.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Maybe we can.","index":346,"end_time":1241.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1240.19,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Could you potentially consider revisiting the budget a little bit, Axel, so that we are able to maybe do something?","index":347,"end_time":1249.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1243.07,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Because I do feel like we''re making some progress in the United States and, you know, we''re getting some lead.","index":348,"end_time":1257.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1249.79,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"You know, I think it would be kind of a shame to just stop it entirely.","index":349,"end_time":1261.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1257.43,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"And also so many new contacts on LinkedIn that potentially would engage with some content relevant to them.","index":350,"end_time":1272.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1262.45,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, once we have that, we can translate it.","index":351,"end_time":1275.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1273.41,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But anyway, we need to.","index":352,"end_time":1279.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1276.53,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, it would still follow up on the contacts that you have and we need to translate marketing or we need to create marketing materials then also.","index":353,"end_time":1288.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1279.89,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But we just don''t have the resources at the moment to support like multiple geographies.","index":354,"end_time":1296.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1289.33,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And there is maybe other options that you could do.","index":355,"end_time":1301.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1297.86,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So I did like a Google Gemini study and what they recommended is use something like marketplaces from SAP or Microsoft or whatever, Salesforce to put your.","index":356,"end_time":1316.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1301.22,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And we have actually add ins for.","index":357,"end_time":1318.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1316.82,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"For them to put.","index":358,"end_time":1321.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1319.31,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Put us there so that you may get some traffic.","index":359,"end_time":1325.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1321.47,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But I think the active one, the marketing, I would.","index":360,"end_time":1328.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1325.87,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I would first of all see how that works in Germany.","index":361,"end_time":1331.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1328.75,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And then once we figure it out there and we maybe have some more time and hopefully it''s getting better on the resources next year.","index":362,"end_time":1336.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1331.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Because right now it''s really bad.","index":363,"end_time":1337.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1336.63,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"There''s so many people away and we''re really exhausting the whole organization going like this.","index":364,"end_time":1346.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1337.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that makes sense.","index":365,"end_time":1349.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1347.84,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I do think that we.","index":366,"end_time":1350.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1349.36,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that totally makes sense what you''re saying.","index":367,"end_time":1354.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1352.32,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"But I also do think that like three, four, three people filling out the forms to sign up for a demo of Desi Dollo is not.","index":368,"end_time":1363.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1354.36,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Nothing like that''s close to being really good.","index":369,"end_time":1366.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1363.04,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":370,"end_time":1366.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1366.56,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But then nothing came from it.","index":371,"end_time":1368.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1366.96,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s.","index":372,"end_time":1368.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1368.36,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s the problem.","index":373,"end_time":1369.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1368.6,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So that''s another challenge.","index":374,"end_time":1370.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1369.28,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They.","index":375,"end_time":1371.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1370.92,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s really hard to follow up and be.","index":376,"end_time":1374.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1371.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And that''s.","index":377,"end_time":1376.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1375.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s a big piece of.","index":378,"end_time":1379.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1377.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of what we''re seeing, you know, kind of almost industry agnostic is the amount of touch points has just increased dramatically over the past few years.","index":379,"end_time":1387.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1379.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, where someone expressed interest and maybe you had to send them one email, you know, a few years ago, and they would sign up.","index":380,"end_time":1393.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1388.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re looking at more like 15 to 20 touch points and people need to make almost like 75 to 80% of their decision before they even talk to you.","index":381,"end_time":1401.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1393.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s where.","index":382,"end_time":1403.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1402.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s where I lean into having more resources to follow up with so that we can stay back of mind with them as the opportunity comes up.","index":383,"end_time":1410.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1403.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, totally.","index":384,"end_time":1412.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1410.44,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":385,"end_time":1412.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1412.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I wouldn''t write off those people by any means.","index":386,"end_time":1415,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1412.72,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I just followed up with one of them was this morning was the second touch, and some of the other ones were yesterday.","index":387,"end_time":1421,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1415,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So I definitely.","index":388,"end_time":1423.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1423.08,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"The real resource limitation will then also be in the sales phase and the demo phase.","index":389,"end_time":1428.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1423.88,"speaker_name":"Joachim Giesen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":390,"end_time":1429.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1429.24,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"That is really when the time zone difference starts to matter because.","index":391,"end_time":1436.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1430.66,"speaker_name":"Joachim Giesen"},{"text":"Then we''re.","index":392,"end_time":1439.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1439.3,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Lacking the people who would be willing to stay that long or.","index":393,"end_time":1443.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1439.86,"speaker_name":"Joachim Giesen"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":394,"end_time":1446.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1444.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":395,"end_time":1446.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1446.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, even in the United States we have several different time zones.","index":396,"end_time":1449.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1446.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":397,"end_time":1449.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1449.46,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right.","index":398,"end_time":1452.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1452.1,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":399,"end_time":1453.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1452.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So put it in the chat what you need from us and then we work on that and then I include someone.","index":400,"end_time":1460.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1453.46,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":401,"end_time":1462.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1461.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are we still planning to record the Eli and David episode I have to show?","index":402,"end_time":1467.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1463.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we could do that.","index":403,"end_time":1469.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1467.95,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yes.","index":404,"end_time":1469.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1469.15,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But I have not have to look at David''s comments.","index":405,"end_time":1472.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1469.51,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m trying to do that now, but I think we should do that.","index":406,"end_time":1474.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1472.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Why not?","index":407,"end_time":1475.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1474.59,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I think it would be great.","index":408,"end_time":1476.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1475.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I agree.","index":409,"end_time":1477.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1476.99,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":410,"end_time":1478.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1477.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then have you Axel reviewed the videos that Hendrik recorded already?","index":411,"end_time":1481.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1478.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":412,"end_time":1482.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1482.12,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, but I told him to redo them because they could not really read anything on them.","index":413,"end_time":1486.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1482.48,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They were so small, the resolution was somewhere wrong.","index":414,"end_time":1490.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1486.48,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":415,"end_time":1491.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1490.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''m meeting with him in about an hour.","index":416,"end_time":1495.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1492.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it was not.","index":417,"end_time":1496.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1495.56,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think he was not super clear on what exactly you need and what for, because I understand you create some.","index":418,"end_time":1502.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1496.4,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s not like a demo.","index":419,"end_time":1504.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1502.76,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s more.","index":420,"end_time":1505.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1504.64,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Some more integrated into something.","index":421,"end_time":1506.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1505.04,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So I think he wanted to check what exactly you need and if you.","index":422,"end_time":1509.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1507.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, we just wanted to highlight different features of the tool and we just needed the screen recording so that we can reanimate it.","index":423,"end_time":1514.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1509.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":424,"end_time":1516.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1515.87,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":425,"end_time":1517.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1517.31,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And talk to him and see.","index":426,"end_time":1519.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1517.87,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":427,"end_time":1519.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1519.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I talked to him afterwards.","index":428,"end_time":1520.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1519.83,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And the cool thing there is we''ll be able to control.","index":429,"end_time":1522.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1520.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if you.","index":430,"end_time":1523.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1523.069,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For example, I know that the.","index":431,"end_time":1525.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1523.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The AI agent is in beta, so if you wanted to switch the response and say, like, it should say this.","index":432,"end_time":1531.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1525.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can obviously animate it to say anything.","index":433,"end_time":1533.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1531.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we can do that also.","index":434,"end_time":1534.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1533.47,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that''s.","index":435,"end_time":1536.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1534.67,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You can hack that, I guess.","index":436,"end_time":1538.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1537.31,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we can control that one for sure.","index":437,"end_time":1541.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1539.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":438,"end_time":1543.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1542.43,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right, well, that is everything from our end.","index":439,"end_time":1545.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1543.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So our action items then will be to start putting together this campaign for the German market.","index":440,"end_time":1549.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1545.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I''ll be meeting with Hendrik, and hopefully we can get all of those videos recorded, and then we''ll start the production of those, and I''ll start thinking through more documents that we can produce to add into our lead gen form ads on LinkedIn.","index":441,"end_time":1568.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1550.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":442,"end_time":1570.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1569.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":443,"end_time":1571.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1571.02,"speaker_name":"Joachim Giesen"},{"text":"All right.","index":444,"end_time":1572.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1571.9,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":445,"end_time":1573.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1573.26,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Thanks, Dan.","index":446,"end_time":1574.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1573.98,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We made on Monday.","index":447,"end_time":1575.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1574.78,"speaker_name":"Joachim Giesen"},{"text":"Yeah, that''d be perfect.","index":448,"end_time":1577.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1576.3,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Great.","index":449,"end_time":1577.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1577.42,"speaker_name":"Joachim Giesen"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":450,"end_time":1578.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1577.82,"speaker_name":"Joachim Giesen"},{"text":"I''ll send over an invite.","index":451,"end_time":1579.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1578.46,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":452,"end_time":1580.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1579.66,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, thank you all.","index":453,"end_time":1581.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1580.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, bye.","index":454,"end_time":1582.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1581.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":455,"end_time":1582.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1582.26,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"}],"dateString":"2025-12-12T14:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86344108572?pwd=qdakcUFJbrjywReJlBZ3DxNLrBYqXb.1","participants":["tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,joachim.giesen@uni-jena.de,guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,voelker@data-assessment.com,bebinger@decidalo.com,osbaldeston@data-assessment.com,pollex@data-assessment.com","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","joachim.giesen@uni-jena.de","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","voelker@data-assessment.com","bebinger@decidalo.com","osbaldeston@data-assessment.com","pollex@data-assessment.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KBQFDB6NASPGZSS3CPZ61A36","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.88,"bullets":["Agreed to shift campaign focus from U.S. to German market to align with team availability.","Colin to rewrite and localize content assets for German outreach and CRMs with Axel''s review.","Axel noted limited resources due to sick and parental leaves, reinforcing need to prioritize focus.","Team aligned on pausing U.S. LinkedIn spending during holidays to reallocate resources efficiently.","Planned to continue German-language podcast and video content production for improved engagement."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I would just switch this to Germany and I think a lot of things will be easier.","speaker":"Axel Völker"},{"quote":"Our action items then will be to start putting together this campaign for the German market.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"I also do think that like three people filling out the forms... is not nothing.","speaker":"Eli Bebinger"}],"topics":["targeting","delivery","campaign","follow-up","resources"],"model":"openai/gpt-4","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-12T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Lead Generation and Campaign Performance**\n\nThe team identified that while the LinkedIn campaign generated **176 connection requests** and achieved a **19% acceptance rate with 34 accepted** (03:29), the conversion to meaningful leads remains low with only **three demo requests** to date, none progressing to sales.  \n- **Colin Costigan** highlighted the campaign’s strong **11,000 impressions and 62 clicks**, outperforming the industry average click-through rate at **0.56% versus 0.44%** (07:13).  \n- Despite promising ad engagement, Eli Bebinger noted delays in follow-up responses, pointing to a lag between lead form submissions and team outreach as a key conversion bottleneck (02:52).  \n- The team agreed that faster, more personalized email follow-ups using softer language about interest in the platform could increase engagement, with Eli adjusting messaging accordingly (08:13).  \n- To support conversions, Colin plans to develop a **leave-behind document or guide** tailored for consulting companies to explain platform benefits and provide a reference point for prospects after initial contact (09:45).  \n\n## **Market Focus and Regional Strategy**\n\nThe group decided to **shift primary marketing efforts to the German-speaking market** due to stronger brand recognition, easier time zone alignment, and richer existing contact lists (10:38).  \n- Axel Völker emphasized the resource strain caused by parental and sick leaves, and the challenge of covering **14 time zones** between Japan, the US, and Germany, making a focused regional approach more viable (12:17).  \n- Colin confirmed that prior research covers European markets, including Germany, enabling a swift pivot by translating ads and content with local adaptation (14:03).  \n- The team expects this shift to improve conversion rates by targeting warmer leads and leveraging success stories and podcast guests already lined up in Germany (11:58, 19:38).  \n- Axel will provide a list of existing German contacts and faded leads from CRM, enabling tailored campaigns for re-engagement and tapping into closed-lost accounts with different messaging (16:54).  \n\n## **Sales Process and Resource Constraints**\n\nThe team recognized the need for more extensive touch points, with Colin noting modern buyers require **15 to 20 touches** and make up to **80% of their decision before contact** (22:55).  \n- Eli committed to following up on all leads multiple times to maintain engagement, despite some unclear or stalled responses (23:32).  \n- Joachim Giesen flagged time zone challenges during demos and sales calls, highlighting the need for extended sales coverage or adjusted expectations around scheduling (23:43).  \n- Resource shortages due to leaves and limited availability were cited as a major bottleneck limiting the ability to sustain US market efforts and follow through on leads (12:24, 22:27).  \n\n## **Content Production and Marketing Assets**\n\nThe video content planned to showcase platform features required rework due to technical issues; Axel reported videos had poor resolution and were unusable (24:37).  \n- Colin is meeting with Hendrik to clarify recording needs, aiming to create flexible, animated videos where responses can be controlled and customized, including beta AI features (24:50).  \n- The team agreed to proceed with podcast production focused on the German market to leverage easier scheduling and richer guest availability, with Axel or local team members potentially hosting (19:40).  \n- Translation and captioning of all content will be handled collaboratively, with Colin’s team leading and Axel’s team reviewing for accuracy (20:02).  \n\n## **Campaign Timing and Budget Management**\n\nRecognizing the impact of the holiday season on campaign effectiveness, Colin proposed pausing LinkedIn ads during this period to conserve budget and refocus efforts after content and market shifts (19:12).  \n- Axel supported the pause, agreeing that a temporary halt would prevent wasted spend and improve efficiency once new German-focused content is ready (19:33).  \n- Eli suggested experimenting with limited-time discounts or promotions to incentivize form completions during the holidays, pending internal approval (15:55).  \n- Colin emphasized focusing budget on one market—either US or Germany—to avoid diluted efforts and maximize ROI (15:09).  \n\n## **Next Steps and Collaboration**\n\nThe team agreed on concrete next steps:  \n- Colin will build the German contact list, rewrite and translate campaign content, and provide materials for review by Axel’s team (16:54).  \n- Eli will continue lead follow-up using updated messaging and explore incentives to boost demo requests (08:13, 15:55).  \n- Content production for videos and podcasts will proceed with Hendrik and podcast guests, focusing on the German market first (24:42, 19:40).  \n- Axel will onboard additional internal resources to reduce bottlenecks and improve responsiveness in sales and marketing (20:20).  \n- All agreed to pause US LinkedIn campaigns during the holidays and revisit strategy and budget allocation at the start of next year (19:12).","outline":null,"keywords":["LinkedIn Ads","Lead Generation","German Market","Marketing Strategy","Resource Constraints","Video Production"],"overview":"- **LinkedIn Campaign Performance:** Achieved 176 connection requests but only 3 demo requests, indicating low conversion rates.  \n- **Regional Focus Shift:** Marketing efforts will focus on German-speaking markets due to easier engagement and existing contacts.  \n- **Sales Touchpoints Needed:** Modern buyers require 15-20 touches before decision-making; follow-ups must be consistent and multiple.  \n- **Content Production Issues:** Technical problems in video content require rework; flexible animated videos will be prioritized for platform features.  \n- **Budget Management Strategy:** Recommendations to halt LinkedIn ads during holidays to conserve budget; focus on either US or Germany market.  \n- **Next Steps Identified:** Action items include building German contact lists and updating campaign content and messaging accordingly.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nPrepare and deliver updated LinkedIn ad metrics slide deck for review (02:26)\nStart building German market campaign list and rewrite marketing content for German audience (16:54)\nMeet with Hendrik to review and improve video recordings for tool feature demonstrations (24:36)\nDevelop supportive documents/checklists for consulting companies to improve lead conversion and follow-up automation (09:28)\nPause US LinkedIn ad campaign during holiday season to save budget (18:48)\nReview feedback and comments on Eli and David podcast episode and coordinate recording (24:21)\nAnalyze closed lost CRM accounts for targeted re-engagement campaigns (16:39)\nCoordinate transcript translation for German market marketing materials and share for approval (16:54)\n\n**Eli Bebinger**\nFollow up with leads Bhavesh, Carlos Testillo, and Ganesh immediately (06:22)\nAdjust follow-up email language to a softer tone focusing on expressed interest, not form submission (08:00)\nExplore possibility of offering promotional discounts to US leads as gentle engagement during holiday season (15:55)\nContinue to follow-up regularly with existing leads and new form submitters (22:46)\nSend calendar invite for follow-up meeting on Monday (26:18)\n\n**Axel Völker**\nProvide lists of contacts and email addresses for semi-warm and closed lost accounts for marketing use (17:29)\nInclude additional team members to support German campaign execution (18:10)\nFacilitate translation of ads and marketing materials for German market (16:54)\nInvestigate and coordinate podcast hosting and guest invitations in Germany (19:38)\nCommunicate specific reasons for lost deals to aid content tailoring (16:39)\nWork with Hendrik and Colin to produce higher quality video recordings (24:50)\n\n**Joachim Giesen**\nProvide input on resource constraints during sales and demo phases affected by time zones (23:43)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"7869383e-8864-4799-8b1f-599d409e7770","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
    '2025-12-12 15:01:20.069087+00',
