-- Meeting: PTO Exchange // New North Weekly Meeting (2025-12-11 18:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '3f032f15-833e-4d7d-9347-381febf6d953',
    '2025-12-11 18:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KBNH14XVQ9BQPD3QHC0T352M',
    'PTO Exchange // New North Weekly Meeting',
    '{"Colin Costigan","Josh Reinhard","Sam Lieberman","Colin Costigan","Nina Belina"}'::text[],
    1396,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/87477024015?pwd=gVpnKPDuNsoZ0giaFoA7gicVcI6afV.1',
    '{"id":"01KBNH14XVQ9BQPD3QHC0T352M","title":"PTO Exchange // New North Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Website Content and Page Updates**\n\nThe team has made key content and layout updates to improve the website’s clarity and user experience ahead of planned launches.\n\n- **Pages were updated based on feedback, including FAQ revisions and switching a testimonial to a benchmark report** to better highlight performance data (01:11)\n    - The background was changed to white to create a full-width clean look, fixing previous layout issues\n    - Nina confirmed the testimonial swap, and Colin proposed using “Acme” as a standard placeholder company name\n    - Industry-specific pages, including healthcare, financial services, nonprofit, manufacturing, professional services, and higher education, are currently being written to support sections on the homepage\n    - These pages’ launch timing will determine whether certain sections remain hidden temporarily to avoid user confusion\n\n- **Integration page was simplified by removing images from the Implementation Works timeline** due to HubSpot CMS limitations, improving layout flexibility (03:31)\n    - Sam suggested changing headers to better reflect employee communications and onboarding rather than just integrations, which Colin agreed to update quickly\n    - The team plans to replace “Workday” mentions with a broader set of integrations to appeal to diverse customer needs\n\n- **Pricing page layout and text are still being refined, with updated versions to be shared for review soon** (06:04)\n    - The team is aligning messaging and design to improve clarity and encourage conversions\n\n## **Lead Routing and Automation Enhancements**\n\nLead management and outreach automation were optimized to increase responsiveness and integrate new team members smoothly.\n\n- **Automation was updated to assign HubSpot tasks the next business day instead of three days across all states, speeding lead follow-up** (06:29)\n    - The **Calendly popup was added to the benchmark report page** to prompt immediate scheduling after form completion, enhancing conversion opportunities\n    - Josh outlined a phased plan for Calendly links: initially combining his and Steph’s calendars for availability, then eventually transferring full scheduling ownership to Steph within months (07:26)\n    - Colin will verify and update the active Calendly links to match this plan\n\n- **Smart Lead and Heyreach automation is live for LinkedIn and email outreach with personalized messages replacing generic templates** (08:49)\n    - Connection requests are limited to around **20 per day** to avoid LinkedIn profile blacklisting, working through thousands of leads gradually\n    - Email campaigns consist of **four emails spaced four to five days apart**, running independently of LinkedIn outreach timing\n    - Josh plans to add a short email sequence triggered after LinkedIn connection acceptance to increase engagement, which will run alongside existing campaigns without removing contacts from automation (11:24)\n    - Colin will check if HubSpot API supports detecting email replies to automatically pause sequences, as LinkedIn message replies currently do\n\n- **Lead data enrichment and workflow rely on Clay, which aggregates info like company size, revenue, industry, and contacts to feed Smart Lead and Heyreach** (15:37)\n    - Colin highlighted Clay’s flexibility and cost advantage over ZoomInfo, combining multiple enrichment sources into one list\n    - Workflow updates add detailed notes to contact records and assign ownership based on LinkedIn profile acceptance, improving sales team visibility (14:30)\n\n## **Performance Metrics and Traffic Insights**\n\nRecent data shows positive trends in lead quality and website engagement, supporting ongoing content and outreach efforts.\n\n- **LinkedIn lead generation is delivering a low cost per lead and cost per click, indicating effective targeting of decision-makers** such as Directors of Payroll and Global Talent Executives at large companies (20:58)\n    - Website traffic increased by **12% week over week**, signaling growing interest and validating current marketing efforts\n    - The team expects the upcoming launch of industry-specific pages to drive significant organic traffic and further improve key metrics (21:52)\n\n## **Team Onboarding and Knowledge Transfer**\n\nThe team is preparing for a smooth transition of responsibilities to new members while maintaining current workflow continuity.\n\n- **Steph was introduced as the newest team member and will gradually take over LinkedIn outreach scheduling after joint calendar setup is confirmed** (00:33)\n    - Josh emphasized not overwhelming Steph during onboarding, with plans to transfer scheduling duties once joint Calendly functionality is verified by Sam\n    - Colin will share the N8N automation workflow code with Steph for review and updates, enabling her to contribute technically (22:26)\n\n- **Josh committed to recording a session reviewing the redesigned presentation deck to help the content team better understand sales perspectives** (20:19)\n    - This recording will assist the design and writing teams in aligning messaging with sales needs and improve future deck iterations\n\n## **Strategic Planning and Year-End Initiatives**\n\nThe team is aligning on upcoming strategic reviews and content projects to prepare for the new year.\n\n- **Plans are underway to book a strategic planning meeting between late December and early January to discuss performance and goals** (18:14)\n    - Josh and Sam confirmed availability outside major holiday dates, ensuring leadership engagement\n    - Colin is organizing scheduling to accommodate team calendars and maximize participation\n\n- **An end-of-year podcast compilation video is being produced to highlight 2025 benefit shifts, aiming to boost brand engagement and content marketing impact** (17:57)\n    - This project will repurpose existing episode snippets to create a concise, compelling wrap-up for stakeholders and audiences\n\n## **Process Improvements and Quality Assurance**\n\nOperational tweaks and process fixes were made to improve data accuracy and workflow reliability.\n\n- **Automation was corrected to handle variations in Washington, D.C. naming conventions, ensuring leads are assigned properly** (18:49)\n    - This fix addresses previous inconsistencies in lead routing caused by location formatting\n    - Colin confirmed ongoing monitoring and adjustment to maintain data integrity\n\n- **The team agreed to send Josh a document with all FAQ updates for review and markup, streamlining feedback and revision cycles** (05:42)\n    - Josh will track changes to ensure clarity and completeness before final publication\n    - This structured review reduces errors and accelerates page readiness for launch","outline":null,"keywords":["LinkedIn Automation","Website Updates","Lead Routing","Clay Enrichment","Calendly Integration","Strategic Planning"],"overview":"- **Website Updates:** FAQ revisions, layout changes for clarity, and new industry-specific pages in development for homepage support.  \n- **Lead Management Automation:** Next-day HubSpot task assignments and new Calendly popup for immediate scheduling boost conversions.  \n- **Performance Metrics:** 12% week-over-week website traffic increase; LinkedIn targeting shows low cost per lead and effective engagement.  \n- **Team Onboarding:** New member Steph will manage LinkedIn outreach; Josh will provide training via recorded sessions for clarity.  \n- **Strategic Planning:** Strategic meeting planned for late December to discuss goals; end-of-year podcast video in production to enhance brand engagement.  \n- **Process Improvements:** Fixes for lead routing issues and streamlined feedback process for FAQ updates to improve data accuracy.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend updated website pages and FAQ Word document with tracked changes for review (05:42)\nVerify and update calendly links used for benchmark report page and lead routing by region (07:26)\nCheck HubSpot API capabilities for automatically stopping email sequences upon receiving external replies (12:56)\nSend out a scheduling poll for strategic planning meeting targeted for late December or early January (18:34)\nMake agreed text and layout changes to pricing and integration pages, then resend for review (06:29)\nShare N8N automation workflow code with Steph and support any needed updates (22:26)\nFollow up on recording of sales deck presentation by Dave in absence of Josh availability (20:31)\n\n**Josh Reinhard**\nCoordinate with Sam on verifying joint calendly calendar functionality for combined availability scheduling (19:37)\nFacilitate Dave to record presentation deck walkthrough for marketing team (20:34)\n\n**Steph (new team member)**\nReview and potentially update N8N automation workflow coding (22:26)\n\n**Sam Lieberman**\nInvestigate joint calendly calendar options for syncing Josh and Steph availability (19:37)\n"},"duration":23.260000228881836,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"id":2,"name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":4,"name":"Nina Belina"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, guys, long time no see.","index":0,"end_time":28.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":26.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What''s up?","index":1,"end_time":29.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":28.49,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Time to see.","index":2,"end_time":31.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":30.25,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Colin.","index":3,"end_time":33.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":32.73,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"This.","index":4,"end_time":33.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":33.25,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And Nina.","index":5,"end_time":34.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":33.53,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is Steph, the newest member of the team.","index":6,"end_time":37.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":34.29,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I told her I wasn''t totally sure what we were covering today, but it''s good for her to kind of know you guys and just kind of hear a little bit of, like, some of the work that you''re doing for us and all that.","index":7,"end_time":50.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":40.81,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":8,"end_time":51.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":51.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great to meet you, Steph.","index":9,"end_time":53.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":52.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You as well.","index":10,"end_time":54.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":53.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Where are you located?","index":11,"end_time":55.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":54.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Boston.","index":12,"end_time":57.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":56.74,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Oh, nice.","index":13,"end_time":58.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":57.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m in Maryland.","index":14,"end_time":59.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":58.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Nina.","index":15,"end_time":61.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":60.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, hi.","index":16,"end_time":64.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":62.98,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I''m in Zagreb, Croatia, and also the Belgrade office.","index":17,"end_time":68.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":64.1,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"It''s nice to meet you.","index":18,"end_time":69.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":68.82,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":19,"end_time":72.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":71.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, some cool stuff to walk through today.","index":20,"end_time":75.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":73.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll get started.","index":21,"end_time":76.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":76.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, everybody see my screen?","index":22,"end_time":82.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":80.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":23,"end_time":83.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":83.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so we''ve updated the pages based on the feedback that we went through, so these are available for review as well.","index":24,"end_time":94.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":87.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll follow up after this meeting with a link to do that, but we can just walk through them quickly.","index":25,"end_time":100.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":94.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So on this one.","index":26,"end_time":105.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":104.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There wasn''t many changes, but I know that one was updating the FAQ down here, which we''ve gone ahead and done.","index":27,"end_time":114.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":108.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we also switched.","index":28,"end_time":116.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":114.79,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"The upper.","index":29,"end_time":117.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":116.87,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"One of the upper sections was a testimonial and we switched it to a benchmark report.","index":30,"end_time":123.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":117.75,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"That was the one.","index":31,"end_time":125.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":124.55,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":32,"end_time":125.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":125.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Caught.","index":33,"end_time":127.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":127.03,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":34,"end_time":128.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":128.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we''ll swap out these and just put Acme.","index":35,"end_time":133.349,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":129.989,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I feel like that''s the boilerplate company that everyone uses.","index":36,"end_time":137.829,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":134.949,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":37,"end_time":139.189,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":138.229,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":38,"end_time":140.229,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":139.669,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But, yeah, I think these are looking nice and clean.","index":39,"end_time":143.749,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":141.989,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Same as we mentioned, we made the background white so that it looks like it goes full width instead of some of the issues that you guys have run into.","index":40,"end_time":150.309,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":144.708,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":41,"end_time":157.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":157.2,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then this section.","index":42,"end_time":164.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":162.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Depends on the launch timeline of when you guys want to go live with these.","index":43,"end_time":168.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":166,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But next up, we''re going to be writing all of the industry pages.","index":44,"end_time":171.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":168.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if we want to go live with this before those are built out, then we''ll just need to hide this section temporarily.","index":45,"end_time":177.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":171.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I was going to ask about that.","index":46,"end_time":180.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":178.48,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And I think there''s like an HR Leaders section.","index":47,"end_time":185.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":183.06,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Right.","index":48,"end_time":185.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":185.7,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And employees on the homepage.","index":49,"end_time":187.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":185.94,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yes.","index":50,"end_time":190.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":189.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":51,"end_time":191.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":190.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right here.","index":52,"end_time":191.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":191.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, that also needs a page to go with.","index":53,"end_time":196.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":191.82,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":54,"end_time":197.099,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":196.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So these are each a page, and we''re writing those currently.","index":55,"end_time":200.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":197.099,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":56,"end_time":202.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":201.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Looks good.","index":57,"end_time":209.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":208.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, looks great.","index":58,"end_time":210.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":209.47,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All right, then we had the integrations page.","index":59,"end_time":213.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":211.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One of the larger changes here was the.","index":60,"end_time":217.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":214.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How Implementation Works timeline.","index":61,"end_time":221.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":219.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just actually went ahead and removed the images.","index":62,"end_time":223.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":221.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As you guys know, HubSpot, CMS is not the most flexible.","index":63,"end_time":229.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":226.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is the cleanest layout that we could get to.","index":64,"end_time":233.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":231.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, that''s fine.","index":65,"end_time":237.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":234.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you scroll up a Little bit.","index":66,"end_time":243.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":242.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We were going to change out, so it wasn''t just workday.","index":67,"end_time":247.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":244.25,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":68,"end_time":248.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":247.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":69,"end_time":250.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":250.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we got to make that change.","index":70,"end_time":251.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":250.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think I added some comments of.","index":71,"end_time":257.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":255.77,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like.","index":72,"end_time":257.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":257.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What to put in these.","index":73,"end_time":260.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":259.62,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"The title.","index":74,"end_time":263.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":262.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You need a title for that one.","index":75,"end_time":265.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":263.5,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And.","index":76,"end_time":267.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":267.46,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Additional IRS and payroll systems.","index":77,"end_time":272.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":270.58,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I don''t know if I put a title for that.","index":78,"end_time":273.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":272.58,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I like the copy beneath it.","index":79,"end_time":275.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":273.9,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But, like, the.","index":80,"end_time":278.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":275.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The header should be.","index":81,"end_time":279.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":278.5,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":82,"end_time":279.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":279.5,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, customized to fit your business''s needs or something like that.","index":83,"end_time":282.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":279.74,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":84,"end_time":283.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":282.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":85,"end_time":284.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":283.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":86,"end_time":284.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":284.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can make.","index":87,"end_time":285.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":284.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Text changes are very easy to make.","index":88,"end_time":286.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":285.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then that also is about employee communications and onboarding rather than more integrations added regularly.","index":89,"end_time":296.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":287.41,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"All right, no problem.","index":90,"end_time":299.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":298.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just thought it would be better horizontal, but if you have to do the vertical, I think that looks fine.","index":91,"end_time":317.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":311.97,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":92,"end_time":319.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":317.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":93,"end_time":331.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":330.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":94,"end_time":333.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":332.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry for the questions on the integration.","index":95,"end_time":336.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":334.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Do you.","index":96,"end_time":337.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":336.98,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Do you want me to look.","index":97,"end_time":341.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":340.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Look at these to make sure.","index":98,"end_time":342.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":341.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":99,"end_time":342.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":342.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Do you want me to just send you a document with all the FAQs that we wrote out?","index":100,"end_time":346.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":342.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that makes sense.","index":101,"end_time":347.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":346.11,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I''ll just, like, track change, whatever.","index":102,"end_time":349.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":347.67,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, because that system''s integrated, I would change the copy there a little bit.","index":103,"end_time":354.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":349.99,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"That first one.","index":104,"end_time":356.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":355.87,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"No problem.","index":105,"end_time":359.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":359.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Send that.","index":106,"end_time":361.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":361.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then on the pricing page.","index":107,"end_time":366.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":364.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Through.","index":108,"end_time":369.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":368.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":109,"end_time":372.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":371.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we still have some text changes.","index":110,"end_time":373.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":372.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To make, going through the layout changes.","index":111,"end_time":377,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":373.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll get those made, and I''ll send these over to you guys to review in an updated state.","index":112,"end_time":381.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":377.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":113,"end_time":385.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":382.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And like I said, so we''re working.","index":114,"end_time":389.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":388.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On.","index":115,"end_time":390.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":389.72,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"The industry pages, so that is.","index":116,"end_time":395.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":392.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just look at my list.","index":117,"end_time":397.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":396.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Healthcare, financial services, nonprofit manufacturing, professional services, and higher education.","index":118,"end_time":404.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":398.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we would be also writing the HR leader Persona page and the employee Persona page.","index":119,"end_time":410.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":405.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":120,"end_time":414.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":413.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We made the change so that the task that''s assigned in HubSpot when a lead is added is not three business days, but it''s just next business day.","index":121,"end_time":424.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":416.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I made that for all the states.","index":122,"end_time":426.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":424.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we also implemented the calendly pop up on the benchmark report page.","index":123,"end_time":432.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":428,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So after someone fills it out, it immediately pops up with that scheduling option.","index":124,"end_time":435.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":432.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are we doing that now?","index":125,"end_time":439.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":437.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Colin, is it me for the east and Dan for the West?","index":126,"end_time":443.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":439.2,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Nina, can you speak to that?","index":127,"end_time":447.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":446.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I need to check into the exact.","index":128,"end_time":449.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":447.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that''s how I did it.","index":129,"end_time":451.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":450.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I need to check on that and.","index":130,"end_time":454.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":453.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Get back to you.","index":131,"end_time":455.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":454.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":132,"end_time":456.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":455.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we''re going to keep it that way.","index":133,"end_time":458.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":457.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then I''m going to invite Steph to the call from the east.","index":134,"end_time":461.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":458.85,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But, like.","index":135,"end_time":462.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":461.81,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Pretty soon, I don''t know if we''re able to do this.","index":136,"end_time":466.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":464.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Sam was going to look into it, but we were going to see if we could have a calendly link that like combines both me and Steph''s calendars so it would only show availability when we''re both available and then for like some interim period of time and then, and then ultimately like in the next couple months, then it''s just like Steph and it''s all, it''s all to her.","index":137,"end_time":485.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":466.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":138,"end_time":486.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":485.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":139,"end_time":486.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":486.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, that''s good to know.","index":140,"end_time":488.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":487.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, yeah, I''ll check on exactly what link is in there.","index":141,"end_time":491.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":488.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know it was one that was sent over, so.","index":142,"end_time":492.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":491.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I''ll update you on that.","index":143,"end_time":494.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":493.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we also have.","index":144,"end_time":500.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":498.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Smart lead and heyreach.","index":145,"end_time":503.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":502.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so everything is integrated, the automation is live.","index":146,"end_time":506.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":503.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so just to walk through what that means.","index":147,"end_time":509.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":507.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you know, every day between Dan and Josh''s profiles, connections are being sent out to the lead list.","index":148,"end_time":515.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":510,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We removed the messages so that you guys could write personalized ones.","index":149,"end_time":520.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":516.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so now anytime a connection request is accepted or.","index":150,"end_time":525.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":520.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, I guess I should say there is a message sent if you''re already a connection with if you already are connected to that person because otherwise we couldn''t get a signal from it.","index":151,"end_time":535.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":526.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So anytime a connection is sent and accepted, or anytime a message is sent, or anytime a message is received, that all goes through our workflow.","index":152,"end_time":545.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":537.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And to walk through this.","index":153,"end_time":547.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":546.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So all of those connections are sent here, then we understand what happened.","index":154,"end_time":552.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":549.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did they accept the connection request?","index":155,"end_time":554,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":552.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did we send a message?","index":156,"end_time":555,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":554,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or did they receive or did we receive a message?","index":157,"end_time":557.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":555,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then it also maps to whose profile it is.","index":158,"end_time":560.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":557.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So once staff is added into the flow, we''ll need to create a, a break off for her here.","index":159,"end_time":565.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":560.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean she''ll just really just replace me.","index":160,"end_time":569.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":567.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So perfect.","index":161,"end_time":570.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":569.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then that''s, that''s even easier.","index":162,"end_time":573.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":572.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It sets then you or Dan as the contact owner.","index":163,"end_time":581.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":575.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We had to create this fallback because in testing they don''t send through actual data.","index":164,"end_time":584.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":581.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s all John Doe at and so it didn''t have you guys as the sender.","index":165,"end_time":588.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":584.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for testing we had to create this fallback option.","index":166,"end_time":590.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":588.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It then passes through a bunch of JSON code which you guys really don''t care about, but it''s all the information that''s needed.","index":167,"end_time":598.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":592.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then updates it adds a note to the contact record in HubSpot saying.","index":168,"end_time":605.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":599.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A connection request is accepted or here''s what we sent or here''s what they replied.","index":169,"end_time":611.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":606.729,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then it updates their lead source to be the LinkedIn outreach option, same that you created.","index":170,"end_time":617.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":612.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then if it is a message reply Josh, then it''ll check Smart lead and then remove them from the campaign.","index":171,"end_time":626.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":617.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you have like a outline of what the cadence itself looks like.","index":172,"end_time":636.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":631.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like when they''re receiving emails, when they''re receiving LinkedIn connections.","index":173,"end_time":641.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":636.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So it''s not, it''s not as cut and dry as that because on the LinkedIn side we have it configured to limits.","index":174,"end_time":650.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":643.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So and this is so that we don''t like Blacklist, essentially your LinkedIn profile.","index":175,"end_time":656.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":651.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you guys are only able to send around 20 connection requests per day and it''s working through a list of thousands of people.","index":176,"end_time":662.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":656.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s whenever that can go through the flow, if that makes sense.","index":177,"end_time":667.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":662.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then someone could take, they could approve or accept your request right away, they could take 30 days and then the flow kind of has to work through there.","index":178,"end_time":676.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":667.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so how many, I guess the emails are happening regardless of what''s happening on the LinkedIn side.","index":179,"end_time":684.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":677.21,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Correct.","index":180,"end_time":684.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":684.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And how many emails are they getting as part of this outreach?","index":181,"end_time":688.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":685.21,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Each campaign is in a 4 email flow.","index":182,"end_time":691.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":688.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And what''s the spacing on that?","index":183,"end_time":693.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":692.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"There''s typically four or five days between the emails.","index":184,"end_time":698.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":694.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":185,"end_time":699.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":698.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because one of the things that we were talking about and I think we, we want to do on our side is like when someone accepts our, and especially now in light of what you just said, if someone accepts our connection request, like we''ll message them on LinkedIn, but we''re also going to message them, like sending them an email and just say, hey, I just, you know, I noticed that you could accepted my LinkedIn connection.","index":186,"end_time":720.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":699.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Not sure if email is a better mode of communication for you, but want to set up like whatever we can do to like to get them more engaged and get a better chance of us converting them.","index":187,"end_time":731.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":721.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So there will be like addition a couple additional emails that we''re going to create like a short sequence on our side.","index":188,"end_time":739.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":732.16,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Once they accept our LinkedIn request, we''re going to continue to do the stuff in LinkedIn but then also email them too.","index":189,"end_time":744.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":739.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay, so do you want us to remove them when they accept from Smart Lead, which is the email cadence?","index":190,"end_time":748.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":744.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You want us to remove them when they accept your connection request?","index":191,"end_time":751.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":748.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I want them to still go through whatever is.","index":192,"end_time":753.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":751.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is just like additive to that.","index":193,"end_time":756.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":753.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So it might be end up being like seven emails, but if it takes them a long time to accept our request, it''s, it could just be that it''s that it''s a longer time that it''s set up, but it''s also going to be very like low key emails where it''s just like I saw you connected, you know, we just want to schedule some time with you, blah, blah, blah.","index":194,"end_time":775.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":757.29,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Whatever.","index":195,"end_time":775.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":775.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yep.","index":196,"end_time":776.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":775.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":197,"end_time":776.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":776.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We''re only sending them two messages from LinkedIn inside of LinkedIn.","index":198,"end_time":781.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":776.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we''re just trying to get more conversions basically.","index":199,"end_time":786.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":784,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yep.","index":200,"end_time":787.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":786.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":201,"end_time":787.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":787.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if we email them outside of you all''s sequence but they reply back to us and it''s captured in HubSpot, does that stop your sequence?","index":202,"end_time":797.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":788,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It does not.","index":203,"end_time":798.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":797.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can see.","index":204,"end_time":801.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":800.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know if that information passes through HubSpot''s API.","index":205,"end_time":808.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":805.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If an email is received.","index":206,"end_time":809.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":808.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let me check if their API allows that email reply.","index":207,"end_time":816.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":812.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, if they reply to our email.","index":208,"end_time":819.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":816.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":209,"end_time":821.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":821.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll have to check if that comes through HubSpot''s API to see if we can automate that.","index":210,"end_time":826.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":821.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":211,"end_time":836.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":836.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we can see all the successful runs here.","index":212,"end_time":839.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":837.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":213,"end_time":840.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":839.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''S check on.","index":214,"end_time":843.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":841.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This one.","index":215,"end_time":848.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":847.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we had this John Doe test showing.","index":216,"end_time":852.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":849.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I go here.","index":217,"end_time":856.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":855.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this one was Vidal or Vital.","index":218,"end_time":866.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":862.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I did change his name just because the name format for some of them has their certification or degree or something like PHR sometimes.","index":219,"end_time":874.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":866.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":220,"end_time":874.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":874.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or I think he was originally Vidal MBA or something.","index":221,"end_time":878.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":874.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I just changed that.","index":222,"end_time":880.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":878.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But essentially.","index":223,"end_time":880.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":880.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So his contact was created.","index":224,"end_time":882.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":880.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He was assigned to Dan because that''s where the profile, the connection request was accepted.","index":225,"end_time":886.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":882.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A note was added that on Heyreach the LinkedIn connection request was accepted.","index":226,"end_time":891.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":887.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And a task was created for Dan.","index":227,"end_time":895.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":893.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, Vidal has a new note added to their record from heyreach.","index":228,"end_time":900.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":897.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Please review.","index":229,"end_time":900.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":900.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":230,"end_time":902.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":902.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"If there''s anything else you guys want us to put in those tasks, just let me know.","index":231,"end_time":906.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":903.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, so then we, we put him in like a two step sequence on our side that does outreach.","index":232,"end_time":913.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":907.23,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But then separately we''re also going to email.","index":233,"end_time":915.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":913.68,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"The guy.","index":234,"end_time":917.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":917.16,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So.","index":235,"end_time":918.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":917.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":236,"end_time":918.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":918.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So is there anything else that currently you want this automation to do?","index":237,"end_time":923.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":920.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t think so.","index":238,"end_time":926.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":925.4,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I don''t think so.","index":239,"end_time":927.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":926.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Where do you, when you pull the.","index":240,"end_time":929.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":928.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Information, what, what databases and stuff like are you pulling it from?","index":241,"end_time":934.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":929.68,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"What do you mean information?","index":242,"end_time":937.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":935.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like this guy accepts a request, you''re populating HubSpot with like their email address and their job title.","index":243,"end_time":944.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":937.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Where does that come from?","index":244,"end_time":946.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":944.95,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So it''s a bunch of JSON, but it''s basically from when we created the list in clay.","index":245,"end_time":950.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":946.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We captured all that information.","index":246,"end_time":952.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":950.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like company and everything and then we uploaded that to heyreach and then that''s coming through in JSON code.","index":247,"end_time":959.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":953.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we can just basically say like, oh, this is first name, this is last name, where he works, everything like that.","index":248,"end_time":964.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":959.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":249,"end_time":965.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":965.03,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay.","index":250,"end_time":966.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":965.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s.","index":251,"end_time":968.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":967.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was the boring thing that I was passing through with all the.","index":252,"end_time":971.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":968.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s called a note payload.","index":253,"end_time":973.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":972.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s where everything''s getting added.","index":254,"end_time":975.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":973.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But Clay is like a lead enrichment kind of a thing.","index":255,"end_time":978.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":975.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Clay, I always say, is, like, true to its name.","index":256,"end_time":981.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":978.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s moldable to whatever you want it to be.","index":257,"end_time":984.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":982.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Imagine if Excel had Zoom Info directly integrated and Apollo directly integrated and all of those types of things.","index":258,"end_time":991.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":984.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You basically, it''s a massive spreadsheet with almost unlimited enrichments.","index":259,"end_time":996.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":992.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, interesting.","index":260,"end_time":998.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":996.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I can even show real quick.","index":261,"end_time":1002.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1000.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, the contact list that we had.","index":262,"end_time":1004.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1003.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Built out for you guys originally.","index":263,"end_time":1006.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1004.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Clay is a really cool tool.","index":264,"end_time":1008.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1007.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s probably one of my favorites.","index":265,"end_time":1010.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1008.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Especially compared to the cost of a zoom info.","index":266,"end_time":1015.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1013.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, for example, we start by gathering a list of companies that fit into parameters, like revenue ranges, employee counts, locations, industries, whether they''re a public or a private or a nonprofit company, their profile, like on LinkedIn, their company domain, everything like that.","index":267,"end_time":1049.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1032.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we say, okay, cool, I want to talk to all of the.","index":268,"end_time":1053.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1050.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Human resources directors there.","index":269,"end_time":1056.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1054.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we would pull that contact.","index":270,"end_time":1059.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1056.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"List from all of those companies.","index":271,"end_time":1061.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1059.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These are the things that are constantly being funneled into Smart Lead, which is email, and Heyreach, which is the LinkedIn.","index":272,"end_time":1067.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1062.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s cool.","index":273,"end_time":1070.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1069.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so some other things that we''re working on is the end of year compilation video for the podcast.","index":274,"end_time":1082.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1075.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just pulling a bunch of snippets from different episodes and creating kind of end of 2025, the benefit shift highlights.","index":275,"end_time":1092.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1082.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''re also putting together strategic planning.","index":276,"end_time":1096.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1094.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so I wanted to see if you guys are open to booking and meeting either.","index":277,"end_time":1100.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1097,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know what your holiday schedule is as we''re getting near the end of the year, but closer to the end of December, beginning of January, going through performance and goals and everything like that.","index":278,"end_time":1112.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1100.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, not.","index":279,"end_time":1115.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1114.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Not working.","index":280,"end_time":1118.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1117.53,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You know, like the 24th and the 25th and then the 31st and the first.","index":281,"end_time":1123.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1119.85,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But other than that, like, you know, I''m around.","index":282,"end_time":1126.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1123.97,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":283,"end_time":1127.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1126.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, same here.","index":284,"end_time":1129.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1127.94,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":285,"end_time":1130.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1129.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, I''ll send out a savvy cow then.","index":286,"end_time":1131.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1130.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":287,"end_time":1137.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1136.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I think I already covered that.","index":288,"end_time":1140.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1138.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We Washington, D.C. people write that different ways.","index":289,"end_time":1144.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1140.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we fixed the automation to make sure that it captures that and assigns it correctly.","index":290,"end_time":1148.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1144.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''re working through what we just met on about an hour ago for the slide deck.","index":291,"end_time":1154.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1149.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":292,"end_time":1155.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1155.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":293,"end_time":1157.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1155.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":294,"end_time":1158.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1158.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll make those text changes to the pages, and then I''ll send that over to you in markup to review, and then.","index":295,"end_time":1164.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1158.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Writing the new copy as well.","index":296,"end_time":1168.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1166.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And great that Steph''s here, because one of the things on here was kind of establishing the timeline of when we switch things over From Josh to her.","index":297,"end_time":1175.41,"sp