INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: PTO Exchange // New North Weekly Meeting',
  '## **Website Content and Page Updates**

The team has made key content and layout updates to improve the website’s clarity and user experience ahead of planned launches.

- **Pages were updated based on feedback, including FAQ revisions and switching a testimonial to a benchmark report** to better highlight performance data (01:11)
    - The background was changed to white to create a full-width clean look, fixing previous layout issues
    - Nina confirmed the testimonial swap, and Colin proposed using “Acme” as a standard placeholder company name
    - Industry-specific pages, including healthcare, financial services, nonprofit, manufacturing, professional services, and higher education, are currently being written to support sections on the homepage
    - These pages’ launch timing will determine whether certain sections remain hidden temporarily to avoid user confusion

- **Integration page was simplified by removing images from the Implementation Works timeline** due to HubSpot CMS limitations, improving layout flexibility (03:31)
    - Sam suggested changing headers to better reflect employee communications and onboarding rather than just integrations, which Colin agreed to update quickly
    - The team plans to replace “Workday” mentions with a broader set of integrations to appeal to diverse customer needs

- **Pricing page layout and text are still being refined, with updated versions to be shared for review soon** (06:04)
    - The team is aligning messaging and design to improve clarity and encourage conversions

## **Lead Routing and Automation Enhancements**

Lead management and outreach automation were optimized to increase responsiveness and integrate new team members smoothly.

- **Automation was updated to assign HubSpot tasks the next business day instead of three days across all states, speeding lead follow-up** (06:29)
    - The **Calendly popup was added to the benchmark report page** to prompt immediate scheduling after form completion, enhancing conversion opportunities
    - Josh outlined a phased plan for Calendly links: initially combining his and Steph’s calendars for availability, then eventually transferring full scheduling ownership to Steph within months (07:26)
    - Colin will verify and update the active Calendly links to match this plan

- **Smart Lead and Heyreach automation is live for LinkedIn and email outreach with personalized messages replacing generic templates** (08:49)
    - Connection requests are limited to around **20 per day** to avoid LinkedIn profile blacklisting, working through thousands of leads gradually
    - Email campaigns consist of **four emails spaced four to five days apart**, running independently of LinkedIn outreach timing
    - Josh plans to add a short email sequence triggered after LinkedIn connection acceptance to increase engagement, which will run alongside existing campaigns without removing contacts from automation (11:24)
    - Colin will check if HubSpot API supports detecting email replies to automatically pause sequences, as LinkedIn message replies currently do

- **Lead data enrichment and workflow rely on Clay, which aggregates info like company size, revenue, industry, and contacts to feed Smart Lead and Heyreach** (15:37)
    - Colin highlighted Clay’s flexibility and cost advantage over ZoomInfo, combining multiple enrichment sources into one list
    - Workflow updates add detailed notes to contact records and assign ownership based on LinkedIn profile acceptance, improving sales team visibility (14:30)

## **Performance Metrics and Traffic Insights**

Recent data shows positive trends in lead quality and website engagement, supporting ongoing content and outreach efforts.

- **LinkedIn lead generation is delivering a low cost per lead and cost per click, indicating effective targeting of decision-makers** such as Directors of Payroll and Global Talent Executives at large companies (20:58)
    - Website traffic increased by **12% week over week**, signaling growing interest and validating current marketing efforts
    - The team expects the upcoming launch of industry-specific pages to drive significant organic traffic and further improve key metrics (21:52)

## **Team Onboarding and Knowledge Transfer**

The team is preparing for a smooth transition of responsibilities to new members while maintaining current workflow continuity.

- **Steph was introduced as the newest team member and will gradually take over LinkedIn outreach scheduling after joint calendar setup is confirmed** (00:33)
    - Josh emphasized not overwhelming Steph during onboarding, with plans to transfer scheduling duties once joint Calendly functionality is verified by Sam
    - Colin will share the N8N automation workflow code with Steph for review and updates, enabling her to contribute technically (22:26)

- **Josh committed to recording a session reviewing the redesigned presentation deck to help the content team better understand sales perspectives** (20:19)
    - This recording will assist the design and writing teams in aligning messaging with sales needs and improve future deck iterations

## **Strategic Planning and Year-End Initiatives**

The team is aligning on upcoming strategic reviews and content projects to prepare for the new year.

- **Plans are underway to book a strategic planning meeting between late December and early January to discuss performance and goals** (18:14)
    - Josh and Sam confirmed availability outside major holiday dates, ensuring leadership engagement
    - Colin is organizing scheduling to accommodate team calendars and maximize participation

- **An end-of-year podcast compilation video is being produced to highlight 2025 benefit shifts, aiming to boost brand engagement and content marketing impact** (17:57)
    - This project will repurpose existing episode snippets to create a concise, compelling wrap-up for stakeholders and audiences

## **Process Improvements and Quality Assurance**

Operational tweaks and process fixes were made to improve data accuracy and workflow reliability.

- **Automation was corrected to handle variations in Washington, D.C. naming conventions, ensuring leads are assigned properly** (18:49)
    - This fix addresses previous inconsistencies in lead routing caused by location formatting
    - Colin confirmed ongoing monitoring and adjustment to maintain data integrity

- **The team agreed to send Josh a document with all FAQ updates for review and markup, streamlining feedback and revision cycles** (05:42)
    - Josh will track changes to ensure clarity and completeness before final publication
    - This structured review reduces errors and accelerates page readiness for launch',
  '2025-12-11 18:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Send updated website pages and FAQ Word document with tracked changes for review (05:42)","completed":false},{"text":"Verify and update calendly links used for benchmark report page and lead routing by region (07:26)","completed":false},{"text":"Check HubSpot API capabilities for automatically stopping email sequences upon receiving external replies (12:56)","completed":false},{"text":"Send out a scheduling poll for strategic planning meeting targeted for late December or early January (18:34)","completed":false},{"text":"Make agreed text and layout changes to pricing and integration pages, then resend for review (06:29)","completed":false},{"text":"Share N8N automation workflow code with Steph and support any needed updates (22:26)","completed":false},{"text":"Follow up on recording of sales deck presentation by Dave in absence of Josh availability (20:31)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with Sam on verifying joint calendly calendar functionality for combined availability scheduling (19:37)","completed":false},{"text":"Facilitate Dave to record presentation deck walkthrough for marketing team (20:34)","completed":false},{"text":"Review and potentially update N8N automation workflow coding (22:26)","completed":false},{"text":"Investigate joint calendly calendar options for syncing Josh and Steph availability (19:37)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: Colin Costigan and Josh Reinhard (2025-12-11 17:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '3f032f15-833e-4d7d-9347-381febf6d953',
    '2025-12-11 17:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KBNAE3D5X38AJ06ZV5J60DTY',
    'Colin Costigan and Josh Reinhard',
    '{"Colin Costigan","Josh Reinhard","Dave Sherman","Sam Lieberman","Nina Belina"}'::text[],
    1697,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85676425517?pwd=SEHeRPazZ264H905bbb2L03BbJ8aw7.1',
    '{"id":"01KBNAE3D5X38AJ06ZV5J60DTY","title":"Colin Costigan and Josh Reinhard","summary":{"notes":"## **Presentation Redesign and Visual Strategy**\n\nThe team agreed to overhaul the slide deck to reduce text and boost visual appeal for broader audience engagement.\n\n- **Dave Sherman** emphasized moving toward a **more modern, less wordy presentation style** to better hold the audience’s attention (03:08)  \n    - The goal is to shift from educating with many words to sparking interest through visuals.  \n    - Sam Lieberman noted the current deck has too much text and lacks professional design polish, limiting its shareability.  \n    - Colin Costigan suggested creating two versions: one downloadable for self-guided review, another optimized for live presentations with less text.  \n    - This approach aims to ease conversation starters and reduce the need for pre-customizing decks.\n\n- The group discussed replacing the **dark green gradient background and green-on-green text**, which impair readability (04:59)  \n    - Josh Reinhard clarified some slides still use problematic green-on-green fonts, signaling a need for consistent color updates.  \n    - Colin proposed using Microsoft standard fonts to improve compatibility when slides are shared and edited by others (05:38).  \n    - This ensures easy deck adaptation across teams and reduces formatting issues during handoffs.\n\n- There was consensus on enhancing logo presentation by using **white logo versions on darker backgrounds** to improve clarity and branding impact (08:18)  \n    - Colin mentioned the current logo slide feels negative and could be reframed for a more positive, clean look.  \n    - This change supports better first impressions and social proof early in the deck.\n\n## **Content Prioritization and Slide Flow**\n\nThe team aligned on reorganizing content to improve messaging clarity and impact, especially around key proof points.\n\n- They decided to place the **“millions of PTO hours exchanged for hundreds of millions of dollars”** metric as a prominent social proof element on the **title or early slides** (19:52)  \n    - Josh Reinhard explained this metric fits early to hook brokers and partners with real proof of success.  \n    - Colin agreed this sets a strong tone for the presentation and frames credibility immediately.\n\n- Discussion around the **turnover reduction slide** revealed a need for clearer, dedicated focus, as it currently blends into broader content (06:29)  \n    - Dave Sherman suggested emphasizing this slide more due to its strong client impact data from a sample of **35 clients**.  \n    - Josh said the slide could be refined and positioned to better highlight tangible savings linked to reduced employee turnover.\n\n- The team explored a **three-column layout** with images or illustrations to better organize content and visuals (10:26)  \n    - Josh and Colin agreed on balancing illustrations with editable content, so the deck remains flexible for future edits without heavy design support.  \n    - They want a clean, consistent look that avoids clutter and improves audience comprehension.\n\n## **Platform Visualization and User Experience**\n\nThe group debated how best to show the PTO Exchange platform within the deck to balance clarity and engagement.\n\n- Josh Reinhard demonstrated the **current platform UI screenshot highlighting the 7.5% service charge**, which is small and hard to read on laptop screens (12:05)  \n    - Dave Sherman expressed openness to alternatives like a **cash-out option slide** that presents clearer space and simpler math examples.  \n    - They want to maintain focus on **constructive receipt requirements** while improving visual legibility.\n\n- Colin proposed using **animated GIFs** within slides to simulate user interactions with the platform, providing a dynamic preview without a full demo (16:24)  \n    - This would show clicking options and filling out forms to convey simplicity and ease of use in a visually engaging way.  \n    - Dave liked the idea but noted it should not replace slides focused on specific features like constructive receipt.\n\n- The team considered whether to show **exact platform screenshots versus more illustrative diagrams**, weighing familiarity against clarity (14:32)  \n    - Dave and Josh were flexible but noted the deck’s role is to pique interest, with detailed demos reserved for follow-up calls.  \n    - The consensus leans toward simpler visuals in the deck to reduce cognitive load while highlighting key features.\n\n## **Slide Design Details and Animation Preferences**\n\nThey reviewed specific slide elements and animation use to improve clarity without distracting from the content.\n\n- There is a preference to **simplify the form display**, highlighting only the most relevant data like contribution amount, service charge, and total before taxes (22:23)  \n    - Nina Belina suggested a bolded, condensed frame of the form’s key parts to improve number visibility.  \n    - Josh recommended using easy-to-calculate examples like **four hours exchanged equaling $92.50 after service charge** to aid understanding.\n\n- Dave Sherman and Josh Reinhard agreed some details like contribution limits and year-to-date usage remain important to show platform safeguards (24:18)  \n    - They want to balance transparency about limits without overcrowding the slide.\n\n- Colin asked about attitudes toward **slide animations** such as sequential reveals of data points (25:45)  \n    - Dave and Josh were open to simple animations like sliding or fading in content to help guide viewers through complex info.  \n    - Colin prefers static slides for faster presentations but endorses animations for users new to the deck.\n\n- The final approach is to build **template slides with flexible backgrounds and layouts**, allowing easy swapping of logos and content by the team without needing design help (21:45)  \n    - This modularity supports quicker updates and adaptation for different audiences or product lines.\n\n## **Next Steps and Timeline**\n\nThe team set clear expectations to move forward with design iteration and future deck versions.\n\n- Colin committed to delivering a **version 1 draft of the redesigned deck by next week** for review and feedback (27:47)  \n    - This will incorporate all discussed changes around visuals, text reduction, and layout improvements.  \n    - The goal is to finalize a channel-side deck before expanding to a sales-focused version.\n\n- Josh Reinhard acknowledged the need for a **sales-side deck as a follow-up project**, signaling a phased rollout (27:28)  \n    - The current effort prioritizes the channel deck to test messaging and design concepts first.\n\n- The team confirmed no major outstanding questions and expressed readiness to proceed with design work (27:53)  \n    - Dave Sherman and Josh thanked Colin for the collaborative session and looked forward to reviewing the updated materials.","outline":null,"keywords":["PTO Exchange","Slide Deck Design","Turnover Reduction","Platform Screenshot","Service Charge","Presentation Animation"],"overview":"- **Slide Deck Overhaul:** Aim to reduce text and enhance visuals for better audience engagement and shareability.  \n- **Color & Font Changes:** Replace green-on-green text and use standard fonts for improved readability and formatting consistency.  \n- **Logo Presentation:** Shift to white logos on dark backgrounds for clarity and a positive branding impact throughout the presentation.  \n- **Content Organization:** Prioritize key metrics like “millions of PTO hours” early in the deck to establish credibility and hook the audience.  \n- **Visual Simplification:** Use cleaner layouts and animations to reduce clutter and enhance understanding of key information on slides.  \n- **Next Steps:** Draft of redesigned deck to be delivered next week; subsequent focus on creating a sales-side deck after initial review.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nDevelop V1 of redesigned slide deck incorporating discussed visual and textual improvements by next week (27:45)\nCreate slide templates with multiple backgrounds and layouts to enable easy client customization (21:49)\nProvide ideas for improved visual layout of financial wellness options and testimonial placement (19:34)\n\n**Josh Reinhard**\nShare slide demonstrating turnover reduction with logos and data for inclusion in the deck (06:29)\nCoordinate with new hire Steph to evaluate screenshot clarity and options for improvement or alternative illustrations (11:53)\nConsider inclusion of mobile app screenshots or icons to represent technology accessibility in the deck (08:59)\nProvide feedback on redesign options for platform UI slides explaining service charges and constructive receipt (13:40)\n\n**Dave Sherman**\nConfirm content priorities for slide inclusion, especially around turnover reduction and platform explanation (06:29)\nProvide input on presentation and demo sequencing, particularly separating overview deck and detailed platform demos (14:32)\n\n**Nina Belina**\nExplore design options to highlight key form elements with bolded text and reduced space to improve readability on form-related slides (22:23)\n"},"duration":28.290000915527344,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"id":2,"name":"Dave Sherman"},{"id":3,"name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"id":4,"name":"Nina Belina"}],"sentences":[{"text":"How''s it going, everybody?","index":0,"end_time":1.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How you doing?","index":1,"end_time":2.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Doing all right.","index":2,"end_time":3.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice to meet you.","index":3,"end_time":6.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":5.84,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"You''re as well.","index":4,"end_time":7.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":6.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Dave.","index":5,"end_time":7.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":7.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How was everybody''s weekend?","index":6,"end_time":11.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":10.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sam, did you get a long weekend?","index":7,"end_time":13.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":11.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I did.","index":8,"end_time":15.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":14.64,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I went to the Eagles game in Los Angeles.","index":9,"end_time":18.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":15.48,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Nice.","index":10,"end_time":19.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":19.12,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"So, Fi.","index":11,"end_time":20.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":19.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was fun, but tough ball.","index":12,"end_time":24.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":21.6,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":13,"end_time":25.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":24.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well.","index":14,"end_time":27.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":27.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I enjoyed myself.","index":15,"end_time":31.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":30.09,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I enjoyed myself.","index":16,"end_time":32.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":31.37,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Saw fake tush push.","index":17,"end_time":33.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":32.25,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Saw two.","index":18,"end_time":34.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":33.69,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Two turnovers in one play.","index":19,"end_time":36.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":34.57,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"It was a very cool stadium.","index":20,"end_time":43.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":41.93,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And it was, you know, like 75 degrees and sunny both days we were there, so I appreciated it.","index":21,"end_time":48.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":43.17,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Played some golf.","index":22,"end_time":49.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":48.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was nice.","index":23,"end_time":50.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":49.69,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"There you go.","index":24,"end_time":50.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":50.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hopefully you don''t have Jalen on your fantasy team.","index":25,"end_time":53.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":51.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, But I have A.J.","index":26,"end_time":55.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":54.18,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"brown, and I lost by, like three points to make the playoffs.","index":27,"end_time":58.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":55.14,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"So tough all around.","index":28,"end_time":60.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":58.58,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":29,"end_time":61.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":61.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because Jalen got a interception and a fumble.","index":30,"end_time":63.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":61.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Same play.","index":31,"end_time":64.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":64.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"A.J.","index":32,"end_time":65.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":65.14,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"brown dropped.","index":33,"end_time":66.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":65.54,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"A.J.","index":34,"end_time":67.059,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":66.66,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"brown dropped three balls that would have won me the game.","index":35,"end_time":69.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":67.059,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And he couldn''t.","index":36,"end_time":70.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":69.74,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Couldn''t get it done and probably would.","index":37,"end_time":72.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":70.82,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Have not forced overtime.","index":38,"end_time":74.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":72.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":39,"end_time":75.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":74.58,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Probably would have won the Eagles game and my fans.","index":40,"end_time":77.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":75.02,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But.","index":41,"end_time":78.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":78.02,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, I guess he needs to read more books.","index":42,"end_time":80.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":78.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You gotta.","index":43,"end_time":82.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":81.31,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"You gotta fight through the pain, Colin.","index":44,"end_time":84.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":82.43,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I''m sure you''re well aware.","index":45,"end_time":85.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":84.31,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"You know, makes it sweeter.","index":46,"end_time":87.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":85.71,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Makes it sweeter when you win.","index":47,"end_time":88.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":87.31,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":48,"end_time":89.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":89.23,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But then you also have to win, which, you know.","index":49,"end_time":92.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":90.03,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Well, we won last year.","index":50,"end_time":93.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":92.51,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Josh.","index":51,"end_time":93.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":93.63,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"No, no, I''m saying to call it.","index":52,"end_time":95.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":93.95,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, well, the.","index":53,"end_time":98.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":97.95,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"The Redskins are in a tough, tough spot, but maybe one day.","index":54,"end_time":104.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":98.83,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Still got Jaden going to the commander''s game on Sunday with.","index":55,"end_time":109.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":104.15,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"In Jersey, and now it looks like it''s supposed to snow, so that should be interesting.","index":56,"end_time":114.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":110.36,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Who do they play?","index":57,"end_time":115.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":115.16,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"The Giants.","index":58,"end_time":116.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":115.92,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":59,"end_time":117.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":116.84,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":60,"end_time":119.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":118.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Foreign favorites for some reason.","index":61,"end_time":123.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":121.96,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We''ll see what happens.","index":62,"end_time":126.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":125.64,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Do you guys see all the stuff about MetLife Stadium that''s going on?","index":63,"end_time":129.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":127,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":64,"end_time":131.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":131.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Someone, like, ran a statistical analysis of all of the major injuries that have happened there in the past.","index":65,"end_time":136.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":131.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":66,"end_time":138.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":137.57,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"I mean, just ACL after ACL.","index":67,"end_time":140.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":138.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":68,"end_time":141.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":140.93,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"That''s the worst stadium, honestly.","index":69,"end_time":144.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":141.97,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"FedEx Field is pretty bad, too, but.","index":70,"end_time":146.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":144.77,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, Northwest.","index":71,"end_time":147.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":146.849,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":72,"end_time":148.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":147.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"MetLife is one of the worst that I''ve been to as well.","index":73,"end_time":151.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":149.17,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":74,"end_time":152.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":151.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the NFLPA actually introduced standardization for, like, whatever the material is of the field.","index":75,"end_time":158.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":152.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice.","index":76,"end_time":160.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":159.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Are they gonna have to rip it up?","index":77,"end_time":162.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":161.12,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Probably, yeah.","index":78,"end_time":164.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":163.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, it makes sense.","index":79,"end_time":166.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":165.36,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":80,"end_time":167.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":166.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s abysmal.","index":81,"end_time":168.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":167.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Top players are going down.","index":82,"end_time":169.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":168.12,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"It''s just crazy.","index":83,"end_time":170.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":169.48,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":84,"end_time":171.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":170.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Anyway, all right, I''ve distracted us long enough.","index":85,"end_time":174.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":171.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s dive into going through this.","index":86,"end_time":177.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":174.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, Josh, I know we lightly touched on this on Thursday, so I''ve been taking a look, but definitely wanted to get Dave''s insights On everything you guys are looking for here.","index":87,"end_time":186.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":178.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I just.","index":88,"end_time":189.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":188.3,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"For the longest time, I liked lots of words.","index":89,"end_time":192.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":189.9,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"You know, it just kind of wanted to educate my audience, and then recently came to realize I''m not going to educate them.","index":90,"end_time":200.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":192.22,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"With one presentation and seeing lots of other presentations, there''s a lot more space and a lot less words.","index":91,"end_time":207.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":200.42,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"So, I mean, I know what I''m saying on each slide, I don''t need and I don''t read the words.","index":92,"end_time":212.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":207.82,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"So looking to make it more modern and less wordy.","index":93,"end_time":216.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":212.38,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"That''s my goal.","index":94,"end_time":217.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":216.86,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":95,"end_time":219.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":218.54,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Colin, one other thing is I think we also kind of, you know, a lot of this is built around that.","index":96,"end_time":228.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":219.9,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like, we expect people to kind of send around the presentation to other people for them to view.","index":97,"end_time":234.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":228.74,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And I think we get less of that than we probably would like or even have anticipated.","index":98,"end_time":239.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":234.46,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"So we would like it to be a little bit more visually stimulating to add to the presentation.","index":99,"end_time":245.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":239.66,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And there''s just a lot of words and text on this.","index":100,"end_time":250.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":245.89,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And we''ve designed it, I think, as far as our capabilities can go, and we''re hoping for a little bit more professional design work done on it.","index":101,"end_time":259.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":250.05,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":102,"end_time":260.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":260.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And.","index":103,"end_time":261.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":260.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And just one note there, too.","index":104,"end_time":262.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":261.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think.","index":105,"end_time":263.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":262.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we can have multiple versions of this.","index":106,"end_time":266.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":264.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we can have a version on the website that is something, you know, someone can easily access, download, absorb the information themselves without you guys presenting it.","index":107,"end_time":275.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":266.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then that starts a conversation at their firm, they have PTO exchange in the back of their mind, and then they can reach out to you guys.","index":108,"end_time":281.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":275.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But, yeah, totally hear you.","index":109,"end_time":282.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s definitely something we''ve implemented over the past few years, is less words on decks and more actually talking to, you know, the main point.","index":110,"end_time":292.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":283.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It also allows you to easily guide the conversation without customizing a whole bunch of text before a presentation.","index":111,"end_time":296.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":292.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know a few other things, Josh, that you mentioned was maybe even moving away from, like the dark gradient green going on in the background.","index":112,"end_time":305.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":299.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because I know, like, even here as an example, green on green is pretty tough.","index":113,"end_time":310.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":307.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And just to be fair, that''s not a slide we''re actually using.","index":114,"end_time":315.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":311.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But there is places that we do use green on green text.","index":115,"end_time":317.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":315.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But this isn''t an actual.","index":116,"end_time":319.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":317.97,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Slide.","index":117,"end_time":321.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":320.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Again, but, yeah, some of that.","index":118,"end_time":323.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":322.37,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We do have the green on the.","index":119,"end_time":325.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":323.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"On green.","index":120,"end_time":325.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":325.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":121,"end_time":326.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":326.08,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All right.","index":122,"end_time":328.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":328.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Going through.","index":123,"end_time":330.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":330.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And another issue was the decision on what to do with your font.","index":124,"end_time":336,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":332.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":125,"end_time":338.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":338.32,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We have not made any decisions on that.","index":126,"end_time":342,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":339.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":127,"end_time":343.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":342.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one thing that we could do is find a very similar font that does come standard in Microsoft''s package.","index":128,"end_time":353.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":344.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That way, when you pass these over, because you Mentioned that you''re kind of like, passing slides over and they''re plugging it in to their deck occasionally, but.","index":129,"end_time":363.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":355.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Enough that we need to address it.","index":130,"end_time":365.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":363.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yep, gotcha.","index":131,"end_time":367.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":365.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":132,"end_time":369.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":369.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All right.","index":133,"end_time":371.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":371.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And.","index":134,"end_time":374.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":373.82,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Is there any other, like, is there anything in this slide deck that.","index":135,"end_time":379.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":376.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or anything not in this slide deck that you would like included, different products, mockups, or different screenshots of the UI or anything like that?","index":136,"end_time":387.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":380.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, Josh, maybe the reduction in turnover, slide.","index":137,"end_time":395.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":389.74,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Sampling of 35 clients.","index":138,"end_time":399.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":397.66,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"You would want to have a slide dedicated to that.","index":139,"end_time":407.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":405.42,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We can do that.","index":140,"end_time":408.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":407.98,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean, we have one.","index":141,"end_time":409.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":408.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":142,"end_time":411.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":411.11,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"I''m just.","index":143,"end_time":411.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":411.43,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"He''s asking, so I''m just thinking what, you know, we might want to stick in, depending what we''re talking about.","index":144,"end_time":416.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":411.71,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"I''m just gonna dump this into the.","index":145,"end_time":423.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":421.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Slot, the slack.","index":146,"end_time":428.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":426.23,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is a slide.","index":147,"end_time":429.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":428.39,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We''ve used another.","index":148,"end_time":429.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":429.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Another deck.","index":149,"end_time":430.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":430.23,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This one''s specifically for healthcare, just because, like, we change out the logos depending on who.","index":150,"end_time":435.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":430.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Who were meeting with.","index":151,"end_time":440.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":439.12,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But this is just like a study we ran comparing turnover rates for people that made exchanges on our platform, people that didn''t.","index":152,"end_time":451.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":444.32,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And we show the different industries.","index":153,"end_time":455.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":454,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We show.","index":154,"end_time":455.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":455.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then we also show.","index":155,"end_time":456.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":455.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"If.","index":156,"end_time":460.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":460.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If these people.","index":157,"end_time":461.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":460.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"If we can reduce your turnover by this much, and you think of how much it costs to replace an employee, studies show that it''s, like, either six months, up to, like, two or three years of the employee salary.","index":158,"end_time":473.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":461.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We''re just using six months of salary.","index":159,"end_time":475.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":473.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, how much does that save you in replacement cost?","index":160,"end_time":477.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":475.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''s what we''re showing on this slide.","index":161,"end_time":479.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":477.69,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Just that when employees engage with our platform, when they''re using it across all industries, across all sizes of companies, those that use the platform, turnover at a significantly lower rate than the people that don''t make exchanges.","index":162,"end_time":492.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":479.41,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":163,"end_time":495.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":495.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, I''m just absorbing the rest of the information on here.","index":164,"end_time":498.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":495.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, there''s not a lot of words on that page to begin with.","index":165,"end_time":501.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":498.78,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":166,"end_time":502.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":501.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":167,"end_time":504.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":504.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We could even just do, like, white versions of all these logos, nice and clean on the background so we don''t have to have a white background.","index":168,"end_time":510.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":504.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I feel like there''s a different way to illustrate this because it almost.","index":169,"end_time":513.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":511.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s super positive for you guys, but it almost is presented in a negative way.","index":170,"end_time":518.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":514.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, unless you really understand what it''s saying or you''re actually walking them through during your presentation.","index":171,"end_time":524.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":519.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":172,"end_time":529.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":528.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so this is one.","index":173,"end_time":530.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":529.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there anything else that doesn''t exist in the slide that you guys would like added?","index":174,"end_time":533.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":530.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have.","index":175,"end_time":539.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":539.41,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"If you go back to the deck, like, on that first page of the actual title slide.","index":176,"end_time":545.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":540.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we have, you know, a version, like a desktop version of, of PTO Exchange and then the mobile version.","index":177,"end_time":554.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":546.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t know if Dave, at some point in here when we''re talking about.","index":178,"end_time":560.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":556,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Isn''t there somewhere in this?","index":179,"end_time":566.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":565.28,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Or maybe I''m conflating this with another thing where we''re talking about like, oh, it''s on the third slide where we''re talking about technology and accessibility and why it matters to have like a tech forward kind of a benefit because that''s the way that employees are using benefits.","index":180,"end_time":582.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":566.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Do we want to show a screenshot of the mobile app or do we want to show something there?","index":181,"end_time":587.999,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":582.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I know we''re trying to figure out what images could go on this, but would that be.","index":182,"end_time":592.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":587.999,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean, that would make sense.","index":183,"end_time":595.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":593.76,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"That little phone that we have in the beginning that has the app on it mean that would be a good icon there.","index":184,"end_time":600.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":595.04,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"I guess it depends on what, what you''re thinking.","index":185,"end_time":603.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":601.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Colin, if you were going to be doing like.","index":186,"end_time":606.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":603.97,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Illustrations and then, and then having an actual picture of, of the phone doesn''t make as much sense because it doesn''t fit with the other two images that we''re talking about, then we don''t need to do it.","index":187,"end_time":619.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":609.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But that would just be somewhere just to show the actual.","index":188,"end_time":623.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":619.61,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Technology itself.","index":189,"end_time":625.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":625.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":190,"end_time":626.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":626.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And as we were going through this, because I reviewed it between our last call and this call, I even think maybe like a, a three column approach almost kind of like what was going on here, just a little bit different.","index":191,"end_time":638.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":626.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Picturing it in my head is like three like vertical images.","index":192,"end_time":643.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":638.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But I don''t know again if they''re illustrations or, or like what they would be to get those points across.","index":193,"end_time":649.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":643.66,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":194,"end_time":650.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":649.9,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And I don''t think we''ll do all illustrations because we also want this, we want you guys to be able to edit or adapt this to whatever you need very easily without like, hey, Colin or Nina, can you guys make a new image for this presentation?","index":195,"end_time":663.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":650.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Custom.","index":196,"end_time":663.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":663.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":197,"end_time":669.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":668.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we got a lot going on here.","index":198,"end_time":670.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":669.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":199,"end_time":671.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":671.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just don''t even like the way that looks with the different size boxes and just a box in the bottom.","index":200,"end_time":678.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":672.66,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":201,"end_time":679.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":679.06,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"That needs to be cleaned up.","index":202,"end_time":681.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":679.54,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":203,"end_time":681.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":681.39,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then the illustrations in the back just get lost.","index":204,"end_time":684.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":681.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":205,"end_time":687.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":686.51,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We have lots of those client impacts, so it''s not only going to be those four.","index":206,"end_time":696.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":693.07,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Do they all follow this type of style though, when you''re writing them out?","index":207,"end_time":701.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":698.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":208,"end_time":702.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":702.03,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":209,"end_time":703.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":702.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the numbers will change too.","index":210,"end_time":706.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":704.99,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":211,"end_time":707.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":707.11,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then this is kind of blurry.","index":212,"end_time":715.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":713.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there a higher quality screenshot you guys have?","index":213,"end_time":718.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":715.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We could also just try and recreate it.","index":214,"end_time":721.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":719.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We were, I Was actually talking to our newest hire, Steph, about this yesterday, because I always do this.","index":215,"end_time":731.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":725.03,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s full screen on my second monitor and I can see all the stuff totally fine.","index":216,"end_time":737.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":732.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"When it''s like in presentation mode.","index":217,"end_time":739.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":737.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"She was making the point that, like.","index":218,"end_time":743.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":741.28,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"If someone''s looking at it on their laptop screen, it is like almost impossible to make out all of this stuff.","index":219,"end_time":750.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":744.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we''ve always had this on here because it really illustrates what we''re talking about with like the service charge.","index":220,"end_time":757.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":750.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And it gives us an opportunity to explain why the 7 1/2% needs to be there.","index":221,"end_time":760.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":757.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And it''s the actual platform itself.","index":222,"end_time":762.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":760.68,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But, like, if there''s a different way to show that that''s easier to read, maybe we don''t even have to, like, I don''t know, Dave, what do you think?","index":223,"end_time":772.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":762.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Do, like, do we even have to have that?","index":224,"end_time":774.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":772.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s nice to be able to point to it and say, like, as I''m showing in the example here, and you walk through what the math is and what it looks like.","index":225,"end_time":783.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":776.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But maybe there''s a better way to.","index":226,"end_time":785.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":783.67,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Do this and maybe we do a cash out option because then you''re not.","index":227,"end_time":791.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":785.59,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Well, you are still limited to the hours.","index":228,"end_time":793.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":791.28,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":229,"end_time":793.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":793.04,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"It''s.","index":230,"end_time":794.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":793.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s always like when I''m doing the presentation, I''m.","index":231,"end_time":796.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":794.04,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"I always forget that I have to go down to the bottom of the screen for them to see the seven and a half percent, you know, because that''s really what we''re talking about, is the seven and a half percent part.","index":232,"end_time":806.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":796.04,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, that''s what the whole slide is really about is for constructive receipt.","index":233,"end_time":811.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":806.12,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"The employee has to accept that.","index":234,"end_time":813.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":811.8,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"And it''s really small on the bottom.","index":235,"end_time":815.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":813.24,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"So I''m not married to it.","index":236,"end_time":816.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":815.2,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"I mean, a lot of the stuff is just because we''ve done it in the past.","index":237,"end_time":819.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":816.69,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Right, Right.","index":238,"end_time":820.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":819.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s easy to do it now.","index":239,"end_time":822.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":820.21,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"I do like it because that''s what it looks like on when you''re on or they''re in the website and they''re going through, but maybe you can put a page and do a whole screenshot where they could actually see, you know, total balance.","index":240,"end_time":836.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":822.69,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"So this is what it looks like when you''re doing it on our platform.","index":241,"end_time":838.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":836.01,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"And I don''t know.","index":242,"end_time":840.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":838.45,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Yeah, and that''s, that''s kind of what I mean by the question because there''s, there''s two schools of thought.","index":243,"end_time":844.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":841.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One, you can say this is the platform.","index":244,"end_time":846.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":844.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, like, if you do sign up, this is exactly what you will go through.","index":245,"end_time":849.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":846.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The, the, you know, this is what you''ll see.","index":246,"end_time":851.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":850.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then it''s very familiar.","index":247,"end_time":853.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":851.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kind of lowers the barrier for them.","index":248,"end_time":854.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":853.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or we could do a little bit more illustrative where we call out the service, charge a little bit more and we can peel or add anything into this that we want to display.","index":249,"end_time":863.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":854.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I guess that question kind of comes back to you guys.","index":250,"end_time":866.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":864.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we want to show them exactly what the platform is going to look like or more illustrative?","index":251,"end_time":871.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":866.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m okay either way.","index":252,"end_time":873.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":872.49,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Again, I''m just kind of doing it the way that we''ve always done it.","index":253,"end_time":877.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":873.65,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"And maybe they don''t have to see the platform because my goal is if I''m not doing a demo after this with the brokers and partners, I want to get on another call to show them the demo.","index":254,"end_time":886.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":878.17,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Josh, have any thoughts on that?","index":255,"end_time":890.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":888.81,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Colin?","index":256,"end_time":891.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":890.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Can I just share my screen real quick?","index":257,"end_time":892.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":891.37,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":258,"end_time":893.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":892.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you might have to rehit it.","index":259,"end_time":896.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":895.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":260,"end_time":899.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":898.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just so you can see, like, what it looks like.","index":261,"end_time":902.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":900.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So if an employee comes in and wants to make an exchange, let''s just say they''re going to do health savings, because that''s the one that we''re showing.","index":262,"end_time":908.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":902.53,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, this is what it is.","index":263,"end_time":912.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":910.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So if there''s a better way to crop this.","index":264,"end_time":915.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":912.25,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"To make it so it fits on the screen better or on a slide better than great, the way that it''s, like, set.","index":265,"end_time":924.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":917.37,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Obviously there''s like spacing on.","index":266,"end_time":927.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":926.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Does take up a ton of real estate on a slide to get to, like Dave was saying, to get to this part right here is what essentially, like, the whole purpose of it is just to get this piece.","index":267,"end_time":940.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":928.81,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So if there''s a more illustrative way of doing it that doesn''t have the form but still allows us to speak to it.","index":268,"end_time":948.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":940.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And maybe it''s even like.","index":269,"end_time":951.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":949.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like diagramming why that''s important.","index":270,"end_time":962.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":958.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Talking like you, you actually, if you don''t use the form that we have on our website, probably gives us an opportunity to like, kind of describe why it''s happening more so than just like, here it is on the screen.","index":271,"end_time":977.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":962.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":272,"end_time":978.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":978.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can you hit the back button real quick for me?","index":273,"end_time":980.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":979.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s what I was.","index":274,"end_time":981.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":981.23,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":275,"end_time":982.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":981.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Because I think so.","index":276,"end_time":986.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":984.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One thing that we''ve also done recently is add gifs into slide decks.","index":277,"end_time":991.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":986.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I think it could be really cool if we show them, like, look at all of these options and then in the gif, you know, click into one of them and fill out the form.","index":278,"end_time":998.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":991.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, that kind of gives that user experience too.","index":279,"end_time":1001.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":998.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This.","index":280,"end_time":1002.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1002.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"For the website, you''re saying no.","index":281,"end_time":1004.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1002.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"For the slideshow, you can add a GIF into the slideshow so it''s like showing that animation happening.","index":282,"end_time":1009.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1004.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like you load this screen, they click on, you know, the HSA savings, for example, and then fill out the form.","index":283,"end_time":1017.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1009.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like that could be the GIF that''s going on while we''re talking through the slide.","index":284,"end_time":1020.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1017.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m having trouble imagining what it looks like.","index":285,"end_time":1027.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1024.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So it''s just like almost like animation in the slide deck.","index":286,"end_time":1030.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1027.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like making a transaction.","index":287,"end_time":1032.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1030.68,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":288,"end_time":1033.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1033.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So let me pull up another example.","index":289,"end_time":1035.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1033.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This was for a Salesforce client.","index":290,"end_time":1038.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1035.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi, Nina.","index":291,"end_time":1054.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1054.09,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"I didn''t say hello to you earlier.","index":292,"end_time":1055.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1054.53,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Nice.","index":293,"end_time":1058.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1057.69,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Nice to meet you as well.","index":294,"end_time":1060.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1058.97,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":295,"end_time":1072.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1072.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So screen.","index":296,"end_time":1074.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1072.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for example, as we''re going through this, like the client recorded some videos and we turned it into a GIF so that you can see like the actual interaction that''s going on in the platform.","index":297,"end_time":1084.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1075.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think of how we would do that.","index":298,"end_time":1095.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1093.12,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s almost like the actual demo.","index":299,"end_time":1099.519,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1097.36,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"You know, the video of the demo.","index":300,"end_time":1102.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1101.12,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":301,"end_time":1104.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1104,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean it does have to be a pretty small file size.","index":302,"end_time":1106.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1104.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the screen recording would.","index":303,"end_time":1108.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1106.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"My recommendation would literally just be to like hit one of those option buttons on that ptodemo.com page that you had and then it opens up the form and that would just be the whole video.","index":304,"end_time":1115.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1108.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just as like a.","index":305,"end_time":1116.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1115.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A teaser to how easy it is.","index":306,"end_time":1118.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1117.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":307,"end_time":1121.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1120.62,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"But I think that slide is more speaking to constructive receipt and not how easy the platform is to use.","index":308,"end_time":1126.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1121.06,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Yeah, gotcha.","index":309,"end_time":1128.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1126.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":310,"end_time":1129.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1128.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"If anything, that would replace like slide four.","index":311,"end_time":1133.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1129.66,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":312,"end_time":1136.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1136.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s not a bad idea either because it lists all our exchange options.","index":313,"end_time":1143.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1139.34,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Right, right.","index":314,"end_time":1144.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1143.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m asking Josh too.","index":315,"end_time":1146.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1145.19,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"I mean, again, we''ve always listed them, but.","index":316,"end_time":1149.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1146.63,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"If there''s a way to show what it looks like on the platform.","index":317,"end_time":1153.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1150.71,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Yeah, but it doesn''t break it out.","index":318,"end_time":1157.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1156.47,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Right.","index":319,"end_time":1157.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1157.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You have to click on social well being to see what the options are.","index":320,"end_time":1161.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1157.95,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Giving, sharing.","index":321,"end_time":1162.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1161.11,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":322,"end_time":1163.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1162.67,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Yeah, I kind of like the way, I kind of like the list better.","index":323,"end_time":1166.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1164.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean, I like the idea of that, but I.","index":324,"end_time":1168.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1166.67,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But I don''t know that it''s solves what we''re going for, fits in for, for our deck.","index":325,"end_time":1173.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1168.31,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay, I gotcha.","index":326,"end_time":1175.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1174.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":327,"end_time":1176.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1176.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I have some ideas for this one.","index":328,"end_time":1177.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1176.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just I think there''s ways that we can still have the emphasis of the breakout of financial wellness options and social well being options without it taking up so much real estate on the slide so that we can like move around where the testimonials are going and this bottom piece as well.","index":329,"end_time":1190.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1177.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":330,"end_time":1192.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1191.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And.","index":331,"end_time":1193.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1192.66,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And like I said in my notes, like that bottom piece, does it necessarily have to be on this slide?","index":332,"end_time":1198.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1193.02,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We should have it somewhere as A somewhere earlier, earlyish in the deck where it''s like, this is being used, this is successful.","index":333,"end_time":1209.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1198.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is not like a.","index":334,"end_time":1211.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1209.85,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You know, fly by night operation that we have here.","index":335,"end_time":1215.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1212.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We.","index":336,"end_time":1215.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1215.49,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We''ve exchanged millions of hours of PTO for hundreds of millions of dollars.","index":337,"end_time":1220.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1215.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":338,"end_time":1221.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1220.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, I got to ask then, why.","index":339,"end_time":1222.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1221.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Why would we not have it on like a title or the first information slide?","index":340,"end_time":1226.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1223.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there any reason we wouldn''t know?","index":341,"end_time":1230.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1228.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It can be, it can really be kind of anywhere.","index":342,"end_time":1234.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1230.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It doesn''t really fit with the second slide like this.","index":343,"end_time":1236.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1234.18,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"The talk track of what we''re doing is different on the second slide.","index":344,"end_time":1239.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1236.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is like why Rob created PTO Exchange.","index":345,"end_time":1242.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1239.78,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And like, what is the landscape of pto?","index":346,"end_time":1245.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1242.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Right.","index":347,"end_time":1245.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1245.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The next one is slide is like, why does it matter?","index":348,"end_time":1249.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1246.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is us trying to hook the broker or the partner of like, these are the things that are relevant in your world that you''re dealing with today to try to get their attention.","index":349,"end_time":1258.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1249.81,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we haven''t, like, right now we just have it on the next slide because we want it early in the thing.","index":350,"end_time":1263.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1258.85,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But like, if we want that on the title page, that''s sitting up there when Dave''s like just kind of introducing himself and getting the thing started as a way to.","index":351,"end_time":1273.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1263.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s like social proof up there.","index":352,"end_time":1275.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1273.66,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''s the exact phrase I was going to use.","index":353,"end_time":1278.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1276.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that''s what it serves as, you know, because he''s doing his intro.","index":354,"end_time":1280.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1278.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Dave.","index":355,"end_time":1280.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1280.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Dave, I''m not talking like, you''re not here.","index":356,"end_time":1282.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1280.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Dave, you''re doing your intro and you know, there you''re going through.","index":357,"end_time":1286.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1282.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The person is looking at the screen.","index":358,"end_time":1287.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1286.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re, you know, they''re listening, but they''re just trying to like, okay, what is this thing?","index":359,"end_time":1291.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1287.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What am I looking at here?","index":360,"end_time":1292.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1291.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, see our logos and their logo.","index":361,"end_time":1294.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1292.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But like showing like the actual proof in the pudding like this, I think is very strong on a title slide.","index":362,"end_time":1300.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1294.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":363,"end_time":1302.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1302.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":364,"end_time":1303.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1303.21,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And so the.","index":365,"end_time":1306.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1305.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think I outlined this a little bit last week, but the approach that I want to take here.","index":366,"end_time":1309.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1306.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll go through with the content as it exists, keeping in mind your comments of where we maybe don''t need something or to add something, but we''ll also just develop like templates, like template slides so that you can say like, okay, I want one with, with this background or this layout.","index":367,"end_time":1324.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1309.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here''s where I would swap logos, things like that.","index":368,"end_time":1327.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1325.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":369,"end_time":1332.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1331.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Other than that, I don''t think I have any other questions.","index":370,"end_time":1336.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1334.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nina, does anything jump out to you that you wanted to ask about?","index":371,"end_time":1338.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1336.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One of the questions that I had for the sixth slide when we were talking about the fill out form, would it also be an option for example to maybe just make a frame similar to the.","index":372,"end_time":1356.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1343.3,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"For example, when we make the logo goes white for them to be visible on a darker background.","index":373,"end_time":1360.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1356.06,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"We can also just make a bolded version of, you know, the most important parts of the form so we lose all the extra space that''s, you know, causing it to be really small in the numbers.","index":374,"end_time":1372.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1360.76,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Now it wouldn''t look the same on as on the web page, but it would be more visible.","index":375,"end_time":1377.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1372.92,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":376,"end_time":1378.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1378,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if we redesign this, like do we want some pieces cut out and more pieces emphasized?","index":377,"end_time":1383.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1378.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":378,"end_time":1387.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1386.67,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean again as we''re like talking through, like Dave said before, we''ve always done it this way so that like that''s what we''re used to.","index":379,"end_time":1394.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1387.39,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, but it, but it takes up half of the slide for.","index":380,"end_time":1398.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1394.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, it''s really like the last things that were on there like the contribution amount, the service charge and the total before taxes.","index":381,"end_time":1408.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1400.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''s the relevant information in this.","index":382,"end_time":1412.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1410.36,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":383,"end_time":1413.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1412.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s like an eighth of the size of the image to get to the part that we''re hammering home.","index":384,"end_time":1420.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1413.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So it doesn''t have to be in the form layout as long as we have an opportunity.","index":385,"end_time":1426.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1421.08,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"To talk about that in a way that looks normal.","index":386,"end_time":1432.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1428.36,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, maybe we don''t even need the actual form approach.","index":387,"end_time":1436.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1432.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Maybe it''s like, maybe it''s more of a like a prompt style or not a prompt style but like a step by step where like they go in and it''s like okay, if your numbers are this and you enter in eight hours and then we like kind of highlight much larger lower on the pay or lower on the slide the contribution amount and service charge and total before taxes.","index":388,"end_time":1454.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1436.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m looking at it and my eyes are blurring.","index":389,"end_time":1457.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1455.22,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"I can''t see it.","index":390,"end_time":1458.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1457.46,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":391,"end_time":1458.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1458.34,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Well if you''re.","index":392,"end_time":1460.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1458.7,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Manipulating this and you can do whatever you want and like size it however you want, the.","index":393,"end_time":1467.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1461.86,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Contribution limit and the year to date and the limit remaining and the limit hours.","index":394,"end_time":1473.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1469.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Those are like actually interesting, relevant things for us to talk about like, or for someone to see on the screen of like, okay, we are capturing what the limit is.","index":395,"end_time":1483.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1474.42,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We are going to make sure that you''re not going to go over like we speak to that sometimes I would say now also looking at it just to make the math even easier, I would use four hours of exchanging which is a hundred dollars less the seven and a half percent which is $7 and 50 cents and then it''s a $92.50 because then it''s just easy for someone to do the math.","index":396,"end_time":1505.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1483.86,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, very, very simple.","index":397,"end_time":1506.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1505.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But it doesn''t have to be in this form.","index":398,"end_time":1509.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1508.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But if there was some way to like, kind of capture all of this, but in a different, in a different.","index":399,"end_time":1513.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1509.87,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Display to highlight it.","index":400,"end_time":1516.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1513.87,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, Dust.","index":401,"end_time":1519.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1518.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"There''s a lot more space if we use the cash out option.","index":402,"end_time":1522.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1519.48,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"I mean, I know, but I like, I like using one with the HSA or the 401k.","index":403,"end_time":1527.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1522.28,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We get to talk about the limits or we show that we capture the limits.","index":404,"end_time":1530.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1527.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But also I think there are some people that we talk to that are turned off by cash out.","index":405,"end_time":1535.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1530.36,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So being able to show a.","index":406,"end_time":1536.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1535.08,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"A more a benefit that''s not as, like, controversial or whatever, I think it''s helpful.","index":407,"end_time":1542.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1537,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":408,"end_time":1545.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1544.61,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":409,"end_time":1546.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1545.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then kind of my last question.","index":410,"end_time":1548.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1546.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How do you guys feel about animations?","index":411,"end_time":1551.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1548.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like what?","index":412,"end_time":1555.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1554.77,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Like, so, you know, let''s say, you know, if we were tearing this slide into a different approach and let me just duplicate this.","index":413,"end_time":1563.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1555.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, like, if we didn''t have this here, but we had.","index":414,"end_time":1567.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1564.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s just say.","index":415,"end_time":1568.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1567.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We had like text up here.","index":416,"end_time":1571.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1570.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of course this is going to be.","index":417,"end_time":1573.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1572.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t use.","index":418,"end_time":1580.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1579.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We use slides.","index":419,"end_time":1580.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1580.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So my PowerPoint''s not working, but just follow me real quick.","index":420,"end_time":1583.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1580.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if we.","index":421,"end_time":1584.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1583.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s say we start out with some information of what their contribution limit is and limit rating and year to date and limit hours, and that''s up top.","index":422,"end_time":1593.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1585.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we want to say, okay, cool, let''s see what four hours would impact.","index":423,"end_time":1598.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1593.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so like that.","index":424,"end_time":1599.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1599.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we would start out with the contribution limit, all that stuff up top.","index":425,"end_time":1602.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1599.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''d click on the slide and then the four hours would pop up and then you click again and then the results would pop up.","index":426,"end_time":1607.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1602.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we want those style of animations?","index":427,"end_time":1609.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1607.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, I''m okay.","index":428,"end_time":1611.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1610.78,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"I''ve done that before where it slides in or comes in or transitions in.","index":429,"end_time":1616.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1611.7,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"I mean, I''m open to anything.","index":430,"end_time":1618.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1616.94,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":431,"end_time":1618.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1618.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":432,"end_time":1619.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1618.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":433,"end_time":1620.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1619.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I just like to gauge that I''m personally not a fan of, of animations just because I talk through my slides so fast and I like, like to have all the information right there.","index":434,"end_time":1629.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1620.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But as you''re getting familiar and everything with your slides, you''ll.","index":435,"end_time":1632.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1629.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''ll have all of those locked into place.","index":436,"end_time":1633.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1632.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":437,"end_time":1633.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1633.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":438,"end_time":1634.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1634.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":439,"end_time":1637.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1637.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, that''s all the questions that we had.","index":440,"end_time":1640.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1638.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think that we''re pretty good to lock in to start designing this.","index":441,"end_time":1643.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1640.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there anything else that you guys wanted to share?","index":442,"end_time":1645.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1643.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, no, I think that''s it.","index":443,"end_time":1651.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1648.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think again, I think the idea for this is.","index":444,"end_time":1653.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1651.46,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We probably like we want to see what this is going to look like on the channel side.","index":445,"end_time":1661.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1658.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But we pro.","index":446,"end_time":1662.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1661.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"There''s probably another deck that we''re going to want you to do on the sales side also.","index":447,"end_time":1666.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1662.74,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But we want to start.","index":448,"end_time":1666.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1666.02,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Start here.","index":449,"end_time":1667.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1666.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":450,"end_time":1668.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1667.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, we''ll have V1 ready next week to go through with you guys, and then.","index":451,"end_time":1672.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1668.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":452,"end_time":1673.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1673.22,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Any tweaks there.","index":453,"end_time":1674.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1673.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''ll be well set up for the next slide.","index":454,"end_time":1676.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1674.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":455,"end_time":1677.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1677.58,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Great.","index":456,"end_time":1678.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1678.3,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":457,"end_time":1680.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1679.5,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Thank you guys.","index":458,"end_time":1681.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1680.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Super exciting stuff.","index":459,"end_time":1682.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1681.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":460,"end_time":1683.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1683.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Great meeting you.","index":461,"end_time":1684.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1683.66,"speaker_name":"Dave Sherman"},{"text":"Appreciate it.","index":462,"end_time":1685.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1684.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great meeting you as well, Dave.","index":463,"end_time":1686.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1685.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Talk to you in a little bit.","index":464,"end_time":1687.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1686.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yep.","index":465,"end_time":1687.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1687.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll see you guys in like an hour, I think.","index":466,"end_time":1689.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1687.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":467,"end_time":1689.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1689.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All right.","index":468,"end_time":1690.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1689.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"See you.","index":469,"end_time":1691.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1690.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"}],"dateString":"2025-12-11T17:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85676425517?pwd=SEHeRPazZ264H905bbb2L03BbJ8aw7.1","participants":["josh@ptoexchange.com,davids@ptoexchange.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,sam@ptoexchange.com,nina.belina@marketersindemand.com","josh@ptoexchange.com","davids@ptoexchange.com","sam@ptoexchange.com","nina.belina@marketersindemand.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KBNAE3D5X38AJ06ZV5J60DTY","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.9,"bullets":["Agreed to reduce slide text and modernize design for better visual clarity and delivery.","Colin proposed maintaining multiple deck versions including web-optimized and presenter-facing formats.","Design improvements include removing gradient green backgrounds and enhancing readability of green-on-green text.","Team plans to highlight reduction in turnover via clearer slide visuals using sampled data.","Considering animated GIFs and simplified visuals to better convey complex platform processes during presentations."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I think we can have multiple versions of this... someone can easily access, download...","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"Looking to make it more modern and less wordy.","speaker":"Dave Sherman"}],"topics":["design","presentation","platform","engagement"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-11T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Presentation Redesign and Visual Strategy**\n\nThe team agreed to overhaul the slide deck to reduce text and boost visual appeal for broader audience engagement.\n\n- **Dave Sherman** emphasized moving toward a **more modern, less wordy presentation style** to better hold the audience’s attention (03:08)  \n    - The goal is to shift from educating with many words to sparking interest through visuals.  \n    - Sam Lieberman noted the current deck has too much text and lacks professional design polish, limiting its shareability.  \n    - Colin Costigan suggested creating two versions: one downloadable for self-guided review, another optimized for live presentations with less text.  \n    - This approach aims to ease conversation starters and reduce the need for pre-customizing decks.\n\n- The group discussed replacing the **dark green gradient background and green-on-green text**, which impair readability (04:59)  \n    - Josh Reinhard clarified some slides still use problematic green-on-green fonts, signaling a need for consistent color updates.  \n    - Colin proposed using Microsoft standard fonts to improve compatibility when slides are shared and edited by others (05:38).  \n    - This ensures easy deck adaptation across teams and reduces formatting issues during handoffs.\n\n- There was consensus on enhancing logo presentation by using **white logo versions on darker backgrounds** to improve clarity and branding impact (08:18)  \n    - Colin mentioned the current logo slide feels negative and could be reframed for a more positive, clean look.  \n    - This change supports better first impressions and social proof early in the deck.\n\n## **Content Prioritization and Slide Flow**\n\nThe team aligned on reorganizing content to improve messaging clarity and impact, especially around key proof points.\n\n- They decided to place the **“millions of PTO hours exchanged for hundreds of millions of dollars”** metric as a prominent social proof element on the **title or early slides** (19:52)  \n    - Josh Reinhard explained this metric fits early to hook brokers and partners with real proof of success.  \n    - Colin agreed this sets a strong tone for the presentation and frames credibility immediately.\n\n- Discussion around the **turnover reduction slide** revealed a need for clearer, dedicated focus, as it currently blends into broader content (06:29)  \n    - Dave Sherman suggested emphasizing this slide more due to its strong client impact data from a sample of **35 clients**.  \n    - Josh said the slide could be refined and positioned to better highlight tangible savings linked to reduced employee turnover.\n\n- The team explored a **three-column layout** with images or illustrations to better organize content and visuals (10:26)  \n    - Josh and Colin agreed on balancing illustrations with editable content, so the deck remains flexible for future edits without heavy design support.  \n    - They want a clean, consistent look that avoids clutter and improves audience comprehension.\n\n## **Platform Visualization and User Experience**\n\nThe group debated how best to show the PTO Exchange platform within the deck to balance clarity and engagement.\n\n- Josh Reinhard demonstrated the **current platform UI screenshot highlighting the 7.5% service charge**, which is small and hard to read on laptop screens (12:05)  \n    - Dave Sherman expressed openness to alternatives like a **cash-out option slide** that presents clearer space and simpler math examples.  \n    - They want to maintain focus on **constructive receipt requirements** while improving visual legibility.\n\n- Colin proposed using **animated GIFs** within slides to simulate user interactions with the platform, providing a dynamic preview without a full demo (16:24)  \n    - This would show clicking options and filling out forms to convey simplicity and ease of use in a visually engaging way.  \n    - Dave liked the idea but noted it should not replace slides focused on specific features like constructive receipt.\n\n- The team considered whether to show **exact platform screenshots versus more illustrative diagrams**, weighing familiarity against clarity (14:32)  \n    - Dave and Josh were flexible but noted the deck’s role is to pique interest, with detailed demos reserved for follow-up calls.  \n    - The consensus leans toward simpler visuals in the deck to reduce cognitive load while highlighting key features.\n\n## **Slide Design Details and Animation Preferences**\n\nThey reviewed specific slide elements and animation use to improve clarity without distracting from the content.\n\n- There is a preference to **simplify the form display**, highlighting only the most relevant data like contribution amount, service charge, and total before taxes (22:23)  \n    - Nina Belina suggested a bolded, condensed frame of the form’s key parts to improve number visibility.  \n    - Josh recommended using easy-to-calculate examples like **four hours exchanged equaling $92.50 after service charge** to aid understanding.\n\n- Dave Sherman and Josh Reinhard agreed some details like contribution limits and year-to-date usage remain important to show platform safeguards (24:18)  \n    - They want to balance transparency about limits without overcrowding the slide.\n\n- Colin asked about attitudes toward **slide animations** such as sequential reveals of data points (25:45)  \n    - Dave and Josh were open to simple animations like sliding or fading in content to help guide viewers through complex info.  \n    - Colin prefers static slides for faster presentations but endorses animations for users new to the deck.\n\n- The final approach is to build **template slides with flexible backgrounds and layouts**, allowing easy swapping of logos and content by the team without needing design help (21:45)  \n    - This modularity supports quicker updates and adaptation for different audiences or product lines.\n\n## **Next Steps and Timeline**\n\nThe team set clear expectations to move forward with design iteration and future deck versions.\n\n- Colin committed to delivering a **version 1 draft of the redesigned deck by next week** for review and feedback (27:47)  \n    - This will incorporate all discussed changes around visuals, text reduction, and layout improvements.  \n    - The goal is to finalize a channel-side deck before expanding to a sales-focused version.\n\n- Josh Reinhard acknowledged the need for a **sales-side deck as a follow-up project**, signaling a phased rollout (27:28)  \n    - The current effort prioritizes the channel deck to test messaging and design concepts first.\n\n- The team confirmed no major outstanding questions and expressed readiness to proceed with design work (27:53)  \n    - Dave Sherman and Josh thanked Colin for the collaborative session and looked forward to reviewing the updated materials.","outline":null,"keywords":["PTO Exchange","Slide Deck Design","Turnover Reduction","Platform Screenshot","Service Charge","Presentation Animation"],"overview":"- **Slide Deck Overhaul:** Aim to reduce text and enhance visuals for better audience engagement and shareability.  \n- **Color & Font Changes:** Replace green-on-green text and use standard fonts for improved readability and formatting consistency.  \n- **Logo Presentation:** Shift to white logos on dark backgrounds for clarity and a positive branding impact throughout the presentation.  \n- **Content Organization:** Prioritize key metrics like “millions of PTO hours” early in the deck to establish credibility and hook the audience.  \n- **Visual Simplification:** Use cleaner layouts and animations to reduce clutter and enhance understanding of key information on slides.  \n- **Next Steps:** Draft of redesigned deck to be delivered next week; subsequent focus on creating a sales-side deck after initial review.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nDevelop V1 of redesigned slide deck incorporating discussed visual and textual improvements by next week (27:45)\nCreate slide templates with multiple backgrounds and layouts to enable easy client customization (21:49)\nProvide ideas for improved visual layout of financial wellness options and testimonial placement (19:34)\n\n**Josh Reinhard**\nShare slide demonstrating turnover reduction with logos and data for inclusion in the deck (06:29)\nCoordinate with new hire Steph to evaluate screenshot clarity and options for improvement or alternative illustrations (11:53)\nConsider inclusion of mobile app screenshots or icons to represent technology accessibility in the deck (08:59)\nProvide feedback on redesign options for platform UI slides explaining service charges and constructive receipt (13:40)\n\n**Dave Sherman**\nConfirm content priorities for slide inclusion, especially around turnover reduction and platform explanation (06:29)\nProvide input on presentation and demo sequencing, particularly separating overview deck and detailed platform demos (14:32)\n\n**Nina Belina**\nExplore design options to highlight key form elements with bolded text and reduced space to improve readability on form-related slides (22:23)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"13d31457-6097-4002-8797-70a5466d27e5","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
