    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85039954260?pwd=7GrXTMosQASbwQapyiVncGn3aAbQCz.1&jst=2',
    '{"id":"01KBZNPJMJP332VAK4PGW059F3","title":"MiD//Noetic: Weekly Set Meeting  5/8 - Onwards","summary":{"notes":"## **Content Production and Campaign Launch**\n\nThe team finalized the updated compilation script and plans to record the intro segment by **Friday**, aiming to complete compilation within **one week** after recording (05:12).  \n- **Colin Costigan** confirmed all feedback was incorporated into the script, with screenshots illustrating episode previews to guide recording.  \n- Recording is scheduled immediately after Chris Boyle’s session, ensuring timely content flow within the production calendar.  \n- The compilation video will be integrated into the content rotation, targeting the end-of-year holiday season for increased engagement as people seek light content during travel and downtime.  \n\nThe LinkedIn ads and landing page were updated based on recent feedback and are ready for launch (07:17).  \n- Adjustments included subtle color changes for better legibility and refined copy targeting AI use confidence and consistency, enhancing message clarity and audience appeal.  \n- The landing page will use a pale yellow color scheme and reordered content to emphasize human skills training upfront, with logos repositioned to the bottom for stronger visual impact.  \n- Colin confirmed the campaign landing page will be hosted on a closed URL, accessible only via ads or direct links, with SEO crawling enabled to allow organic traffic growth.  \n\nThe campaign launch will consolidate into **three active campaigns**: the new AI campaign plus two ongoing infographic campaigns for healthcare and first-time CMOs, balancing market presence without overwhelming the audience (13:18).  \n- The infographic campaigns have been in market for about **one month** but have generated only **two leads** in the past 30 days, indicating low current lead flow and prompting a planned review after an additional two weeks.  \n- The AI campaign launch is expected to bring fresh engagement and will be closely monitored to evaluate lead quality and user interaction, with plans to retarget near-threshold audiences on LinkedIn for increased conversion.  \n\n## **Lead Generation and Market Targeting Strategy**\n\nLead volume concerns prompted discussion on refining target industries for 2026, focusing on sectors with higher potential and dropping less active ones like higher education and attractions (15:12).  \n- **Nathalie Mintjens** highlighted financial services, healthcare, professional services (including law firms), and nonprofits as key sectors showing growth and alignment with current service offerings.  \n- Independent agencies, exemplified by a recent lead from a **400-person agency**, were identified as fitting the ideal client size for the AI campaign due to their marketing sophistication and team structure.  \n- There is exploratory interest in targeting VC firms, leveraging their role in recommending agencies to portfolio companies; however, the lack of existing contacts and complexity of sales cycles were noted as hurdles. Colin plans to develop a framework for targeting VC-associated companies and will present list parameters for approval.  \n\nThe team emphasized the importance of precise list building and due diligence to ensure campaigns reach organizations with the right size, sophistication, and need for branding and marketing services (18:50).  \n- Discussions considered geographic clustering and company size as additional filters to optimize targeting efficacy.  \n- The goal is to avoid wasting resources on enterprises that either have internal solutions or are too small to invest in marketing services.  \n\n## **Website and Podcast Integration for Engagement**\n\nIncreasing website engagement through owned experiences was flagged as a priority, with the podcast page seeing a measurable **increase in page views** (28:04).  \n- Colin shared an example of a direct integration with **Buzzsprout** that includes embedded audio, episode summaries, guest LinkedIn links, and quote cards, designed to keep visitors engaged longer on the site.  \n- The team agreed to discuss with Rachel the feasibility and ownership of implementing this podcast integration on their website, weighing whether internal teams or the hosting provider should build the functionality.  \n\nYouTube views have declined compared to initial posting, but recent data shows a **10% increase** in traffic relative to the previous period, suggesting content shelf life and the need for strategic re-promotion, such as the upcoming compilation video (28:53).  \n- The potential to drive YouTube and other external platform audiences back into the website environment was recognized as key to owning the user experience and increasing lead capture opportunities.  \n\n## **Metrics and Traffic Insights**\n\nOverall website traffic showed a **5% dip** approaching the holiday season, attributed to reduced work focus and seasonal distractions (23:27).  \n- Colin pointed out an unusual recent rise in traffic from **Bing**, hypothesizing it may relate to new device usage or default browser settings impacting search engine distribution (29:28).  \n- Anomalies such as visits attributed to **Pipedrive** and **SharePoint** were noted as likely API or tracking artifacts; Colin will coordinate with developers to clarify and resolve these data irregularities (30:05).  \n\nLead generation remains a critical concern, with few qualified leads appearing on the board despite ongoing campaigns (30:47).  \n- A call with Waymo is scheduled, though the client is reportedly overwhelmed, which may delay engagement and decision-making.  \n- The AI campaign launch is seen as a key opportunity to stimulate engagement and attract qualified leads, with careful monitoring planned to identify drop-off points and refine messaging accordingly.  \n\n## **Scheduling and Team Coordination**\n\nNext team meeting is confirmed for **December 17th**, with flexible attendance plans accommodating personal schedules, including Nathalie’s potential delay due to her husband’s knee surgery (33:10).  \n- The December 24th meeting is canceled given the holiday.  \n- The content compilation is expected to be ready by the December 17th meeting, contingent on timely recording this week (34:34).  \n- The team agreed to keep the AI campaign launch on track for this timeline, with only minor changes such as lightening the gray color on one ad before going live (34:06).  \n\nColin committed to delivering updated industry targeting parameters, list sizes, and insights alongside resolving the tracking anomalies before the next meeting (34:13).  \n- The team plans to continue observing campaign performance through the holiday period and into early January, considering potential boosts to sustain engagement during typically low activity times (34:55).","outline":null,"keywords":["AI campaign","LinkedIn ads","landing page","lead generation","industry targeting","podcast integration"],"overview":"- **Content Production Deadline:** Recording of the updated script is set for Friday, with compilation completion expected within one week.  \n- **Campaign Launch Updates:** LinkedIn ads ready with improved visuals and copy, emphasizing human skills training and targeting increased engagement.  \n- **Lead Generation Focus:** Targeting key sectors for 2026, including financial services and healthcare, while refining list-building strategies to optimize outreach.  \n- **Website Engagement Strategy:** Podcast integration will enhance user experience, with plans to explore embedding functionalities for increased site interaction.  \n- **Traffic Dip Observed:** Overall website traffic dipped 5%, attributed to seasonal distractions, with a need to monitor metrics closely moving forward.  \n- **Next Meeting Plan:** Team meeting is set for December 17th, aiming to discuss campaign performances and finalize industry targeting parameters.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend updated compilation script and ask for feedback for review (03:00)\nLighten gray color on LinkedIn ad as requested (07:00)\nBuild landing page as a closed page with option for Google crawling; confirm website access and URL deployment (11:00)\nLaunch AI campaign and infographic campaigns; monitor performance for at least two weeks (12:00)\nInvestigate why Pipedrive and SharePoint appear in metrics and report back (30:00)\nDevelop industry-specific marketing list framework and run it by the team, including pros/cons of targeting VC firms and sub-sectors (21:00)\nCheck on podcast integration technical requirements with development team (24:00)\n\n**Nancie Ruder**\nRecord and deliver the intro portion of the compilation by Friday (05:00)\nCoordinate with Julia and Rachel regarding podcast integration feasibility and metrics (24:00)\nAttend meeting on December 17 and notify in case of any scheduling conflicts (33:00)\n\n**Julia Oher**\nFollow up with Rachel on podcast site integration details and share updates (24:00)\nWork with Nancie to deliver recording for compilation (34:00)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nMonitor leads generated from infographic campaigns and advise on continued run or revamp (14:00)\nAssist in sharpening messaging around industry targeting and support list-building plans for 2026 focus (15:00)\nCoordinate with Colin and Nancie to prioritize AI campaign launch and measurement of engagement thresholds (31:00)\nAttend meeting on December 17 and support scheduling logistics (33:00)\n"},"duration":35.459999084472656,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"nancieruder"},{"id":1,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"id":2,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":3,"name":"Julia Oher"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hello.","index":0,"end_time":4.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":4.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Hey, how''s it going?","index":1,"end_time":7.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":5.36,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Good.","index":2,"end_time":9.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":8.64,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"How are you?","index":3,"end_time":9.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":9.04,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Doing all right.","index":4,"end_time":11.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":10.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hello.","index":5,"end_time":43.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":43.61,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Hey, how''s it going?","index":6,"end_time":45.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":44.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It is going well.","index":7,"end_time":47.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":46.25,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"How are you, too?","index":8,"end_time":48.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":47.45,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Doing all right.","index":9,"end_time":49.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":49.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just trying to stay warm, which bet you guys are as well.","index":10,"end_time":52.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":49.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":11,"end_time":53.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":53.22,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"I don''t know about you, Natalie, but I''ve definitely, like, had my heat in overdrive.","index":12,"end_time":59.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":53.94,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"I just had to, like, open my door because I stepped out of this room and I was like, oh, my God.","index":13,"end_time":64.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":59.94,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"The heat between.","index":14,"end_time":65.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":64.82,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"My heat.","index":15,"end_time":66.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":65.78,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"My space heater, it''s oppressive.","index":16,"end_time":69.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":67.06,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"So I was like, I gotta get some air in here.","index":17,"end_time":71.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":69.78,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s really hard.","index":18,"end_time":73.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":72.1,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Especially because I. I get so hot at night that I turn off all the heaters.","index":19,"end_time":78.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":74.26,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But then when I wake up, it''s.","index":20,"end_time":79.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":78.34,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Freezing, so you have to.","index":21,"end_time":81.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":79.54,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I am the exact same way.","index":22,"end_time":82.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":81.02,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"So you have to start from zero.","index":23,"end_time":84.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":82.18,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":24,"end_time":84.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":84.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"This is also about the time of day where, like, my redness comes out really, really strong because, like, I clearly am abusing my skin through.","index":25,"end_time":94.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":85.12,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Through all these methods.","index":26,"end_time":96.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":95.12,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Oh, fun.","index":27,"end_time":99.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":98.24,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"I think we''re just waiting for Nancy.","index":28,"end_time":103.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":101.84,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"I''m hoping it was clear that Rachel''s out today.","index":29,"end_time":107.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":104.64,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Cool.","index":30,"end_time":109.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":108.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi, guys.","index":31,"end_time":182.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":182.36,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Sorry to be late.","index":32,"end_time":183.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":182.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s coming up.","index":33,"end_time":184.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":183.88,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Hello.","index":34,"end_time":186.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":186.37,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Hello.","index":35,"end_time":187.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":186.61,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I did not have a chance to review the deck, Colin, so just telling you that because I''m not as prepared as usual.","index":36,"end_time":194.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":187.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, no worries at all.","index":37,"end_time":195.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":194.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a pretty light deck, honestly, so we''ll hop right in.","index":38,"end_time":200.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":196.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":39,"end_time":205.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":204.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we got all the feedback on the compilation script, and so I''ll send that over to you guys to review, but I wanted to take more minute to just go through this, so updated the script based on all the feedback, and we have some screenshots in here, too, of the episodes and how they would look.","index":40,"end_time":224.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":207.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I think this will be much more aligned to what you guys were looking for out of this.","index":41,"end_time":230.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":225.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And can you go back to the top of just.","index":42,"end_time":233.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":230.88,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I just wanted to see the intro.","index":43,"end_time":235.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":233.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Obviously, I''ll read the whole thing, but.","index":44,"end_time":237.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":235.28,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, let me see if I can zoom in.","index":45,"end_time":240.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":239.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I may want to just make some small.","index":46,"end_time":261.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":259.18,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I agree with the gist of this, and I might just want to add a line here or there just to try to make it even more compelling.","index":47,"end_time":270.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":262.38,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, compelling people to watch.","index":48,"end_time":271.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":270.3,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":49,"end_time":274.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":272.02,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And if my memory serves me correct, you are set to record that tomorrow.","index":50,"end_time":278.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":274.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that''s right.","index":51,"end_time":281.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":280.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Let me see before.","index":52,"end_time":284.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.94,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right after.","index":53,"end_time":284.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":284.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re doing it right after Chris o''.","index":54,"end_time":290.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":287.86,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Boyle.","index":55,"end_time":290.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":290.02,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yep.","index":56,"end_time":291.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":290.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":57,"end_time":292.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":291.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, well, we''ll send this over in the meantime to take a deeper look, but all feedback has been incorporated.","index":58,"end_time":297.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":292.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":59,"end_time":300.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":299.68,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":60,"end_time":300.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":300.24,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":61,"end_time":301.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":301.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Very excited to see how this comes out.","index":62,"end_time":303.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":301.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So then what''s your timing look like?","index":63,"end_time":305.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":303.44,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like we''ll get you that intro portion.","index":64,"end_time":308.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":305.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"There''s no outro.","index":65,"end_time":310.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":309.04,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":66,"end_time":310.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":310.04,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Just intro.","index":67,"end_time":311.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":310.4,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Mm.","index":68,"end_time":312,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":311.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll get you that by Friday and then what.","index":69,"end_time":317.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":312.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"What are you looking at, timing wise for getting it compiled?","index":70,"end_time":320.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":317.72,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":71,"end_time":321.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":321.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Natalie, do you have that in front of you?","index":72,"end_time":323.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":321.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it should be about a week once we receive the recording.","index":73,"end_time":327.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":324.18,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":74,"end_time":329.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":328.66,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So Julia will want to work that into our rotation.","index":75,"end_time":331.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":329.1,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yep.","index":76,"end_time":332.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":332.02,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":77,"end_time":334.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":333.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, Nice.","index":78,"end_time":335.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":334.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Season of giving, end of year, wrap up type, you know, posts.","index":79,"end_time":339.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":336.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":80,"end_time":341.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":341.22,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And hopefully people, you know, will be almost upon the holiday at that point.","index":81,"end_time":345.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":341.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And hopefully people will just be trolling social media.","index":82,"end_time":348.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":345.22,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":83,"end_time":349.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":349.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Avoiding work.","index":84,"end_time":350.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":349.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":85,"end_time":351.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":350.83,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Hopefully people are getting into a car or on a plane and looking for content.","index":86,"end_time":355.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":351.31,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":87,"end_time":357.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":356.67,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"There you go.","index":88,"end_time":358.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":357.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I could do a Netflix movie or I could watch.","index":89,"end_time":360.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":358.19,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m gonna go with a compilation.","index":90,"end_time":363.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":362.35,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I.","index":91,"end_time":364.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":364.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Why would I watch a movie when I can watch Nancy and her highlights?","index":92,"end_time":368.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":364.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Short.","index":93,"end_time":369.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":369.39,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Short bits of content are quite appealing to some of us these days.","index":94,"end_time":374.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":370.11,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Yes.","index":95,"end_time":375.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":374.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":96,"end_time":377.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":376.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":97,"end_time":377.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":377.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so we''ll send that over and then if we''re all good on the script and you can record your part, then, yeah, we should be able to turn that around in about a week.","index":98,"end_time":383.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":377.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re also working on the assets for Trip Randall, Pam Forbis, Patrick McMaster, and Barbara Goose.","index":99,"end_time":391.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":384.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we sent over, we''re just waiting on any feedback for Kate Warnock, Christine Calvinez, and Jenny Colopy.","index":100,"end_time":398.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":392.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Will you just make sure?","index":101,"end_time":402.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":400.21,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Okay.","index":102,"end_time":402.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":402.13,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Kate, Christine, and Jenny.","index":103,"end_time":404.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":402.93,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Great.","index":104,"end_time":405.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":404.93,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yep.","index":105,"end_time":406.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":405.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We are just a little bit backlogged, so I''m just jotting that down as a note to myself that we will attempt to get that by end of week.","index":106,"end_time":415.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":407.05,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Okay, fantastic.","index":107,"end_time":417.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":415.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We also updated the LinkedIn ads based on our conversation last week.","index":108,"end_time":422.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":419.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think these will align with everything that you guys gave us.","index":109,"end_time":426.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":422.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As far as feedback, we were pretty good on most of the images.","index":110,"end_time":429.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":426.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just changed some colors on the CTAs and things like that, and I think we were all pretty excited to see this one.","index":111,"end_time":436.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":430.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":112,"end_time":438.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":437.87,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I might just go a hair lighter on the gray even.","index":113,"end_time":441.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":438.11,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":114,"end_time":442.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":441.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we can do that.","index":115,"end_time":444.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":443.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just a hair for legibility.","index":116,"end_time":447.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":444.99,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Got it.","index":117,"end_time":449.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":449.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can you scroll back to the top?","index":118,"end_time":453.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":451.71,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yes.","index":119,"end_time":454.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":454.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just want to look at the copy.","index":120,"end_time":455.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":454.43,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay, good.","index":121,"end_time":473.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":471.32,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yep.","index":122,"end_time":482.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":481.8,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"This headline feels vague.","index":123,"end_time":496.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":494.37,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Get started with Noetic.","index":124,"end_time":499.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":497.97,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The other ones are more AI.","index":125,"end_time":501.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":499.33,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I don''t know, it just feels less hardworking.","index":126,"end_time":514.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":512.94,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":127,"end_time":515.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":515.34,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Maybe it''s maybe like get started.","index":128,"end_time":521.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":519.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Doing AI the right way with Noetic.","index":129,"end_time":523.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":521.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, something like that.","index":130,"end_time":525.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":523.5,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":131,"end_time":525.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":525.06,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So this one, like, I don''t disagree with what it says, but Is it about confidence or is it about consistency?","index":132,"end_time":555.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":549.75,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Or is it about both?","index":133,"end_time":556.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":555.19,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think it''s about both.","index":134,"end_time":558.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":557.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we have that alliteration also.","index":135,"end_time":560.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":558.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like here.","index":136,"end_time":561.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":561.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think the play on words is pretty nice.","index":137,"end_time":564.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":562.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There it is.","index":138,"end_time":565.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":564.15,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"The alliteration is nice.","index":139,"end_time":566.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":565.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":140,"end_time":567.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":566.49,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Should we say your team may be using AI with different levels of confidence and consistency?","index":141,"end_time":574.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":568.73,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yes.","index":142,"end_time":576.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":576.41,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"And then I think the headline is correct.","index":143,"end_time":579.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":577.13,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Bring consistency.","index":144,"end_time":581.129,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":579.85,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":145,"end_time":582.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":581.61,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":146,"end_time":584.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":583.85,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Because the.","index":147,"end_time":584.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":584.25,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because the lack of confidence drives the.","index":148,"end_time":586.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":584.73,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The inconsistency.","index":149,"end_time":587.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":586.57,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So.","index":150,"end_time":588.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":587.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":151,"end_time":588.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":588.13,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then we could.","index":152,"end_time":589.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":588.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we help leaders now.","index":153,"end_time":590.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":589.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":154,"end_time":591.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":590.73,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Scattered it now it doesn''t feel like two separate thoughts.","index":155,"end_time":594.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":591.45,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They feel.","index":156,"end_time":595.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":594.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So we help leaders turn scattered experiments into clear workflows.","index":157,"end_time":598.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":595.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":158,"end_time":599.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":599.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because that is the pain point, right?","index":159,"end_time":600.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":599.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It is.","index":160,"end_time":601.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":600.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s confidence of knowing how to use it or that your team''s using it the right way, but also if.","index":161,"end_time":605.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":601.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are they even using it the right way or is one person using it differently than another person?","index":162,"end_time":609.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":605.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And maybe they''re both doing something right and something wrong.","index":163,"end_time":611.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":609.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":164,"end_time":612.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":611.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right, right.","index":165,"end_time":613.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":612.49,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All the consistency.","index":166,"end_time":614.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":613.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All the consistency things.","index":167,"end_time":616.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":614.73,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":168,"end_time":616.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":616.01,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":169,"end_time":616.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":616.45,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":170,"end_time":617.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":617.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":171,"end_time":619.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":618.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we also updated the landing page based on your feedback.","index":172,"end_time":622.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":619.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we updated the images.","index":173,"end_time":624.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":623.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Much better.","index":174,"end_time":626.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":625.7,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then we changed the colors here to use that sort of pale yellow that Rachel had mentioned.","index":175,"end_time":632.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":627.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Mm.","index":176,"end_time":633.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":632.9,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then swap the order of these.","index":177,"end_time":639.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":637.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it starts out with the human skills training built into every engagement.","index":178,"end_time":645.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":642.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then move the.","index":179,"end_time":647.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":646.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know, we need to.","index":180,"end_time":647.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":647.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll swap out these logos with whatever you guys need, but we move this down to the bottom.","index":181,"end_time":652.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":647.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that feels better.","index":182,"end_time":653.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":652.52,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Yeah, it does.","index":183,"end_time":654.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":653.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":184,"end_time":654.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":654.6,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And the images are much better.","index":185,"end_time":656.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":654.96,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They''re lighter and brighter.","index":186,"end_time":659.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":656.4,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And the people look more people.","index":187,"end_time":665.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":662.92,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, A little bit more real.","index":188,"end_time":667.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":665.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Mine going to the top image just so I can see it.","index":189,"end_time":669.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":667.48,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"I missed it.","index":190,"end_time":670.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":669.84,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":191,"end_time":671,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":670.48,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":192,"end_time":674.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":674.37,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The only face that still looks a little bit plastic is the woman by herself in the.","index":193,"end_time":679.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":674.57,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"No, no, the middle.","index":194,"end_time":681.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":680.37,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"This one.","index":195,"end_time":682.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":681.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":196,"end_time":683.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":682.77,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"She just looks a little too perfect.","index":197,"end_time":685.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":684.13,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But.","index":198,"end_time":685.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":685.61,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"She had a good.","index":199,"end_time":688.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":687.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A good day for her photos.","index":200,"end_time":690.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":688.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I think we''re good.","index":201,"end_time":691.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":690.85,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think we''re good.","index":202,"end_time":692.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":691.81,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So, logistically, how does it work to get this.","index":203,"end_time":697.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":692.77,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Launched?","index":204,"end_time":700.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":699.78,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"So I''m 99.9% sure we have access to the website.","index":205,"end_time":704.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":701.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we''ll just build a new template file so that it doesn''t affect the rest of your website and then launch it as a page.","index":206,"end_time":713.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":704.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And since it''s not going in the navigation or anything right away, we''ll just have that URL.","index":207,"end_time":716.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":713.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":208,"end_time":719.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":719.06,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s a closed page, so to speak.","index":209,"end_time":722.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":719.94,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":210,"end_time":723.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":722.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not like, openly navigable.","index":211,"end_time":724.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":723.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":212,"end_time":725.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":725.6,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Let me.","index":213,"end_time":726.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":726,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Give me one second.","index":214,"end_time":728.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":727.36,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So the only way someone will get there is through the ads themselves or if we share the URL with them.","index":215,"end_time":734,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":728.12,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Correct.","index":216,"end_time":735.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":734.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":217,"end_time":735.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":735.28,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"And there are two options.","index":218,"end_time":739.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":738.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One, you can.","index":219,"end_time":740.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":739.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can request that Google doesn''t crawl the page so that you wouldn''t populate for any SEO results.","index":220,"end_time":744.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":740.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or we can say that they can crawl if you want organic traffic.","index":221,"end_time":748,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":744.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, I don''t know why we wouldn''t.","index":222,"end_time":751.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":749.76,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, I lean towards.","index":223,"end_time":752.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":751.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If they''re searching for it and you pop up as relevant, then.","index":224,"end_time":755.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":752.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, let them come.","index":225,"end_time":757.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":755.93,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yep, agreed.","index":226,"end_time":759.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":757.45,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":227,"end_time":760.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":759.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, then we will get that built.","index":228,"end_time":761.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":760.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":229,"end_time":763.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":762.81,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right.","index":230,"end_time":765.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":764.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":231,"end_time":767.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":766.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So now that the ads and everything are final, we can launch that campaign on email and LinkedIn ads.","index":232,"end_time":771.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":767.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then.","index":233,"end_time":773.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":773.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Question for you.","index":234,"end_time":776.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":775.61,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Just.","index":235,"end_time":776.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":776.45,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Just as we launch this campaign and bearing in mind the conversation we had.","index":236,"end_time":781.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":776.81,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Last week, I think it was last week about.","index":237,"end_time":785.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":784.01,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Not.","index":238,"end_time":787.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":787.53,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Not stretching across too many campaigns.","index":239,"end_time":791.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":788.97,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So with the launch of this campaign, all told, what will we have out there?","index":240,"end_time":795.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":791.53,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And is it too much, in your opinion?","index":241,"end_time":797.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":795.929,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think we were including this in the three when we narrowed it down.","index":242,"end_time":801.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":798.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The AI campaign was one of those three, so it was that and then the infographic campaigns.","index":243,"end_time":806.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":801.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so it''s.","index":244,"end_time":808.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":807.72,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So what''s going to be live is this one.","index":245,"end_time":810.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":808.52,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then the.","index":246,"end_time":811.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":810.2,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"When you say infographic campaigns, it''s the smaller playbook for healthcare and the smaller playbook for first time cmos.","index":247,"end_time":820.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":812.12,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Correct.","index":248,"end_time":821.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":820.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":249,"end_time":822.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":822.44,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":250,"end_time":823.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":822.96,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"And the smaller playbook, what you''re calling infographic for healthcare and CMOS now, has been in market how long?","index":251,"end_time":834.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":823.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Probably approaching a month.","index":252,"end_time":838.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":837.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Natalie, I don''t know if you have the date on top of your head.","index":253,"end_time":841.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":839.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it''s around a month.","index":254,"end_time":842.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":841.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think it''s somewhere around that.","index":255,"end_time":844.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":842.53,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":256,"end_time":845.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":844.85,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''m just not seeing new leads in the board is why I''m asking.","index":257,"end_time":849.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":845.21,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s.","index":258,"end_time":852.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":851.73,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s been other than a couple spam leads.","index":259,"end_time":855.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":852.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So that concerns me about our effectiveness in the market.","index":260,"end_time":862.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":858.1,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I say that knowing we''re about to put the AI out there, so maybe that''s enough different.","index":261,"end_time":867.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":862.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But do you have thoughts on that?","index":262,"end_time":869.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":867.94,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, let me pull it up because I know that we also disabled the automatic integration for anyone filling it out.","index":263,"end_time":876.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":870.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ve only had the two.","index":264,"end_time":879.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":877.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Past 30 days.","index":265,"end_time":885.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":884.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think.","index":266,"end_time":892.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":891.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what I would say is since we''re narrowing down to the three and we''re able to utilize that budget much stronger, I still want to let the infographics run for probably another two weeks before we say do we, you know, rip down and rebuild or come up with something new.","index":267,"end_time":908.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":892.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Mm.","index":268,"end_time":909.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":909.25,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Mm.","index":269,"end_time":911.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":911.01,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Okay.","index":270,"end_time":912.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":911.65,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then I think.","index":271,"end_time":914.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":912.53,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We need to be thinking about, like, in the new year and in Q1, what we want to do from an industry focus.","index":272,"end_time":927.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":920.53,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I''m working on our 2026 plan right now because we''re definitely going to drop higher ed, and I think we''re also going to drop attractions.","index":273,"end_time":936.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":927.13,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I know we''re not active with those anyway.","index":274,"end_time":939.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":937.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But just in terms of replacement factor.","index":275,"end_time":942.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":939.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":276,"end_time":942.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":942.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, two that have always stood out to me is finance for you and consumer goods.","index":277,"end_time":951.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":942.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":278,"end_time":952.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":951.58,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Financial services, I think, will definitely be in the mix.","index":279,"end_time":954.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":952.38,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"My research is making professional services pop.","index":280,"end_time":959.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":954.74,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yep.","index":281,"end_time":961.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":960.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Financial services.","index":282,"end_time":962.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":961.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And it''s also telling me nonprofits, which.","index":283,"end_time":966.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":964.32,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That''s such a range.","index":284,"end_time":968.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":967.12,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":285,"end_time":968.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":968.24,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, we''re not talking, like, small nonprofits.","index":286,"end_time":970.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":968.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":287,"end_time":971.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":970.88,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"But that''s just where they''re saying, like, when you overlay, like, these are our services and these are the industries that are spending.","index":288,"end_time":978.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":971.6,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think there was one other one.","index":289,"end_time":982.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":980.96,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Let me look.","index":290,"end_time":982.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":982.32,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So, like, a big health care.","index":291,"end_time":990.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":988,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Healthcare is still there.","index":292,"end_time":992.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":991.11,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":293,"end_time":993.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":992.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, Julia.","index":294,"end_time":994.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":993.35,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I was just trying to get a good sense of, like, nonprofit.","index":295,"end_time":997.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":994.79,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"So something like.","index":296,"end_time":998.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":997.91,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Dana Farber or something like that.","index":297,"end_time":1004.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1002.07,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Like a big, nationally known.","index":298,"end_time":1006.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1004.07,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":299,"end_time":1007.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1006.87,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Who has tons of money behind them.","index":300,"end_time":1009.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1007.31,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"A huge team, most likely.","index":301,"end_time":1011.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1009.67,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Or even.","index":302,"end_time":1012.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1012.23,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Or even like a.","index":303,"end_time":1014.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1013.03,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, it doesn''t have to be as mammoth as them, but like, I think Capital Area Food bank is a good example.","index":304,"end_time":1019.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1014.55,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Interesting.","index":305,"end_time":1020.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1020.07,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Got it.","index":306,"end_time":1021.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1020.63,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"They''re probably like a few hundred people, but they almost hired us for a hundred thousand.","index":307,"end_time":1030.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1022.19,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":308,"end_time":1030.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1030.43,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So.","index":309,"end_time":1031.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1030.83,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So, so I think it''s like the medium to the.","index":310,"end_time":1034.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1032.11,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"To the big.","index":311,"end_time":1035.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1034.99,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yep.","index":312,"end_time":1036.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1035.87,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":313,"end_time":1037.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1036.83,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then, of course.","index":314,"end_time":1038.429,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1037.47,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And this can make your head spin, but like, nonprofit, like, you know, Mayo''s a nonprofit.","index":315,"end_time":1043.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1038.429,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But it''s also.","index":316,"end_time":1044.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1043.99,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So there''s.","index":317,"end_time":1045.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1045.15,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"There''s going to be some message.","index":318,"end_time":1047.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1045.71,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":319,"end_time":1047.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1047.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Does it need to fall into any sort of, like, classification?","index":320,"end_time":1050.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1047.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":321,"end_time":1051.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1051.17,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"It''s a great question.","index":322,"end_time":1053.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1052.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":323,"end_time":1054.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1053.81,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because, I mean, we could, you know, have a really dedicated campaign around 501C3s or something like that.","index":324,"end_time":1062.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1057.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right, Right.","index":325,"end_time":1063.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1062.21,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":326,"end_time":1065.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1064.69,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"It''s a good.","index":327,"end_time":1065.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1065.09,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That is a good question that I don''t know the answer to quite yet.","index":328,"end_time":1068.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1065.81,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":329,"end_time":1069.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1068.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":330,"end_time":1072.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1072.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":331,"end_time":1073.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1072.85,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"And then what about, like, law firms?","index":332,"end_time":1074.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1073.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":333,"end_time":1076.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1075.89,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So that would fall into professional services.","index":334,"end_time":1077.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1076.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So law firms, I mean, consulting firm.","index":335,"end_time":1082.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1078.29,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":336,"end_time":1082.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1082.24,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But I think there, too, it''s like, what''s the click down?","index":337,"end_time":1085.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1082.88,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I think there''s a couple different ways of looking at it, like size.","index":338,"end_time":1088.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1085.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And, you know, what services they might be most right for.","index":339,"end_time":1096.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1092.16,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But I do think.","index":340,"end_time":1097.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1096.72,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I do think law firms, you know, you have to weigh, like, how much are they going to care about audience and brand.","index":341,"end_time":1104.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1097.68,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They have to have Enough of a sophisticated marketing sense.","index":342,"end_time":1109.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1106.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":343,"end_time":1110.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1110.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And just from what we''ve seen, you know, from all the businesses we''ve done marketing for and if legal is in their niche then it tends to be a, as you can probably imagine, tough process of getting from like first conversation to actually close deal.","index":344,"end_time":1125.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1110.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Working together.","index":345,"end_time":1125.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1125.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A lot of time in legal review, things like that.","index":346,"end_time":1130.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1127.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":347,"end_time":1131.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1130.7,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So I probably put like kind of thinking like financial services and health care here, some professional services here, our client who''s the credit union, they''re just an ideal client in so many ways.","index":348,"end_time":1145.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1131.06,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Financial services sector, it''s a merger.","index":349,"end_time":1149.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1145.75,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So they, they need all the brand things and size wise they''re putting together kind of two medium sized organizations and becoming like a larger medium sized organization.","index":350,"end_time":1159.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1149.51,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So they don''t have like, they''re not unsophisticated in their marketing.","index":351,"end_time":1163.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1159.91,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":352,"end_time":1163.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1163.19,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"They value, they, they have a, they have a CMO who knows their stuff, but they''re not so big that they''re like in this enterprise world where they''re so, so I think we just, we''re going to have to do some really important due diligence around list making.","index":353,"end_time":1180.689,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1163.39,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":354,"end_time":1181.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1181.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This might be off the wall.","index":355,"end_time":1184.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1182.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have you ever pursued like VC firms?","index":356,"end_time":1187.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1184.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because I know, you know, when, when investments are being made they tend to bring in a full team of people that they work with consistently and say like okay, you know, whether it''s we''re investing in this company and we want to you know, bring up the brand, bring in new leadership or we''re merging these companies together and now we need a whole new brand out of that pollen.","index":357,"end_time":1209.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1189.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ve always loved the idea of that, but I would say we were only operationalized on that back in time with one.","index":358,"end_time":1215.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1209.09,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"One VC firm who like essentially recommended us and helped us get hired by two of their clients.","index":359,"end_time":1223.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1217.33,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I don''t have contacts in that world.","index":360,"end_time":1227.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1224.92,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I would say is just like the, the challenge, you know, but, but I do think that there is a.","index":361,"end_time":1235.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1227.44,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Academically at least there is definitely like an opportunity there because I do think that when they infuse cash they''re like, okay, you know, these things have to be grown up.","index":362,"end_time":1248.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1237.88,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And typically they''ll say, they won''t say like you have to hire this firm, but they''ll strongly recommend it.","index":363,"end_time":1255.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1248.36,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, they kind of put their thumb digging in a little bit.","index":364,"end_time":1258.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1255.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":365,"end_time":1258.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1258.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s how the one that we worked with.","index":366,"end_time":1261.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1259.39,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So it''s more so that we don''t have, I just don''t have contacts in that world.","index":367,"end_time":1266.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1261.15,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But could it be like you''re kind of selling to the not end buyer Right.","index":368,"end_time":1277.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1267.95,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You could do the not end buyer.","index":369,"end_time":1279.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1277.05,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''m not saying well, but you know what I mean.","index":370,"end_time":1281.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1280.09,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I am.","index":371,"end_time":1282.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1282.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m following.","index":372,"end_time":1283.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1282.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll put together a framework for it and parameters for a list and then we''ll run that by you and see, you know, just kind of a litmus test.","index":373,"end_time":1292.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1284.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if.","index":374,"end_time":1293.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1292.81,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"And if the firms who are doing the investing, like, I think it''s about, like it''s not the firms that are investing in the tiny startups.","index":375,"end_time":1303.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1293.33,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, right.","index":376,"end_time":1304.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1303.74,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It''s the ones that are investing in firms that are already like, of a certain size.","index":377,"end_time":1308.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1304.86,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":378,"end_time":1309.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1309.18,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"There might be some geographical.","index":379,"end_time":1310.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1309.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The mid is more.","index":380,"end_time":1312.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1311.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Is that a marketers in demand joke?","index":381,"end_time":1316.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1314.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, it is.","index":382,"end_time":1319.739,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1318.94,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":383,"end_time":1320.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1319.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And geography could be maybe another factor we can play on there as well.","index":384,"end_time":1323.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1320.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we find any that have a heavy cluster of companies they''re investing in in the area, we can tap into that.","index":385,"end_time":1329.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1323.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":386,"end_time":1331.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1331.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so professional services, nonprofits, and then check into VC as well.","index":387,"end_time":1335.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1331.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":388,"end_time":1336.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1336.07,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Healthcare, financial services, those are the contenders right now.","index":389,"end_time":1339.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1336.39,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m still in the process of the, of the Noetic business plan, which then, you know, will guide the Noetic marketing plan.","index":390,"end_time":1349.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1339.83,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But those are the, those are the four that popped.","index":391,"end_time":1353.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1350.95,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Overlaying.","index":392,"end_time":1354.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1353.91,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We do these services with what industries are most hiring for these services.","index":393,"end_time":1359.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1354.87,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":394,"end_time":1360.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1360.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And obviously keeping in mind our conversation of last week, so if it''s not on the table, no worries.","index":395,"end_time":1366.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1361.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I was.","index":396,"end_time":1367,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1366.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we.","index":397,"end_time":1367.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1367.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or if you have a timeline for when that plan is going to be ready and if you want to meet and go through, like, how we can assist, you know, through the rest of our engagement, then more than happy to do that.","index":398,"end_time":1377.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1368.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":399,"end_time":1378.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1378.04,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":400,"end_time":1378.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1378.4,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yep.","index":401,"end_time":1379.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1378.92,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Work in progress.","index":402,"end_time":1381.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1380.36,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":403,"end_time":1382.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1381.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s.","index":404,"end_time":1384.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1384.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s one of those months where it''s like either the day is incredibly busy or it''s like, oh, everyone''s, I guess, off and not sending anything.","index":405,"end_time":1393,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1384.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we love one of those.","index":406,"end_time":1395,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1393.48,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Yeah, I hear you.","index":407,"end_time":1397.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1396.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We don''t have like, clients are like, let''s go.","index":408,"end_time":1400.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1397.24,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":409,"end_time":1401.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1401.16,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, can''t you go on vacation now?","index":410,"end_time":1403.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1401.72,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":411,"end_time":1404.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1403.72,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And just taking a look at metrics, it''s negligible.","index":412,"end_time":1409.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1407.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But a 5% dip in total visitors to the website.","index":413,"end_time":1412.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1409.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, we are getting closer to the holiday season.","index":414,"end_time":1415.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1412.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"People''s attention span seems to definitely turn away from work around this.","index":415,"end_time":1419.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1415.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we do see website traffic kind of drop across the board.","index":416,"end_time":1422.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1419.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we know what the.","index":417,"end_time":1425.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1423.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The lift is to be able to have the podcast on the site?","index":418,"end_time":1432.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1427.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think, I think, Julia, that''s a purple hippo question.","index":419,"end_time":1436.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1432.92,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But yeah, it''s something we develop all the time.","index":420,"end_time":1443.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1441.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We develop direct integrations also with buzzsprout, which is the tool that we use to publish on Spotify and Apple and everything.","index":421,"end_time":1450.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1445.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can even pull up an example.","index":422,"end_time":1453.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1452.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll discuss with Rachel, see if she knows off the top of her head, Nancy, and then get back to you.","index":423,"end_time":1462.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1458.13,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"I''ll talk about it.","index":424,"end_time":1462.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1462.45,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But we didn''t pull the trigger on it.","index":425,"end_time":1465.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1462.97,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I feel like there was a reason we didn''t.","index":426,"end_time":1466.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1465.17,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Got it.","index":427,"end_time":1467.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1466.77,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"But, but, but it does stand to reason.","index":428,"end_time":1472.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1469.04,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That, like, if the, you know, our website traffic is kind of holding steady, but our YouTube is up.","index":429,"end_time":1479.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1474.72,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So.","index":430,"end_time":1479.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1479.56,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":431,"end_time":1480.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1479.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Drive those people to your site.","index":432,"end_time":1482.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1480.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":433,"end_time":1482.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1482.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s what we refer to as like owned experiences.","index":434,"end_time":1484.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1482.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you''re bringing them into your environment of the website, then you own that.","index":435,"end_time":1488.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1484.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That experience that they''re living rather than them browsing on YouTube or anything.","index":436,"end_time":1491.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1488.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here''s just an example.","index":437,"end_time":1493.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1492.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we put a direct integration with buzzsprout.","index":438,"end_time":1496.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1493.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have the audio here, the summary of the episode.","index":439,"end_time":1499.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1496.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I had to draft this earlier today, but this was showing the video.","index":440,"end_time":1502.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1500.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But they had.","index":441,"end_time":1503.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1502.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They had a text change that they didn''t let us know about, so we had to switch that out.","index":442,"end_time":1509.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1504.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Guest profile here, link to their LinkedIn Key Insights and then quote cards.","index":443,"end_time":1515.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1509.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just making a note of it.","index":444,"end_time":1520.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1518.75,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":445,"end_time":1520.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1520.15,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So Julia, let''s huddle with Rachel on that because I feel like she may have already asked the question.","index":446,"end_time":1525.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1520.99,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So we.","index":447,"end_time":1526.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1526.23,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"When.","index":448,"end_time":1527.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1527.11,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"When we''re doing things that are more complicated to our site, we have the hosting company do some of that functionality.","index":449,"end_time":1535.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1527.51,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So it''s just a question of whether or not does it make sense for them to do it?","index":450,"end_time":1540.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1536.07,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"For you guys to do it?","index":451,"end_time":1541.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1540.15,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"For us to do it.","index":452,"end_time":1541.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1541.15,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":453,"end_time":1542.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1542.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I think it''s something we should do.","index":454,"end_time":1545.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1543.43,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I would 100% agree with that.","index":455,"end_time":1548.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1546.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re like inviting people to leave.","index":456,"end_time":1549.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1548.43,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":457,"end_time":1552.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1551.95,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Or we''re not inviting people to go, actually.","index":458,"end_time":1555.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1553.23,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":459,"end_time":1556.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1555.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s kind of a little bit of both.","index":460,"end_time":1557.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1556.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because even.","index":461,"end_time":1559.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1558.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":462,"end_time":1560.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1559.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s mostly not bringing them to the website because it''s.","index":463,"end_time":1562.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1560.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Check it out on Spotify or YouTube or Apple rather than visit the website.","index":464,"end_time":1566.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1563.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":465,"end_time":1568.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1567.23,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"That is.","index":466,"end_time":1571.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1571.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I don''t know if you saw that on the screen, but that was the note that we had on there as well.","index":467,"end_time":1575.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1571.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":468,"end_time":1577.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1577.35,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Can you go back to the metrics?","index":469,"end_time":1579.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1577.55,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"That metrics page.","index":470,"end_time":1580.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1579.03,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m looking at.","index":471,"end_time":1587.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1585.99,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Page views.","index":472,"end_time":1594.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1593.43,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Let me pull up.","index":473,"end_time":1597.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1596.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is a screenshot.","index":474,"end_time":1597.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1597.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let me pull that up live.","index":475,"end_time":1598.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1597.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any travel or any fun plans for the holidays?","index":476,"end_time":1615.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1613.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just took my last trip of the year, put my suitcase away.","index":477,"end_time":1619.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1616.4,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Probably a little traveled out, I imagine.","index":478,"end_time":1621.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1619.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, a bit.","index":479,"end_time":1623.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1621.76,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":480,"end_time":1623.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1623.44,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I do have many next year, but December, I''m going to stay put.","index":481,"end_time":1629.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1623.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Julia, are you going anywhere at the end of the year?","index":482,"end_time":1635.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1633.12,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I am.","index":483,"end_time":1636.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1635.52,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"I''m going on a family tour of duty, if you will.","index":484,"end_time":1639.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1636.08,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"So starting with my family in New Hampshire and then visiting my husband and my family in New York.","index":485,"end_time":1647.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1639.36,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"So it''s going to be a busy 2 weeks.","index":486,"end_time":1649.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1648.24,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"I have a fun weekend of getting a 18 month old packed 3 days early or 4 days early this weekend.","index":487,"end_time":1658.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1649.76,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Figuring out how the heck to do that.","index":488,"end_time":1660.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1659.1,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"I see how much stuff the little people require.","index":489,"end_time":1663.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1661.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m going to bring like three outfits.","index":490,"end_time":1665.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1663.98,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"She''s going to have everything she''s ever owned in every suitcase.","index":491,"end_time":1669.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1665.54,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Okay, so this is showing us page views team.","index":492,"end_time":1676.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1672.38,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":493,"end_time":1681.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1680.62,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So that page, the podcast page is.","index":494,"end_time":1684.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1681.06,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Up, which is.","index":495,"end_time":1685.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1684.62,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Insights pages up a little bit.","index":496,"end_time":1691.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1689.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''ve been pushing the insights page at people.","index":497,"end_time":1693.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1691.14,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":498,"end_time":1695.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1694.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s the other cool thing with bringing the podcast really a little bit more into the fold of the website is you can have the insights and podcast page play off each other where they''re constantly like referencing, you know, go check out this blog where we talked about this or in this blog.","index":499,"end_time":1708.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1695.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, check out this episode.","index":500,"end_time":1709.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1708.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":501,"end_time":1715.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1714.83,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Our, our YouTube views.","index":502,"end_time":1723.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1719.79,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Are like all like quite a bit lower than where they were initially.","index":503,"end_time":1729.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1725.39,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"What do you make of that?","index":504,"end_time":1730.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1729.55,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So we''re up 10% compared to the previous period.","index":505,"end_time":1736.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1733.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it''s also just.","index":506,"end_time":1739,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1737.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These things have a shelf life.","index":507,"end_time":1742.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1741,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So when they''re first posted is when they''re going to get the most views and traffic and then it just sort of dies down from there.","index":508,"end_time":1748.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1743.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Unless it''s brought back up like we can do with the compilation video.","index":509,"end_time":1751.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1748.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that''s another good opportunity to point people back here.","index":510,"end_time":1756.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1754.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":511,"end_time":1758.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1757.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Anything else from this that you think needs attention or implication?","index":512,"end_time":1767.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1763.17,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"No, I mean Adroll is driving traffic, so 10 people for the budget that we have there is pretty good.","index":513,"end_time":1774.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1768.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One interesting thing that I''ve been seeing is an increase in Bing.","index":514,"end_time":1779.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1776.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know if people got like new Dells or something for Black Friday.","index":515,"end_time":1784.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1781.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Microsoft Edge is already installed on there with Bing.","index":516,"end_time":1787.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1784.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I have been seeing a increase across the board of Bing traffic compared to Google recently, which is interesting.","index":517,"end_time":1793.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1787.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Huh?","index":518,"end_time":1794.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1794.16,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"That is interesting though.","index":519,"end_time":1797.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1796.08,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You know, Google''s still much higher.","index":520,"end_time":1799.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1797.52,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But why does, why does pipedrive show there?","index":521,"end_time":1803.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1799.08,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"This might be an API call that we have.","index":522,"end_time":1808.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1805.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll have to check with the developer on that.","index":523,"end_time":1811.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1809.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, same thing with SharePoint.","index":524,"end_time":1816.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1814.65,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I don''t know why that would be there.","index":525,"end_time":1818.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1817.37,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Because this is all outer facing metrics, right?","index":526,"end_time":1824.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1821.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":527,"end_time":1825.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1825.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll ask the developers to check on that.","index":528,"end_time":1832.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1830.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then not set is typically when someone has a browser, like a DuckDuckGo or something.","index":529,"end_time":1838.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1835.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":530,"end_time":1840.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1840.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":531,"end_time":1843.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1842.46,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":532,"end_time":1843.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1843.02,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"All right.","index":533,"end_time":1846.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1846.38,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":534,"end_time":1847.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1847.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I mean, my, my biggest concern remains around, you know, leads and that right now I just don''t see them coming into the board.","index":535,"end_time":1855.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1847.78,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I do have a call with Waymo next, so we''ll see where that goes.","index":536,"end_time":1861.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1857.1,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The challenge with Waymo is that they''re slammed.","index":537,"end_time":1864.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1862.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":538,"end_time":1865.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1865.24,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So can they slow down long enough to bring us into something?","index":539,"end_time":1869.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1865.64,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So we''ll see.","index":540,"end_time":1870.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1869.48,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We''ll see what she has to say.","index":541,"end_time":1871.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1870.36,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":542,"end_time":1872.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1872.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Slow down to speed up.","index":543,"end_time":1873.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1872.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":544,"end_time":1876.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1874.68,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think they''re just flying by the seat of their pants in a lot of ways.","index":545,"end_time":1879.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1876.56,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":546,"end_time":1882.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1880.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we have the AI campaign launching as well, so looking to tap into that audience with a new offer and message.","index":547,"end_time":1887.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1882.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":548,"end_time":1888.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1887.8,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I''m hoping that''s going to bring in some good engagement.","index":549,"end_time":1892.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1888.16,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And I think it''s.","index":550,"end_time":1892.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1892.01,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I think we need to look as that launches.","index":551,"end_time":1895.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1892.89,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Like, even if people aren''t meeting the threshold to make it for a lead, let''s really look at.","index":552,"end_time":1904.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1896.17,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":553,"end_time":1905.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1905.13,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Engagement may not be meeting the threshold.","index":554,"end_time":1908.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1906.489,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I mean, I hope it is, but if it doesn''t, what parts of it are they engaging in?","index":555,"end_time":1912.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1908.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So that we can, like, you know, refine.","index":556,"end_time":1917.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1913.61,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"If we need to refine.","index":557,"end_time":1918.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1917.3,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":558,"end_time":1919.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1918.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we can even develop an audience of people who haven''t hit the threshold, but they''re like, say, a nine out of 10.","index":559,"end_time":1924.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1919.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":560,"end_time":1924.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1924.5,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then even focus on them a.","index":561,"end_time":1926.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1925.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Little bit harder once it.","index":562,"end_time":1927.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1926.66,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":563,"end_time":1927.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1927.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Once it reaches a high enough count, we can develop its own LinkedIn audience.","index":564,"end_time":1931.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1927.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I like that idea.","index":565,"end_time":1933.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1931.62,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":566,"end_time":1933.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1933.26,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Because I do think there''s.","index":567,"end_time":1934.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1933.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"There''s a there there, but I, but the, the people who are going to buy that.","index":568,"end_time":1939.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1934.82,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They can''t be at organizations that are the really big ones, but they can''t be at organizations that are too small.","index":569,"end_time":1946.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1941.46,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Because if they''re at the really big ones, they''ve got like a.","index":570,"end_time":1949.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1946.93,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"A team or they bring someone in.","index":571,"end_time":1951.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1949.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Guys, you know, they''re working it out over there, and it wouldn''t be up to the marketers to solve for themselves.","index":572,"end_time":1957.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1951.65,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yep.","index":573,"end_time":1957.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1957.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":574,"end_time":1959.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1958.61,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I do think, like, a independent agency could be a good.","index":575,"end_time":1962.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1959.17,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Could be a good target for that.","index":576,"end_time":1966.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1964.69,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":577,"end_time":1968.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1966.37,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"The one lead that we do have specific to that is within an independent agency.","index":578,"end_time":1974.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1968.49,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"They''re like 400 people.","index":579,"end_time":1977.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1974.82,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Right.","index":580,"end_time":1977.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1977.22,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":581,"end_time":1978.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1977.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":582,"end_time":1978.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1978.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s good size for that.","index":583,"end_time":1979.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1978.54,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":584,"end_time":1981.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1980.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":585,"end_time":1982.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1981.7,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So let''s look at that.","index":586,"end_time":1982.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1982.1,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And then are we.","index":587,"end_time":1983.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1982.82,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"So next week''s the 17th.","index":588,"end_time":1988.179,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1986.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"You guys are good to meet on the 17th?","index":589,"end_time":1990.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1988.179,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"We are.","index":590,"end_time":1990.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1990.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":591,"end_time":1992.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1992.02,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I have a slight.","index":592,"end_time":1993.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1992.58,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I Think it''ll be fine.","index":593,"end_time":1995.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1994.34,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I have.","index":594,"end_time":1996.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1996.1,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"My husband''s having knee surgery that day.","index":595,"end_time":1998.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1996.82,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"I should be back.","index":596,"end_time":1999.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1998.42,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Only if I get, like, dramatically delayed will I miss it.","index":597,"end_time":2003.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1999.9,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"But it should be fine.","index":598,"end_time":2004.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2003.26,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Well, just, you know, Jimmy and email.","index":599,"end_time":2006.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2005.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re flexible.","index":600,"end_time":2007.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2006.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":601,"end_time":2008.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2007.9,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And.","index":602,"end_time":2008.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2008.3,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"And worst case, Julia, you''re still working.","index":603,"end_time":2011.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2008.54,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"The 17th, and so is Rachel.","index":604,"end_time":2013.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2011.1,"speaker_name":"Julia Oher"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":605,"end_time":2013.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2013.34,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So if I have to miss, we can always record, too, but I think it''ll work.","index":606,"end_time":2016.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2013.66,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":607,"end_time":2017.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2016.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then 24th, are you guys out?","index":608,"end_time":2019.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2017.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":609,"end_time":2021.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2021.26,"speaker_name":"nancieruder"},{"text":"Okay.","index":610,"end_time":2022.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2022.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Cost